What 's the future of travel ? Nowadays , people can travel around the world almost without any limits . During the last 100 years , people have changed the way they travel . Even our grandparents spent days or weeks to travel between continents . Ships were the fastest mode of travelling . Then airlines started to offer their services and now we can fly in 24 hours around the globe . People are trying to develop new means of transport to minimise the length of the journey . On the other hand , we are looking beyond the horizon of the globe . We are interested in traveling into space . There are two companies which are working to make traveling into space more accessible . There is a big chance that in the near future people will start traveling into space . At the beginning it could cost a fortune for ordinary people , but it will change when more companies have developed their technology and services . It will still mean we will move from one place to another , but we will use different modes of transport . Maybe we will sleep during the trip to minimise the effects of traveling in space , because we still do not know the impact on our body and mind when traveling in space . 
First , I would like to say thank you for letting me write this request in this amazing magazine . As you already know , I will write about " The School Of The Future . " I will especially write about in what ways do you think schools will be different in the future and in what ways might they still be the same . I think schools will be different in the future by accepting ICT equipment , such as projectors , sound boxes and so on . I think by using this equipment , it will be so efficient and both students and teachers will be able to facilitate their classes very smoothly in the future . On the other hand , schools will still be the same in offering school lunches . I believe that we need a school lunch dietitian to ensure students ' individual health . Plus , school lunchtime should be fun ! I like schools today , but I hope that future schools will also be nice by having a great balance between accepting new technology and maintaining an old school 's tradition . 
My best holiday ever . A couple years ago , I went with my family for a summer holiday . We booked a trip in a German office for two weeks stay on a Spanish Island . We started our trip in Dresden , where we entered a plane and after a three -hour flight we arrived at the airport in Palma , the capital city of Mallorca . We stayed in a 3 -star hotel close to the beach . We enjoyed delicious food in local , traditional restaurants . We spent a wonderful time traveling around the island . Mallorca is not a big island , so tourists have an opportunity to visit almost every corner of this amazing place . We enjoyed sunbathing in the evening when the temperature had fallen . Traveling by car , we had a chance to stop in every place we wanted . In my opinion , everyone will find something interesting to see . I really recommend ti closter , colorful harbours , beautiful small bays , caves and mountains . I believe that due to the many interesting places , tasty food , nice weather conditions and friendly people , this was our best holiday ever . 
