" Television entertains , but can it also educate ? " If I answered this question , I would say , " Yes . " I have a reason to support this statement . Firstly , of course I agree that television entertains , by showing audiences variety shows , quiz shows , comedy shows and so on . Usually , these kinds of TV shows are very popular among kids and teenagers . In fact , I also enjoy watching these types of TV shows . Moreover , TV can also educate by broadcasting about recent news , science , social studies and so on . Of course , learning something in school and learning something from workbooks are important , but I think TV shows will also be part of education . On TV , you can learn things that ca not be taught in school and it can sometimes be very educational for kids like us . In conclusion , I think that we should live well with mass media like television , and I think that it will lead us to a better life in the future . 
Money ca not buy happiness or serenity . It is more important to be healthy than to be rich . I am in total agreement with that . Health ca not be replaced by anything . There are a lot of rich people who are ready to give up their wealth just to be healthy . Some illnesses cannot be cured , even with all the money in the world . Sick people have to go through the pain and the fear of losing their life . They wish there was something to do to help themselves . I remember one of my dad 's friend 's had a rare disease . He traveled around the world and spent all of his money just to find a cure . But sadly he died after a tragic journey of trying find the medication . Eventually , I learned from that situation that health is the most important thing in life . Besides , it is a gift from God that deserves to be grateful for . 
