It 's a debatable issue whether one needs a still and steady life or an intense life which is full of excitement and challenges . I personally believe that life should be challenging and deep enough so that we can be remembered by all the other people until the time life exist in this universe . To start with , an intense life has its certain benefits . The one most common one is that such a life teaches you new and different skills required to solve issues further boosting your confidence level and making you famous . To illustrate this , the famous scientist Einstein , belonging to a small village , accepted the challenge and invented the bulb , which further made him a famous scientist and still remembered by all of us . Secondly , such a life reduces stress and makes life more happening and lively to live , whereas a calm and steady life is good for an initial time , but after some time , you easily get bored with such a life and you follow the same routine from many years . For example , a recent survey conducted by The Times newspaper shows that people living in hilly areas , those who are doing the same kind of work , do not have any excitement for life as compared to city people . To sum up , it 's only the intense quality of life which helps an individual to learn new methods and techniques , further boosting their confidence level to accept new challenges in life and making them famous personalities . 
