The truth sometimes could be painful , but it 's always important to tell the truth . Honest and truthful people are always loved in their communities . Lies that have been told by dishonest people could lead to big problems and trust issues . Truthful people are well respected in their societies . It 's not acceptable to tell a lie even if the truth is difficult to deal with . Being explicit and straight forward is better than being known as a liar . I remember one time one of my friends lied to me about something . When I found out that she was lying and that she told me false information , I was angry at her . Furthermore , the respect and trust that I had for her was broken . I could really appreciate it if she just told the truth . Lies do not make the matter any better , it will make the situation even worse . Some people choose to be implicit to avoid facing a specific problem . For example , my friend Sara has a problem with our friend Suzy . Their relationship was bad , so Suzy asked her what was the problem . Sara chose not to tell her and she replied that she does not have a problem with her . Instead of confronting her , she just ducked Suzy . As result of that , they ended up not talking to each other , which they could simply have avoided by just being honest to one another . 
