I went to Guanajuato last December with my boyfriend and another couple . My boyfriend and I had been planning that trip for six months . We were in Guanajuato for three days and walked around the city . The first day , we visited San Miguel de Allende . It is a beautiful magic town . There are many museums , restaurants where they sell Mexican food . After , we stayed in Guanajuato , my boyfriend rented a hostel for four people . During those days , we visited the kiss alley , the Miguel market , Diego Rivera 's house , the wax museum and Alondiga de Granaditas museum . At night , we visited Juarez theatre , it was built in 1910 by government for Porfirio Diaz . It is a beautiful place in Guanajuanto . And finally , we bought tickets for " Callejoneadas , " which are night tours where the people sing and dance together with mariachis . The mariachis give away coplas to the tourists . The holiday was very nice . 
