Hi Billal , I am writing an email to tell you about how my trip went last weekend . I know that if you had not got sick , you would have come with us . Last week , we went to a beach instead of the floating market . Yes , we changed our plan of a one day trip because we had a lot of time to stay at the beach for one night . In the morning , we walked along the the beach and took many photos . It was a windy and sunny day . We played banana boat and volleyball in the afternoon . Then , we went to a seafood market to buy seafood like shrimps , oysters , and crabs to cook that night . The seafood was very delicious and fresh . We were singing while Brian was playing the guitar . It was a good time in the last school year . I hope you get well soon and join us on the next trip . Miss you , Por 
My favorite subject is math . I never get tired of it , even though I have been studying it for ten hours every day . Thinking about math problems renders me nothing but pleased . But I have some troubles . I can solve difficult problems if I have a lot of time , but the exam I 'm going to take is a time -limited one . This is why I want to reduce the amount of time I need to come up with the solution for problems . On top of that , I 'd like to improve my arithmetic ability , which also reduces time loss . To achieve this , I will do a problem solving exercise every week . In this exercise , I must solve six problems within 150 minutes , as I do in the exam . Then , I will analyze the causes of time loss , and consider feasible measures for them . And , I also make it a rule not to give up calculation in the middle . 
--- Should computers and tablets completely replace books in schools and universities ? --- If I have to answer this question , I would say , " Yes . " I have a reason to support this opinion . I know that traditional books , such as textbooks or workbooks , are very good for both students ' and teachers ' learning and teaching method , but recently , there is a movement that supports the use of technological textbooks or workbooks . ( So called " e -textbooks or e -workbooks . ) I totally support this movement because by using ' e -textbooks ' or ' e -workbooks ' , I believe that there will be a lot of benefits . For example , I believe that e -textbooks can help visualize some complicated things , such as chemical compounds or body mechanisms , and e -workbooks will be able able to do answer checks automatically . Plus , by accepting this method , I believe that there will be less burden on both of students and teachers and they will be able to focus on some other things . I think that 's good ! For these reasons , I think there is a high possibility that school textbooks and workbooks will be replaced by technological ones . 
My reasons for learning English Learning English is very necessary nowadays . When you speak English , many things are opened to you , such as jobs , studies , or even friends ! For example , I personally spend a lot of time surfing on the web , and during all of this time , I sometimes met new people from all around the world . Having learned English the way I did allowed me to talk to those people and to discuss with them ! Being interested in new cultures , new ways of thinking and countries . But that 's not it , learning English is also important to me for my studies . I would love to be accepted in a prestigious high school with anglophone students . Maybe I 'm too ambitious , but it 's important to have dreams and to follow them ! Moreover , I just love learning languages , especially English . I do not know why is it so special to me , but I do not always need a reason to do something , right ? Just go for it , and have fun ! 
The school of the future An exciting assumption : the school of the future . There 's something that always put me in questions . Why have schools had the same profile since I was a child ? They try to update the schedule , try to improve the qualifications of teachers , but the time is always the same . Today , parents , especially mothers , need to work not only at home . So they need to leave their children in a safe place where they know their children will have many educational activities . But the time that schools offer are rarely in accord to parents ' timetables . If they supply this necessity , they are very expensive . So it 's important to readapt schools . They should be flexible with hours . They will need to offer activities related to information technology . If they do not , students will be bored and not interested in classes . Some professions will be replaced by modern ones . So , we will need courses to qualify workers in these new tendencies . 
Hi Billal , How are you ? I am fine , I have done many things this month . Last week my classmates and I went to a conference in Monterrey , the trip was too long because we traveled on a bus . We arrived in Monterrey at night . Some students decided to stay in the hotel but my friends and I would rather go out to a karaoke bar . The next day , I woke up very early because the conference started at 8 o 'clock . We came back to Mexico City last Monday . It was a good trip . 
Dear Cristina , I did not have any idea that you have had an accident , I am sorry to hear that . Do you want to tell me what 's up , because I am worried about you and I want to know how I can help you ? Please , tell me when I can visit you ? I will visit and give you some fruit , vegetables , desserts , books and movies . I am very happy because you are fine and soon you could come back to university , it could not be better ... . 
I partly agree with the opinion of living a long time . Because the possibilities to see something I ca not imagine now and to watch the world cup soccer in Japan increase if I live a long time . Besides , if I knew my life span was 100 years , I could make various life plans . I think that it may be more useful to know my life span than to live a long time . But I mainly agree with the opinion of living a short life but much more intense . There are two reasons . First , I know who I am . I 'm not a good man nor am I diligent . If I have long -span life , I will definitely become lazy and just live in vain . I have no confidence that I will make my life fruitful . Second , if I can live a long time , nobody knows my healthy life span . If I am in a hospital for more than 50 years , it will be the most painful thing for me . A life that is short but intense is so cool . I think that great people 's lives are relatively short . Like them , I want to live actively and accomplish something great . To be honest , I do not want to know my life span . In spite of the length of the span , I will be disappointed at everything and wo not be able to do any more . I manage to live my life because I do not know when I 'm going to die . 
Two months ago , I went on a sightseeing holiday with my family , in Italy . That was the first time I had ever traveled abroad , thus I was very excited . It was mostly because I had to convince my parents that it was the perfect moment in our lives for such a holiday . The flight there lasted only for about two hours , although it felt like an eternity for me . Once there , we went to the hotel to leave our luggage . Then we visited Vatican city . I had such a wonderful sensation walking through the galleries , like I could see Michelangelo and Raphael working . The guide made us feel as if we were a part of that extraordinary piece of art . We also saw the Colosseum , the Pantheon and La Fontana di Trevi , and we could not avoid eating pizza and ice cream . Although I liked everything we saw , I felt a deep attraction for the Vatican 's art galleries . The paintings looked so alive , like I could transfer myself into that period only by staring at them . All together , it was the best holiday I have ever had because , after all , I visited more than one place and learned a lot of things . 
Hello my friend , I loved the film ' 1917 ' , it is a different film about the war . All the time the camera follows the principal actors , creating a sensation that you are in the scene , with the characters . It is a new way to show the war , hard , not easy to watch , but very interesting . 
Hello John , First of all , congratulations . The celebration of a birthday in my country is similar to yours . We often prepare a meeting with friends , everybody takes a gift , and then we eat a lot food This is common in Brazil . Afterwards , everybody sings " Happy birthday to you " and then everybody holds the birthday person . 
Hello . I think I have so many goals which should be done this school year . And one thing for sure , I achieved some foreign language courses but I never stopped improving my level . My studying never ends . Besides , I would also love to learn something else to enhance my journey on the path to a creative career . The best point is that I would learn instruments , so that I can write my own songs and perform them on stage some day . Playing the guitar so well has been built into my head recently . Though I 'm not sure it 's easy to learn but if I achieve it as well , that will be the most wonderful feeling I have ever experienced . Thus it motivates me to get it as soon as possible . Taking a guitar course would lead me to acquire a new skill and enable me to cope with problems more creatively . Currently , I do not know how to play at all , so I should write down for myself a process for tracking my learning speed , so that I can appreciate my progress . Hopefully , the process should be right like the way it is intended . 
Hi Tom , How are you ? This time I want to write to you about my favorite film : ' The Lord of The Rings ' directed by Peter Jackson . It is based on a famous trilogy written by Tolkien . I have watched it probably more than ten times . It 's great because of the fantastic cinematography . The scenery of New Zealand is fantastic . Also , the actors are great in their roles . My favorite is Viggo Mortensen as Aragorn . If you have not seen it , you have to ! I am looking forward to hearing from you . Bye , 
Usually I am reluctant to do any exercise , except dancing , because I do not really have fun when I do sport . For instance , I have bought new jogging shoes , but I have only used them once for this purpose . The only exception is street jazz . I have so much fun when I am dancing . Therefore , strictly speaking , dancing is not an exercise but a hobby for me . Furthermore , I like going for a walk with Max at the weekend , regularly . 
Hi , My name is Angel . I usually like to exercise . I try to exercise 3 times per week , but sometimes I ca not because of my job or my children . I prefer exercising in a gym because I can exercise with weights . But I never go to the gym because of my schedule . I usually exercise at home . Early in the morning I get up to do squats , planks , crunches and others . My favorite activities for exercise are : running , cycling and dancing . 
I do not like to do exercise , however , I do exercises almost every day . I stop only on one day per week . I prefer to exercise at home , sometimes on the street , sometimes in the square and rarely at the gym , because I am too lazy to go out sometimes and I have a routine to do at home , it 's better for me . Usually , I spend forty minutes on the force exercises and half an hour on the aerobic exercises . 
In my opinion , every student should at least have a few lessons of music . Of course , there are schools that prepare students for a career in the music business . There , more lessons are needed . For " normal " schools , though , I think that music should be a relaxing session to calm down and forget about the daily stress . I think that music really helps to get into a good mood again . That is why everyone should have at least some music in school . Music is not necessarily a subject you get a grade on , but more of a group building free time activity . There should not be any restrictions , so that teachers can create individual experiences for every class . I am sure that music has a good influence on everyone 's health and it could also help to prevent illnesses . For example , burn -out , which is common among pupils , could be eliminated . Therefore , every school should offer some music courses ! 
I like to exercise very much because I want my body to be stronger than before and I want to lose weight . I exercise every day in the morning and evening . In the morning , I work out for 30 minutes following a trainer on the You Tube channel . I run for 30 minutes every evening . Normally , I exercise outside and I prefer exercising outside too . The first reason is that by exercising outside I can breathe fresh air and not air conditioning that is not good for my health . The second reason is that my house is far from the gym . I like running and swimming because I use every part of my body to do these exercises and I use fewer accessories . 
Hi , How are you doing ? I hope you are doing fine . Today , I have just seen the most emotional and beautiful movie ever . It is called Me Before You . It is about Will who had a motorbike accident , which left him with a spinal cord injury . That is why he needed to be taken care of . Louisa took up the job of taking care of him , but they dislike each other . Then Louisa overheard a conversation between Will 's parents , that he did not want to live anymore . She decided to make a plan to let Will see how beautiful life is . During the vacation , they fell in love , but Will decided to choose euthanasia . When Will died , he left her a letter and it was the most beautiful letter I have ever seen . Kind regards , Leanne Klaver 
I like to do exercise . I do exercise twice a week . I prefer to do exercise outside my house because it is quieter and it is a lot more fun . To exercise I like to jump with a rope , trot around the track , and play lots of different sports so that I can lose weight . 
I like to exercise a lot . Especially after I knew and read about the benefits of physical activities , I am trying to do some exercises for at least 30 minutes per day . I am feeling better . My performance has improved and I can see that I can walk for a middle distance without tiring . It 's awesome ! ! 
I think that studying abroad is the better choice that a student can take . Studying abroad , especially for foreign language students , is the right opportunity to improve in language and speak a lot . It 's an opportunity to grow first , far from the family , but also to make friends with students all around the world . But there are also disadvantages to this type of opportunity , like the accommodation . In some cases , the accommodation for the students abroad are so far from the university and high schools and they must take a lot of buses to go to school . Another problem is that , nowadays , young people are so spoiled and so some of them maybe ca not do housework . Studying abroad means that you must follow the school lessons , do homework , do the washing , cook and thousands of other things and not everyone , in my opinion , is capable . So , studying abroad is an important opportunity , but if a student decides to take this opportunity , he has to roll up his sleeves . 
Actually I spend my free time writing or watching TV . Every day I write , I want to write about a lot of topics , especially because I am professor and researcher , and I do not have a lack of subjects . On the other hand , I like to watch TV so much : nowadays we have many good programs , series , films , and documentaries , etc . 
I like to play video games , jump with a rope , do crafts , watch TV , play board games with my family , and draw and color mandalas . I usually have free time every day , after finishing my homework . I like to play games , like video games and board games , because I like to play with my family at those games . I like to draw and color mandalas , and do crafts because it relaxes me . The last time I had free time was yesterday afternoon , I watched TV . 
I think that all students should have to study music . Why I think so is for the following 2 reasons . First , studying music can bring some good influences for another subjects . You know , when we play music , we use another part of the brain compared to studying maths , chemistry , biology and so on . Using the parts which you usually do not use , you can activate your brain and you may break through something . Second , I think that all students should study as many subjects as possible . Of course , college students and students who decide to major in particular subjects may not need to study music . But for other students , there are no reasons why it is good to regulate their subjects . Studying music , they can feel their talents that they could not notice before . I think that it is important that we should offer whatever opportunities all students may have an interest . We should not cut their curiosity to study something . And all students may not like studying music . But it is necessary for them to experience things which they do not like . School is the place not only to study subjects but also to get experiences with your classmates . Students should experience various things for their future . 
I love practising sports : swimming in a pool is the best sport ever , because I started swimming 5 years ago , and I had the best teacher ever , he taught me every technique to be able to swim better . Years later I started doing judo , and I learned a little Japanese : I can count to 10 in Japanese , and that was a good experience . Nowadays , I do not do exercise anymore because I do not have time , and because I work and study a lot , I do not have enough time . And , honestly , I prefer exercising in a gym because there you have some motivation . 
Here is one of the major areas for the production of rice in Japan . There is a new hotel in the middle of the rice field that was designed by a famous Japanese architect . We also offer an Italian restaurant , which uses a variety of local ingredients . 
Of course there are many people who have no choice where to live because of financial reason . But if they can choose the place , I partly agree to the opinion that students move away and live on their own . There are two main reasons . First students can experience various things . They have to do all chores by themslves . They also must control themselves and judge evreything they are related . Whatever they experience are useful for the future . It is efficient to live on their own ealier so that they will leave their home soon or later . Second It save time that they live near university . I think that commuting time is one of the most meaningless . If they can save their time , they are pleased to live on their own . But I mainly agree to the opinion that students live at home with their family . Because the time that you live with your family is the most precious for your life . Besides this time is limited . When you want to be with them or you want to do something for them , they may not be there . Almost all the students will leave at home in the future . So they should be with their family as long as possible . Many things that you would experience if you live alone do not be needed for you in your college days . You should be with your family and you should make precious memories . 
In my free time , I like to go to the beach . I usually go there every month , but I have not gone recently . I like the beach because my children like to bathe in the waves . Also , we play baseball or soccer on the beach and build sandcastles . The last time that we went to the beach was on December 3rd to celebrate my daughter 's 5th birthday . She said that it had been the best birthday in her life ! 
Zoos are one of the most interesting attractions for children , but also for their parents . But there are a lot of different opinions about zoos , many people believe that zoos are good places for children to learn about animals and I completely agree with them . It 's an important place where kids can learn and discover such different and also uncommon animals . On the other hand , many people believe animals belong in nature and it is wrong to keep them in zoos . This is also an important point of view , it 's true that it is wrong to keep them in zoos , but lots animals that we see in zoos are animals that were taken from difficult situations , where would not have survived in captivity . If , on the one hand , I agree with people that believe zoos are good places for learning about nature and animals , I completely disagree with circuses , where animals are forced to perform funny scenes to amuse spectators . 
Nowadays , video games are an important part of children . If , on the one hand , some parents feel that video games can have a negative impact on their children , and I agree with this feeling , on the other hand , there are others that believe that video games may have some positive effects . It is a complex question . It is true that video games may have some positive effects , such as improving skills , but I 'm completely sure that new video games can have a big negative impact on children . Now , there are a lot of war video games , where children must kill each other to win , and this , in my opinion , is sad . Educational video games are not attractive for children , they prefer violent video games . In the end , parents of young children must try to tell their children that video games can be dangerous and also they must try to avoid children playing for many hours . 
I love exercise . Even though I do not have too much time , I spend about 4 hours a week on working out . I go to the gym every Saturday . When I am too busy , I also take an outdoor walk for about 15 minutes in the evening . I prefer outside activities rather than working out indoors . Going outside is more interesting . I can exercise and be relaxed at the same time . When I walk outdoors , I can breathe fresh air , enjoy the atmosphere and watch the daily activities of people . Going to a gym is not very comfortable for me . Many people gather in the same place . Sometimes , it is very noisy at the gym . You cannot enjoy as many things as going outside . I like walking outdoors . As I mentioned , when walking outside , I can enjoy many things at the same time . Walking is actually very beneficial for your health , both physically and mentally . 
MODERN SCHOOLS The older we get , the more technological progress we can see . We are creating flying cars in our heads , thinking about the future . But what about schools ? What will they look like in the next hundred years ? When you turn back a hundred years , you see how many changes came from that time . We already learn from different devices in school . Teachers are showing information not only on blackboards , but also electric boards , on which they can fluently turn to the next topics . So what 's next ? It is believed that in the future , robots will replace humans ' work . So this is how I see it ... Teachers will be replaced by robots , but they would still look like real human beings . That would solve the problem of the teachers ' deficit and the elderly average age . I also think that in the future , students will have to give their fingerprints to prevent burglaries . But I suppose sitting in wooden chairs in front of a desk will never change , because it is the only way teaching can be done . 
Dear mayor , I ’m writing to you regarding the issue with the use of portable devices , such a mobile phone in public spaces . Recent research indicates that the number of users in the last years has rapidly increased . Especially the newer generations want to have all the mod cons to hold a < u201C > step with the time < u201D >. On the one hand , during the usage of mobile phones in public places , people are showing a disrespect to the community . On the other hand , for many people , mobile phones are a necessity due to work or a private matter . That ’s means they must use their mobile phones , for example , in a restaurant . There is no doubt in my mind that there is a need for taking measures regarding this matter . The burden of responsibility lies in the hand of any of us . As regards the most appropriate response to this situation , one suggestion would be to start a campaign to show the nation the disadvantages of overusing their mobile phones in public places . In my opinion , it would be wrong to take the law into your own hands and completely prohibit using cell phones . It would be great to put all factors into perspective before concluding . The world would surely be a better place to live in if we all have respect for each other . After all , we are only humans but have all the time in our hands to make a better tomorrow for our children . 
Yes , I like to exercise . Going to the gym is my hobby and I do my routine 5 days per week . I love it . I definitely prefer to do training inside because I feel I can concentrate more . My favorite exercise is doing squats and I enjoy the treadmill . I also like barbells , dumbbells and doing heavy lifting . 
Yes , I do like exercise . I often do exercise on two or three days every week . When I am doing exercise , I prefer to do it outside because I can explore nature at the same time . My favorite exercises are jogging and bicycling . 
As a working single mum , I do not have a lot of free time . But yes , I have some occasionally . Any time I 'm free I love to spend in the gym and doing exercises . This is very empowering for my body and mind . I just got back from training 30 minutes ago , and I feel amazing . I will recommend this to everyone . 
Hello Matt , Great to hear from you . Yes , you are right , I want to improve my English because it is necessary for further study . My plan is to write essays every day and do a lot of reading . I watch TV in English as well ; I 'm sure this helps . 
Hello Samantha , It was lovely to hear from you . You asked me the last time about my favourite movie . It is very difficult to say . It 's hard to choose just one . I think it is " Match Point . " This story is about an Englishman who became rich . I think you will like this movie because you like all of Woody Allen 's movies . 
Hello Jack ! I was so happy to hear from you . Let me explain a little bit more about birthday traditions in my country . Well . . nothing to say really : ) it is exactly the same as in Poland . My last birthday I also spent in a restaurant and I invited friends and family . I did have a birthday cake and candles and they also sang " Happy Birthday " to me . I hope to hear from you soon . Bye , 
Like I said before , I do not have a lot of free time . But every day I try to organize at least one hour in which to do my exercise routine . I have been a gym member for the last year and I truly love it . This empowers me and gives me so much positive energy . 
