Hi Leila , I hope you are OK . Firstly , I want to apologise because I could not come to your party . As you remembered , my family was visiting me last week and I was busy looking after them . And , exactly on that day , I had booked cinema tickets for me and my mum and I could not cancel that evening . I hope you can understand . Please , tell me how it was . Did you have a nice evening ? What about next week ? Do you fancy shopping together ? Bye , Miss you . 
Dear Mark , As I mentioned in my previous letter , at last , I convinced my father to go to cinema with me to watch my favourite movie , " The Matrix . " This is my sixth time watching The Matrix . Each time I watch it , I find some new information . I like this movie because it gives me a sense of why we are here in this world as humans and it makes me appreciate the beauty of my life . Especially , the character of Neo is amazing : the way he is presented and how he fits into the story . I believe if you give The Matrix chance , you would love it as well . 
I 'd like to study math because I could not understand some formulas that I was being taught in the previous semester in my class . I am a humanities person , but I think it is better for me to learn both math and literature . If you are available on Tuesday or Friday afternoon , do you think you could help me with this course ? 
I enjoy exercising very much . I try to do it every day . I prefer to exercise in the fresh air . I think it 's healthier than the gym activities . I like running and playing football with my friends . But my favorite activity is hiking in the mountains . I love mountain trips . 
Gdansk is a lovely city . The Old Town is just 20 minutes from the place I live in . My area is great , it is a walking distance to the beach and this is great during the summer time . If you want to go shopping , I would recommend " Alfa " as this is the best shopping centre in the city . My best place for walking is called " Regan 's Park , " this is a lovely quiet place . 
This is a great question . I have a 10 -year old boy . He loves video games and computer games . I agree with both . It all depends . There is nothing wrong with technology . When you play games , your imagination is working in an amazing way . It builds your creativity . On the other side , some adults and kids suffer from addiction . Not every situation is the same . I believe we are living in the amazing time in history and we can use technology any way we want to use it . It is very important to know your limits . Everything has to be balanced . Playing games and playing in the playground are equally important for kids . Both are important . My son does both . He 's a games ' lover , but he also enjoys meeting friends and cycling . You have to have a balance . We are living in a modern world and there is nothing wrong with this . 
I think this is a very difficult question , because if you think deeply , you can easily agree with both . Some of the questions are not possible to answer in just one word . Yes I agree . Animals belong in nature , but from another point of view , we learn a lot during observation in a zoo . I think all places like this have to be well prepared for animals , including huge extra space for certain animals . Yes , in a perfect world , all animals will be living free outside . But we are not living in a perfect world . We are still learning and we are still improving . This is what I think has to be done . Improvement . Another important thing is to make sure the right people work in the right departments , especially if we are talking about places like zoos . They have to love animals . This is important to make sure these people are responsible for all standards and that they are doing what is good for the animals . 
Studying abroad is a fantastic life experience . I can understand how difficult it is to live alone in a different country without friends and family . Anyway , in my opinion , there are a lot of benefits to doing this . First of all , if you study abroad and you are alone , the first thing you learn is responsibility for yourself . I believe if you live in a different country , you become a more open -minded person . It is very interesting to meet different people , try different food . This is a great time to learn or improve a new language . Of course , there are a lot of advantages and not everything is easy . You may feel lonely sometimes and you are not able to pop in for dinner to your grandma 's . Everything has a positive and negative side . I have lived abroad for 10 years . I will probably study here as well . I want to think this is a good choice . 
Well , of course not . I do not think every student has to learn music . It is not a basic important thing in our lives . Some people have a big passion for music and art , and they should have an opportunity and chance do study whatever they want to study . Not everyone is the same . I remembered myself as a child in primary school . I did not like music lessons . I had a very bad teacher and she pushed everyone to sing alone in front of the others . It was one of the worst experiences in my entire life . When I was a child , I was very shy . This situation did not help me at all . It was traumatic for me . Some people are great at sports activities . Some people have a mathematical mind . Some people love technology . There is no rational point for me to push students to play or sing . 
There is no better choice . I think it all depends on what type of person you are . Some people like to be independent and they are mature enough to live alone . Being alone gives them more space and they learn more about life and themselves . Some people may need extra support and attention from their parents or family . This is up to personal circumstances . I think it is nice to have a free head , free from worrying about food or washing . This is helpful if you study a lot . But from another point of view , I believe it is great to be an independent person . This is equally important with education . Which one is better ? Living on your own while you attend university or living at home with the family ? If you have a nice and helpful family . I would say " why not ? " 
I do not like video games . But a year ago , my son asked me a Play Station 4 as a birthday gift . My husband convinced me to buy the video game machine , considering that it was his birthday and we had the capacity to afford an expensive present . I remember that I had video games when I was a child , but I have never enjoyed them a lot . I was never a very good player . I think children should spend time playing games that involve physical activities . For the children 's development , it is important to run , to jump , to dance , etc . Video games are addictive . The children who play video games usually do not go outside to run or jump . Also , video games do not allow the social interaction that children need . In order to create a balance , my husband and have decided to limit the video game playing time . Also , my son has to do his homework before playing video games every day . He is in a baseball league which makes him exercise regularly and , every weekend , we go outside as a family . 
Greetings , I would like to state that I support this policy personally . Nowadays , even though the appearance of mobile phones does really have a huge positive impact on our everyday life in aspects of convenience , we unfortunately have a few more issues due to the over -reliance on mobile phones . That is , the reasons for banning the phone in public areas will help people to live a healthy life . First of all , people will see how the policy helps them by acknowledging the risk of not paying enough attention to their surroundings . For example , last week 's accident in a coffee shop near my apartment happened just because all the victim 's attention had been drawn to their mobile phone , which makes them unable to react when it is still not too late to do so . Therefore , if we decide to forbid mobile phones in public areas , it will save a lot of people from scalds when they can notice it early . Second , it is not hard to find out that a lot of people tend to have humpbacked poses while using their phone , it may be common to everyone . Nevertheless , the potential risk to our spine is definitely one thing no one ever wants to run into . If people do not correct their stance while using a phone or just prevent themselves from using it too much , it is reasonable to have such a strict policy to protect our citizens . As a result , restricting people from using phones might be inconvenient , but it is still good for public health in the long run . 
Last week , I went to a concert of Maan . Maann is 23 years old and her music genre is pop and hip -hop . She has won the Voice of Holland and has since broken through in the Dutch music industry . First , she sang in English , but then made the step to Dutch . I think she is the best and nicest singer in the Netherlands . And I can also do almost all of her songs . The concert took place in Paradiso Amsterdam . A very nice venue . She sang all her songs from her new album and sometimes guests like Ronnie Flex and Tabitha came by . And I had so much fun ! 
In my free time , I like to ride a bike . I do it almost every day . I go to my work by my bike . I use it on weekends also . My girlfriend and I are members of a bike club that organizes bike trips on Sundays . I like this activity because I can improve my condition and also visit new places . Last time I did this was one month ago . We went by bike to visit a local museum . 
Yes I do like to exercise . I do work outs about 3 times a week on a regular basis . I prefer to gym outside . In the winter , I often do an exercise on the Tacx home trainer . The exercises that I do like the most are running and cycling . I also like swimming . 
In my free time , I spend time with my family . Mid week I go after dinner for a run . Due to the Corona virus we have had to stay at home over the last few weeks , so there are not many trips outside the house . Meanwhile I cycled 3 times to work this week . The thing I like most about cycling is the early morning ride . You can see the sunrise . The last time I cycled to work was last Friday . 
People have been always told that honesty is one of the most important virtues since they were little , which means they should always avoid lying to others . Even though no specific reasons were given at that time , teachers prefer to tell children moral stories . When someone looks back on his childhood through photo albums , these memories might be reminiscent of how necessary it is to be honest as their teacher once told them . That is , people will have to face several consequences if they are found being deceitful . There is a really simple fact about lying to others , and they will choose not to listen to you next time . That is as clear as it seems . However , if our society has fraudulent criminals disguised as charitable helpers all over the place , it would have a devastating impact on people 's faith about giving a hand to those in need in the long run . When it is becoming harder and harder for them to receive any help , it could be one of most despairing things can happen to society . Also , bragging about yourself , as a form of lying , always makes your feelings hollow eventually . Not to mention , trying to cover up these lies with other lies , and it will end up out of hand . Last but not least , lying will make you blind to where you can improve to be a better person overall . Not knowing their short -comings , some people create a false impression of themselves by lying to others . Those are my thoughts about how unacceptable it is to tell a lie . 
In my free time , I usually go out to take photos . I do it on at least one day every week . Photography has given to me the ability to freeze moments of my life which I can enjoy again in the future and share these moments with people who have not had the chance to be there with me . The last time I did it was in Budapest , when the Coronavirus let me take photos of the city when it was not too crowded . 
Recent research indicates that life span has increased through the last decades . Even if we have a way more dynamic life than our ancestors , humanity has made a huge development in medicine , which allows us to live longer . What impact , if any , have these developments had on the general public ’s opinion ? There is no doubt that most of the people would want to live a long intense life . However , we ’re not able to choose for how long we can stay on the earth . Anyway , we could decide if our remaining years will be intense or not . Let ’s consider the two situations . Firstly , if we could have a relatively long life indulged with plenty of leisure time , Weu2019ll maybe bee less career oriented and abandon ourselves more pastime . So , we could have more time for socializing and bringing our friends and acquaintances together . Secondly , if we consider a shorter life filled with intension . In my opinion , the master work in this case is to find the right work -life balance . Our lifestyle needs to be so aligned that we can compromise having a successful career and enough time to hang out with our family , spouse and friends . The world would surely be a better place to live in if everybody had a satisfying life filled with enjoyment and happiness . The obvious conclusion to be drawn is that we are confronted with a limited duration of lifetime , so we are forced to use it for the best . 
I do not like to exercise . I exercise less than once a week , so I make myself walk a lot and stretch my body every day . When I exercise , I prefer exercising in a gym . In a gym , I do not have to care about being watched by passersby or I am not affected by the weather . 
In my rare free time , I like reading books and watching films a lot . I like to read self -help books because they improve my self -confidence . Generally I select films with laureate actors : they know how to act dramatically and the scenes become more sensitive . Yesterday I watched a film , a very good one , and I had time to read some pages of a good book . 
In my free time , I enjoy walking through nature , walking around and seeing if you can find something interesting . Nowadays , I do this around one or two times a week . I enjoy walking around in nature because it clears up your mind and you completely forget what stressing work you did before that . The last time I walked around was yesterday , it was rather windy , and that made it cold , but the sun was out and I enjoyed myself . 
I am very satisfied with my marks in English and philosophy , as I have got an A + in both the subjects . However , I think there is still space of improvement in the latter , as I do not quite feel comfortable in that subject . I often perceive that I just do not understand the context of the philosophers ' theories , for instance . One of my worst subjects is music , yet unfortunately , it is , besides German , my advanced course . I am not bad in it , though , at least it is still an A , even though with an appendaged minus . But I must have high expectations , due to the difficulties you can come across with getting a rare place at university . But how to improve in music ? I could ask my music teacher in the case I do not understand her explanations . It is also always helpful to become more devoted to the lessons , as the written examinations only count a third . Just raising your hand more frequently can work wonders , I guess . 
In 2017 , we spent a fortnight in Edinburgh , Scotland . It was an important experience for me because I had just begun being interested in the English language and culture . We did a lot of standard tourist programmes , including two bus trips through the Highlands . Even though I normally despise mountains , I could not help be fascinated by the magnificent Scottish mountains and their light green tinge . Furthermore , we visited the famous Edinburgh Castle , which lies exactly in the center of the city . We even hiked in the bosom of Edinburgh , as there is a vast stretch of land incorporating large rocks only a few bus stops further on . And believe it or not : There was access to the North Sea as well ! Sea , mountains , and a capital city , all in one ! Moreover , that holiday gave me a first -hand experience about how multifaceted the English language with all its different accents is . Even being a complete layman in that language back then , I could notice that the Scottish people spoke differently from what I had so far heard . All in all , that stay was one of my best holidays I ever had , maybe even the best of all . 
Hi Leyla , I could not come to your party because I had a bad headache and fever . How was the party ? Did you have fun ? Did all your friends come ? I think I can come next weekend to your house . I ca not wait for that day ! Our mothers will talk about this . See ya ! Cezara 
Nowadays , it is a fact that the vast majority of children like to spend their time playing video games . I think that it is a good way of entertaining but only if it is done with control . Firstly , it is understandable that parents do not like video games because they can bring about several problems to their kids , for example , they can make them more violent , antisocial , addicted ... . On the other hand , I believe that this hobby can help young people because it can bring some benefits too , such as improving their creativity , developing their imagination , helping them to make friends ... A further point is that the most important facts when deciding if video games are good or bad are how much time you spend and what type of video game you are playing . In conclusion , from my point of view , video games are not such a negative thing like most parents think , but it all depends on how much control you have when you are playing them . 
