When I was a child , video games were launching . It was very excited and it was considered to be an encouragement for some neuromuscular and cerebral exercises . But they have become very popular and sometimes take so much time from young people that they become a concern , not only for parents but educational professionals and public health . Some of those young people are so involved with video games that they forget of their actual responsibilities like studying and working . If they are not used so much but only for leisure , enjoying time with friends , they are healthy . But the problem is that this line is so subtle . Beyond these problems , they increase the risk of obesity and its consequences . In my humble opinion , I think parents could establish limits for their children , such as time for enjoying video games , but time for their studying ; they should also encourage physical activities or playing physical games . 
