At this time of inequality in the world , a big round of applause must be given to the front -line volunteers who have been battling poverty and health issues for underprivileged people . We are in desperate need for more volunteers in order to continue the fight and win this poverty war . Forcing high schools to complete volunteer work might increase the number of volunteers in the short run , however , it is not sustainable in the long run . This requirement can impose on students to take positive action for their community , but it will not highlight their concern over the struggling of the underprivileged in their community to cope with the worsened air pollution , drought and hunger . Forcing students without educating them about volunteer work can mark a new point of conflict . They will solve the problem without emphasizing the beneficial living conditions . I suggest the school initiate the volunteer course . This course will make the students believe and be interested in the volunteers ' work story given out by the guest teachers who have adopted volunteer work into their routine life . This course will mention a possible way to start volunteer work easily . If the students are educated , it will be easy to convince them to take small steps in action . To make volunteer work contagious , the school needs a wise communication campaign and intriguing reward . The school might offer a certificate for those who have finished this volunteer course . The purpose of this course is to mitigate the damage from misunderstood actions . Enlightening the value of volunteer work instead of imposing a school requirement seems to be an effective and sustainable approach to ensure all students have access to a set of knowledge before taking the meaningful work for others . 
