How employees feel at work is becoming a main focus nowadays . Managers admitted that workers are more effective when they feel comfortable at work and , for the last recent years , have wondered how to make it happen . In order to make workers comfortable , a lot have ideas have seen the light . New work organisations have appeared like : homeworking , open spaces , relax rooms , and many more . In my opinion , all of these arrangements are an excellent thing . The new open spaces , one of the best ideas of these new organisations . First , open spaces broad to the co - workers the chance to communicate much more . They are now able to exchange information much more quickly than before . In cubicles , people had to phone their co -workers or go to their desk in order to give some information . Also , open spaces are a good way to reinforce team building , and to create an even stronger team spirit . When people are in enclosed workstations , they easily can forget they are a team . With open spaces , relationships between co -workers are stronger . Of course , open spaces can offer some difficulties toward some employees . Some people find it too noisy and are having trouble to concentrate on their work . Other people will miss their intimacy , and might feel uncomfortable in a space with no walls . For the first difficulty , employees can use headphones to reduce the noise , and not be disturbed for a time period . For the second difficulty , it 's up to every employee to decorate their desk with photos , or souvenirs to make it more intimate . Regarding this different points , I believe open spaces are a great new way to organize the work place and should be encouraged . 
