Nowadays , people who live in the affluent countries are getting older . Therefore , the demand for medical access is increasing swiftly . However , there are a less medical doctors in the rural areas compared to cities . There are various reasons why a medical doctor prefers to work in a city than a rural area , according to different research that has been executed by different European medical hospitals . First of all , some research that was conducted by Erasmuc MC in the Netherlands shows that medical doctors prefer to work in cities because of their family . Both their wives and children are against living in a small city , therefore doctors have to make a difficult decision . Moreover , it turns out that the partner of the medical doctor a work has that is settled in a city . Secondly , medical doctors have problems that are associated with transport if they want to work in a rural area . The roads in a lot of wealthy countries are getting busier , so traffic jams are increasing rapidly . This problem has deterred medical doctors from working in rural areas . Many medical doctors show that they are willing to work in rural areas , however they avoid these areas due to the traffic jams . On the other hand , the research indicated that there are medical doctors who avoid rural areas because the care demand in a rural area is lower than a city . In big cities , there a lot of people , therefore the demand to care activites is higher than a rural areas . To summarize , a medical doctor would earn more money if he or she worked in a city than in a rural area . To solve this problem , the government has to stimulate the use of public transport . If the people who work in other sectors use more public transport instead of cars , the traffic jams would decrease . This will make it easier for medical doctors to travel from the city to a rural area . Another solution would be that the health insurance companies paid more to those who work in a rural areas to stimulate medical doctors to work in a rural area . 
INTRODUCTION Telling the truth has been an issue always argued for centuries , and all men have always wandered the importance of it . Poets , philosophers , musicians and , more generally , every kind of artist have posed the question . However , I think that neither themselves nor their audience can be given an exhaustive answer . WHAT IS THAT ? In accordance with some of the most prestigious philosophical theories , we cannot find a precise statement to sum up what the truth is . In other words , they argue that the truth does not exist . To be more precise , they assume that there is not only a single truth , but thousands or billions of examples of it . Everyone of us knows what is real for him and the underlying reasons that lead him to believe in something . EXAMPLES As I see it , telling the truth is not always the best thing to do . In the same cases , a lie is a way to protect people , especially our dearest and nearest . On the other hand , every one of us should be intuitive enough to know when the moment to lie or tell the truth is , and above all , recognise who is ready to accept a difficult and harmful truth even when it could convey a big sorrow . Some examples can be related to relationships or diseases where your doubts do not let you to decide what is better for others . CONCLUSIONS As I said before , we are required a large quantity of braveness , but also a sharp spirit of observation to decide when the moment to speak clearly is . 
