My opinion is that it is good to study abroad for a time during high school or university . There are 2 advantages . First you can learn something abroad , which people who live in Japan cannot experience . You have some different experiences , so that you have your own strong points and you can be successful in the future . Those who can think of an original idea are always needed for all fields . Second , you can learn another language . It is difficult to learn a language unconsciously as we get older . No matter what language you may study , it must be your strong point if you can master it . And if you can speak a language , you can communicate with many people . You can improve your personality with this experience . On the other hand , there are also 2 disadvantages . First , no one can know whether the environment where you go will suit you . The risk of leaving your hometown is bigger than you expect . It is not big problems where you can check some information in advance , like diseases or a culture . But you cannot check what the locals are like and how the weather and the humidity will influence on you . These are serious problems . Next , if you think you will be successful as an elite in Japan , I do not recommend you to study abroad . It may be not good for your career , because the Japanese culture is so unique and many Japanese come to be conservative as they get older . You do not need to take an additional risk . You 'd better enter a high school and a university in Japan . Anyway , I approve of the opinion that students should study abroad in their youth . The experience you get there is your treasure . 
To be honest , I think that video games are dangerous . They reward you with too much dopamine for too easy tasks . Everything else is so hard in comparison to games . Children do not want to do something useful , because the dopamine rush produced by video games is so high . Everything else seems too boring and it decreases their productivity and development . One of the biggest problems is that video games can result in increasing violent behavior . Soldiers are learning a huge responsibility with their weapons . It is strictly regulated when they can use violence and they know all the consequences . But in video games , children are receiving good points for killing a virtual enemy , with no punishment for killing innocent people . They are used to killing . They are nurtured to kill without consequences . Another thing is that the video games do not reflect reality . You can drive a virtual car at a speed of 200 mph and there is no danger from doing it . So why should you drive responsibly in real life if you do not know any better ? 
I do not think zoos are good places at all . I have never liked them , all that animal abuse makes me sad . But thanks to new technologies , like the Internet and virtual reality , people can learn about animals differently nowadays . For example , in Japan , they 've created a 7D Holographic Projection Display Zoo , where you can get close to animals safely , both for the animal and for the visitors . With this technology , reality feels close , because it uses different dimensions to capture an object ( 7 Dimensions ) . Reality has a 3D space , we know that , but the reason why we are talking about so many dimensions here is because the hologram is captured from a large number of positions and each position is described in a 3D space . And each captures a variety of viewing directions in a 2D space . Plus , two additional parameters are captured for each direction : image intensity and time . In other words , 7D technology is like having a bunch of photographers surrounding an object . This technology is fascinating and can help us to get into the wild and learn about it without animal abuse . Maybe in the past zoos were important for us , helping us to see nature in a fantastic way . The times have changed and we need to catch up with the changing times . 
I spend my free time watching films . There are a bunch of films on Netflix , Amazon Prime , and so on . They seem to be interesting and funny . Thus I book many of them on " my list " and watch them later , probably at the weekend . 
In these times I am forced to use my computer more than I normally do . In these times I use my computer for around one or two hours every day , this is more than I used to . I use my computer mostly for school : lessons , essays and other tasks , but in my spare time I play games on it . I prefer gaming on my computer over writing essays . 
I have heard : Music accounts for 80 % of life . In my opinion , we should learn music or learn how to play a musical instrument . There are a lot of musical instruments so if you do not like the drums , you can be interested in the piano or guitar and so on . I think there are many benefits if we know how to play an instrument . Firstly , music will make you feel happier and love life more . You will be more motivated to do more and more good work . Your soul will be relaxed and comfortable and have more energy than before . Secondly , music also helps you love yourselves more . You will respect yourselves and behave well with them . If sometimes you feel stressed , you should close your eyes and listen to some soft music . You will feel better than before . Thirdly , learning a musical instrument is not only good for morale , but is also improves your IQ . Fourthly , your reflexes will be more sensitive and you can solve the situation or problem quickly . Finally , learning a musical instrument is a way to discover your talent . From that , you wo not miss your chance to grow . Therefore , we should learn them . 
ENGLISH , ONE OF THE MOST IMPORTANT THINGS IN MY LIFE I started learning English when I was 5 years old , but it was not until I was 11 that I realised how much this language means for me . On the one side , English is the most spoken language in the world . Therefore , knowing how to speak it is really worth it . It will bring you better jobs , more opportunities and quite a bit more prestige , not to mention how useful it will be for you when you travel and can speak easily with everybody . On the other side , English is really important to me because it has made me discover the delightful American and English cultures , with which I have fallen in love . And it has helped me to finally know what I want to do in my life , which I was struggling to sort out . To sum up , I really think that English is a very important language to learn nowadays , not only because it will bring you a great deal of opportunities , but also because it will help you to grow as a person and will open your eyes to the real world . 
Television can educate us , but only on the surface . You do not know the sources of the information from television . You have to watch with caution and check the information and make comparisons with other sources , like books . The problem is that television needs to get your attention . So it has to be exciting or funny . And real events sometimes seem boring , so the directors make them a little more spicy . For example , they connect two different events into one or they may double the number of enemies in a historical battle . Education via television really depends on the quality of the screenwriters and advisers . Usually , the most capable scientists do not work for television . They write books and teach at universities or work in business . So I think that television can educate us , but it cannot be the primary source of knowledge . 
As we know , health is wealth and it is a well known fact and universally accepted . If you are healthy , then you can enjoy your life as you wish . But for a healthy life , you have to give sufficient time for exercise . Meanwhile , many more things are as important as exercise in different age groups of human beings ' lives , which I wish to explore in this writing . As we know , there are the three basic stages of life , childhood , adulthood and old age and every stage has its own importance and liabilities . When one is a child , one had to learn things , while for that they had parents and teachers . No doubt , at an early age of life like childhood and teenage , they do not have family and social liabilities and they can arrange a lot of time for physical activities , like exercise and playing outdoor games , while a lot of time is needed for studying if they want to beat any competition . In addition , most teenagers are healthy . Meanwhile , when you grow up and get married , you have a lot of liabilities , like social life , caring for parents , with their own personal family and also earning money and enhancing their skills and qualities to get promotion in their job or business . 
I am going to describe my experience with Write and Improve . To begin with , I totally like it for four reasons . Firstly , its variety of topics . Since I can face to many kinds of topics , I improve my writing skill more and more . Secondly , its marking speed . As soon as I push the check button , it marks and corrects my writing . It saves a lot of time . Thirdly , its score history . I can see my past grades . It allows me to know how I am improving my writing skill and stay motivated . Lastly , its design . It is very tidy and helpful to go around the site . However , I have one dislike point . It is its correction degree . It is very hard to understand where or how I can correct my writing to make it better . It adds shades to the sentences , but is not helpful . I want it to add more detailed notes to my writing . Finally , I really rely on this service . I recommend you to start using it . 
Have you ever thought that the means of travelling will change in the future ? There is nothing in the world you think that people are not capable of doing . Let us have a look at the progress we have made until now . For a start , smartphones are developing each day . If you compare to what we had twenty years ago , you will see that non -touchscreens do not exist anymore . Mobiles phones possess a lot of applications that can replace most of the devices that we use every day , such as a calculator or a chronometer . I must also mention that cars have developed too , particularly hybrid cars , which did not exist two decades ago . Apart from that , some buses can work without a driver . They can detect people who want to take the bus via an application . Personally , I believe that in twenty years , there will be a huge change in the means of travelling . Maybe journeys through time may be possible . Who knows ? 
Have you ever imagined what it would be like if Summer did not exist ? There is nothing in the world like going to the beach or sunbathing . You can appreciate those feelings only in Summer , when the weather is hot . For a start , we can buy ice cream everywhere , especially by the shore , and that with all flavours , such as chocolate , vanilla or mocca . I must also mention that you do not have to wear a coat or tights and particularly gloves and a bonnet . Apart from that , it is not very possible to catch a cold or have the flu like in Winter . Personally , I believe that Summer is like a sort of holiday for everybody and it is not that bad , even if sometimes we can have hay fever . But for me , Summer is the best season , because the daylight lasts longer than in Winter . 
There are four main sources for our human life . They are exercise , diet , oxygen and water . Our health needs a workout , therefore exercise is essential . However , if you are doing exercise without a diet , it is not effective . Dramatic dieting keeps up with exercise though . Firstly , exercise not only improves our heath , but also our body . Recently , all around the world , the obesity rate has grown higher and higher . Because of that , they do not have extra time to make a meal and only rely on take -out food , which has loads of fat and salt . For example , instant noodles are pretty popular globally and most people have those instead of meals . Secondly , gyms are getting more and more expensive , that 's why people also need money . Apparently , working hours are longer and it is more competitive to get a better job or earn a load of money . Last but not least , diet is vice - versa with exercise , which can keep you fit . For example , some people do not do exercise , but they eat a balanced diet , so they live for more than one hundred years . On that document , do not underestimate diet . In conclusion , exercise is essential for our health , but some of the following things need to be kept up . 
Dear Thảo , How are you ? I miss you so much . Today , I 'm writing this letter to you to share with you my favourite film . As you know , I really like watching films , such as romantic films , science fiction films or comedy films . In all of them , what I enjoy most is Harry Potter by J . K . Rowling . That is a science fiction film . There are a lot of people who like this film or this story . For me , I like this film because of its meaning . After the wars , the suspense , there is the brave , intelligent main character Harry Potter and his best friends Ron Weasley and Hermione Granger , ready to fight against the evil forces . Finally , they win , that means righteousness is always victorious over evil . So , I think you should watch it . If we have a chance , we will watch it together . I 'm looking forward to your reply . Send me your letter soon . Your best friend , Blue Berry . 
Hello , Today I want to write to you about my favorite film . It is not easy to point to one , the most favourite . So I decided that I will write about the first film I remember when I think about my favorite film . It is called Vanishing Point . According to my opinion , the main character of the film is a car , a Dodge Challenger . It sounds strange , does not it ? But it is quite a deep film . The plot is simple . A driver , whose name is Kowalski , has to deliver the car to some distant place and time is running out . But there is deeper meaning . It is about freedom and about the human soul . Kowalski reaches his breaking point and sets himself free of all the conventions and just drives . He meets some interesting people on his journey too . Altogether , it is really a masterpiece . I guess you can try it yourself . Let me know if you liked it . I am looking forward to your answer . Best wishes , Kuba 
I love my free time . I respect that free time . I have a lot of things to do or to think about in my free time . I usually watch the sky and think about goals , health , the voice from my heart and what things I have done . I always listen to music or watch my favorite films . Sometimes , I write my diary . I usually read books . I read from a lot of categories such as science fiction , . . . I also play sports with my best friends . Of these , I like reading books the most because they make me love life more and have more motivation to do good works and to study . So I really enjoy and respect my free time . 
The future of travel Nowadays , everybody uses a way of travelling . Whether it is by a personal car or taking public transport , people need to go to their job , because the majority of them do not work near their homes . However , I think that in the future , travel will be different . Technology is developing every day in order to help humans with their lives , so why would not creating new ways of travelling be possible ? I think that travel will change dramatically in the future . The trams might be suspended above the streets and descend when people need to get off . The cars ' engines will work on more ecological fuel , like compost or solar energy , instead of gas . There will also be more express trains , which will travel all the way around a continent , offering , in this way , the opportunity to see the world to more ordinary people . Whatever the future might bring , one thing that I think will not change for a good amount of time is the way in which airplanes work and look . These are already quite developed and I do not see what changes might be brought to them . The truth is that nobody can surely know what inventions will be brought to life in the future . But the thing I am sure of is that these will surprise us . 
My name is Daniel and I started to use Write and Improve two days ago , so my experience with this website is not very long . What I noticed in the first few days is the team 's professionalism . They have plenty of subjects to cover every level , even if you are beginner or advanced . One of the things that I appreciate most on this website is the feedback which they give you after every activity . In my opinion , this feedback helps the students a lot , because this is the only way you can know if you are right or wrong . I found many websites on the internet where you can practice your writing , but not many of them give you feedback . If one of my friends/colleague asks me about a place where they can improve their writing , my advice will be to use this website . I 'm very happy that I found the website and now I can practice my English . 
In my opinion , studying abroad is the best way to improve knowledge . As for improving languages or about any other knowledge , living abroad offers the opportunity to exchange some experiences , so we can learn more . The problem is that living abroad is not always good for everyone . You can miss your family and friends . You have to adapt to new cultures and sometimes they 're against your beliefs . And you need some money of course , especially if you are from a country where your currency has less value than the country you are moving to . But when you are far from your family and friends , you can establish new relationships . You can reflect on how your life is going . Which is better for you , the way your country lives or the way of life of a different country ? Of course , studying abroad , you are going to expand your social circle , because you will meet people from different countries . Maybe instead of disadvantages , we will have more advantages . 
I think that in the future , humans will be able to buy flying cars we might get rid of some means of transportation , like the bike , the bus , etc . I think that we are not going to walk anymore , I think that we are just going to travel in a more sophisticated and modern way . I think there will be flying hotels ! The flying hotels will transport you to where you want to go , while you relax and have fun in the hotel during your stay . Maybe we are even going to live on Mars ! I think that life on Mars would be cool , with lots of new means of transportation . I think in the future there are going to be beds inside cars , like you go peacefully to your bed and drive at the same time ! I think it would be cool to see all those modes of transportation in the future . 
