I agree with the opinions that video games can have a negative impact on children . They have many negative points and few positive points . To begin with , I 'll show you two negative points . Firstly , their violent situations . Children cannot recognize the difference between real and virtual . Secondly , the time . Children may spend a lot of time playing games . As a result , they do not make time to study , which is the duty of children . Well , do not we have a compromise plan ? Yes , we have . It is intellectual games . I think this is the only positive point the video games have . Playing intellectual games , for example studying games or puzzle games , children can activate their brain . It is very useful to improve their structural thinking . In conclusion , I almost agree with the opinions that video games can have a negative impact on children , however I also have a compromise plan , that intellectual games can be valuable for children . 
My favourite indoor activity is tennis . I usually take a racket and I play with three colleagues on the court wall . We do not have the same level , so we often play the best one with the worst one . We play for an hour and we are very tired when we finish each match . We enjoy playing this sport a lot , but we have not been playing recently . We have to go to work and we work at different times , so it is very difficult for us to be able to meet up to play . 
I use a computer every day . I use a computer when I go to work , but I do not use it all the time . I use it for about two hours at work . But when I go home I always switch on my computer and I usually use it for studying English . I hardly ever use my computer for playing computer games . I 'd prefer to play with a game console . My computer is my best friend . I like it a lot . 
Hello everybody , it 's Nael ! Today , I will talk to you about a website for learners of English . Many people say it is very hard to find a great website or a great tool to learn English , but today , I will present to you the best website to improve your abilities and skills in English when you are beginner or confirmed . Its name is Write and Improve , this website was created by Cambridge University in 2016 , it is free and it is very easy to access . First of all , on this website , you can write about many subjects , like global warming or your favorite hobbies , according to each level and , when you have finished , a robot checks all your answers and it shows you all your right and wrong answers . After that , you can see your evolution and be better than yesterday , you can practice by yourself all the time and also be more confident when you write in English . Personally , I have used " Write and Improve " for two months and I can see a very big progression between when I started and now . I have also increased my vocabulary and I 'm able to write an email . I recommend you " Write and Improve " for many reasons , but if I have to choose only one to come here , it will be because it 's pretty easy to learn on " Write and improve " and do not forget , studying is the worth thing you have to do . 
Firstly , Write and Improve provides me the opportunity to write English . If you carry on every day , it is meant to improve your English writing skills . Learning English is sometimes quite solitary , so it could be helpful to receive the correct sentences . Secondly , Write and Improve corrects my wrong words and weird sentences . We , the Japanese , are careless of articles so much because this idea never exists in Japanese . Meanwhile , there are many intricate words which have similar meanings , thus we also struggle to find appropriate words for each sentence . I think native speakers feel that Japanese English is weird . We sometimes really do not know which word is correct on a case by case basis . However , Write and Improve teaches me the correct word in my sentences . Finally , I got to look up these intricate words in the dictionary . Write and Improve encourages me to learn English deep inside . Therefore , I strongly recommend my classmates to try Write and Improve and keep up their English practice . 
Since I always have plenty of projects to carry out , I do not have enough free time , therefore as soon as I find some spare time , I appreciate it and try to utilize it effectively . One of my favourite hobbies is reading ancient novel books . Reading such books takes me from the present time and brings me a new environment to spend time in , so I am able to find moments in which I am living in another time far away from the chaos of my life , and which makes my mind feel relaxed . I try to read these types of books every day and make it a habit . 
I work as a graphic designer , so I always use a computer . If I work at home , I do not use a computer , instead it is a laptop . I usually use a computer for work and to learn skills on the internet . In my spare time , I surf social media on my computer , read the news and watch movies . I love working the most with my computer because I can earn a lot of money . 
During quarantine , I found myself having a lot of free time on my hands . My English teacher advised me to practise my English with the help of Write and Improve . I really like that everything is automated . Therefore , you do not feel the pressure of someone judging you , which gives me more freedom to write and practise . I also like that the feedback is provided very quickly . This encourages me to write more and it stays enjoyable . The only thing that maybe could improve the whole project is better feedback in grammar . I sometimes do not know why I am getting a low level score or why a sentence is wrong even if the spelling is on point . Because I am dyslexic it is very difficult for me to see my own mistakes in a sentence structure . I would recommend Write and Improve to everyone who wants to write more in English . I think the best way to learn English is to stay active with it . 
I read books in my free time . Whenever I have time , I want to read something . Reading is like a virtual journey and also you are being taught by famous experts . Therefore , I like to read and learn a lot from books . I am reading a text about programming written by a programming specialist now and I am enjoying it a lot . 
I like doing exercise a lot . When I was young I went with three friends to a court wall near our house . I wore a t -shirt , my shorts and my trainers . I took a racket and a ball . We played from eight to nine in the evening twice a week . When we finished we were very tired , but it did not matter because we enjoyed it a lot . In this confinement period , I do exercises indoor every day . I have an app on my smartphone and I do exercises with all the parts of my body . I like to be healthy . 
At first , I 'll tell you the advantages of studying abroad , after that the disadvantages . I have come up with three advantages . Firstly , you can study what you are interested in more deeply than in your country . It makes your knowledge broaden . Secondly , you can learn the language spoken there as well as English , the international language . It leads you to be a global person . Thirdly , you can feel the culture there , which you do not touch unless living there . It makes you understand the diversity of values . I think all of them are important or essential to be an educated person . It 's not vain for you to experience this life . Well , I have one concern , the disadvantage . It is that you may have to delay your graduation . It depends on the curriculum of your university . In case you want to graduate with your friends , you need to take care of the system . 
Volunteer work is an absolutely wonderful way to help others and grow within your experiences . People get the opportunity to help injured and sick children who are in hospitals or spend some time with animals in animal shelter . There are thousands of places where volunteer workers are hardly needed . I personally support the requirement of high schools . The students should be forced to learn that there are so many people who need our help . I am not just talking about hospitalized or homeless people . I am also focusing on the staff working there every day . They will be , for sure , more than happy to get a helping hand . The most important point is to let the students choose their preferred working place . The motivation to complete the amount of volunteer work will be there as long as the student likes and enjoys the work he is doing . Furthermore , the students will be impressed with how much joy it will bring into their lives when they can lighten up the day of another person . No amount of money could pay this amazing and heartwarming feeling off . Have you ever looked into the big , shiny and happy eyes of an thankful kid ? Yes , it is amazing ! Besides the joyful opportunity of helping others , the students will also learn what hard work looks like . It is the perfect preparation for life after high school . However , volunteer work will teach every student a lifelong lesson . They may even find inspiration for their future workplaces . I am very sure that some students will love the feeling of helping others and they could spend some months abroad and work perhaps in South America or Africa . 
Now I have a lot of free time but I do not have enough free time when I go to work . I work one month in the morning and the other one in the evening . When I work in the morning I usually have a nap . After that I study English for about an hour . Then I go out with my family and we meet up with our friends . On Wednesdays and Fridays my wife and I go to our children 's training . I like reading books in my free time and I also like watching TV series . 
As every grown person in the 21st century ought to know , not every human being looks , feels and desires the same as one other . Due to these facts , in order to respect each individual 's personality , a considerable amount of freedom should be given to each person . Inside the concept of freedom , free choice is an essential issue . On the one hand , despite I might sound quite idealistic , I have to say that I strongly respect and understand the importance of rules . Without them , our society would be an anarchism and daily life would be like putting an elephant into a car . However , regarding volunteer work , I have a completely solid point of view and I will wholeheartedly defend it . The reason why I am so concerned about this topic is that I absolutely believe that there are certain things that come out from the deepest part of our soul , and forcing those feelings and emotions result in an awful ending . Volunteer work is not for everyone , those courageous people who dare to volunteer have some kind of magical attitude inside themselves . Therefore , Incluiding this activity as compulsory at school could not be more useless . Nevertheless , there are endless activities to do in order to teach solidarity and empathy such as playing a team sport or planting trees . In conclusion , considering carefully all the things mentioned above , as far as I am concerned , only those who hugely desire to volunteer should do so . It does not mean they are better people , they just have something special to give to those people who absolutely need their help 
