When I was a child , video games were already quite diffused , but with time , their amount has grown . This is due to several factors : on one side , technological progress , on the other side , parents who are always busy every day and do not have time - nor patience - to stay with their children . I 've often seen exhausted parents who give their children their mobile phone so that those children would stay quiet for - at least - the following thirty minutes . And I 've also seen children who did not care going out with their friends , preferring instead to play with their Xbox console . This is a serious problem and governments should try to solve it , based on the very useful help of childhood psychologists and schools . I think children should be encouraged to spend time outside , playing , running , going on the roaller , biking . They need to understand what it means to stay in nature , they need to have time to explore what they are surrounded by . Moreover , staying in nature helps to develop stronger antibodies , which are always useful . Video games , if abused , can bring a child to believe what happens in them is real : so that maybe they can learn to believe that social relationships should be based only on social media interactions or that it 's fair and consented by law to kill , bite or ram someone with a car . Children should play video games for a limited period of their day also to preserve their vision . Video games are , however , a good option to spend some time in the day , maybe one hour or a little more , to socialize with friends if it 's raining and it 's not possible to go outside and to develop confidence with technological instruments from a young age because learning having fun is always a good thing . 
I agree with volunteer work as a requirement to graduate . For many years , volunteer work has been a requirement that high schools students must complete in order to graduate . When I was a high school student , I worked in the school 's library in order to clean , classify and arrange the books . Others planted a garden in the school , taught maths to younger students or helped in the city hospital . The experience taught me to manage the time . Also , I learned to be more tidy and responsible because of the classification and arrangement work . I learned that I had a boss who manages the work . I understand that the boss should teach , but sometimes , he does not do it . And finally , the boss always makes the rules . Personally , I understand that there are people who do not know how to work as a team and are just interested in achieving their goals . I ca not expect others to wait for me and I ca not wait for others who do not work as a team . 
There is no doubt these days , more people are caring for themselves , eating healthy food and doing exercise every day . The question is , is exercise important for health or are there other things important like it ? In this essay , I will discuss all the causes and draw my conclusion . In terms of the reason , it is said that exercise is really necessary . The main reason they give is it keeps our health better , we have to do it every day if you are busy or free . To illustrate that , exercise helps blood circulation work effectively . In other words , it increases the effectiveness of our heart , because of that , we have good health . Moreover , others believe to have good health , you have to focus on many things , like food , relationships , work , and exercise . This is because all of these things effect your health . In conclusion , some people say exercise is the only way to get good health , but others think there is more than one reason to have a healthy body . Therefore , I believe that exercise is significantly necessary for a healthy body , but other things like unhealthy food and hard work could effect our health if we are not paying attention . 
It goes without saying that there are different kinds of offices , after all , each country has its own culture , in addition to requiring different necessities . It is widely accepted that enclosed workstations are a good alternative when the profession demands more concentration . However , Could ? Would it be a more pleasant and productive fellowship to undertake ? 
I find this topic interesting . I have never given a thought about it , but I have my own choice related to the office furniture for employees . I am listing the important points which should be considered for finalizing the type of office design that is most appropriate for employees . These are : - 1 ) As employees sit with their co -workers , an adequate distance must be maintained . 2 ) Two employees who are sitting adjacently are not able to see each other 's computers or works . 3 ) All employees can be seen from one end . 4 ) The hall should be airy enough for maintaining good hygiene . 5 ) People who are dealing with clients must have sitting arrangements in front of them . 6 ) Sufficient space between two workstations must be maintained . Considering the all points mentioned above , we can think of a better design of office furniture . I will suggest the design which has two desks , i . e . two employees can work simultaneously . Both desks are adjacent to each other but separated by a wall . Each desk has a chair for clients in front of the employees . By providing a sufficient gap between the tables , optimum space can be utilized in the hall and the office will be airy enough at the same time . 
I belong to a typical countryside area , namely Canada , which is located 25 km from the main city centre . I have been living here since my childhood , it has been for 25 years now . It can be said that this place is a perfect example of magnificent beauty . It is a very spacious and peaceful place . It offers a host of services to its residents such as parks , restaurant , hotels , as well as educational institutes . This place is perfect if someone wants to admire the sky during the night time , the overall view is so picturesque that anyone can feel relaxed while looking at it . 
The fundamental idea sounds great . I support the idea that kids should do some work . There are so many children that do not know what work really is . The only problem is the word " volunteer . " Why call it that ? Is it some kind of political correctness ? If they have to do it , it is not volunteer work . And it is OK . Let 's be honest and call it duty . Duty is an important part of life , too . Children can learn the basic aspects of their duty in school . Without these programmes , the children would not be able to value the hard work which is done by the people around them . Hard work will make them humble and it is the most important part of the idea . Children should be humble or they will be humbled . Nothing is for free . Their parents can buy them stuff but to graduate they have to work . And that is right . 
