Do I want to live a long calm life or shorter more intense life ? I never thought about this . I understand some people may have different opinions , but if I could have a choice , I would answer I would prefer the first option . I wish to live a long life because I want to see how the world will change one year after another . I do like the advantages as well , but I believe I can do my hobby and stay calm . First of all , a few years ago , I started searching some information about meditation and this one is the subject I 'm very passionate about . This is why I do not feel like I do not need to look for an extremely intense situation in my life . I feel nice and stable during a normal day of doing nothing . I mean nothing extreme . My dream life is the possibility to wake up any time is suitable for me without rushing and stress , make myself a cup of coffee and slowly start to concentrate on my work I have to do . I do have a cycling passion , but it is just city cycling and , to be honest , I do not think it is extremely dangerous . I would not consider this hobby a dangerous one at all . To summarise , I wish to see how the future generation will change , this is why the length of my life is important to me . 
I am going to outline the most significant holiday I have ever had . What makes me say that was the best holiday I am exploring in this essay . Firstly , my young age life experience was not a smooth road , due to the fact that I had been staying with my paternal aunty and uncle in Myanmar ( Yangon ) , because my parents were earning money in Taiwan , so I had few chances to meet with them , only once in five years . When I was young , the technology had not improved so far . Nowadays , you can keep in touch with all countries , friends and family with internet applications , such as Messenger , Viber and Wechat , etc . I did not use to know my parents ' care , warmth , sweet hearts , patience and I was stuck with loneliness , monotony and cold . I wish I could have stayed with my parents every day , it was my dream . However , my dreams came true , because I got a chance to go to my parents in Taiwan . Taiwan is the heart of Asia , with a pack of skyscrapers . Among them , Taiwan 101 is the tallest and most breathtaking , also included in the world 's top ten tallest buildings . Other famous places are the night market , shopping districts , bubble tea , Chinese cuisine and snacks . I was on cloud nine going to Taiwan . When I got there , it was more sensational than I expected . My parents came to the Taoyuan airport and waited to meet me . When I saw them , I ran and embraced them . I stayed with them for about 5 or 6 months and had a very awesome experience in my life . I hung out with them , such as shopping , eating and playing some games . When I had to go back to Myanmar , they gave me so many souvenirs , snacks , gadgets and by the way , I got an i Phone present from my mother . So , in the nutshell , that holiday was the most exciting and tremendous experience in my life . I hope I will go back to Taiwan to meet my parents again . 
