These days , mobile phones have become an integral part of our daily life . Wherever we go or do , our mobile phone always remains with us . The technology associated with mobile phones keeps on upgrading and a lot of things can be done with phones . The mobile phone was invented for communication and , now , it can perform all kinds of jobs for which we generally use a computer or laptop . The enhancement of the use of phones is also because of the various social media apps which are very attractive and very difficult to get rid of it . I do not agree with the idea of banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants . The town council wants to limit the use of mobile phones in public places so that people around the mobile phone user should not get disturbed . I will suggest that , instead of banning mobile phones , the town council must start an awareness program regarding the benefits of limited use of mobile phones in public places . In addition to this , the town council should start penalizing the people who use the mobile phones other than for an emergency work . For more awarenesss , posters and advertisements should be done in every public places , it helps the user to understand the importance of limited mobile phone use . After a few weeks of advertising , the town council can start penalizing the users and gradually people will cultivate the habit of not using mobile phones in public phones . 
There are always arguments about zoos . On one side , they 're really appreciated , especially by children , on the other , they 're strongly criticized , especially by young people and animalists . Certainly , zoos should not exist in the way they currently do . We always see animals living in places , or to better say cages , in really different conditions from their original habitats . The animals seem to live in another world , far away from their reality . They often have astonished expressions , as if they have been hypnotized . They look tired and their movements are extremely slow . Captivity denies them their natural freedom and makes them like dolls to admire behind glass . I was taken to zoos too when I was a child , and sometimes I 've visited them more recently . When I was a child , I was excited , as is normal for a child , to see animals I did not even know existed , but right now I understand that it 's not good . In the Orecchiella Park , there are six hursas locked in 60 square metre cages under the sun . They seem to be suffering the heat of the summer quite a lot . Animals in zoos also loose their predator 's abilities , because they always get food , both from visitors , who give them food despite the denies - and the zoo 's employees . I agree more with safaris and natural parks , because animals which live there can benefit from better conditions and walk and run in bigger spaces , often pretty similar to their natural habitats . 
It is clear that the future of travel their own have different and same . In this essay , I am going to demonstrate about different and same . Based on my knowledge , there will be four main sources of traveling systems , such as the bus ( coach ) , normal train or underground , airway and cruise . The coach system is almost nearly perfect , that is why there is no way to change it a lot . Even though the normal train system is slow , farmers , cultivation person and who stay in outskirts person are relied rely on that due to the fact that it is cheap and accurate . The underground railway is absolutely accomplished , it will not change in future . Most people believe that there will be a supersonic speed train appearing soon . On the other hand , the airway system will not be dead because we all rely on aircrafts to travel aboard . Some scientists are planning to announce a gigantic aircraft , with faster speed and could allow to board more than one hundred people . And last but not least , a cruise is also a main support in transportation . I read an article in the newspaper , cruises will have more luxuries such as playgrounds , swimming pools and shopping centers , etc . and will also be faster , more accurate than in the past . Secondly , hotels will be the biggest change in the future . Instead of humans , they are planning to replace with robots . For instance , China , in some pricey restaurants , especially hotpots , if you order some side dishes , they come with robots and are served on your tables . And another example , in Japan , hotel staff are running with all robots , they can show you which room you reserved and give you some lunch , a dinner box and morning breakfast . My personal point of view , food will change consequently , traditional cuisine is being replaced by fast food , the which , . in the nutshell , I think the following things will change in the near future . 
Dear Rie , I was so excited when I received your letter . I really enjoy eating meals . So I have a lot of food to tell you about for the dinner . For the dinner , I 'd like to eat some food that has low calories and is also easy to digest . We should eat a little bowl of crab soup for an appetizer . After the appetizer , we could eat a mixed salad or mixed greens . Then we can enjoy the main dish with a plate of spaghetti . There are so many kinds of spaghetti that you can choose to cook , such as cream spaghetti , tomato spaghetti and so on . What about drinks ? We can choose orange juice or a fruit smoothie . They are good for the health . For dessert , we could also eat fresh fruit or seaweed . This is my opinion what about yours ? What about your menu for the dinner tomorrow ? Tell me soon , Rie . Of course , I can come to enjoy dinner with you and your family , it will be a really big pleasure for me . I 'm looking forward to your email , Rie . Your friend , Blue Berry 
Studying in another country has recently had a growing trend among students in different degrees . Although this experience has some positive effects on the student 's life , its drawbacks cannot be denied . On the one hand , to study abroad , students have to learn a new language and overcome the language barrier in the new country , which is a very valuable experience . Besides , they will be in touch with a new culture and new people and this would help them to improve their interpersonal skills . Also , the experience of studying in another country could be a bright spot on the student 's resume and enhance their employment chances . On the other hand , being away from their family can be a difficult aspect of this matter for some of the students . Furthermore , when they feel the lack of family support , they may feel homesickness and depression , which may affect their performance in the university or college . 
I 've studied English since 2018 . My first teacher is called Vinicius and is not a native teacher . He has not been in the USA or England and his only experience with the language was speaking with a native , but I really liked him . Two year later , I changed my English teacher . Now , my sister teaches me and it 's been working it all . As she actually lives in the USA , she has daily contact with native speakers . So , she can share with me all the knowledge that she 's learned on the streets or in her job . Then , with my experience , I can just see positive points to having new teachers because my current teacher is better than the last one . If , instead , the change of teacher had resulted in a worse teacher now , I think that I would not share this idea . Thus , having new teachers can work if you trust your new teacher . If you 're sure that you 'll win with that teacher change , go on ! 
Hi , Thank you for inviting me . I 'm going to your house tomorrow night with my homemade cake . I would like to eat a delicious beef stew because it 's pretty cool recently . See you , Yoko 
To improve my English writing , I 've started using an on -line platform called " Write&Improve . " It has been really useful to me because I finally had the chance to get my writing checked . My opinion about this platform is very positive . I found it extremely easy to use , very intuitive . The layout is clear and linear . Write&Improve offers exercises of several difficulty levels : everyone can practice using this platform . There are exercises for beginners , for intermediate ones and for advanced ones . It is also possible to develop our English business skills . I found very interesting the possibility to get back to my past writing to try make them better . The checking process is very fast and it is the most useful part of the platform . I could verify my ortographical mistakes and correct them . There are also two colors which highlight that maybe a certain sentence can be written in a different and more fluid way . About this point , I have to underline the only defect I found : when the algorithm finds a speach not correct , it does not suggest a correct way to improve it . 
Dear neighbour , I am going on holiday . I want you to keep my house keys and look after my plants and pets . I also want you to look after my mail . 
Always more students choose to study abroad and in a larger part they have always great experiences . Here , in Italy , we call these kinds of experiences " Erasmus " or " cultural exchanges . " They usually last at least three months , but most times , students study abroad for circa six months . Some of them , the most motivated ones , stay outside of Italy for one year . There are a lot of advantages for those who choose to study in a foreign country : first of all , learning another language and getting to know another culture . Indeed , learning a language living in a country where this language is not spoken could become quite difficult , because people do not have the chance to practise in real life . Moreover , facing the people of place and their customs is really helpful to understand the culture and allows us to come closer to the language too . Going away from home means getting older too : guys start to organize their days , to clean their rooms , to pay electricity , rubbish , gas and water . They eventually learn to live as adults , out of the glass cup in which they have lived for all their lives . Erasmus is a good option also to know new people , which maybe will help in an eventual future job . Studying abroad can , however , have disadvantages because we Italian people are really close to our families and the absence of them sometimes is too intense that someone can feel alone and suffer solitude . In some cases , moreover , going away from home could become an excuse to run away from responsibilities and duties or to get a life out of rules . A lot of student think that what happens in Erasmus remains in Erasmus and they use that period just to have fun and not to study . Studying abroad could be the greatest of the experiences with fair behaviour . 
Vancouver is the capital city of British Columbia . It is one of the most fascinating places in Canada . Some of the important landmarks in Vancouver are Stanely Park , Gastown and Granville Island . The museum of Vancouver is a popular place for visitors . 
