Dear Leyla , I really want to apologise to you because I could not come to the party . I could not go to the party because I was not at home at that time . I was visiting my grandparents and my relatives with my family in the village of Ninh Binh for nearly 2 months . I tried my best to go to the party , but I could not go . At the same time , my younger brother was having a party for his birthday so it was hard for me to choose . I have a little regret about your party . Can you tell me some details about the party ? How many people did you invite ? Can you tell me about the dinner and also the atmosphere at that time ? I 'm quite curious . Were you dancing together ? I have not leapt for a long time . I have an idea . Why do not we hold a party and invite some of our best friends to come ? We can eat and talk together . We can also share with each other about the sadness and the challenges in the study process . We can also sing karaoke and dance together under the orange glow of the candlelight . I can imagine that the atmosphere at that time will be really awesome and great . You and I can plan for the party . What do you think about the idea ? Tell me your opinion as soon as possible . I 'm looking forward to your reply . My love , Nguyen Nguyen 
Dear Cristina , I 've heard about your accident last week . I am really sorry to hear that . I 've heard your doctor said you must stay at home for two weeks for recovery . I would like to take you for a walk from time to time . I will visit you tomorrow . Thank you . 
My favourite season of the year while I live in town is winter . Because I like to use winter clothes and it is so much easier to get warm . I mean you can put on a coat and gloves and the problem is resolved . When it is a cold and rainy day , there is nothing better than you going to watch a movie with your girlfriend or with your friends . Also I love cold weekends and going early in the morning to Starbucks and drinking a hot caramel macchiato while I read a good book . But if I can go on vacation , I love summer and going to the seaside with an amazing and beautiful beach with white sand and a deep blue ocean . I like to sunbathe while I read a good book too . And at night , I like go to dinner to a seafood restaurant . 
To my opinion , studying in another country is a very good idea . In 2016 , I went to Canada for my law and history studies . It was my best experience in another country . This allows students to discover new countries , new cultures , new friends and new relationships . It is very important when we are young to understand the way of thinking of the natives . It opens our eyes ! Of course , in another country , we can learn a new language or visit some monuments . Moreover , going to another country shows you what you like and what you miss in your own country . An example , for me , when I was in Canada , the thing that I missed the most was the bread ! Of course , my family too ! To conclude , during a trip to another country , remember that the most important thing is to have fun ! It is a great experience ! 
Some people believe that employees who work in enclosed work stations or open design stations on their own have benefits and drawbacks . In this essay , I am going to outline two main reasons for enclosed work stations or cubicles and open design stations . Based on my knowledge , I am going to demonstrate the advantages of enclosed work stations or cubicles . If she makes that kind of work stations , her employees will have more space and can put anything they want , such as some snacks , water bottles and personal things . Recently , every country has had to face the Noval coronavirus , everyone has to stay at a distance . Enclosed work stations can easily defend from that virus due to the fact that there is more distance and who has less chance to keep in touch with people . However , they not only need space but also need fortunes to make rooms , which need air -conditionals or ventilation fans to clean the office 's air fresh . They have to communicate with some acquaintance workers and colleagues by phone . Besides that , it is mentioned that the upsides of open design stations . They can communicate , help each other without any phones or technical devices . The work stations have an open design , air could circulate and they can get more fresh air . For the employer , she needs to rent only a small place where she can also make many office desks and not need a lot of exhaust fans and air -conditioners . On the other hand , employees might not get personal space and if she puts some experience things , like mobile phones , she has to take care of that . Nowadays , Noval coronavirus infects with a least 20 m which someone get with it , everybody will be infected within 20 seconds . In the nutshell , the following parts are the upsides and downsides of enclosed work stations and open design stations . It just depends on personal preference which stations are more effective . 
Music and schools . This topic reminds me of my years in high school . And to be honest , I hated music classes . However , there is a serious dichotomy . Do not get me wrong , I really love music . I ca not sing or play any instrument , but I need to listen to music every day . Still music classes used to be a torture to me . Why is that ? I think that the problem is that the school makes you listen . You have to listen , have to play and have to sing . This is not the proper way to approach music . It is the same with books . I have got my own little library , I love to read books . But in high school , we had the mandatory books . The word mandatory . Once something is mandatory , you do not like it even if it is really great . So I would recommend voluntary music lessons only for those kids who want to learn something more . You ca not and should not impose music ! 
