I 'm really fond of listening to music . When I listen to music , I get more relaxed and calmer , and when I 'm cleaning the house , I get really excited with that . I also use this kind of activity for learning English . The last time I listened to music was on Thursday as I was cleaning up my wardrobe , but I also listened to music today to learn English . 
In this essay , I am going to outline the two main problems about all doctors desiring to work in urban areas where they can get money rolling in , but in rural regions , there are not enough doctors . Based on my knowledge , I am going to demonstrate the difference between urban and rural regions . The first thing is money due to the fact that in city center where can give you a lot of money especially a month more than $ 50000 dollars or more . Nevertheless , in rural areas , money is lay income , so they can not spend too much on medical health . The second one is convenience , if she worked in the city center , she could rely on public transportation such as taxis , subways and city -bikes . However , in the outskirts , they only can trust the tuktuk or motorbike , which take ages to commute from one district to another district . And also , the motorcycle is the most dangerous thing in transportation because , every year , in rural areas , people are killed by motorbike accidents . On the one hand , working hours , in downtown , take only six to eight hours a day to eight hours a day to takes duty and in hospitals which have so many sections such as morning , midday , night . On the other hand , in the countryside , it is so strange , consequently , it is only a doctor with two or one nurses to struggle with a 3 -month or 6 -month shift , which is pretty hard to control . From my point of view , the government or each medical university / college is responsible for branch each states . For instance , if she lives in the suburbs , she had better work in suburban region hospitals . Do not give them a choice . And the second one , controlling the amount of salary which can separate crowded doctors in city centers . If she 's a nurse who has two years ' experience , she might get $ 20000 dollars a year . The third one , fixing the roads and providing subways or round district buses in the countryside , that kind of thing could fix not only the long hours ofcommuting but also long hours of duty . In the nutshell , that following things could fix all problems of packing doctors in the city center and every region will be balanced . 
If you want to study at university , you should be able to live on your own . It is not like high school . No one cares about you and you have to study by yourself . And no one should care about your living either . It is great if your parents support you but you do not need " mamahotel . " But to be honest , I am not the best person to ask . I am studying at military university and it is a really different way of life . I do not have to buy clothes or pay my flat . I am living in the barracks with the whole regiment . I get a salary every month , but I have to work for forty hours a week . I do not have holidays . Our holidays are in the form of field exercise . But I think that all of that has taught me independence and I am glad for that . I do not understand how somebody could live with parents in his or her thirties . 
I totally agree with this statement . Unless we are healthy , we do not have the opportunity to spend money . We can discuss the importance of money only under good conditions . I have three reasons to support my opinions . Firstly , why is money important ? We spend money to buy something . This action enriches our minds and as a result , our lives . If we are sick , we cannot fill our heart with just satisfaction . People are eager to acquire a healthy body instinctively . Secondly , we can try anything to earn money with a healthy body . I have heard of many entrepreneurs who had been poor , but succeeded in the end . With health and patience , we all have the possibility to be billionaires . Thirdly , if we stay healthy , we are satisfied with our life , regardless of being short of money . I know it is mostly a capitalistic world , but we have organizations which take care of each other . I hope everyone in this world seeks health to live a happy and satisfying life . 
