Education life is an essential part of everyone 's life who normally start their student life since three or four years old . During those years , kids usually have the same teacher from kindergarten to primary school , who teaches them the basic subjects and spends most of the day with them . During those years kids usually have the same teacher since kindergarden to primary school who teaches them the basic subjects and spend most part of the day with them , in high schools , preparatory schools and colleges , people have different teachers for each subject as a resource to teach students to get used to learning no matter the teacher 's teaching style . This process of teaching in high schools is good for students because they learn to learn indistinctivily to the person who teaches and they just focus on the subject and knowledge behind it . For me , having different teachers each year has more benefits than having one teacher for several years because students have the opportunity to experiment with different styles of teaching during their educational process . They can also develop abilities to make investigation projects due to each teacher asking for homework or papers with specific points to be scored in order for each student to be able to develop that homework with those specifications and investigate the best way to present their works with the correct topic and framework . That 's why I consider it better to have different teachers through the years instead of one teacher with the same style and the same way of working , something that many times become tedious to students . 
