Books and Technology In the world of today , more and more areas have been taken over by technology . Now , many schools and universities are thinking of replacing books for computers and tablets . Of course , using a tablet instead of a book has its advantages : Firstly , many students complain that they have to carry so many heavy books . If they used their laptop , with everything saved on there , they would not have to carry loads of books with them . Secondly , the internet can sometimes give more information to people who are doing research , for example . There is a greater variety of websites available . However , books are not completely replaceable . First , on the internet , there are not only trustworthy pages . Sometimes wrong information is published . Books mostly tell the truth . Also , many people enjoy the feeling of reading a " real " book . They like to " touch " the pages . This gives them a positive feeling . To conclude , I believe that books cannot be totally replaced . They are still an important part in nearly everyone 's lives . A tablet will never give you that typical book feeling , after all . 
The new year is a new beginning . Like every year , I decide to make better many aspects in my life . Nevertheless , it 's very challenging because it depends on my self -control . However , I hope I 'll achieve everything I want . The most important thing in my life is learning , so I focus mostly on it . I 'm aware that I 'm pleased with some areas of my learning . For sure , I can say that I 'm proud of my listening skills . I have trained this for a long time . Especially in my free time , I watch movies with the original sound and with English subtitles . It helped me also with my reading skills , actually . So I believe that I did not waste my time . I only did something in cheerful way . Obviously , there are areas which are incredibly challenging for me . Undoubtedly , writing and speaking are my Achilles ' heel . Of course , I 'm trying to improve them . In that case , I 'm writing a lot of essays and letters . I also have an English -speaking friend with whom I 'm writing . And what about speaking ? I 'm connecting with other people who speak English and talk with them online . I 'm sure all those things help me to improve my skills . 
