I have many things to do in my free time such as reading books or novels , or hiking in the mountains . I spend hours hiking alone , or with my husband , exploring different areas and drinking from the rivers or waterfalls in the mountains . Also , I take my bakebake with me on every adventure , it has my tools and snacks . I like to read every day and , if I can , I also read stories to my little daughters . But I also like hiking when I travel to some countries that have mountains , like Turkey . 
I think computers and tablets should completely replace books in schools and universities . I have four reasons to support my opinion . Firstly , it is cheaper with a long -term view . Once we get a device , it does not cost as much money to add new literature as a paper book . Secondly , it keeps a tidy condition as if it is new . Books get old , but devices do not get old . We do not need to re -buy them . We may spend more for the initial cost , but not for the running cost . Thirdly , it does not need space because it 's portable . We waste lots of spaces with stacked books . It 's useless and dangerous . We can substitute this space for something else with a device . Lastly , it 's easier to look up literature . Wherever and whenever you are , you can do that . It 's very useful . On the other hand , I think it is better for novels to read with paper books . It is one of the precious times to go around bookshelves to find an attractive book . If you have decided which book you want to read , devices are better , but if not , paper is valuable . 
This year I want to focus on Math and English , Math , because next summer I want to start studying chemistry at university . While I am pretty good in chemistry , I had to improve my math knowledge . A good understanding in math is essential for a lot of areas in chemistry . I also want to improve my English capabilities , because I intend to go abroad and visit Oxford University for a summer term in two or three years . Also , to be almost fluent in English is not only good for studying . but in general is a wanted capability . So , to improve my Math , I plan to attend special lessons , where the teachers will repeat all the necessary stuff . To improve my English , I started reading English fiction , read BBC news on a daily basis and watch a lot of English television . Last month , I watched a series on Netflix , where I often switched language between English and German to check if I had got the content . 
I will introduce my home town , Abeno . We have a famous landmark named " Harukasu , " which is the highest commercial building in Japan . There are a hotel , a department store , and a shopping mall in it . We also have a big city park . There are a track field , a soccer stadium , and a botanical garden in it . 
Most medical doctors prefer to work in cities than in poor and rural areas . They have more opportunities to make money in big hospitals than in a little town . On the other hand , in poor and rural cities , there are not advanced medical tests , drugs and machines . Most doctors are interested in learning how to use and apply modern treatments and medical devices . I think they prefer to work in big cities not only for the money . The poorest people face many challenges to have access to medical attention . The main problem is that there are not enough specialized doctors who work in poor and rural areas . Most countries send the younger doctors to work in poor and rural areas . If they have a patient who needs specialized attention , they send the patient to the city 's hospital . It is difficult for the patient to be far away from their home , but it is necessary . I think it is the only one way to solve this problem . 
It has been suggested that some people like to live a long , calm life until 100 years old and others want to prefer a shorter life but much more intense . I personally do entirely choose a calm life until 100 years old , and I will explain why in this essay . Firstly , for a long and calm life , we have to consider how to earn money because money is just like water for humankind , when not having much , the person will be in trouble . However , nowadays , everyone has to do a job until retirement due to everything being insisting especially household goods , such as a flagship performance phone , laptop and other gadgets . If he gets married , his life will be perfect because two individual people could earn money whether get children they might encourage and know about how sweet life is . Furthermore , when they get older , they are not concerned about fortunes due to the fact that life insurance and elderly care are obviously coming to support even though their children have not looked back . I do appreciate that some people think differently , saying that it is better to live a short life and more intense , saying that is better to live a short life and more intense is way more to have succeeded degrees and earned money . If he goes shopping , he does not need to consider his pocket . Nevertheless , it is a fact that the person is thoroughly famous and successful , but that person dies at 30 , the fortunes are undoubtedly going to be nationalized . Life is so meaningless and do not know what real life is . In the nutshell , I do prefer to live a long , calm life until 100 years old , which is more meaningful and gives opportunities to taste life . 
Some people think that every paper book can be changed into electronic books . However , is it possible ? Nowadays , technological development is incredible , so a group of young people who are familiar with it can understand easily how to use it . Furthermore , electronic books are easy to take anywhere and at any time , because if you take only one computer or tablet , you can read every book . And also , they are not heavy . Moreover , electronic books are good for the environment , because they do not cut down trees . On the other hand , electronic books have some disadvantages . They need electric energy . If they do not have any charge , we ca not read the books . We need to worry about losing charge or possible charging places . In addition , it will happen that they will be stolen in the school or during the break frequently . If it happens , we ca not study anymore . And also , electronic books are bad for our eyes if we use them for a long time . Electronic books have a lot of advantages , however , I think it is difficult to change to all electronic books . 
For me , my best holiday ever was in August 2019 , when I went to the south with my girlfriend . It was a road trip of two weeks and I have a lot of good memories about this . The first stage of our road trip was Toulouse . We visited the " Space city " and we saw a lot of rockets , it was very impressive ! After this , we went to meet some friends in the town and went to a restaurant . The second stage of our road trip was Carcassonne , a medieval city near Toulouse . We visited the castle by night , it was very beautiful . The last stage of our trip was Le Verdon , a beautiful city known for its river and its mountains . We visited the area and saw a beautiful panorama . We did some activities , like " Via Ferrata . " Precisely , we were climbing through the mountains . For all these reasons , it was my best holiday ever . 
Technology nowadays is an essential part of everyone lives . That is the reason why education has adapted many technological devices to teach and to replace physical resources like books or paper . People today use technology every single hour in their lives , keeping them always connected . In education , computers and tablets are good devices to use in interactive classes , but books definitely keep on being the principal information source . Of course , many books are online these days , making work , homework and projects easier , however , we should keep physical and technological resources working together to get good projects and the teaching and learning process can be developed in an efficient way . Instead of replacing books or using only technological devices , teachers and students should use both in order to get a balance between the old and the new , getting tested information as well . Personally , I use both resources for my university homework or projects which I am developing , books , computers and tablets being a great support to me . 
