People in distant villages and the countryside are still barred from significant healthcare service . In one way , doctors , who had studied for a long time in search of welfare , may avoid living in such sectors and , in the other way , it seems the governments do not have an effective plan to deal with such a problem . Lack of facilities and also medical equipment in the countryside causes the occurrence of a wide variety of illnesses , therefore people who have lived in these areas - that are not a few - need to have more access to doctors , but actually , doctors do not want to spend their life away from their families , friends , and also without their hobbies and modern life . According to the issues we mentioned on the top , only the law is able to help us to solve this kind of problem . If the governments are forced to provide an appropriate welfare plan for doctors that are willing to visit patients in these areas , and consider some awards for them such as tax freedom , so this may encourage doctors to move to the countryside , at least for some days of a week . 
