Hi Billal , Last week I went on a trip with my class to Amsterdam . I was so excited to be in such a wonderful place full of colors and art everywhere . I visited all the famous museums I could and in the evening I went into some pubs to have a beer and chat with the local people . I enjoyed this trip because I had always wanted to visit this country and see how it 's organized and structured . I was fascinated about the art , and the pictures that they have all around the buildings are great . Ivan 
Today zoos are an alternative to the wild , for everyone . This place allows you to learn , watch and admire some of the beautiful creatures who belong in the wild . Perhaps zoos have a negative impact on animals . They are forced to leave their birthplace to be sent to these big cages . Many of us do not understand that this situation is not right for them , because you disallow them to live their real life , in the wild . People are so amazed by zoos , that sometimes they forget what is hiding behind these structures . Animals are creatures that should not be captured , because this will ruin their normal living routine . For example , thinking that a lion , " the king of the savannah " is forced to live in this cage , is so sad . A free animal whose freedom is taken away from him is unacceptable . But also the other species , every one with their own living methods , are moved to zoos , thanks to hunting . They are forced to sleep and then once they are awake , they see a different world , a world where they cannot hunt their prey , or where the prey cannot escape from their hunters . Zoos are so uncomfortable . But there are natural reserves . They are like zoos , but without cages . The animals are free to walk in their territory , hunt and live as if they were in the wild . No one get hurts , but they get protected . 
Many people consider truthfulness a very positive virtue . I also believe that , yet I dare to say that under some specific circumstances it is better to tell a lie . Firstly , we need to determine why we lie . By doing so , we can hide inconvenient facts about ourselves or we also can avoid being punished for things that we have done . For a short amount of time , lying might even be beneficial for us , however when the truth is revealed , we often get into a much bigger predicament than we would have if we had not lied . Another consequence of lying is that people could start to perceive us as a dishonest and unreliable person . This obviously aggravates our relationships with friends or acquaintances . Lastly , not telling truth is considered a sin by most religions in the world so if we do so , it will be against our beliefs and conscience . I see only one exception in which we are justified to tell a lie . That is when we gain nothing for ourselves and , by telling truth , we would cause pain to other person . I can give an example of such a lie from literature . There is a book called " Kamizelka " written by Bolesław Prus . The novel depicts the story of a marriage , in which husband is terminally ill . He is losing weight uncontrollably , so in order no to worry his wife , he notoriously shortens his vest 's bands . To summarise , I think there are conditions under which we can lie , but normally , I strongly believe that it is better to just tell the truth . 
Making volunteer work obligatory for high school students would not , in my honest opinion , bring positive results . The main purpose of school is to teach students various subjects and prepare them for their final exams . I believe that this is a period of time in which we need to really focus on our education . From my personal experience , I can say that there are pupils who actually learn a lot on their own and who take part in many competitions , which consumes most of their free time . I am completely convinced that if volunteer work was required of them , they would become distracted and extremely tired so they might not achieve as much as they want . The second drawback of compulsory volunteer work is the fact that it might be perceived as a duty or errand . If something is compulsory , we usually tend not to like such a thing . I think people who willingly participate in this kind of work can gain experience or help others . However , if someone is not kin for such thing , then it will be only a burden for them . Volunteer work might also collide with some extracurricular activities of some students . In such a situation , they would need to resign from their interests . Some people might as well consider work just as a way of earning money , therefore they would have even more reasons to dislike the idea of volunteer work . To summarise , volunteer work can be beneficial for some people , but making it obligatory for everyone is pointless . 
In order to develop any task , humans need to gather a wide range of skills which are adopted during our lifetime , therefore , practise is completely required when it comes to acquiring abilities . It is known that the more skills that we have , the more tools to solve a problem or hard situation are available . On the one hand , my career is highly related to human beings . As far as I am concerned , no matter how physically fit or strong we are , every activity we do is absolutely related to our core " computer , " which is our unbelievably clever brain . What is more , childhood and the beginning of the teenage years are the most essential moments for its proper development . In addition of taking care of it by protecting it from strong hits and holding an adequate diet and the right amount of sleep , there is a pattern which is crucial , it is called " mind sharp , " it basically means , brain training . When the first studies in this field appeared , almost every school took wonderful policies with the aim of encouraging children to take up habits which put their minds in motion . Commonly , most primary schools introduced music to their basic studies , nevertheless , some high quality learning institutions have taken up stunning activities such as theatre , philosophy , farming and so on . Believe it or not , the world of education is witnessing a revolution in the way that children are taught . Contrary to the old beliefs of learning everything by heart , the new systems gives extreme priority to team work , leadership , entrepreneurship and critical thinking among many other skills marvellously useful for the adult lives of the future generations . To sum up , the government has endorsed these practises by raising the education budgets looking forward to seeing the first changes in society within the next fifteen years . 
