MEDICINE FOR EVERYONE It is widely known that , when it comes to rural places , the vast majority of doctors do not desire to develop their career in such places . The reasons why it all happens is going to be pointed out next . Despite the fact that living in the countryside could be seen as a dream come true to many people , it may not be the case for someone whose career ambitions are unlimited . The thing is , living in a rural area gives people sometimes the impression of being trapped in a small space . Besides , technology and progress do not normally arrive on time to these places . Another issue to have under consideration is the fact that the economic resources of people who live in rural areas are far less substantial than the ones of those who live in big cities . Nevertheless , the importance of an equal and balanced medical system for everyone is beyond doubt . Having said that , the primary focus of any kind of government should be based on developing the medical and care system of the most harmed areas by investing more money in them and turning those places into more attractive ones . Last but by no means least , improvements in rural facilities , in general , should be something to take stock of . Rural life is a luxury that must be preserved . 
