My favourite film is " Big Fish . " It is about the relationship between a son and his father who is very sick . They never had a good relationship during their lives . That is because the father always told amazing and weird stories to his son . However , his son never believed him . When his father was lying in bed , very sick , he started to tell his son the same stories again . At the end , his father died and , during his funeral , all of his friends from the stories show up . Finally , his son believed in the stories his father told . This is an emotional movie , a beautiful story about a father and a son . I believe you are going to love it ! I know you have a great relationship with your father . I think you should invite him to watch it with you . 
It 's an important statement . I have already heard that many people lose their health trying to be wealthier . And after some years , they spend this money trying to rescue their health . It 's interesting and true . Of course we need to work , being important for our society . But sometimes we lose our awareness about this and work a lot , trying to have more and more . So family , friends and loved ones become less important than they should be considered . We need to be alert about this , because there are many attractions , but we need to think if they are really important for our happiness . So , some months ago , I decided to learn more about minimalism . If our needs are less , then we need to buy less and have less money . Less money means that we do not need to work so much time and lose our health . So I think I will learn how to balance my daily life . 
