I think there are things that are more important for our health . Exercise is absolutely important , but it is not the only way to keep our health . Eating healthy food at regular times is important . We should eat balanced meals . We should also regulate their nutrition and volume . Eating too much is bad for our health . It causes high blood sugar . We have to eat a determined amount of calories divided into 6 times a day to keep blood sugar value . Sleeping well for 8 hours is also important for our health . Good sleep makes our bodies and mental health better . In order to sleep well , we should not eat anything 2 hours before going to bed . Avoiding stress in daily life is more important . We need proper stress to keep our motivation in our work or private lives , but excess stress may cause illness , not only in our bodies but also our minds . There are many things that are more important for our health besides exercise . But the most important thing is to continue with these activities every day . 
I think that Write&Improve is one of the best programs that a learning student can use in order to improve their learning skills . This program is so great that I use it every day in order to improve my writing skills . The best part is that you can use it from everywhere , you can use it from your office , your smartphone , tablet and even from your desktop at home . The best part is that it gives you the result in a couple of seconds , so you know what your English writing skills are . The program gives you grades from A to C , A is the lowest one and C means that your level of English is very high . If you use this language tool and also Duolingo , you can really improve your English level . Duolingo is also a good tool so you can learn a foreign language . Duolingo is a program which you must sign in to , then you do a test to see what your level is and then you start practicing your English skills . The best part of Duolingo is that you can make friends , you can follow them , they can follow you and also your teacher can see your progress . 
If someone ever asks me which was the best holiday I have ever been on , I would definitively say that it was the one I went on last summer . To start with , in July of 2019 , my family and I decided to go to the south of Spain , to visit some wonderful and astonishing beaches at the seaside . We set off in July and came back in August . We felt so grateful when we arrived and saw how well cared for and gorgeous the beaches are in Spain . First of all , we checked in at the hotel and unpacked , then we took notice of a lot of trip advertisements in the hotel and determined to start with a scuba diving lesson 24 miles away from the coast . It was just incredible , an unforgettable experience in which we got to see uncountable species of fish and marine life . The next day , we went on a kayak trip towards the " agua dulce " port . And the last day , we did some tourism through the city and visited a huge aquarium , in which we could touch sharks . We saw several famous monuments and finally , we saw the best restaurant in the city . 
If my children play video games , I will not agree with this , because I consider that video games do not improve their behaviour , their temper , or their vocabulary . I consider that video games will not improve or evolve the players . Furthermore , I think that video games will destroy the perspective of the world , the people and their concern about their future . Also , I think that a child who does not play video games is more productive , more social and more friendly with the people around them , instead of a child who plays video games in their free time , who gives all their attention and energy to video games and does not pay attention to interaction with the other people that go to the same school as them . I also consider that children that do not play video games are more successful than children that play video games , because they are more concerned about their life , their behaviour or their development . 
You just graduated and now the very next part of your life is to begin : university . But when it comes to the housing situation during this time , opinions differ . Some argue that living at home with your family is the best option , whereas others argue that living on your own is the best choice to possibly take . Actually , both options have their positive and negative aspects . On the one hand , living on your own obviously helps to become more confident and reliable , but simultaneously , the responsibility increases a lot . You have to buy your own groceries , do your laundry , tidy up , pay your bills and cook for yourself . Meanwhile , you have the opportunity to do whatever you want - if it is not illegal though - and have experiences being dependent on your own . On the other hand , those responsibilities need a lot of your time , which is less while living with your family . Your mother might be very gentle and do your laundry , cook dinner for you and iron your blouses , whereas throwing a party with your new friends could not amaze her the same way as you . As a conclusion , it is important to mention that everyone prefers different ways of living and there is nothing wrong with it at all . 
I am fat and I am crazy and I want to be slimmer . I know that I must do exercise , but it 's really difficult for me . Then I met my teacher in college who really inspired and affects me to love exercise . And yup , I have liked exercise since then . Lately , I did my exercise 2 to 4 times a week . It depends on my type of exercise . In the past when I was studying in Bandung , almost every day I ran in Poltek 's field . Then , when I routinely joined Zumba , I did exercise twice a week , every Monday and Thursday . But because of the pandemic , the Zumba place has closed . I felt confused for a moment . What exercise should I do ? Fortunately , my dad has a static bicycle . So I brought the bicycle to my room and I am cycling for 20 minutes per day , 4 days a week . 
There are both positive and negative effects of video games for children . The benefit of video games is training eye -and -hand coordination , which is the basis of many jobs in children 's lives . Moreover , children who play video games have faster problem solving skills as they are exposed to new puzzles in the games . However , the disadvantages of video games are many more than the advantage . Most families suffer from their children 's inappropriate behavior copying a violent situation from fighting video games , which are the most popular type of game . Many crimes are caused by game players who imitate a character 's brutal action . Another negative effect of video games , which mostly affects preschool children , is a language problem caused by limited interpersonal interaction and one -way communication between children and a video screen . It is normal to see a toddler watching Youtube clips or playing mobile phone games by himself while his parents are also using their phones separately . Moreover , it causes long -term health problems , such as near eyesight , muscle soreness and constipation , and social problems . In conclusion , even though video games give children some learning skills , their disadvantages affect children 's lives severely . Thus , parents must limit their children 's playing time to balance the benefits and drawbacks caused by playing games . 
Well , I guess that there are advantages in both spaces . If you need to be more concentrated , it could be better to have a space only for you , but if you need some time to interact with your partners , it would be better to have an open design . Another question is the kind of work , if you want to produce , only produce , you must be fast . In this case , there is no problem to stay in open spaces , it could be better . However , if you need to be creative , to produce new ideas , for instance , you could choose , because for some people , it is better to have other people around . For others , it is very important to be alone , quiet , to think deeply about the topic , the issue , the goal , the idea , not being disturb . So it is a question of the place , it depends on the job , it depends on the person , it depends on the conditions . 
There is no doubt these days , the important schools have special requests such as volunteer activities . The question is , is volunteer activity helpful for students or not ? In this essay , I am going to discuss both views and draw my own opinion . In terms of volunteering advantages , some people say they will improve personal skills . The main reason they give to support this idea is that students need a realistic experience in real situations . To illustrate that , helping people will develop their character , let them see life like it was without any change . In other words , these activities teach them how to be flexible dealing with complex problems and ways to solve them as they can . , . some people said there are disadvantages to volunteering . Firstly , it will let students focus less on their studies and subjects . This is because they spend a long time on these activities . Secondly , some of the volunteering activities are dangerous for young students , maybe have a risk like relegions for poor people which does not have safty . In conclusion , there are a lot of opinions about this subject , all of them have good causes to show their views . Therefore , I believe that volunteer activities are useful and they give students a chance to see another side of the world . 
Dear Sir or Madam , Due to the latest idea of banning the use of mobile phones on public transport , in shops and restaurants , I am writing to you . Nowadays , mobile phones are included in our daily life as well as food or clothing . The problem is that many people are being distracted by them during situations that need special attention . The amount of casualties a year caused by distractions due to a mobile phone is , in fact , increasingly high . Therefore , I would genuinely recommend them being banned . It is not just dangerous , but our social life basically suffers a lot from the immense use . You can see families sitting at a table in a restaurant not talking to each other , while each and everyone of them is glaring at a screen in front of them . To some extent , you need to have your phone with you and it is also very useful in some situations , but we all should not forget our ancestors survived without them too . Of course , you can negotiate , many listen to music , read or play games on their mobile phone , but to me , this is as distracting as everything else . Anyways , I should mention that my phone is used by myself very often too , but I tremendously suggest trying to enforce this ban because our social life will benefit a lot from it . 
