Should people always tell the truth ? Or is it sometimes acceptable to tell a lie ? The first thing we need to do is to ask ourselves : Is it a moral question or a social one ? To start , since our childhood , we are told to never lie . We heard : " Lying is a bad thing , and you will hurt people if you do so . " Indeed , we grew up and we believed that liars were terrible people . So , if we are responding this question from a moral point of view , I would say : we should never lie . Nevertheless , I believe it 's more complicated than white or black . Sometimes , grey can help to avoid a lot of trouble . In my view , lying from time to time is acceptable if the purpose is noble . Sometimes , a lie can be used to protect someone from being hurt and not the other way around . Actually , let 's take an example . Someone cheats on someone else . What is best thing to do ? To tell the truth and destroy everything you built ? To lie and to avoid hurting the one you love ? Of course , some people are just cowards , and lie beyond the truth . But it 's a very difficult question to judge . Regardless of this kind of interrogation , my opinion is : Hide the truth if the purpose is to avoid hurting someone . Otherwise be bold and brave and speak your mind . 
What is the Future of Travel ? Will planes still be as numerous ? Will trains be able to run faster ? Will cars be flying ? Or conversely , will we stop travelling ? To begin with , all these questions still have no specific answer . Nevertheless , if we look at the big picture , we might find some responses . These past few years , we have witnessed new political ideas . People are more concerned than ever about ecology and their well -being . We know the traveling business brings a lot of pollution . And we also know that the earth ca not take it anymore . So , in my view , we must stop traveling the way we do . We are killing our home and it ca not last any longer . Indeed , discount flight companies have allowed many people to access plane travel . We might see it as an improvement . It is not . I believe , twenty years from now , car ownership will drastically plunge . Public transportation will rise and develop . Finally , I trust plane travel will be used for business trips only . To conclude , the future of travel needs to be more responsible and eco -friendly . It is our duty to be aware of what is coming . 
