In my opinion , there are two sides of video games and they impact on young people . Children playing video games has some positive effects on them . First of all , it improves their reflexes and concentration . It may help them in the future in other actions in real life . For example , in some sports , reflexes are very important to win games or fights . I also see another positive effect of video games . Especially nowadays , when a huge part of communication is on the Internet , children can talk to each other while playing video games . On the other hand , I see many negative effects of video games . First of all , playing for many hours every day can make children obese , damage their vision and backbone , because they are sitting of course while doing that . Because of that , they do not do any sport or something like that . They ca not talk in real life and in adult life they have a problem with communication and things like that . 
Good morning , I am writing to in case of case of your future decision about banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants . In my opinion , a decision like this is too restrictive for the people living in our town . I think this decision is also bad for many reasons . First of all , especially nowadays , mobile phones are not only used for calling and messaging . For many people , their mobile phone is used as a calendar , notebook , calculator and stuff like that . Thanks to the Internet , they can also check , for example , bus departures or shop opening hours . On public transport , people like to relax and do things which can help them to kill the time . On their mobile phone , they can read the news , listen to music , read books , play video games and many other things . So that is the next good example , in my opinion . Let 's see the shops . There are many reasons why you need to use your mobile phone there . Many people have a shopping list on their mobile phones . If you do not have your shopping list , you may forget something . If you forget something , you have to maybe call somebody who will remind you about it . The next place is the restaurant . I think there using mobile phones is not necessary , but there are some groups of people who need to always be in touch . I think my arguments are strong and you will change your decision quickly . Best regards , Pat 
Living is a privilege not everyone is completely aware of , in spite of this awareness , everyone wants to live to the fullest . The question is , what way is the right way to live your life ? Therefore , the next question arises : A long life until 100 years old or a shorter life but much more intense ? For me , the answer is obvious , as I chose my goals from very early on . I want to achieve something that stays after I no longer live . Subsequently , the more time I have , the higher is the chance of accomplishing it . 100 years is a tremendously long period of time and the chances of getting ill at some point of this are comparatively high , that is why you should always treat your body the best possible way . Then you can use those years effectively for whatever goal you have set yourself . Another reason for choosing the longer period of time is the history you will have , as nearly no one gets that old , you will have a lot to tell and to experience in the first place , of course . Imagine getting a child , then becoming a grandparent and , afterwards , even a great -grandparent . Is there anything more fulfilling than love ? Moreover , exquisite things are to be explored , memories to be made and stories to be told . In conclusion , regarding the shorter life , there are reasons for choosing this one too , but those for the longer one outweigh them by far . 
