There are , in the society , many problems about doctors and health care . But this problem is not just about doctors , because it includes many other jobs . People , in general , want to work in the bigger cities not just because of the money , but also because of the many opportunities which are not in villages or rural areas . For instance , in the Czech Republic , there is a lack of doctors in these places , even when doctors could get a bigger salary there . It is , in my opinion , about the lucrative living in the city . Even if there were more money in those areas , the doctors would not go there . And it involves also the lucrativeness of working in a big hospital . There , you can see much more interesting medical cases than anywhere else . The solution to this problem is hard to find , but I would say that there are two things which could make this situation much better . The first thing is to speak with the young doctors and try to convince them that the living in rural areas has a good side . The other solution could be to build small hospitals in those areas and try to get the doctors there . It would surely help everyone because it is better to have a good healthcare network in your country for every patient . 
School is a place where kids can learn new concepts , make new friends , fall in love , find their calling and I 'm positive that there must be even more possibilities and opportunities for them to gain while they are considered to be enrolled in one of these institutions . However , modern schools are bombarded with lots of criticism and nasty remarks . People do not like how children are being taught . Instead of teaching them by showing them how something works , teachers choose to expect their students to know only the theory and the best part is that making a mistake is something that is regarded as a stupidity . But to be honest , all of us know that making mistakes enables us to learn new things better , because we are aware of what we 've done wrong . But let 's move on to talking about how schools will be different in the future . So , in my opinion , they 're gonna be more about teaching kids by practising a given skill . Lessons will be fulfilled with various experiments , mistakes are going to be thought of as priceless opportunities to sharpen your knowledge . I 'm sure that classes are gonna be much smaller , because as we all well know , it 's difficult to teach a group of 30 kids on your own without aid of any kind . It all sounds magical and almost unrealistic , but let 's not get so cozy about this thought . Schools cannot change completely , there are some aspects that are irrevocable . For example , there is a huge possibility that children will still have to learn until they reach the age of 18 years old . It does not sound that awful , does it ? Well no , but some kids could move at a much more quicker pace and by setting this bar so high , we only slow them down . There will still be teachers who hate their jobs and try to make their pupils ' lives miserable . I 'm sorry that it was a wrong choice , but it does not give you any permission to hurt innocent children with your harsh comments and your general gloomy state , which does not motivate them to even come to school in the first place ! 
Write and Improve is a very good way to practise English writing . It is based on an internet site and it follows your progress . You can sign in , so everything is saved . The automatic correction and checking tool is very easy to use . There are five levels , Beginner , Intermediate , Advanced , Business and just for fun . I like the learning method because you can do it in your spare time . My experience with Write and Improve is very good , I often use it for my work to study the English language and improve my writing . I definitely recommend the program to my classmates . What I do not like is the fact there are no tests that you can do . I would like to know in which level I am at the moment . Nevertheless , it is a very good program to improve the English language . 
Hello Mattia , I 'm writing some notes that can help you to look after my house while I 'm on holiday . Remember my keys are under the doormat and you must water the plants every single day during the evening . Thank you so much . Peter 
Dear council , Your latest idea of banning mobile phones in public areas has caused many discussions . Many people , including me , are worried about missing important messages or calls . Especially if your bus is running late and you have no chance to inform your waiting friends , because it is not allowed to take out the phone on public transport . Many of our citizens have a very busy workday and need their lunch break to make a phone call . This would not be possible if they were in a restaurant or on the bus . I do also love to sit in a local cafe and have a phone call with my family members who I cannot see every day . However , I do really like the idea of putting my phone away when I meet friends for dinner . Everyone else and I should be encouraged to talk face -to -face with others while having a meal in our local restaurants . My solution would be to still allow mobile phones on public transport and in shops . People want to be up -to -date and chat with others while they take their tram home . What we could try is to ban mobile phones in restaurants and bars . It would be amazing to see how groups of people start to talk more and make new friends . There is always the chance to go outside to quickly call a friend if it is really urgent . 
In my free time , I like to study English and I like to watch movies . About studying English , I study it every day , especially in the evening when I finish doing the dishes . I watch movies on the weekends , but I like to watch a little before I go to bed . 
To start , I would like to say that volunteer work is really helpful and people should do it in general , but the question is whether schools should require it from their students . To put it another way , this work is called volunteer work , which means that people should not be forced to do it . In other words , students should decide themselves whether they want to help without the pressure of the school . In my opinion , there are people who are forced to do something not really happy and they do not do it properly . I am convinced that schools should support their students to participate in this type of volunteer work and they would probably have some benefits for the students who actually do that . And most importantly , when someone requires volunteer work , it is no longer voluntary , which is the essence of this kind of work . 
Working in an office means , for most people , stability . This is certainly due to a defined work time and to a long -term planning of activities , both personal and of the work team , both on the work side , like the projects getting to term , and on the private side , like the vacation period . Moreover , an office job offers the chance to have a personal space which no one else is allowed to touch : a desk . Having a private desk , on which to organize files as we think is best , can really make the difference in our productivity . However , there are a lot of different types of desks . In some offices , employees work locked in cubicles , with empty walls and no chance to personalise their locations , neither attaching photos on the walls nor putting little plants on the desks . This denied personalisation could have negative consequences on employee productivity : they are supposed to spend all their work time sitting alone , in front of their computers , avoiding every human interaction . In this way , workers are isolated and they can neither exchange their ideas nor spend a word to interrupt the routine . On the opposite , an open space allows employees to talk to each other , to act like a group escaping the isolation to which cubicles would force them . In this way , the job gets to be more dynamic and ideas can develop easier . If workers had the opportunity to personalize their desks too , their productivity would be , out of any doubt , much bigger , because they would work in a place they feel homey . 
Dear Sir or Madam of our town council , I am writing to you this letter regarding your idea of banning the use of mobile phones on public transport . I am a citizen of the city and would like to tell you my opinion according to this issue . First of all , I would like to tell you that I may understand why you want to ban mobile phones . A lot of accidents , which have happened , happened because people used their mobile phones in traffic and for sure : that is dangerous . According to the number of accidents , I would counsel you to ban them . But nevertheless , we cannot overlook the other aspects . As you know , mobile phones have become pretty important in the last decade . and , at the moment , you can do almost everything on the internet . Do not forget that there are people who buy their tickets on an online shop . These tickets are not printed , but on their mobile phones . At least , for that part , mobile phones are not only useful but necessary . Moreover , a lot of people hear music during the wait time for their transport or on the transport . As I said in the beginning , it may be dangerous but I think instead of banning mobile phones , it might be better to invest in warnings because through banning , you limit the freedom of the people . It is the same in restaurants and shops . It is a limitation which is not necessary and will annoy the people . So I would like to ask that you just leave it . Kind regards , Anna 
Globalization has , as an inevitable consequence , increased the population in the cities - especially in the city centres - and decreased the number of people who live in rural areas . These two factors inevitably conduced to a huger concentration of services , including those which are considered of first necessity , in the cities . As it always happens , everyone sfrutted the thing on their own advantages , even doctors , who are supposed to be charitable and altruistic people . On the contrary , most of them revealed to be interested much more in money and success instead of people 's health . First of all , doctors should not be allowed to earn all the money they earn because they are supposed to do their job because of a vocation they have inside them . Secondly , they should not be allowed to have three , four or five jobs in different structures , a solution which would also solve part of the disocupation problem . Thirdly , they should not have the possibility to conduce private visits in public hospital structures . Here , in Italy , this process is called " intramenia . " On the other side , the problem of fewer and fewer people in rural zones should be solved with repopulation campaigns . It 's obvious that in a village with three or four people living a doctor ca not stay every day : it would be a waste of public money , which we really need to save and spend accurately . 
I like going to the gym . Why ? Because the gym brings me many health benefits . It makes me healthier , and helps me have a toned body . Over 3 years ago , I was 1.83 meters tall and only 58 kilos . People said that I looked so thin . After that , I went to the gym every day and about 6 months later , my weight had improved significantly . I was still 1.83 meters tall but 65 kilos . I kept going to the gym from then until now . At present , I am 76 kilos . A significant change , right ? Oh , about the last question , I last did it this morning . 
I use a computer every day . I use it for many purposes : to relax , to watch movies , to play games , to listen to music , . . . What do I enjoy doing most with a computer ? Well , if it was a few years ago , I would say I liked playing games most . But now , what I love doing most with a computer is learning . Sounds hard to believe but it 's true . Yeah ! Games no longer attract me . 
To begin with , zoos have become very popular these last decades . They allow people to learn about animals . They are a popular place for a family to spend some quality time . However , some people trust it is wrong to keep animals in zoos . In the first place , I will tell you why zoos are important . Then I will explain why I believe zoos are not good for animals . Finally , I will give you my opinion about the future . To start , zoos are not only created in order to entertain people . As a matter of fact , most zoos helps to prevent the extinction of endangered species . For instance , only a few pandas still live in the wild and zoos have a duty to develop the panda population . Of course , humans are responsible for the animals being missing , but some zoos are trying to make it better . Furthermore , zoos allow people to discover animals and to learn more about them . In this way , I trust zoos are good places . On the the other hand , I believe zoos are terrible for the welfare of animals . I believe it is wrong to keep a wild animal locked up into a forty meter square cage . As an example , tigers need to run one hundred miles a day . How is it possible in a zoo ? Moreover , I think animals in zoos are unhappy and some might even suffer from depression . In my view , zoos are a dangerous place for animals and their well -being . Unfortunately , it had become important to develop some endangered population species and only zoos are able to do so . In the future , I hope we would find a way to live peacefully without destroying animals ' homes . 
Music is a part of art and I believe that all people should know some basics about music . The question is whether it should be taught in schools . Firstly , music is part of our lives . We are in touch with music every day in movies , shows , many people listen to music in their free time and some people go to concerts . If music is really that important in our culture , we all ought to know something about it . music is also important for our thinking and mind . According to research , I have read music evolved our right hemisphere and helps us to concentrate . On the other hand , there are people who do not like music at all and they are bad at it . For example , one of my friends was forced to play the piano and he did not like it at all . Now , he hates music because of his bad experience . All things considered , it seems to me that the students should be educated in the theory of music , but they should not be forced to play any musical instrument . 
My reasons for learning English There are many reasons to learn English and everyone might have a different point of view . To begin with , I will give you the reasons that led me to learn English a few years ago . Additionally , I will tell you why it matters to me . To start with , I was not very interested in learning English when I was a young girl . I believed it was useless . At the age of fifteen , I changed my mind , for crying out loud ! My main reason for learning English was to be able to watch American movies in their original version . As a matter of fact , I was a huge fan of Buffy , the vampire slayer and it was important to me to hear their voices without coverage . Of course , I used subtitles . Furthermore , when I arrived at college , I had to take English classes . It made me understand how necessary it was to improve my writing and speaking abilities , not only to be able to graduate , but also because a lot of companies value it . Last but not least , I love to travel and I am very interested in learning about other countries . Speaking English offers me the possibility to communicate easily with foreigners . 
Today , knowing English is crucial for any worker . So that 's why I am studying English . Articles and manuals are all in English . Some of them are in my native language . With globalization , we need to work with foreign professionals . So how are we going to communicate if we do not speak English ? Many times they are not native English speakers . Many of them are Chinese , German and Spanish , so it 's important to have a language in common . This language is English . If I am not wrong , there are more English speakers who are non -native than native English speakers . Of course , if you work in some rare areas that other languages are not important , then it 's not important to learn . But if you are in this situation and like to travel abroad , knowing English is very important . Travel companies always have instructions in English . So if you would not like to be left behind , study English ! 
Hi Rie , Thanks for the invitation . I will come for sure . I like to eat many things . How about ordering pizza ? In this way , you do not need to cook and I do not need to do the dishes . I think it 's a good idea . What do you think ? See you . 
Hello Anna , How do you do ? Five days ago , I went to an absolutely incredible concert , it was really mind -blowing to listen to the six musicians , all the other people around me and , last but not least , the awesome fireworks at the beginning and at the end of the concert . Since I was a teenager , I 'd dreamed about going to another concert of the Scorpions . Yes , this wonderful German band that plays German and English spoken songs . I did not get some of the English songs , it was a pretty amazing night . If I had learnt more English vocabulary , I would have understood more . Because of this , I must learn more and improve even further my knowledge of your tongue . Maybe you can continue to give me some advice . Kind regards , 
Hi friend ! How are things ? Sorry for being so slow getting back to you , but as I told you , some weeks ago , I 've been to an incredible concert in the city next to mine . I 'm glad that you dropped me a line . So , in your letter , you wonder about how that came to be . Well , my girlfriend 's really keen on music , so she persuaded me to go with her to a concert that was taking place in the city next to ours , and although I had to work that day , I could not call it off because she already bought the tickets . She 's infatuated about a Latin singer called Bad Bunny and when she heard about the concert , she freaked out . I 'm not fond of Spanish music , though . , I enjoyed the concert pretty much . The atmosphere was really cozy and cool , there were much fewer people than I expected , so it was not too crowded , which was something I felt really thankful for , and despite the event lasted 3 hours , surprisingly , I ended up singing and dancing as if that was our last day on earth . The guy performing wore flashy fashionable clothes so it was not easy to lose him . Well , that is all for now . I 'm looking forward to hearing about your weekend . Best wishes , Ale 
It goes without saying that the use of cell phones is , and is being enogh commun in the nowadays , and is common enough nowadays . After all , we watch films , series , read newspapers , books ; seeing that this is a great way to connect with the breaking news . However , there is an addiction to mobile phones in the present day . Alternatively , the resolution is not in prohibiting this device . Whereas that measure is not going to reduce the problem of interaction between individuals , apart from interfering with humanitarian law , since it disturbs the choices of the citizen . 
I think that telling a lie is a very big mistake . If you respect somebody , you should tell him or her the truth . Telling a lie is not going to solve your problems , sooner or later , they will find out that you have lied and they will never trust you again . After telling a lie , you are forced to say another lie and another lie , until you start to believe your own lies . I do not like to lie to my son , wife or mother , it is not fair to anybody . I remember that sometimes my father told us lies and it was pretty obvious , when you are lying , your body is still telling the truth . Grown ups usually know when you are telling a lie , it is easier when you have to lie to your children or your grandfather in order to protect them , that is not a good strategy either . Children learn this way that it 's right to tell a lie in order to get out of a difficult situation . I like and I search for people that do not tell lies , I want to be able to count on them and a liar is not a person who I can trust . Regarding this subject , I think that I have nothing else to add , I am looking forward to going to sleep . 
If we want to discover what the future will be like , a good way to start this search is looking at the past . In the 60s decade , traveling around the world was a utopian dream . There were few flights and they were very expensive . Therefore , the knowledge about the universal language ( English ) was not a common practice in schools around the world . However , with the power of globalization , traveling to several countries in the same life became a possible dream . The amount of flights increased - side by side with the market demands - and traveling culture has been spread as a new hobby and a synonym of happiness . Finally , we arrived to the 21st century and we wonder : in the next years , will I travel more ? Will it become cheaper ? The answer , for me , is yes to everything . In an increasingly connected world , the borders will decrease . On the other hand , I 'm scared about the loss of culture shock between countries . First of all , we need put in our bags just the will and leave at home the colonizing instinct that unfortunately still lives in our society . 
When I was a child at school , during music class , we learnt songs to sing at the end -of -year concert . It was funny because our teachers taught us new words and dances . When we were older , sometimes we would do a musical with soloists . There were competitions to assign the parts . Once , I won and I became the protagonist . I was the happiest child ever . When I was a girl , at secondary school , during music class , we listened to classical music , as Mozart , Beethoven , Bach or Puccini , and we studied the history of the opera , like Aida , the Traviata or the Turandot . We also studied how to play melodies with the flute , like " jingle balls " or " hallelujah hallelujah . " Although studying music was funny when I was a child , when I grew up , it became a complete waste of time . My teacher did not take his job seriously and , most times , we wasted our lessons talking about other things or studying other school subjects . The hours used to study music can be useful when children are still little because they need to have fun and to understand which are their interests . When children grow up , time should be spent in better ways . For example , in schools , the study of our constitution could be introduced again , whose articles should be known by every Italian citizen , or civic education , whose knowledge is really missing , because people have lost their good common sense . Moreover , geography teachings could be developed because people , especially the young ones , ignore what they are surrounded by . They do not know neither that Rome is our capital , nor that Pisa has the Leaning Tower , nor that Po , Arno and Tevere are our biggest rivers . 
Hello Leyla , How are you ? I want to apologise to you because I could not go to the party yesterday , but I had so much work and my client wanted the project on his house . I hope you had fun at your party . Do not forget that I love you very much and I feel so bad with myself for not going . How was the party ? I want to compensate you for not having gone , what do you think if we see each other next week and I invite you to watch a movie or to have dinner in the evening . 
As far as I am concerned , there is something essential about benevolent work at all . So as for me , it definitely ought to be a part of compulsory training to finish school . Some people could take it strange to force young pupils to go for something like that as a part of their education . But why not ? ? Education is not purely something professional , it should prepare youngsters not only for working to get good money , but mainly , to be a good person - sensitive and eager to support others . Unfortunately , hospitals are crowded with suffering people waiting for someone to bring them relief . Moreover , kennels are full of adorable animals craving a warm smile . Places like that require some backing , especially from young , strong and healthy people who can provide those in need with their care and a helping hand . If schools did something like that habitually , they could contribute to students ' personal and mental development . It could be exceptionally educational as well as beneficial for future chores as mothers , fathers or children taking care of their ageing parents . 
Dear Sir or Madam , It is Mike Smith , a citizen of this town . I would like to tell you my opinion about the idea of the restriction of mobile phone usage in public spaces . In my opinion , it is not a good idea . If the usage were actually banned , it would result in being criticized by a lot of people . There are three reasons why I oppose this idea . First , we cannot respond e -mails or phone calls quickly . Although some people have bad manners , it is too severe for you to prohibit us from using phones in public places . Most of us usually interact with others anywhere via mobile phone . For example , I send an e -mail to my friends on the train when I make appointment with them . I have to tell them when I arrive at the place where we are gathering . Moreover , when I receive e -mails from my business partners , I will opt for responding them as quickly as possible , in order to ensure our relationships . Second , we enjoy sharing our experience with others on time . We often take photographs of our lunch . If it were restricted , some people would avoid visiting shops and restaurants in our town . It might damage their sales . Third , it is harmful for our rights to prohibit us from using our own mobile phones . It depends on our free will whether we use mobile phones anywhere . Thus , it should be a reputational risk for our town . It is not desirable for our town 's council . After all , I oppose the idea for the reasons above . Yours sincerely , 
Yes , I not only like it , but I also love it . Well , usually . I do it most days of the week . When I exercise , I prefer doing it in a gym . Why ? Because it 's more comfortable . A gym has many training tools which can help me develop my whole body . And at a gym , I do not have to worry about the rain . Sometimes I exercise outside as well , but I still prefer doing it in a gym . Here are some activities I like doing for exercise : squat , bench press , and go jogging on a treadmill , . . . 
Some people think that always being honest is an important moral virtue . In my opinion , however , telling the truth is an important thing , but telling some lies in some crucial situations is acceptable . On the one hand , the importance of honesty could not be denied for several reasons . Firstly , honesty brings other people 's trust to us and they can have a reliable relationship with us . Secondly , when we learn to not lie to others , they will also learn to answer us with the same behaviour . Also , building our relationship based on lies will give us a high level of stress about maybe my lie being revealed . 
Hello , How 's it going ? Yesterday , I watched that film again . Do you remember what film it is ? It begins with the number 50 . Okay , I 'm going to say it : 50 First Dates . I love this film . I 'm always excited about watching it . Its name is very different in Portuguese . We called it " Como se fosse a primeira vez . " I have no idea how I would translate this name into English because I do not have a lot of vocabulary and grammar . The context is similar , but the translation is very different . It 's a romantic film and it tells the story about a guy that falls in love with a girl , but she forgets overnight everything . So , he needs to seduce her every day . It 's incredible . I always watch this film and it never gets boring for me . Well , how about watching it ! Okay , it is not an action film , but it 'll pay off to watch it . Watch it and tell me afterwards what you think about it . See you . 
Dear Suzy , How are you ? Today I want to tell you about my favorite movie : Titanic ! Have you seen it ? As a matter of fact , I am sure you have heard of it . It 's based on a true story , even though I think the characters are made up . At first light , I appreciate this movie because I used to watch it with my mum every Saturday night when I was younger . Actually , we would order a pizza and baked some cookies . I trust it was the best evening possible for crying out loud . Furthermore , the scenario is great , and I believe you would like it as well . Please watch it and let me know if you enjoyed it . However , I recommend you have some tissues near . Looking forward to hear from you , Have a pleasant week , Kind regards , Lola 
In many schools , children learn how write an essay , how to solve a mathematical problem and many other important subjects . All these subjects are meant to impart the children the skills and the knowledge that they need for their foreseeable future and education . For some children , it also helps to determine their hobbies . In other words , why can music be a part of each school curriculum ? I believe that studying music supplies many advantages for children . In this essay , I will provide evidence that endorses studying music in school . Firstly , studying music in school gives children the opportunity to discover their musical talents . There are many children whose home situation does not enable them to come in contact with music . Furthermore , there are children whose parents cannot afford the instruments that they need to perform some kind of music . For these children , school is a good place to discover whether music is a subject they want to specialize in or not . Secondly , studying music in school helps children to develop social and creativity skills . Many schools who impart music lessons also gives the children the chance to establish their own music groups . Through this , many children will learn how to work with other people , but also how to deal with problems like quarrels . Another advantage of studying music in schools is that music will encourage the child 's creativity because children have the chance to write their own songs and to provide group performances . To conclude , it is very obvious that studying music provides many advantages for children and that music is even as important as other school subjects , like history and biology , because children learn the needed social and creativity skills . 
I think it is important to tell the truth in general . However , it is sometimes necessary to tell a lie , too . There are situations in which it is harmful for others to tell the truth . For example , suppose that your friends ask you what you think of their clothes . Even if you think they are bad , you will praise their style . In this situation , it may annoy your friends to tell them your opinion frankly . In another example , if you are not satisfied with a gift from your friends , you will not complain about it . After all , you should avoid disturbing others ' feelings by telling them your true feelings . Although you should not be sometimes honest , it is significant to tell others the truth otherwise . If you choose not to be honest , it may lead to undesirable consequences . For instance , if you concealed making mistakes in your company , it would lose the trust of others owing to your faults . This is a problem not only for you but also for both your colleagues and your boss . Perhaps your boss might have to resign from his post to take responsibility for the distrust . Thus , you should not tell a lie to others in a situation in which it harms others . In conclusion , it is never acceptable to tell a lie . However , it depends on the situation . It is more important to distinguish the situation in which you should tell a lie from the one you should not . 
In my free time , I always find something to do . When I am at my grandmom 's , I read , do puzzles and laugh about other people . When I am at home , I play funny games with my little brother . I love my free time ! 
Every season has something special about it . However , to me , autumn happens to be the most magical season of the year . First of all , I find the weather change to be quite endearing . The chilly winds of September are a nice energising break from the summer heat . Cold weather also signals the beginning of sweater weather . Personally , I am in love with jumpers and anything with long sleeves , hence the cold weather is a great opportunity to start wearing layers once again . The landscape also becomes magnificent . The colourful leaves falling majestically off the trees are almost mesmerising . The ground covered with a blanket of colours makes any stroll become much more pleasant . Autumn is also special because of Halloween . Although I no longer celebrate it as I used to , I feel delighted seeing other people enjoying themselves . This time of the year also unites several communities on social media , and together we celebrate the arrival of the spooky season . 
I 'm writing to tell you that I could not go to your party yesterday because I had to visit my mother , seeing as she was not feeling well . But tell me about the party , was it good ? Did you have fun ? I would like to invite you to hang out with me next weekend . How about going to the cinema and after that we can go to the new restaurant in front of the cinema ? 
My favorite indoor activity is drawing a watercolor creation . It 's procuring me a huge personal satisfaction . What I prefer a lot about this activity is obviously the things that I discover after ending each painting work . The last watercolor creation I have just finished is about a famous historical Moroccan building . I enjoyed it a lot . 
Hi Billal , I 'm writing to tell you about my trip last week . I went on a trip with some students from my class . During the trip , we visited some amazing places in Rio . We visited the Christ Redeemer and we went to the zoo too . The view from Christ was unforgettable ! You have to go there one day . What I most enjoyed was the opportunity to spend some time with friends . We took a lot of pictures and I will show you them . 
Our relationship with our teachers is usually linked to many factors like mutual trust , respect , as well as esteem . Like a majority of students , I think it 's more interesting and good for students to have new teachers each year . There are many reasons to believe that : first of all , meeting different teachers during our learning gives us a good opportunity to improve our knowledge and skills not only about topics but also about life ; secondly , having one teacher could not give you the possibility to discover different points of view . Finally , meeting different teachers means earning new learning approaches as well as new ways to resolve our usual problems . In other words , being taught by one teacher each year remains very boring and uninteresting , even if the teacher is very qualified . To summarize my point of view , I would say I 'm very convinced that changing teacher every year is very useful . 
My dear friend , Finally , I had the chance to attend the " Kayhan Kalhor " concert last week . As you know , I have been a fan of him for several years , but had never found this opportunity to go to his concert . Kayhan is a Kurdish Iranian artist , who is a professional player of Kamanche , one of the traditional musical instruments in Iran . He is not only a special player for Iranians , but also he is known as a famous artist in many other nations . At the concert , he played several of his prominent pieces of music , like Halbach . The air of the concert was full of traditional senses , which took us to the villages of Kurdistan . What I needed at that moment was only silence and to listen . I felt that I was on another level of life and I was looking at my life from another perspective . It was really fascinating and I hope you could also one day find this opportunity to attend his concert . Yours sincerely , Fatemeh 
Over the last few years , I have traveled a lot and I have been to many places . However , my holiday in Sri Lanka remains my best memory ever . In the first place , I will tell you where I went and what I saw . In the second place , I will explain to you why it was the best holiday I have ever had . To begin with , it was the first time I ever visited Asia . When we landed in Colombo , the capital of Sri Lanka , it was hot and it was like nothing I had seen before , for crying out loud ! My boyfriend and I decided to make a road trip . We did much sightseeing . As a matter of fact , we climbed Adam 's peak ! Indeed , we had to walk 5500 stairs to reach the summit . Moreover , we started our hike at 1am and we were just in time to admire the sunrise . It was as right as rain ! After that , we went to chill on mesmerizing beaches all around the country . Not only the landscape was beautiful , but also the people were warm and welcoming . Both of those aspects combined made this trip unforgettable . Last but not least , my boyfriend asked me to marry him . I had to wait a long time before he proposed to me , but it was worth it . Better late than never ! 
Dear Elliot , How are you ? Lately , I have been thinking about you ! As you are well aware , I am a fan of Torino . And guess what ? They were performing last weekend in my town , for crying out loud ! First of all , I was not sure I could attend their show , as my mum came to visit me the same week . As a matter of fact , she came in order to spend time with me , so I was feeling guilty abandoning her . Then , I decided she could come with me , as she had never been to a concert in all her life . Better late than never ! Moreover , the show was outstanding . The lead singer , John , was on fire , and the atmosphere was electric . Although I was worried my mother would get bored , she was actually dancing all over . Last but not least , at the end of the concert , they played their new song . Both my mum and I loved it . But all good things must come to an end . Nevertheless , last Saturday was one of my best memories ever . If some day you get the chance to see them live , I am sure you will love it . I am looking forward to meeting you . Sincerely yours , Lola 
Video games are widespread among children . Playing video games might be advantageous to them . Nevertheless , it will bring some drawbacks if parents cannot control how their children play video games . This essay will analyze the advantages and disadvantages when children play video games . On the one hand , playing video games can be beneficial . Firstly , it helps children relax after hours of studying . When they have time to rejuvenate , children will have more energy to go back to their studies . Secondly , while playing games , children can learn some new skills such as problem -solving , time management , and teamwork ( if they play games together ) , which are necessary for them later in life . Challenges in video games force children to think , to use their minds to find solutions , and to help each other for the final target . These are some benefits when children play video games . On the other hand , it might be harmful if children play games too much . Hours of looking at the screen will damage their eyes , which leads to many negative effects on children 's lives . They will not learn effectively and fully develop with unhealthy eyes . Also , playing games too much makes children tired . From that , they will be less active and lose their interest in other kinds of activities , such as running and playing outdoors . These are the reasons why parents should monitor and limit the time of playing video games of their children . In conclusion , playing video games is a double -edged sword . Although it contributes positively to the development of children , there are still many drawbacks . Parents should be aware of these advantages and disadvantages to help their children control the use of video games . 
Keeping children occupied with useful activities is usually a great challenge for parents . In the past , reading a book or watching television were enough for children to enjoy , but now it 's very difficult to satisfy them . Video games are obviously the favourite occupation that children prefer in this century , but why ? In my modest opinion , it 's due to the frame of the games . them all the things that they need , like advertisements , connection with other friends or a self - esteem feeling . Many parents are not conscious about the danger that video games represent . It 's proved that using video games for a long time leads children into a dangerous type of psychological disease , like schizophrenia . In my case , I strongly believe that video games are very dangerous and I will do everything in my ability to avoid my children using them . Instead of that , I will certainly encourage them to be friends with books and magazines . To summarize my opinion , I will encourage my children to be creative . 
Many people believe that having the same teachers for several years is beneficial for students . And some think that changing teachers every year is better . For me , both reasons have pros and cons . The advantages of having the same teachers are the teachers know best about their students and they also keep tracking the development of students . On the other hand , the teachers will be biased with some students and like some . Another reason , the students have been taught the same idea of living and that is not useful because the students should be taught in different ideas . For people who would like to have new the teachers each year , there are many benefits , for example , the students will learn new things and new critical thinking . Both teachers and students learn how to adapt together because it is a good lesson for real life . But the problem of changing the teacher is the teachers do not know their students well and it will take a long time in order for them to get along with each other well . In conclusion , I think having a new teacher is better because leaning new things with people is good for life learning skills . 
First and foremost , it is common knowledge that working out is important for our health . However , doing sports is not enough to be in good shape , for crying out loud ! There is another major aspect that needs to be taken into consideration . First of all , I will explain why exercise should be part of our daily routine . Then , I will shed light on the need to have good eating habits . To begin with , to do some exercise , you do not need to run a marathon . Most people resent sport because they believe it is too demanding and painful . As a matter of fact , you just need to walk thirty minutes per day to be in shape . It 's not rocket science . For those who like to challenge themselves , there are a lot of activities that can be done , like crossfit . Moreover , exercise can have other positive impacts . Not only does it shape our body , but also it is essential for our mind . Indeed , exercise prevents depression , stress and anxiety . Notwithstanding , exercise being important , our eating habits come before anything else in order to be healthy . In any case , we need to be careful with what we put on our plate . For instance , it is important to have the right amount of carbs , proteins and nutriments . That is to say , we should avoid fats and sugar . Furthermore , we need to drink at least two liters of water each day to help our body recover . There is no age to start a healthy way of living . Better late than never ! 
Hi Ana , I am glad to hear from you . I am learning English because it could help me with my job and my career . Learning English is very important for me because it can also give me more opportunities to travel around the world , and to meet new people . 
Many would agree that the ultimate goal of life is to live longer and in happiness . Clearly , living a modest life for 100 years for me is more valuable than living only 20 years in abundance . I believe that living longer is better because it is a sign of a well -lived life and a longer service to other people . I believe in the old adage that says " to live better , you need to hide . " People who live a good life are generally those who have chosen to do everything moderately . For example , having good health habits , such as eating moderately and not allowing excess alcohol , might lengthen the live . Although the length of one 's life can be determined by many things , one should definitely avoid dangerous activities . Some people , for instance , choose to drive very carelessly or very fast on road just to show to the world how smart they are . This behaviour , sometimes , can lead to a sudden death . Moreover , living an intense life does not always mean living well or being helpful to other people . For example , mother Theresa of India had lived a long life but had been of a tremendous help to many people in the world . This means that life does not necessarily need to be intense to be meaningful . Many have lived a long an enjoyable life without being famous or known by everyone on every side of the globe . This said , I prefer a longer and smooth live instead of a short life full of excessive behaviour . To conclude , we do not all determine the length of our life . And we can only try to bring the best out of the time we have existed . 
I started using Write and Improve few days ago and I am really excited about it . Firstly , Write and Improve is a program on the internet which helps you improve your English writing . There are many different topics you can choose and write about them . The program is capable of correcting your text and showing you what level of English it has . After that , you can correct the essay and it will show you your progress . But how does it correct your text exactly ? The program shows you all the mistakes in spelling and grammar , which is common in most of the writing programs . What 's more Write and Improve can check your whole sentences too . On the other hand , there are some things missing in this program which I would use . These are , for instance , suggestions on how to improve or correct your sentence and , most importantly , the explanation of your exact level of English and how to improve it when you correct everything and have no mistakes left . Furthermore , on Write and Improve , there were some mistakes too . I used one common English phrase and this program corrected me . All things considered , I would recommend Write and Improve for all students who want to learn how to write in English . Anyway , there is still a lot of space to upgrade this helpful tool for students . 
Since the world was created , animals have lived in the free areas , like jungles or great forests . Our unsustainable development led us unhappily to an ecological disaster during these three last centuries . We saw how pollution and immoral modernity had massively destroyed all the ecosystems around the world . The biodiversity was highly and negatively impacted . The animals were eventually among the unlucky victims of those huge impacts and some people thought they were doing good , imagining this tragic and stupid invention , the zoo . Zoos could be a real space for protecting animals , but actually they are a real prison for animals . In other words , zoos really change the animals ' behavior . In my modest opinion , zoos remain a bad solution for protecting animals , whereas the real solution is to provide animals with free space and give them protection in order to leave them living as the ever creature of god live : free . 
Dear Mayor Muller , I 'm writing to ask you to dismiss the idea of banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants . Mobile phones are an important part of our lives these days . While we are using the public transport , they can help us to catch up with the latest news or stay in contact with our friends . These days , they are also a wallet . Some people have their credit card on their phone or their ticket for public transport . I understand that it can be annoying if someone is making a phone call while being in a restaurant or using the public transport , but in a world where everything is connected that is the price we have to pay . If our town were to ban the use of mobile phones in public transport or in shops and restaurants , we would disconnect our town from the world . Furthermore , some people would use their car instead of public transport . This would lead to more traffic , which is bad for the environment . But most importantly , it is more dangerous if people to use their phone while they are driving than if they used it on public transport . As there is no harm done to anyone , it makes no sense to ban the use of mobile phones on public transport or in restaurants and shops . I appreciate everything that you do for our city . Sincerely , Ben Singer 
First and foremost , digitalisation had brought us many changes and challenges . Our environment had drastically evolved and no realm has been left aside . In that situation , what about schools ? What will they be like in the future ? Will they still be the same ? First of all , I will tell you why I believe schools will be different in the near future . However , I will explain to you why some things will remain the same . To begin with , digitalisation has entered our lives at any stage . As a matter of fact , we now have access to a large range of skills and tools . Smartphones , computers and tablets are made available for everyone . Additionally , artificial intelligence can provide new ways of learning . Knowing that , I think the school of the future will use those different applications to reinvent itself and offer new possibilities . For example , screens could be implemented on desk boards . Furthermore , kids need to be able to use any technological devices easily . Not only is it a way to fit into the world , but also it is essential to find a job . Moreover , I believe , in just a few years from now , students wo not need to attend classrooms anymore . Indeed , I think e -learning will become extremely popular . Actually , a lot of business schools are already using it and it is an outstanding success , for crying out loud ! However , I believe some aspects will still be the same . For instance , there will still be teachers and grades . Last but not least , I believe human contact is a need for young children and it ca not be replaced by artificial intelligence . Finally , all those transformations will take some time . Better late than never . 
My hometown is small but very beautiful at the same time . As an important landmark it has got an ancient palace in the center of town . There are a lot of food stores where you can go shopping . Regarding entertainment , you can find many night clubs where you can have a good time . 
Hi Cristina , I know that you had an accident . I 'm so sorry about it . I really want to help you , so I can bring your homework every day while you need to stay at home . I 'm not going to visit today because I have arrived now at school and I 'm very tired . So , I 'm going to visit you tomorrow , OK ? Take care ! Matt 
Hi Mat , You must be happy about the new school year . I hope you can deserve your target to improve in math and history . I need to improve my English . I 've arranged what I want to do to improve it . First , I 've just joined a private course in pronunciation . I 've done the 30 -day writing challenge to post on the English Course App , and I 'll continue in the next 30 -days by adding to it something else , probably speaking . If you do not mind , I am going to send you my writing so you can correct it . I 'm still confused about what I should do to improve my reading . I intend to find a good book in English . Would you mind giving me a recommendation about what I should read , Matt ? Good luck for your new school year . 
I would live a shorter life rather a long life . There are two reasons why I think so . First , I cannot be viable during all my lifetime . At the end of my life , I will not be active like before , and I will only be able to stay in a hospital . I cannot endure the situation that I manage to live with the aid of medicine . I would like to perform something until my life is ended . Even more , we can enjoy our freedom because it is limited by the surroundings . If I lived a long life , I would have few things to do and would be bored with my freedom . Second , in my opinion , a shorter life is more stimulating than a longer one . As I become older , I will experience less owing to physical restrictions . It seems to me that people face too many things between in their 20s and in their 50s . Therefore , unless I die in my twenties , I could have varied experiences . I could become satisfied with it . Moreover , I set my life plan in which I will be dead in my seventies . Considering the scheme , I am willing to try anything as long as I am viable . It results in making me busy , but at the same time , I can enjoy my time more than others . In conclusion , I prefer living a shorter life to living a longer life . It is significant for me to be active during my lifetime . Thus , I always make much effort for fulfilling my life . 
Fighting ignorance is a huge and difficult struggle . From when we are children , we are involved in that way . By integrating into school earlier , we choose our way towards discovery and learning . Students almost all have the same dream , which is to follow their studies abroad , especially when they are living in less -developed countries like mine . This difficult choice has advantages , like it has disadvantages . The biggest advantage that it has , in my opinion , is that it allows students to follow their degrees in a high level of education . One other important advantage is it allows students to discover a new culture , as well as a new civilisation and eventually learn about new concepts and a new field of learning . The disadvantages of this painful choice are numerous , like the psychological impact of being abroad and the difficulties that students face in foreign countries , for example racism or xenophobia . To summarize my opinion , I prefer continuing my studies in my country , even if the conditions are not sufficient , rather than taking useless risks . 
First of all , I would like to say that I am not a university student yet . That means that my opinion is not based on my own experience . Firstly , the life of university students might be hard and many students spend at their school more than 40 hours per week , which is usual working time in the Czech Republic . With this in mind , it would be very hard for some students to do a job . I believe that parents ought to support their children financially during their studies . The important question is whether the student should live at home . In my opinion , it is subjective . The main advantage of living with your parents could be the fact that you have really great background and it is cheaper than living on your own . On the other hand , when you decide to live alone or with your friends , you will probably become more responsible and independent . Furthermore , I believe that staying too long with your parents is not good for your relationship and your psychological development . All things considered , I think that everyone should choose for themself and both choices are all right . 
First and foremost , globalisation and digitalisation have brought many changes in our world , for crying out loud ! They have changed the way we work , travel and communicate . For instance , low -cost airline companies appeared and home office has become common knowledge . Better late than never . Not only is it more important than it used to be , but also is it an obligation in some cases . First of all , I will tell you why I believe it is essential to speak a foreign language in 2020 . Then , I will share my views regarding some aspects . To begin with , it has become more and more difficult to find a job nowadays . Repeated crises have transformed the world . It has become particularly difficult to reach a company 's expectations . Currently , major market brands are asking people to be fluent in another language , like English , Spanish or Chinese . It might sound demanding , but this is the way it works . Moreover , people are travelling way more than they used to . For example , a lot of students go on a world tour after finishing their degree . In this case , it is better , if not obligatory , to speak English , in order to able to communicate with foreigners . Last but not least , some people are interested in learning another language because it 's part of a country 's culture . Notwithstanding , in my opinion it is important to discover a different language than your native one . I believe it also depends on your way of living . Indeed , if someone does not like to travel , or is not interested in working in an international company , there is no need to spend time learning another language . I believe it matters to shed light on different points of view . 
Dear teacher , As you know I love studying English with you but recently I watched a documentary on television about the second world war and I 'd like to start studying this new subject . I 've always loved history since I was a child . I 'd like to begin this new course as soon as possible and I hope you will help me . 
During my free time , I do a lot of activities like watching series or reading a book . Actually , I read a novel after work at 6 pm . It takes about one hour . In the evening , after dinner , I usually watch TV or a movie in my bed . 
It goes without saying that being an honest individual implies oftentimes to be truthful and not tell lies . However , is it even necessary ? After all , there are countless situations where there are a lot of advantageous to count a little falsehood . A good illustration of this is omitting a case that can harm the feelings of one person . Furthermore , there are some educational untruths ; for instance , to teach to eat , make a bed , or even to instruct how to brush your teeth . 
