I believe having different teachers for students each year is a good thing , because each teacher has their own style of teaching , that they use to foster students ' understanding . In addition to that , each teacher has different qualities and skills , thus , introducing new teachers to students each year is an opportunity for them learn more skills and helps them engage more academically . For me , at university , we had multiple lecturers for each individual subject . It was very nice because we had the chance to learn many useful things from them . Some people believe that students should have one teacher for many years . In my opinion , that would create some sort of boredom among students , as well as students would not have the chance to learn different skills that may be found in multiple teachers . Education has become an important thing in our lives . And in my opinion , different teachers with different perspectives and horizons would influence the academic experience of students to the fullest extent . That 's why I see it is very important to introduce different teachers to students each year . 
Hi ! My favourite film is " Aladdin . " I like that movie , because I like all the action . I like the story . One of my favourite parts is when the actors sing the song called " Prince Ali " and I laugh at a scene where Aladdin is very funny . I also like the part where Aladdin and Jasmin sing the song called " A whole new world . " Something really cool about the movie is that the dancing is really good and it 's amazing how the actors dance . The bad guy in this film is called Jafar . He is a greedy wizard who wants the entire kingdom for himself . You should really see it , because you like films about magic and fairy tales . You also like the dessert a lot . I hope you see the film I recommended for you . Hope you are well , bye ! 
In my opinion , playing video games has more benefits for children than other people think . Children can play video games , but parents should arrange their time to play games properly . The most important thing for children is they can grow , play , have fun and are happy at their age . Video games are part of children 's memories . I support children playing video games for many reasons . The first reason is that video games can improve fine motor skills and also language development , because most video games use English as a communication language with other players . The second reason , if someone is fond of the game , they may have a dream to be a game developer , a person who invents or creates new games or new items . The third reason , now there are many world game competitions or Electronic sports ( E -sport ) . Many children become E -sport gamers . Another reason , some children can earn money by themselves , because when they reach any high levels , they can sell special items to other players . The last reason , video games can help to solve the mental problems of children who are addicted to games . In conclusion , the games have both pros and cons . If people arrange the time properly , they can get many benefits from video games . 
In my opinion , zoos are good places for people to learn about animals , because it is necessary to understand their way of life . Zoos could be important places to open the minds of people who do not care about animals ' well -being . Moreover , zoos raise awareness in people about endangered species . Many people do not know that a species like the polar bear could disappear by 2100 . Additionally , zoos are very useful to help injured animals . Near my home , we have a zoo specialized in dolphin re -education . However , there are a few reports of animal abuse in zoos . Some of them do not respect the animals ' dignity and their principal needs . For example , a monkey died at Abidjan zoo due to a lack of food and love . Furthermore , some species become crazy because of visitors ' noise , small cages and loneliness . As a consequence , some of them hit themselves . To conclude , zoos have a great purpose , but instead of saving and protecting species , they drive them to a premature ending . 
I am an accountant so I often use a computer every day . I usually use a computer for inputting data , analysing data , preparing financial reports , learning English , reading news and so on ... What I most do with a computer is self -study learning English . I have been learning English every morning for 2 hours . In conclusion , the computer is the greatest invention of human beings . Using a computer makes it easier for us to do anything . 
I often listen to music in my free time . I like listening to music because it makes me less stressful and I have new energy for working . The most favourite music of mine is classical guitar . I like the romantic songs performed by the most famous artists from all over the world . I listened to music last night . 
Hello Matt , How are you ? I hope you are in good wellness . Thank you for your kind to be my English buddy . I want to tell you about my favourite film . It is from India , and the title of the film is " Mumbai . " I do not know exactly the genre of this film . Probably it is an action , comedy and historical film because the story is based on a real tragedy in India . Then , there are some funny scenes in it . It is about terrorism so , as I said , the film is an action film . The film tells us about the tragedy which happened in one of the hotels in Mumbai . There were three terrorists who hijacked the hotel . They are Muslim terrorists who were being commanded by a person they did not know . Their commander said that they were in a ' God ' way . But actually , it 's not about that , I mean , the commander was just exploiting the people to his advantage . There is one scene I really love . It is when there is a conflict among the terrorists . They argue about killing a Muslim woman . One said that he ca not kill her because she is a Muslim , but the others said he must kill her because the commander had said that . You must watch this film Matt . I think you 're going to love this film too . Regards , Uly 
I agree with this statement , as health is the first and most important factor for human beings . In the absence of health , an abundance of money cannot help . Therefore , the importance of health and well -being cannot be denied by anyone . If one person does not have a good state of health , he/she cannot do any type of activity during the day , even if his/her bank balance is high . On the other hand , the influence of many things on a healthy lifestyle cannot be underestimated . Those who have more money can afford better living conditions and high -quality food , which cause a better level of body health . Also , they will take enjoyable holidays , which help their mental well -being . 
I think it is more important to be healthy than to be rich . It is more important to be healthy because if your body is not healthy , you will feel very sick , you will have a lot of complications in your body , you will have to take a lot of different kinds of medicine , and if you get even worse , you will die . If you are rich , and decide not to be healthy , and waste all your money on things that do not help you to be healthy , or that are just useless , it wo not help you . You will get worse and die and all that money you had was useless . Being healthy helps your body to be strong , and to not have any bad diseases . That is why you have to be healthy , you should do exercise , eat healthily , and to have a balanced diet . That is my opinion about which is better , to be rich or to be healthy . 
For this year , I have many purposes : at first , I would like to learn English as the main language for my career ; in the second step , I would like to improve my level in math as well as science and , finally , I will be happy if I could learn more about geography . The area that I want to improve a lot is obviously philosophy . The reason for that choice is so clear : That 's the field where my parents would like to see me in the future . In order to achieve my goals , I will manage many efforts such as spending much time working hard and exploring books and attending conferences linked with that field . I am so convinced that this challenge will be hard and so difficult , but it 's my final choice and I have to assume it whatever the needs of it . I count hardly on the support of my parents as well as my teachers . 
Currently , travelling is an entire part of our exciting lives . We love and enjoy travelling , either inside or outside our countries . The history of travel is so exciting . Humans started to travel by using camels and now we see the endless opportunities that we have to travel around the world . I am thinking about a plane , boat or train , but what about travel in the future ? In my modest opinion , travel will be more exciting and innovative in the future . We will certainly see many new kinds of travel . Not only will we have a new form of travelling , like through space , but also humans will be able to discover another planet and maybe a big hotel will be built there . The future of the travel would be obviously more enjoyable and surely linked with environmental questions , like climate issues or energy efficiency . 
My favourite indoor activity is playing video games , also I like to do some workouts , just to be in good shape . I like these activities because I want to be healthy and ready to do any activity that requires physical effort and I play video games because they make me have a good time , and forget about my problems . The last time that I did this activity was a few hours ago , I played a soccer video game , and I did a workout in the morning . 
I use a computer every single day and on average for 5 hours a day . I use a computer to search for information about cars and English courses , I also watch some videos and listen to music . I really enjoy watching videos about cars and how people restore them and share their information . 
Of course I like to do some exercise . I do exercise very often , five days a week , for one hour every day . I prefer to do it in my house , because I do not like being with strange people around me , and I like to be focused on my routine . I do different activities , like push ups , squats , jumps and a lot of Burpees . 
In my opinion , doing exercise is very important for our health and our well -being . Obviously , you do not have to do exercise each day , because it takes a lot of your time and it is tiring for many people . On the contrary , you can do daily exercise , for example , twice per week . Moreover , if you do sport with a friend , you can get more motivation and you could become better . To do this , it is also important to fix a purpose . However , exercise is not the only important thing for our health . Indeed , there is an obvious link between nutrition and health . Having healthy food is the first step to having better health . Additionally , eating better is also good behavior to protect our environment . Combining daily exercise and healthy food is the best answer ever to maintain our health . To conclude , I think that exercise and nutrition are important for our health . 
We have a great change in our society nowadays because of this COVID -19 situation . We are forced to stay at home and do remote work . Many schools also need changes in this circumstance . In the future , students wo not have to go to school . They will be able to learn all subjects at home using internet school . They will cooperate with other students using online conference systems . They will be able to get any information needed for their studies from websites all over the world . They will even do sports using online sports applications named " e -sports . " As I said above , we can do everything online , except direct interaction with others . We know that physical contact is still important for children 's development . We need a playground or gymnasium at school for children 's play , but we do not need school buildings anymore . We may not need as many teachers as we have now , because a few teachers can teach all the students via the internet and AI may help teachers ' work . 
Hi , I am studying English because I am taking a proficiency test at the end of the year and the result of it will be very important for my resumé . Besides that , I enjoy studying English , it is like a hobby for me . 
Hi Matt , I was glad to receive your email . Of course I know Monday is the time for us to begin a new school year . I said that I wanted to improve my English and I am going to try my best to reach it . Firstly , I am going to read and practice English more frequently . I will take part in an interesting English group to share and learn lessons on learning English . In addition , I will try to communicate with foreigners who are native English speakers as much as possible to improve my speaking . Good luck . 
Dear Town Council , I think banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants is not a good idea at all . As mobile phones have been near humans for over two decades and these electronic devices can be taken anywhere and can be opened within seconds . Banning them would result in people taking laptops everywhere they go and also using laptops all the time , which would again lead to a mass protest . As the digital age grows , mobile phones are getting better and more advanced than other devices . As the name suggests ' mobile phone ' , people can take it anywhere without an additional 2.3 kg . Imagine this , people taking laptops everywhere they go . Restaurants , shops , restaurants and public transport . Some people would just be using their laptops to navigate and call and even take photos . That would be awkward for a normal mobile phone user as laptops can only be used for selfies and when not held correctly , it may drop and get damaged . While on the other hand , mobile phones can be used for both selfies and normal photos . As other devices are mostly just for work , school and others , mobile phones can do everything . They can be used for work , banking , researching and more . Consider this whether mobile phones should be banned or not . If mobile phones are banned , it would lead to a huge protest which could make the most of the high ranking workers resign from the office . 
I disagree with it . There are three reasons why I oppose that opinion . First , it is not necessarily limited to sports activities to keep them healthy . Running or doing yoga can replace them . Some students and children will prefer doing such exercises to playing other sports . If universities and schools made their students exercise in their facilities , it would be difficult to fulfill all students ' favors . Some students would not be satisfied with the schools ' policies . However , if the schools let their students exercise outside , it would also be hard to manage the students ' activities . Briefly , it is absurd from scratch to force students to do exercises regularly . Second , there is little scientific evidence to support the frequency of playing sports . Is it really enough to do exercise three times a week ? This opinion explains nothing about how many hours we should exercise . At least , those who are in favor of this opinion should provide information about the basis of their statement . In my opinion , we cannot improve the lack of physical activity by imposing unreliable evidence on students . Third , I think it is not always good to make much effort to become healthier . It is true that there may be no problem for many people to be forced to do physical activities . However , it is not the case for some people with disabilities . Such people cannot participate in sports as well as ordinary people . To improve our inactive lifestyle , we only have to increase the opportunities for exercise . It is appropriate only for healthy people , and this idea utterly ignores people who are willing to exercise but cannot do so . If the given opinion pervades among a lot of universities and schools , it will be natural to get rid of people with disabilities . Thus , I am against this opinion . It seems to me that this opinion is not persuasive and dangerous . Therefore , I will never admit it . 
In my opinion , the transport sector has been highly hit with the currently pandemic . Therefore , this sector will need to be more ecological . For me , in the future , people will travel by plane or by train because it will be faster and safer . Planes could go to any city in less than 2 hours thanks to supersonic technologies . Of course , people still take boats , but only for pleasure . Indeed , in our future society , taking a boat to travel will not be ecological with the use of petrol . Therefore , a majority of people will take the train for the same reasons that they will take planes , the speed . In the future , they will only take transport for the speed and not for the landscape . Of course , cars would always be used , but only electric cars . To conclude , the future of travel will combine two factors , ecology and speed . They will be necessary to protect our earth and travel in our planet . 
My hometown is a very beautiful place . It is a small town in the countryside and nowadays , it is a tourist place , especially because of the sport of fishing . The town is very safe , the hotels and restaurants are very good and the best part is that they are very cheap compared to other places in Brazil . Definitely , my hometown is a place where people can find peace and quiet , it is possible to rest and the adventures that can be found in a lot of activities such as riding a bike , skateboarding , running and many other outdoor activities . 
These days , balancing between practical work and theoretical work is one of the most important conflicts in the education system . One program which is offered by specialists involves students in practical work through volunteer work . Community service has some pros and cons and considering them is important to make a good decision for teenagers . At first , working in a volunteer environment in high school can help students to improve their skills . Working as a volunteer increases their confidence and prepares them for doing a real job . In addition , learning work ethic is one of the most important aims of doing community service . Students learn to how they can help other people . Volunteer teachers mostly are patient and energetic people . These characteristics help teenagers to change their bad behaviors and develop their passions and ingenuity . On the other hand , volunteer work can unsettle students ' balance of time management . Students must deal with doing homework , sporting , preparing for exams and practical work . Generally , community service lacks structure and this can lead students to confusion in managing their time . Besides , some volunteer atmospheres are unsafe and uncertain . People who work in these places can be different and unknown . So , finding a good environment is important and parents and the school ’s staff must consider it precisely . In conclusion , developing social and professional skills is valuable and useful for students . Achieving these goals needs a practical plan and enough time in school . Therefore , community service has some significant advantages for teenage students . The disadvantages of volunteer work are less important than its goodness . By helping peers to manage their time and providing a secure surrounding can reinforce volunteer plans in high schools . Hence , students will be able to be professional people in society after finishing high school . 
