It is the start of a new school year , and I would like to take it as an opportunity to achieve certain goals to improve my English learning . Firstly , I would like to mention that I am very pleased with my progress in both speaking and writing , because I have been practising them very often over the last year . However , I do want to improve my grammar skills . My knowledge of English grammar is so basic and I thought I should do my best to improve it this new school year . On top of that , I would also like to improve my listening skills , although my listening is quite good , but I sometimes get lost when listening to Australian and New Zealand accents , because I am more used to the British accent , and it is the first accent I heard when I was learning English . There are certain things that I will do to accomplish my goals this new school year . Concerning my grammar , I will read one grammar book thoroughly and try to practise as much as possible . And regarding my listening skills , I will listen to English podcasts in different accents simultaneously . 
Taking care of animals is always attractive to people . Environmental concerns make people find ways to keep species safe . But preserving animals in zoos or in nature is the disagreement between the different groups . Some people believe animals belong in natural surroundings and others prefer to visit animals in zoos . In my opinion , there are some reasons for both arguments , but visiting species in nature is more acceptable for me . Being in a secure space is the first reason for keeping animals in zoos . Some people believe humans can protect species which are in danger by putting them in a cage . In addition , keeping animals in zoos is the best way to educate people about their habitat . Researching about animals ’ behavior and how to treat illnesses is easier in zoos . On the other hand , the species suffer from physical and mental problems , because they are forbidden from being in nature . The space in zoos is not the same as in nature for them . Mental problems cause stress for the animals and they may die earlier than when they live in a natural environment . Also , keeping animals in a small cage ruins their freedom . They cannot function like living in nature . In conclusion , one stage of overcoming nature is dealing with wild species . Some people prefer to keep animals in zoos to control and know about them . But others enjoy seeing animals free and living somewhere they belong . I also prefer to see animals in their natural environment and respect their freedom . 
Last week , I went on a holiday to Vancouver city in western Canada . It was the best holiday I have ever had and it was full of joy and experiences . I have learnt so many things . Vancouver is a bustling metropolis , full of life . I visited wonderful places , such as Stanely Park , Gas Town and the Museum of Vancouver , and I saw incredible things . I can say those were the most astonishing places I have ever been to . I also gave myself a chance to experience the landscapes , so I went 30 minutes away from downtown Vancouver to be in the Capilano suspension bridge park , to experience breathing the fresh air . In the Museum of Vancouver , I took lots of pictures of the World War II veterans and I also read a little bit about the history of that place . What I like most in Vancouver is the cultural diversity and open -mindedness of its people - they are very welcoming and friendly . In addition , the nightlife is Vancouver is incomparable to other cities in the world . It is very special for the restaurants and cafes . I really fell in love with this fun -loving city and I hope I will have the chance to visit again . 
