There are many polemics about video game use for children . In my opinion , it depends on how they will use the device . It can be good or it can be bad . First of all , time . If children use a video game in their free time , for instance , for hours continuously , it will be so bad . If they play violent games , with deaths , and they are very young , the routine will be worse . It is dangerous if it becomes an addiction , that the child needs to play every day , and if she does not have a video game , she will be nervous . It is very common nowadays . However , if the time with the video game has a clear limit , if the parents supervise the time and the kind of game , no problem . I guess if the game is interesting and stimulates logic and intelligence , it can be great for children . Another good option is to use the video game to exercise . Today we have some games to do movement too . 
I started learning English when I was 3 years old , from my mother . I learnt it as my second language , which made me be able to communicate with more people and just for fun . However , when I started high school , I realized that English was more important than I had thought , because it would help me get more opportunities to study abroad with a good English score . Moreover , most reference textbooks I read are written in English more than using my native language . And also , I need to improve my English communication skill , because I do not use English much in my everyday life , so I still feel uncomfortable communicating in English when I have not used it regularly . Finally , I hope I could get a good score in the exam and could attain a good school because of my good English skills in the future . 
