Hello Matt ! How 's it going ? Yes , you 're right ! I need to improve in English . Well , to improve my English , I have created a schedule . The activities begin on Monday and finish on Saturday . Every day there is an activity . Every morning I wake up at 6:00 am , I make my bed and when it is 7 o 'clock , I begin to study English on BBC Learning English . On BBC Learning English I study for at least 5 days per week . When the evening arrives , I begin to improve my skills in English . They are speaking , reading , writing and listening ... I also answer some questions . Every skill is worked on for one specific day . On Monday , I work on my speaking skills using the app Cake and Elsa . On Tuesday , I work on my reading skills using the Lit2go . On Lit2go there is available one story with a transcription and audio . It 's a kind of audiobook and it is also available as an activity . On Wednesday , I work on my listening skills . I also use the app Cake . I choose one idiom available on the app and I try to use some rules for improving that skill . I 'll stop for now , otherwise the text will be very large . See you ! 
