To start , I would like to say that telling the truth is important and that it ca not be bad in any situation . Furthermore , every moment is totally different and you have to choose for yourselves in all of them . There is no general rule for telling the truth , being silent or lying . I am of the opinion that people should act always by their best conscience . The main question is whether it is sometimes better to say a lie than the truth . I believe that telling the truth cannot be bad at all , as I said before . Nevertheless , the truth is that you can hurt someone with the truth or cause some problems in relationships , etc . For instance , if someone asks you whether he ’s fat , you might lie to him because you do not want to hurt him . There is also the option of not saying anything , which could be the best decision in many situations . I think that it is always better than a lie because a lie is bad in substance . To put it another way , if you do not want to answer the question with a lie , you should probably not say anything . All things considered , I think that , in situations where you should not tell the truth , you ought to not answer . If it is not possible , than you might lie but only because of a good purpose . 
Well , in the school of the future , there may be some changes , like in history class , there could be Virtual Reality to see the past in 3D , like maybe what it was like . Also , there could be some changes in the way students and teachers interact . Maybe there could be machines that can convert us into holograms to go to school even if we 're sick . But some things need to be the same , for example reading will not disappear . Like in this time , most reading is in digital formats . Books need to be there , because screens produce a lot of blue light that can make us so blind when we use them for a lot of time . Also , face -to -face education will not disappear , because it is the most perfect manner to teach students , because we can be sure that they will learn something that is not possible in online classes . Thank you 
One of the main skills to develop nowadays is related to being able to communicate properly . This skill not only involves mastering your own language , but includes learning several languages . This is especially important in toddlers , as it is well known that the ability to learn another language is developed in human brains from the early years . For that reason , parents invest a lot of money in their children 's education , mainly in bilingual programs . In fact , there are many surveys that correlate learning a foreign language with better opportunities in the future . In a world connected by the internet , there will always be a demand for learning as many new languages as possible . Moreover , today , more than in the past , to be fluent in as many languages as possible is a key factor to having a successful career . For that reason , there is a huge demand for online language learning and language teachers , as well as online resources . Probably , today , more than ever , we have a demand for learning language , and because of the advantages of technology , we do not have any more excuses not to undertake this demand . 
Volunteer work is a type of activity that enables to realize many good actions towards people or communities around the world . In order to graduate , some high schools ask their students to achieve a certain amount of volunteer work , such as donating blood , becoming a leader in a youth club , facilitating art workshops , being a positive role model for a young person , and much more . Many students respond positively to this requirement , otherwise others see this demand like a loud and additional charge . For many students , this kind of work enables them to see a new horizons and discover their capacities . It is also an occasion for students to explore a new social as well as the political issues that impact our world . In my opinion , schools should not impose this requirement because volunteer work must remain voluntary ; furthermore , graduating from school should be the result of the personal effort of each student not conditioned by other activities . 
