I think medical doctors are fleeing from countryside hospitals because of the poor working conditions that they face in their everyday life at work . A hospital in a small town can never be like a big city one . I believe that the doctors who work in a small town hospital always struggle to have proper medical equipment to do their job , so that is one of the big challenges every doctor who works in a small town or village has . They do not have long hours like the doctors in a big city . Working overtime means you are making more money , but that it 's not the case for a doctor in a little town hospital . That is why they all try to work in big cities so that they can make a massive fortune . However , the doctors who work in a big city hospital always have a lot of opportunities around , they have a big salary and never face any difficulties in their job . To sort this problem , I think the government needs to give equal opportunities to all the hospitals in the country . 
