Well , in my opinion , it 's good to have the same teacher for several years , especially in younger children that often adapt to a unique way of learning . But in primary and high school students , it 's better to have a lot of teachers , because one teacher does not know all that a student needs to finish their studies . Also , it 's good when you study languages , because a language has a lot of ways to speak it and it 's better to know different accents . In conclusion , it depends on each child , because some children only learn with just one teacher , but others learn with a lot of teachers . Also , an important thing is the parents , because when if at home they are only with one of them , so for he or she , it is easier to learn with just one teacher , but when the child grows up with both parents , for he or she it is easier to learn with a lot of teachers . Thank you 
