To achieve a high level at university is the purpose of many university students . Some students prefer to live at home with their family during their university studies . This modest choice is dictated by many reasons : on the one hand , these students do not have enough money to cover their university fees ; on the other hand , by staying with their family , the students can count on their parents when they face some difficulties . Other students prefer to move away and live on their own when they start their university studies . In many cases , they choose to travel even abroad . This second choice is dictated essentially by their hope to become free and independent . It is also the result of personal maturity and an open minded spirit . To sum up , both of these two strategies are valid and defensible . The most important thing is indeed how to mobilize effectively all of the means on their own in order to achieve their goal . 
Hello teacher , There are a lot of changes that have happened since you suggested Write and Improve to me and because of that , English has become my favourite subject . There are many options to use in the Write and Improve program and one of the best features of this program is the analytics . Whenever you attempt a workbook , a very beautifully designed feedback algorithm suggests feedback and areas to improve upon . There are many levels present in this program , from beginner to advanced writing . One can create or join a workbook , which is also one of the nice features . It is surprising to see that this feature which is in this program is absolutely free , which means one need not pay a penny for this program . One of the things I do not like about this is the website interface . I mean it could be better , but this has no effect on learning with this program . Thank you teacher for suggesting this wonderful program and I 'll suggest all my classmate to join this program . It is for all , whether you know English or not . 
There can be many thoughts on this topic , but I personally feel that the teacher should be changed every year , because that 's how life works . You 'll not always get a chance to work with the same people . We need to get out of our comfort zone and that 's how life goes . We need to interact with different people , so that we can understand the maximum amount of people 's thought progresses and get a chance to learn something from others ' experience . This is the same with teachers too . We need to get used to learning from different individuals , so that we can make a good thought system . For example , if we go for a particular topic in particular reference books , one reference may say the same thing in a different way and the other in a different way , but in the end , we get to know two ways to approach a particular problem . Teachers also teach us different approaches to reach a particular problem . And that is what counts in the end and as it should be . 
As a child , everyone learns always to tell the truth . But is it the right option to do it every time without exceptions ? I think that lies always come up . At first , you can think that lying can be convenient . But often , it has the same scenario : you begin with a little lie about something unimportant , but with time , it grows bigger and bigger and , in the end , it will burst because it is impossible to think about every detail and to remember everything you have ever said . For example , you lie to your friend about being sick , so you cannot go to his or her party . Then you have to think about what kind of sickness it is , where it comes from , how long you will have it and so on . And at some particular point , your lies will break down . And you will have a big argument with your friend about everything you said to him which was not true . But on the other hand , if you will tell everyone the truth , you cannot live in a community . Sometimes , you have to lie to stay polite or to motivate someone . To be honest with everyone about everything will only make trouble . For example , if your fellow asks you how you like her dress , it is polite to say that it is good instead of telling her the truth that you do not like her look . In summary , I think that the question about when you have to be honest and when not is a very complex topic . 
