Computers and tablets should not replace books in schools and universities . Instead of that , they ought to be used as complementary resources for learning and education . Firstly , we would have a huge problem . The students would spend too much time on their screen . Nowadays , we are already used to using our phones , computers or tablets at least once a day . More than that , studying on screens would definitely spoil our eyes and our brains . That was the first reason . Second , they would have many inequalities in education . I do not think that the governments of the countries would agree to pay for all these products . That means the families themselves would have to use a huge amount of money to support the education of their children . So that would not be fair , because everybody does not have the same salary or the same heritage . That 's why I think that . 
There is no doubt that these days video games are becoming very popular among children . However , the question is , are they useful for children ? It is considered one of the most controversial issues today . In this essay , I am going to examine this phenomenon from both viewpoints . On one side of the argument , there are people who argue that the benefits considerably outweigh the disadvantages of video games . The main reason for believing this is video games help children to learn new skills and focus on achieving the goal of the games at the end . Additionally , video games create competition between children to do their best and win . On the other side of the argument , there are people who believe that video games are not of benefit and have negative effects on children . To illustrate , children spend a long time playing without stopping . That is not healthy for them . As we have seen , there is no one easy answer to this question . On balance , however , I tend to believe video games are a good choice for entertainment for children , but parents must be careful about their children , to be aware of what they are playing . 
Well , zoos are places where there are a lot of animals . It 's a good idea to be in contact with animals and learn about them . But the animals do not have to be in a place , because they want to be free , because animals for centuries were in the jungle and other places around the earth , and only 20,000 years ago , the human appeared . That is so short compared with other species . Being in a zoo for an animal can be stressful too , because being outside is necessary for everyone . If a human is only 50 days at home , he is stressed , so imagine an animal being all his or her life without leaving a place In conclusion , zoos are good places to learn about animals , but the animals need to move . An alternative is to do a zoo where for every day in a cage , they can be outside . That 's a great idea . 
LEARNING HOW TO PLAY AN INSTRUMENT Music is often said not to be an important subject at school , but I could not disagree more . The reasons why I consider music useful knowledge are explained below : It goes without saying that music is one of the oldest forms of communication for human beings and , no matter what your mother tongue is , everybody can understand the message that every piece of music contains . Another point to take into account is that you can develop your creativity by learning music , especially when it comes to playing an instrument . By learning how to play an instrument , not only can you understand better that universal language , but also you will value and understand better the effort it requires . In my humble opinion , everybody should know how difficult it is to compose music , just like we learn the difficulty the rest of the subjects have . Music is one of the oldest communicative instruments created by humanity and it will always be a part of our development as species . Apart from that , we can also learn very much about our own history by studying and understanding music changes and tendencies through the years . Last but by no mean least , art subjects should have the same importance the rest of the subjects have , due to people who are good at art ought to have the same opportunities to develop their skills the rest of the people possess . 
Studying abroad is an opportunity for students to explore new lands with different cultures and traditions . It is also a chance to discover new horizons in life , which ultimately add to our life experience . I think the experience of the trip itself from one place to another around the world is really amazing . I am one of those students who has struggled a lot to study overseas in Canada , because I have a passion to experience life in Canada , which is rich in cultural diversity and human values . Studying abroad broadens students ' mindsets , because they 'll have the chance to live on their own , away from their families , for some time , which enables them to cope with the challenges they could face . In addition to that , getting to know people from different cultural backgrounds is a great opportunity to learn so many new things . Although students may step out of their comfort zone and there might be some sort of culture shock , eventually the students get used to it and will start to love their new destination . Students usually choose to study abroad to get quality education , so that they can get into a good career in the future . However , some people believe that there are advantages as well as disadvantages . For me , I do not think there are disadvantages of studying abroad , except the fact that minor young people may be prone to some problems because of their young age if they are studying alone overseas away from their family . But recently , universities and colleges have arranged specific types of accommodation for such minor young people , by putting them under the guardianship of a local family - and that 's very good . Some people have conservative ideas about studying abroad , and they fear the process of acculturation , because they want to keep their cultures without adopting new cultures . 
Hundreds of years ago , travel could be very difficult for people , due to the fact that means of transportation were not available compared to the world of today . In addition , travel at the time might not have been as important as today , because people had everything that they needed . But with the industrial revolution , new means of transportation were invented , such as aeroplanes , cars and modern ships . Therefore , travel has become easier and more accessible to everyone . As a consequence , that has opened up new opportunities for people to discover new lands and start global businesses , which has led to the globalisation that we witness now . Furthermore , with the increasing scientific progress and technological advances in sciences like computer engineering and astronomy , mankind has introduced many more possibilities , such as space exploration . Now people need to travel to new countries for diverse reasons , such as business , education , immigration and tourism , etc . So , in my opinion , I think the future of travel is very promising , as long as we see a very thriving global economy , as well as education and immigration sectors . Hundreds of years ago , people could not imagine the travel possibilities we have now . Similarly , travel can definitely change . 
My experience with ' Write and Improve ' is amazing . I have been using it for almost five months now , and my writing has improved dramatically . I have memorised a lot of vocabulary and my grammar skills have expanded . What I like on the ' Write and Improve ' website is the instant marking of the text on a scale from zero to five . I like the feedback tool which guides me throughout my writing task . The timer is also a significantly important tool when it comes to time management ; so it helps me to prepare for my IELTS writing test . The ' test zone ' subscription gives you access to a variety of services , such as the ' IELTS academic and general ' and B2 first . ' Write and Improve ' is the right place for people who want to improve their English writing as well as those who are looking forward to taking the IELTS test . 
First of all , I would like to say that I have not worked in any kind of office or workstation . That means that I have no experience with it and I can only write my own opinion . I believe that there are some ground things which affect the efficiency of employees . For instance , it is a good environment , a good purpose of the work and also fun in the work . Based on that , I think that a good employer should take care of these things in the first place . The ground question is whether employees should work together in open places or in some closed cubicles . In my opinion , both have some pros and cons . In open places , you have no privacy and you are under pressure . On the other hand , in small cubicles , you have no space and you will feel probably very uncomfortable . I believe that there is a better way . The best option would be to have a private office for every employee . All things considered , I would like better to have privacy and work in a small space with walls , but I wouldnu2019 t be happy about it . 
