Offices tend to have two types of workstations for employees . In one of them , workers are secluded from others while , in the second kind , no walls separate them from each other . As usual , these two situations have both some advantages as well as drawbacks . On the one hand , people might be prepared to work in open workstations because they are surrounded by other co -workers , who are likely their friends or acquaintances . That may lead to the creation of a pleasant atmosphere at work . For that reason , employees might enjoy their work , which would result in being much more efficient . Furthermore , if someone had any difficulty with their work , then it would be hard to ask for help since other co -workers would be next to him . On the other hand , I must admit that there are some people who prefer to work on their own . The presence of other people might only disturb them , which would impact on their performance . Moreover , I strongly believe that enclosed workstations or cubicles are much more quiet , which also may enable employees to focus more on their work . To top off , it seems to me that the answer to our main question depends on particular worker 's personality . For employees who like to be surrounded by other people an open workstation would be more suitable , whereas for people who can be described as lone wolves , it would be the most optimal choice that they should work in enclosed workstations . 
It is true that zoos are good places for people to learn about animals . And I used to go with my family to the national zoo in my country , and it was a really amazing moment . We saw various wild animals and it was a great experience for me . However , some people believe animals belong in nature and should not be kept in zoos . It is right perhaps , especially when we think of it from a freedom point of view , that all animals should have the freedom to live in nature where they belong . Keeping animals in zoos is not only a means of entertainment , but also a chance for animal caregivers to look after sick animals where it may be difficult for them to survive alone in nature because of predators . Furthermore , veterinarians carry out scientific research about animals to better understand animal diseases and why they arise and how to prevent or treat these diseases . That 's why animals may be kept in zoos for such studies . I think it makes sense to keep animals in zoos , as long as this achieves promising scientific outcomes as well as entertainment . Nevertheless , I still see animal confinement as sort of suppressing their freedom . So , it is highly recommended that animal welfare authorities provide safe zoos with suitable environments , so that the animals can still feel satisfied while they are being kept in zoos . In my opinion , animal care should be given importance , because they are an essential part of the ecosystem that we live in . So , protecting animals is protecting our ecosystem . In conclusion , I would say animals may be kept in zoos for entertainment , scientific research purposes and care -giving . Apparently , if there is no way to release all the animals in zoos into nature , we need to be mindful to give better care . 
