Radio , television , the internet , etc . appeared according to the decades and with the improvement of technology . If you have a conception that the basic principle of all means of communication is spreading a fact or an idea , and in that there is an opinion , it 's possible to conclude that these devices are powerful . In television 's case , its invention brought an important new : the power to choose ( despite this power being limited by the few options of channels ) . Because of that , the people did not need to enjoy , or not , just one channel , but they could make choices about what they wanted to watch . Because of that , television has different powers . It can educate with amazing channels that make the viewer think about several questions , but it can also harm people when channels or advertisements manage to manipulate who is watching . Therefore , who decides what the rule of television will be is the viewer . And this decision is very important . 
It is not a modern way to learn about animals from zoos . Many people experienced going to zoos in their childhood . In my memory , almost all of the animals in the zoos were just sitting and lying in their cages with an uneasy face . Nowadays , many TV programs focus on animals in nature and the animals move moved lively in the program . It is quite different between animals in zoos and ones in nature . I thought that keeping animals in zoos should be stopped and we should let them belong in nature after watching such TV programs . The origin of zoos was rare animal collections for the aristocracy . They treated animals as unique objects , not creatures . In the present times , people treat animals in zoos as things that tell us the motion of animals in picture books . Being in a cage and being exhibited to human sight is very stressful for animals . It was reported that a giant panda in a Hong Kong zoo that was sterile for a long time got pregnant , and the reason for the pregnancy was that pandas could spend their time without any witnesses due to the zoo 's closure due to the pandemic of COVID -19 . This news indicated that human witnesses might be harmful to animals in zoos . And what 's more , there are many other ways to learn about animals without zoos in modern society . We can learn about animals from books and TV programs and photos of nature magazines . These ways do not harm animals belonging in nature . It is not suitable to keep animals in the cages of zoos . It stresses them and distorts their lives . Animals are not toys for humans . We should treat them as they are in nature . 
