Sometimes , telling truth is the collar of the surviving from the conflicting , worthless , unreliable aurelaible because the vast majority of people hate a lying person . Lying to people means losing confidence , nobody accepts that . Moreover , most of them ignore lying people . The reason is the consequence that comes after believing them or even the problems of their speech . We always see lying people spreading rumors and trying to make problem for others . Deception and lying are common human behaviors . There is much research proving that . Psychologists have utilized research on body language and deception to help members of law enforcement distinguish between the truth and lies , and the results providing the signs of lying people are : 1 - being vague : If the speaker seems to intentionally leave out important details , it might be because they are lying 2 - vocal uncertainly : If the person seems unsure or insecure , they are more likely to be perceived as lying 3 - indifference : shrugging , lack of expression and a bored posture can be signs of lying 4 - overthinking : if the person seems to be thinking too hard to fill in the details of the story , it might be because they are deceiving you . The conclusion here is while body language may be helpful , it is important to pay attention to the right signs . 
My favourite season of the year My favourite season of the year is spring , because there are a lot of colours , flowers and more , Once , when it was spring , there were lots of different animals in one place near my house . It was very beautiful . It 's special for me , because in winter , most of the things are white because of the snow , but in spring , all is colourful , but sometimes there are lots of flowers and obviously lots of bees , and the bees are sometimes very uncomfortable . I would like to have a place with lots of flowers , but without bees , or bees , but in another place , because one of the benefits of the bees are that they help to reproduce the flowers , and they produce honey too and that is very delicious . Spring is very special for me because I feel very happy with lots of colours around me . 
Dear Mr . Aizen , Thanks for recommending me to use the Write and Improve program . I have used it for a week and today , just like you want , I 'm going to tell you my experience with it . It 's just my opinion , so maybe there are a few things you wo not agree with . First of all , its interface . Well , the interface is quite eye -catching , with many options . Secondly , you can connect by using your Facebook account . Hence , you can share your study process to your news feed . And last , lessons of Write and Improve are divided into levels . That means you can select a level which is right for you . This is what I like most about this program as well . But , nothing is perfect . Although it 's good , there is a problem that I do not like very much . This program has a checking system . Most of the time , it works well . But , sometimes it 's quite confusing . For example , a few days ago , I studied a lesson on this program . While doing this , there was a quote I copied verbatim . Then it said that it was not correct , but did not say what the error was . I tried to check again many times , but to no avail . That 's what I do not like about this program . In general , this program is still a good choice for someone who wants to learn English . So I recommend our class to try it . Phuc . 
People have been arguing about those two things for a long time . Actually , each has its particular benefits . One has something that the other does not have and vice versa . It is hard to say which is better , but if I had to choose , I would say having new teachers each year is better for students . Why did I say that ? Multiple teachers allow us to see things from a different perspective , explain concepts with new insights , share ideas we have considered and take on topics we feel unqualified to explain . None of these benefits detract from our role as parents and educators , but these partnerships provide opportunities to offer our children more than ever . Have you ever read a book named " Benefits and drawbacks of using multiple instructors to teach single courses " written by Jones , F . & Harris , S ? There is a sentence like this : " Multiple instructors working together can be especially effective at meeting high level learning goals . " Well , I completely agree with that . 
The last holiday was very important to me , because it was the first after the COVID -19 pandemic started . Me and my family were at home for three long months , so last July we were able to stay in a camp house for four days . My children were very happy , my wife was so enthusiastic and I was happy because of them . That house was so special because of the long period before , when we needed to stay at home all the time , my children did not have another child to play with , to join them and to be happy together . So that house on the camp was perfect , a swimming pool , a large space , grass and a field to run , everything my children wanted . Everybody would have liked to stay more time there , unhappily it was impossible . We will think about a new opportunity to return there . My children are waiting for a new holiday , and me too . 
There is no doubt that these days studying musical is becoming very popular in schools . However , the question is : Is studying musical good for students ? It is considered one of the most controversial phenomena today . In this essay , I am going to examine this from both viewpoints . On the one hand , from the argument , there are people who argue that studying music in school has considerable benefits which outweigh the disadvantages for many reasons . The first reason , it is teaching the students new skills and they can have a funny time playing on the instrument . The second reason , almost some parents want their children to learn music because they know learning music maybe will be a good chance for their children in the future to earn extra money . On the other hand , people claim that studying music is not very important . They believe that it is a waste of time and effort and they also think it is extra and their children can learn it any time . These people have their children change to other subjects in school that are more useful than music . As we have seen , there is no one easy answer to this question . On balance , however , I tend to believe that studying music is very interesting if the students want that , so I think studying music is good to be an elective class for students who are interested in learning it . 
The experience of studying abroad at a young age is an advantage . Recently , studying abroad is not an uncommon experience for ordinary people . Some parents are eager to let their children go to another country to study the language and culture in that country . On the other hand , it is said that studying abroad with no purpose is meaningless . In my opinion , it is a useful experience for young people to go to another country and learn about their culture . It allows them the opportunity to see the world from another perspective . People who live in another country should learn about the language and culture , which is usually not familiar to them . It might be hard to understand all of them . However , they can achieve another perspective , by touching new thoughts and cultures , and that is a strong advantage to have . If they are not familiar with another culture , the experience of studying abroad might be their worse memory . It is not easy to have friends and a reliable person casually in a foreign country . The sense of failure and unfruitful memories may frustrate them after returning home . Anyway , studying abroad can be a positive challenge for young people . If you can get such experience at a young age , you have the advantage already . The best teacher in life is your own experience . 
The way to travel in the future will be so different . Maybe we 're going to start having holidays in space , and that 's not science fiction . There 's a project called holidays in space and recently a rocket went into space . It was amazing , even if you were watching it on TV . There will be more ecological ways to travel , like cars that can travel with solar energy as fuel . Travelling to other countries will be easier and cheaper than now . Flying from the United Kingdom to the United States will cost the same as going on the underground . But travelling will be the same as today in some aspects . For example , we 're not going to travel by thae way of thinking . For example , if you want to go to China , with only thinking about China , you are not going to be in China for at least in 90 years , you 're still going to pay to travel too , because even in the future , there will be lots of things to pay for on a trip . 
Sure , exercise is very important for my health , however , it is the only part of total health . I believe that , for instance , not being nervous is often more important , to have peace , so you should not be stressed frequently . Another very important thing , and sometimes difficult , is to eat very well , fruit , vegetables , meat , milk , all the vitamins , minerals and drink a lot of water . You need to think about doing exercise , OK , but many people that do it , at the same time drink alcohol and worse , have the habit of smoking . One thing that many people forget is to sleep well too . It is necessary to keep the mind and the body healthy . It is important not to take medicine when you do not need to . And last but no less important , sunbathe , for good bones . So , to be healthy , it is not necessary to only do exercise , you need much more ... 
In my opinion , learning a foreign language is more important today than it was in the past . Today , people have money , they travel to another country for jobs , vacation ... . Local people from one country want to have different international customers . The customers that live in another country means that they are rich . They can invest a lot of money in a project . If you try to learn a new language , you can easily communicate with foreign customers . You can understand more about what they say and you do not need to spend money to hire a translator . A translator can be a spy from an enemy company and they can translate to a different idea . In the past , there were less customers or travelers . They did not have enough money to travel to a different country , so it was less important to learn a foreign language . 
The television was created for the purpose of entertaining people , but considering this unfortunate situation , some countries are using television to educate children that do not have enough money to buy a computer , tablet or smartphone . Everyone knows that in the last century , TV has had some incredible changes , converting a machine that can project images and audio to being able to search on the internet . Incredible , right ? But can television educate well ? No , it ca not . Television can teach sometimes , but if the student does not understand about a topic , the TV is not going to resolve his or her questions , and children ca not be 1 hour per day looking at the television , especially for young children , when their learning needs to be more interactive than a recorded class on TV . In conclusion , TV can educate , but it is not as good as being in touch with your teacher to answer all of the children 's questions . 
In my opinion , I think that school should replace books with computers and tablets . Books are hard to find in the library . They are very thick and it is easy to destroy them by tearing and pouring water onto them . Students ca not read a book in the dark without a light , but with computers and tablets they can . Computers and tablets can light up the screen with the light inside them . Tablets and computers can also find a book for you online . For example , the book that you want to read is not in your school 's library , so you ca not read it . But tablets and computers can search for the book for you . They can search every book online for you and you do not need to worry about having no books to read . Tablets can also translate new words for you online , so you can concentrate on reading the books . 
There is a big diversity of subjects we have at school . Some of them we like and another ones we hate . But do we really need all these subjects at school ? A good example of a subject whose importance is often discussed is music class . On the one hand , only two or three pupils from each class do something related to music in their later life , but everyone has to endure music classes during school time . For some children , who have no talent for it , it is very difficult not to fail in this subject . It is also not fair when some students are doing music in their free time and others only have one lesson a week at school . In such situations , some students have an advantage and better grades only because their parents sent them to music school or because their parents can play some instruments themselves and can teach their children too . On the other hand , some parents even come to the idea of sending their child to play the piano , so this student will never find out whether he likes it or not . And by having music classes at school , the same students can explore a new subject and maybe even find a new hobby . And it is the function of school : to bring children to new spheres which can interest them . To sum up , I think that schools have to offer music classes , but do not need to make them compulsory until the end of school , but for example , only until fifth grade . 
