In order to answer this question , I say yes . Television today has some channels , series or films , which educate a lot . Today you can see so many different channels that could entertain you , like comedy films or series . Although these types of films are underestimated , they also give us so many life lessons . For example , letting children watch cartoons can teach them how to love , to be friends , or even find out about something they do not know . Every type of TV program educates in a specific argument . Documentaries teach you what to do in case of an attack by a predator , or to survive in a storm , tsunami and so many other types of bad weather . There are series on TV which tell you how to do something , like cook special foods , or how to do beautiful birthday parties . After all , with these types of programs , there are some in which their first goal is to make people laugh , letting them forget the outside world . In conclusion , I agree with the fact that the TV can educate us . 
