For me , the best holiday was the trip to Hueco Mundo last summer . I went with my family and some of my friends . We chose this destination because we had heard that it was one of the most must -go countries in the world . It was also where my brother had been studying , so we wanted to visit him as well . The rumors were indeed not wrong . It was gorgeous , more than you could imagine . The beauty of Hueco Mundo was unbelievable , the buildings with glittering lights , the incredibly clean streets and so on . The food was really good too . It was simple , with rice , vegetables and some meat , just like we had in our country , but it tasted delicious . We stayed at a hotel in the capital . Next day , we visited our brother , about 5 kilometers away . He took us to many places : museums , galleries , etc . We learnt many things : culture , custom , clothes ... We stayed there for 2 more days and on the last day , we got on the plane and went home . It was the best holiday for me . I not only had a lot of fun , but also learned many useful things . 
Being healthy is important as you get older . Some people work hard all their life to earn money , then they ignore their self care , both physical and mental health . Therefore , this could lead to spending their earned income to cure a sickness , instead of preparing for their retirement . In my opinion , taking care of your health and your wealth is crucial for living . Why wealth is necessary . As we live in a capitalist society , money could provide a high standard of living , therefore , getting rich is the ultimate goal for most people . Wealth is a major supporter for optimum health , because it gives you the financial freedom to make healthy choices and avail yourself of any existing health and fitness resources . Unfortunately , in our marketplace today , the healthier food choices are more expensive than the damaging processed varieties . This is why wealth is also our freedom for our financial security . In contrast , better health is central to human happiness and well -being . It also makes an important contribution to economic progress , as healthy populations live longer , are more productive and save more . Many factors influence health status and a country 's ability to provide quality health services for its people . 
I think the two ways have benefits , because if you have the same teacher for a few years , he 'll be able to help you in specific ways , like in which topics you need more help and which ones you do not and the way that he should teach and everyone can understand him , although this can cause some kind of boredom , since every class can turn into a repetition of the other classes . However , if you have a different teacher every year , this allows you to learn different techniques and tricks to learn new things from the new teacher , since that new teacher has some new methods to teach . Even so , this can turn bad , because that new teacher does not know the students and he wo not know how find the best way to help to improve the knowledge of every single student . Having said that , I 'd prefer a new teacher every year . I think that 's the best way to improve for me . 
