I have a lot of favorite indoor activities , such as : reading , making cakes , playing the piano , but now I want to tell you why I enjoy baking . For me making cakes is like an art project , but to which you have to apply a piece of maths as well . Last week I made a birthday cake for my daughter . It was a delicious sponge cake with Mascarpone , raspberries and chopped up chocolate . 
I like exercising for at least 30 minutes every day . I know that regular physical activity has great health benefits ; for example , it can lift my mood and boost my energy level . I prefer exercising outside . Research shows that spending time in nature can have a healing effect on our minds and bodies . I love walking and doing light yoga stretches , with both activities helping me to clear my mind . 
We often see TV news about elderly women living close to 120 years old , with the reporter asking her the secret of healthy living . It cannot be denied that recent developments in the medical field has dramatically lengthened the average life span . However , I do not value highly those news reports , as shorter but intense lives should be more meaningful . Firstly , not so many 80 or 90 -year -old people can afford to live on their own , forcing their sons or daughters to support their daily lives . Although living together makes family bonds stronger , it must be a burden for younger generations to support their parents while working or raising their children . Some even spend their last ten years of life hospitalized , which is accompanied by tremendous medical costs . In no way should lives without health be happy . Secondly , having shorter lives may be a motivation for younger generations to appreciate their lives well . Despite having adequate free time , some businessmen waste their time , staying home on weekends ideally . As most people spend their twenties through to their sixties working at the same company , such activities like doing hobbies or travelling on weekends are indispensable to avoid mundane lives . Having less time after retirement encourages younger generations to seek what leads them to spend their time happily . For these two reasons , I believe not having an excessively long life span should be a shortcut to spending a meaningful life . 
Have you ever wondered , what will our travel look like in the future ? Will we still travel in the same say as we do now ? My prediction , it may be different . We may travel faster , more safely and with less impact on the environment . At present , you can see that there are so many problems with travel : emissions , traffic jams , traffic accidents ... Therefore , many scientists and engineers have started to think about how to change our travelling . They are working and testing to create new vehicles to minimize the problems I mentioned before . Several ideas have been introduced . In 2017 , Elon Musk showed his project the Hyperloop , a sealed tube or system of tubes with low air pressure , through which a pod may travel substantially free of air resistance or friction . He also conducted a test and it worked . I know there will be many concerns surrounding this project , but it 's still a positive signal for our future travel . I guess you have heard about flying cars . Many prototypes have been built since the early 20th century . Most recently , a flying car named Cezeri was first introduced and it worked fine . There are still many other projects and ideas to change our future travel . I hope they will come true . 
