With the current pace of life in this generation , an activity that supports living stationary is continuously rising from the existence of technology and all the services that attempt to obtain profit from our laziness . As a result thereof , do we need to encourage a more active lifestyle by enforcing mandatory sporting class in school curriculum ? I fully disagree with this question , and two reasons are accounted for this . Firstly , every student possess their own time schedule which is varied and different in each person . Including three classes of sport in each week can possibly consume an excessive amount of time that one can utilise in a way that is beneficial for their living . For example , some students may need to be a part timer in order to earn enough money for their tuition ; or give every vacant timeslot possible to their valuable can be a case for some , like one of my friends whose her mother has Alzheimer 's disease that tries to reduce the cost of hiring nurse for her mother . Secondly , although one decides to not do any sport , this does not guarantee that one has an inactive life since several activities can do this duty in lieu . Gardening , housework , or grocery shopping are considered activities that demonstrate the usage of a large amount of energy and the increase of human stamina . Instead of compelling students to do sport , which can possibly lead to a hatred of sporting , if educational institutions recommend an activity that can potentially be incorporated to student daily life for an improved active lifestyle such as using the stairs instead of the elevator , this may be a more appropriate choice for many . To summarise , why mandatory sport class , personally , expresses disagreement : the existence of personal time and a plethora of sports - substitute activities in order to achieve active lifestyle . 
Learning a non -native language is hard work . Even though , in this generation , a lot of artificial intelligence has been created to translate languages from around the world , personal communication skills in a foreign language are still important in our lives . There are two outstanding reasons to support this idea . First , being multilingual is an advantage . Students who can speak a foreign language fluently tend to achieve better grades at school and college . Most people feel more comfortable communicating with people than computers or robots , so we would choose to communicate with one who understand us first . Speaking in the same language , we can work faster . Second , there are still people who cannot use other than their primary language . Being able to communicate in a secondary language , we would be able to contact them properly . Using a language translator or dictionary wastes time . Therefore , these are the reasons why I think learning to speak a foreign language is as important these days as it was in the past . 
Musical activities are important to develop imagination and creative skills . Music is an essential part of everyone 's life because human beings from the bassinet hear sound , music or melodies like lullabies or any other kind of sound . That is the reason why people since pre school years begin to learn or to play an instrument , being the reason why schools add music in their school 's framework . Nowadays , a lot of schools have on their schedules music classes every week in order to give cultural knowledge , distraction and to develop abilities in students . Besides , students have the opportunity to discover if music is a hidden talent to develop and start to practice and improve their musical abilities . I personally consider that music is an essential part of people 's lives , so all students should study music at least once in their life because this activity allows people to find a way for distraction or to find their passion . To summarize , people who have had music classes in their academic life are capable of managing stress better . They also have had the opportunity to discover something new and to take a break from stressful routines or simple daily lifestyle . 
In my opinion , Write and Improve is a useful tool for any person that is learning English . It is a terrific way to improve English writing . What I most like about Write and Improve is the feedback . In a few minutes , it is possible to know what aspects are necessary to improve and the main mistakes that were made , including grammar and vocabulary . On the other hand , it is very hard to know what the mistake is when only a sentence in a different color appears and there are no suggestions to make the sentence better . I would love it if the program could show me some options to improve my sentences . To sum up , I definitely recommend this tool for my classmates . It is an easy and interesting way to improve English writing any time you want without worrying about judgment . 
This report is about my experience with Write and Improve for practicing and improving my English writing . The first thing I like most about Write and Improve is its variable topics . There are many topics that you can choose to practice writing in English . Those topics are about all things and from beginner to advanced levels . The second thing I like , this course is an online course . That means you can practice writing English at any time and anywhere . The third is the progress report that helps me to know how my writing is improving or not after finishing each piece of work . On the other hand , I disliked how the Write and Improve course corrected my writing . It revised and commented on my sentences in general , but did not give me suggestions or replace sentences . In general , Write and Improve is an interesting website to practise and improve your English and I am sure to recommend my classmates to try it . 
I disbelieve the claim that doctors want to work in cities for money . Yes , it is a fact that in cities doctors get more wages than in any rural area . But it is not for the money but for facilities that are not there in rural areas . Doctors have the most hectic schedule and they do not get enough time for rest , and suppose a doctor gets to work in rural areas where there is no infrastructure and facilities , so how can the doctor make ? There is lot to change in rural areas and the first thing to do is to work on infrastructure so that there can be scopes of making new hospitals . People in rural areas are not knowledgeable enough to recognize the importance of medical science . There are a lot of incidents happening recently that support the fact that doctors in villages are not safe . Though people believe doctors are god but when the purpose is not fulfilled they do not hesitate to show their anger to doctors in the form of physical violence . Also people in villages do not prefer to go to hospital , they prefer either local remedies or they involve themselves in dark magic . 
Well , both have their own advantages and disadvantages . First , starting with the open design , in which there is no partition and everything is spacious while , in enclosed workstations , there is a small partition which is present for privacy . I personally like a spacious place where I do not feel suffocated and can think freely watching the different things , which helps in getting the ideas . Also it is not an easy task to just sit in one place bound to a small space . Now , as time advances , we are moving towards working together and , for that , an open design is a must . Many big companies , like Google , Facebook , etc . , prefer to use a spacious environment where everyone can interact with each other and can get the helpful ideas from everybody . Now , an open environment is necessary for all the offices , not because it helps in work life , but it also affects mental health . To maximize the output of the employees , many companies are now considering and focusing on mental health and physical health because if employees are not fit on the inside , there is no chance that they can give the company their full potential service . Environments affect mental and physical health . Where you sit , where you eat , where you work all matters . 
