Learning a foreign language was so important in the past , but is still important to learn a foreign language in these times ? Yes , it is even more important to learn famous and recognised languages , like English , Spanish , Chinnese , etc . But now , with useful tools for translating words in one language to another language that you do not know , some people believe that it is not important to learn a language . That idea is very , very wrong . What happens if you need a word in a language that you do not know in your original language ? In new languages , you even learn new words in your original language , and that is why it is important to know a language without any robots ' help , because some recognised jobs require at least an upper intermediate language level , and in an international exam , you are not allowed to have a translator with you . If you want a better life , learn a language , it 's a big step . 
Hello everyone . When I was fifteen years old , I went to San Andres Islands with my family . My family was poor and they saved money for years so we could travel there . We did that trip to celebrate my birthday . We were there for four days . We always remember that trip and all its adventures , it 's impossible to forget it . There we saw Jonekey Island . It was beautiful . There were many and different fish species , the water was totally blue , its climate was very hot and the seafood was amazing . We spent the day swimming , eating , playing , laughing and walking around the rocks and beach . Another day we walked around the island . We went Morgan 's cavern , a natural pool in the sea . It was five meters deep . People jumped into pool and the fish got close to them to eat pieces of bread that they had in their hands . Also , we went to the blowhole where the sea hit the rocks and went through a hole to go out , wetting people . It was a bit dangerous , because people could not run , as the rocks could hurt them . Another point of view , my family and I shared a lot , resting and travelling for the first time by plane . 
Television , a media which appeared in the 1950s , is one of the most important inventions that changed our lives . Everyone knows that the main purpose of television is entertainment . But have you ever wondered , " Can it also educate ? " From my point of view , it definitely can . How can television educate ? By the programs shown on it . When I was a kid , there was an educational program shown every morning . It lasted for 30 minutes and it provided some Math lessons for children . Nowadays , more and more programs are produced to teach students Math , Geography , Science ... Even cartoons can play that role . For example , Tom and Jerry teach children how to be a good guy . As you can see , now we are dealing with COVID -19 . Students ca not go to school . Therefore , in many countries , televisions are used to teach the students while they 're at home . In a nutshell , there 's no way that television ca not educate . Television has the potential to do that . It depends on us . 
