Nowadays , most students decide to study overseas for a while . Studying in another country has some pros and cons and I will argue both sides in this essay . The main reason to choose studying abroad is to broaden your horizons . People who go abroad could gain new experiences and face a new culture to deal with . For example , students who are living overseas could learn to adapt themselves to new situations and think more rationally about their surroundings . Secondly , moving away helps students to learn a new language and gives them a good opportunity to research with a wide range of references . Moreover , dealing with a new language increases their brain capacity as well . Turning to the other side of argument , there are some drawbacks to studying abroad . The main disadvantage is culture shock . Students might face new people who they are not familiar with and this can make them feel lonely . It is not possible for them to cope with this new condition easily . The other problem that must be mentioned is students have to start from scratch . It means they must start a new life and it is possible that they will have to live with little money at first . Also , they might get a student loan to pay the university fees . In conclusion , although there are some considerable pros in moving away to study , there are some disadvantages to consider carefully . Studying abroad could open students ' minds and also improve their language skills . On the other hand , they might not adapt themselves to the new place quickly and also they might have difficult financial problems . 
Television is one of the most popular tools for amusing people , also , in some ways , for teaching new things in the world . The main aim of using TV is to broadcast programmes which are entertaining for people . Firstly , people want to be amazed . Indeed , they work hard during the day and they prefer to rest and find peace at home . For example , there are a lot of movie genres , like comedy , action , animation and TV shows on television that can be a lot of fun for the public . Secondly , TV programmes are much cheaper than going to the cinema or theater . Finally , people like to watch their favourite celebrities , such as actors or actresses , sportsmen or sportswomen and singers on TV . On the other hand , educationally , there are some programmes which are designed for students and help them based on their curriculum . The other reason is related to having good access to TV for poor people . And the final reason for using television for education is the low cost of educational programmes on TV . In conclusion , people watch TV to enjoy themselves and learn in their free time . 
