As you know , we now are living in a flat world , so that some students choose to study abroad for a time during high school or university . However , there are advantages and disadvantages of studying abroad . There are many advantages of studying abroad . Firstly , the students will learn modern and quality educational programs . Secondly , they are taught by lecturers who are qualified . Besides that , the students will live in a variable culture , where they can interchange and learn from each other by themselves . On the other hand , studying abroad has many disadvantages . The students need to pay more money for accommodation , food and the study costs . Besides that , they are far from their family , so that they do not have close support from them . Especially the students who are in high school grades will be affected during their growing up without their family caring for them . One more disadvantage is the weather . For instance , England is too cold and wet for students who come from tropical countries . In conclusion , studying abroad is a good opportunity for students to get better knowledge and skills to develop their future career . 
