Speaking personally , I think that having different teachers each year is better , because it means an opportunity to learn in different ways , to get to know a new person with diverse qualities and thoughts , which can be enriching for the students ' personal and professional growth . On the top of that , if a student has a different teacher every year , he or she will likely develop his or her ability to adapt to changes , which represents a great chance for the student 's development . Furthermore , having a new teacher implies new challenges and new ways to learn or to explain the subject 's topics , as a result that the students can use a set of tools to learn better and they will feel enthusiastic to do new exercises and activities . On the contrary , when a student has the same teacher for several years , they would be unlikely to discover the way she learns and understand better or develop the skill of adapting to the changes , as well as the student can stay in a comfort zone and lose enthusiasm little by little , because there are no changes , no new ways and probably no more challenges . 
