Well , I think this is a issue debate because there are many elements to take into account in order to express an opinion . As for me , I think video games have a negative impact on children when they are too young and there are grounds for believing this . The first reason is that nowadays there are so many kinds of video games , but the most popular video games are about violence and killers , which increases the probability of aggressive behavior in children , such as bullying or being aggressive with their siblings . Then , one of the most crucial bad effects on children of playing video games is on their health , owing to them spending a lot of time in front of the screen and this damages their sight . Besides , the lack of physical activity has repercussions on their muscles and bones , as well as increases the probabilities of being overweight . Apart from this , other negative consequences on children are isolation and poor interpersonal skills , due to them playing video games for many hours in closed spaces . They do not interact with other people , so they do not practice communication skills , which could bring some problems in the short and long term in school , such as difficulties in making friends and challenges in teamwork , among others . Additionally , there are so many cases that have shown how children get so obsessed with video games , that they try to do less things in their houses and other activities , which takes their valuable time . One instance could be they just eat junk food and drink some sodas , which are not healthy , to save time . Another example is that they do not do their homework or do not study at home so that they can invest much more time in playing video games . As a result , they do poorly in school . Finally , it seems to me that video games are harmful for children 's development , owing to the bad effects which I 've already mentioned , in personal , physical and psychological aspects . 
