Nowadays , people are looking for online English courses . This is a new type of education and has some advantages and disadvantages that have to be take into consideration before applying to an online course . One of the main advantages is that online education allows to reduce costs , as courses do not need a classroom and all the facilities like computers and printed materials that usually schools have to provide to their students when they are attending a face -to -face course . For example , Write and Improve is an online platform that helps students with writing activities through interactive exercises , moreover , this system has digital resources like different writing levels and virtual examinations depending on IELTS or general training . Indeed , students can monitor their progress and recognize their strengths and weaknesses in real time in front of their computer wherever and whenever they wish . An additional factor to consider is that this online learning platform has some educational resources , such as edition and writing programs with the aim to facilitate the learning process . On the other hand , some people could criticize that lack of human physical contact that is inherent on this online platform . Most importantly , being bilingual or multilingual is a social skill that humans developed in real situations , and can only improve this skill in real life . The online platform relies on course materials but lacks the human interaction that languages have like body language . There are some language abilities that can only be acquired in real interactions that obviously the internet cannot replace . For example , pronunciation online programs are unable to teach about all the phonic variety , accents and intonation . Despite these drawbacks , the future is online education , and this is linked with technological advances that obviously are going to tackle these situations , and probably are going to replace somehow face -to -face classes . 
