Dear Ana , I hope you are very well , in fact , my mum told me that she had met you in the supermarket yesterday . I am studying an English course because I want to do a Ph D in science , in Biotechnology , and I require a B1 level for this . As you know , the English language is very difficult for me , although I wish to learn and improve my speaking , writing and listening skills . 
First of all , lies are in general not a bad thing , it is how most of the people these days use them . They lie to avoid uncomfortable situations and make things even worse with that . Lying is never the solution to a serious problem , it might delay the consequences , but in exchange , the are most of the time a lot more severe . If all human beings communicated honestly and tried their best to avoid lies or misunderstandings , it would be so much easier for everybody . Everyone would know exactly what the other wants from them . I mean , at some moments , it easier to lie than tell the truth , just because you do not want hurt someone else 's feelings , but in the end , they will know what the truth is and then it will hurt even more . There are some exceptions , for example , when your children ask you something you can not answer properly so they would understand so you better come up with a good lie . A prime example is Santa Claus or anything similar to that , you do not want to ruin your children 's dreams or their childhood by telling them all those fairy tales are not real , it would crush them . So in conclusion , lying is most of the time just postponing the drama , so only lie to your children or grandchildren . 
Many countries sponsor students to study abroad during high school or university and others have some programmes for professionals to do their Post -Graduate degree or Master 's degree abroad too . It is so interesting , because people can learn not only new subjects , but they can also learn about a new culture and can expand their horizons . Some people disagree with countries sponsoring students to go abroad to study , because they believe that the money that the government spends on these students could be used in collective actions to help more people , because for them , all citizens pay taxes and this money from taxes should not be used for individuals ' interest . That money needs to be used for collective interest only . However , there are many people that agree that the government sponsors students to study abroad . For them it is interesting , because these students will achieve a good qualification and they can contribute to the development of their native countries when they finish their studies and come back to their native countries . I think it is really interesting and important for the students , because they will achieve more than just a formal qualification . They will learn different ways to do things , different ways to think about the same problems and the possibility to interact with another culture is really great for all people . I know that many countries sponsor their students to do it , but if the government does not provide it and you have the chance to go abroad by yourself to study , it is perfect for you do it , so your horizons will be opened more than you can imagine after finishing your studies . 
About office designs , I believe an open space is more efficient than an enclosed workstation . People that prefer an enclosed workstation are the ones who like to work in a prison -like space . To me , it feels like no freedom and limiting your working area into a confined space . However , working in an open area enables people to talk freely , work freely . Such a condition enables people to come closer and work together instead of distancing themselves in a cubicle space , which limits the cooperation with each other . One good example is Google . Google has a free open environment for people to work anywhere they want . Today , they may choose to work near a park . Then , the next day , they may choose to work near a playground . Such freedom enables workers to have a choice . Having a choice is where the imagination comes from and gives value to the company . This is a valuable asset and it could not be present in enclosed workstations . 
In a world that promotes mainly comfort and a sedentary life , sport should be a form of escaping . Introducing more sports classes can be regarded as a solution for this problem , but I do not consider that forcing students into taking them is a wise decision . First of all , the most beneficial part of doing sport is improving your health quality . For example , in most cases , children tend to spend time only on the computer and this can lead to scoliosis , obesity and other health issues . Secondly , playing sports can have other benefits , like learning to be part of a team . It is generally thought that being a team player is an advantage for job applications . A good illustration of this is the structure of an interview when almost always the employer asks you how well you can collaborate with other colleagues . Furthermore , the current generation , known as ” Y ” generation or ” snowflakes ” , is at great susceptibility of mental health diseases . Under these circumstances , playing sports can help children be happier . Evidence for this is provided by the secretion during physical activities of substances that makes you feel relaxed and peaceful , such as serotonin and dopamine . In addition , there is a reason to believe that sport can take the form of a hobby , hence giving students the opportunity to have a leisure activity and take a break from all the studying . In spite of all the advantages that come from sport , I think that forcing children into doing it is wrong . We can see this from early childhood because whenever you coerce a child into doing something , he will not want to do it . Thus , obliging students to take more sport classes can have a negative outcome , for instance , they will drop sports for good . Taking everything into consideration , even though physical activity has many pros , forcing that on students can result in the exact opposite . 
If you have a lot of money , but you 're not healthy , money does not have any value . However , if you 're healthy , but you do not have money , that does not make any difference , because you 're healthy and it 's important to mention that money ca not buy health . Some people are very attached to money . For them , money is everything . If you 've money , you can have anything you want . Perhaps they think that they can buy health and be immortal . The reality is that you do not need a lot of money to live well and be healthy . The important thing here is you need to live your life well . What I mean is , just living life responsibly , eating vegetables and fruits , doing exercise and feeling good with yourself . If I have a lot of money but I ca not spend it because I 'm in a hospital due to an illness , what do I need money for ? 
I love to exercise , so every morning I do exercise at home or outside and at my school . On Saturdays and Sundays , I do exercise in a gym in the morning and the evening . I prefer to do my exercise outside because it is free and it is also better than being in a gym . I usually run around the park and on the running machine in the gym and a lot more exercise that I can do when I am in the gym or outside the gym . It is very good for your health and it makes you fit and strong . 
I like doing exercise . I exercise every morning . I like to do exercise in a gym , because you can see other people and work with a coach , and you can learn a lot of things . I prefer to do dancing , aerobic and fitness . Another reason to go to the gym is my best friend . 
Given to the fact that most medical doctors prefer to work in cities where they will make a lot of money instead of working in rural areas , an unbalanced situation appears where people in rural areas receive poor medical care and people in urban areas receive good medical care . This unbalanced situation has caused people to move towards cities and leave rural areas . One of the reasons behind this is there is not enough financial support from the government and poor administration in rural areas . It causes doctors to lose their motivation to work in rural areas if they can receive more incentives in cities . To solve this situation , the government plays a great role in minimizing the gap between cities and rural areas by trying to provide more incentives and support for doctors who work in rural areas . Such incentives could be present in the the form of financial support . 
For me learning English is very important , due to knowing another language gives you opportunities , like getting a better job , meeting people , visiting other countries , and it particularly allows you to get relevant information about important topics . However , speaking in a professional context , knowing another language is very important for better development of a professional . I 'd like to be an engineer and if I want to work for an international company , I have to know another language , because I 'm going to be in contact with people of different countries and all of the information that I 'm going to work with is going to be in English , due to this language being very common around the world . Changing the context to another more personal one , I 'm learning English because it is a personal challenge that I gave to myself , since I noticed if I learn another language , I 'll be able to know more things and I 'll become a better professional . 
Hi Matt , It 's nice to hear from you . I hope you are very well . I 'm nervous about the start of the classes , because I must work on my weaknesses in the English language . However , I have been learning English during the holidays . I had a course with a British teacher , so I improved my skills during this time . But I think that my abilities such as in speaking and listening are not good . Nevertheless , the classes and course in the English language helped me to improve my skills ! I really hope to see you soon at school ! Take care . Sylvia 
