In my opinion , it is not wrong to keep any animals in zoos , because zoos can save many animals ' lives for many reasons . The first reason is many zoos are places that any endangered animals can live without being hunted by hunters in their natural habitats . The second reason is to breed some animals that are almost extinct and reintroduce them into their habitats again . This program can improve the genetics in the wild and reduce cross breeding in animal herds . Moreover , some animals have problems to mate , for example , clouded leopard males are very aggressive when they are on heat and they can kill their mate while they are mating . That is of no use if clouded leopard females die from mating . Scientists and veterinarians have found the way to increase their population by artificial insemination techniques . The last reason , zoos are shelters for animals from wildlife trafficking and we ca not let them go free , because they were brought from the forest when they were young . On the other hand , zoos should provide an environment in animals ' cages like their natural habitats and strengthen their behavior by supporting enrichment in the cages , in order to avoid stereotypical behavior . 
