It is argued that telling the truth is vital for every moment in life . While lying has some drawbacks , I quite agree that we need to use lies on some fundamental occasions . There are some benefits to hiding the truth in some ways . On the one hand , if people face a situation which is a matter of death and life for them , they must tell a lie . Sometimes you must not reveal the truth if you think it could put you and people who you love at risk . For example , when somebody is threatened by a thief who wants to give important information , they have to ignore telling the truth to save their life . In addition , on some national circumstances , decision -makers have to give wrong data or lie to the public . It means when a country faces a foreign interference , like a war , politicians must prevent telling the truth about their strategies and missions . For instance , in the war between Iran and Iraq in 1980 , the Iranian commanders did not reveal any data about the weapons and their plans for the public or media to avoid any dangerous situations by soldiers . If any vital information was disclosed to people showing honesty , the country would fail in the attack . In conclusion , although telling lies is unacceptable among some individuals , in my view , in some specific situations , we must neglect the truth to save our life or for national benefits . 
Hello Tresa , What have you been doing lately ? I miss you . We have not seen each other for a month . I want to tell you about the concert I went to last week . As you know , I am a hard -core fan of the South Korean boy band named BTS . I 've always wanted to attend their concert . But I never had a chance to go , because their concert tickets are too expensive for a student like me to buy . But you know , my grandfather had given me pocket money before they announced the concert date . With that pocket money , I bought the ticket . Some might think that it is unreasonable spending such an amount of money on a concert ticket . But I 'd waited for so long to see them live . That was a once -in -a - lifetime opportunity . So , I decided to take it at any cost . I still ca not believe that I saw them performing on the stage live . I have just always watched their performances on my phone screen . Their real voices are really amazing . But the trouble was that I could not watch the performance till the end , because I fainted during their performance , since it was the very first time that I 'd stood up for so so long . I was very sorry about that . Next time , I will watch the performance till the very end . I think my letter is too long , so let me stop it here . I hope to see you soon . 
In my opinion , an open office design is beneficial for both workers and employers due to the following reasons . First of all , because of the spacious design , workers are able to communicate freely with one another . Thus the missing physical border might also diminish the mental border of advancing on a superior with a question which would otherwise obviously limit the interaction between employees of separated cubicles . In my view , these interactions add real value to the company and the product or service which is developed . So not only the workers themselves but also the firm might gain an advantage from this kind of office design . Moreover , the office has always been a social place . This fact is again stressed by the outbreak of the coronavirus right now , which shows that the social culture is a crucial part of a company 's identity . This culture must be lived in everyday conversations and everyday acting , which is difficult in an environment where everyone is working in their limited space . 
Write and Improve is a new online tool available freely on the web . It enables you to practice writing in English while being graded fully automatically by an AI system . The grading is most likely based on a combination of natural language processing and machine learning algorithms , which are deployed to accurately assess your level of written English . Maybe the system is both trying to infer whether you are using words in the correct context and if your able to use a wide range of vocabulary effectively . Furthermore , Write and Improve gives you active feedback about especially strong weak parts of your writing , giving you the chance to quickly improve yourself and your respective scores in different tests of English as a foreign language . The usage of the tool is quite straightforward , thus making it a boon for nearly every user , from the young professional trying to improve himself to the school kid or the senior adult . In summary , I can fully recommend using this new web -based software to everyone who is willing to put some effort into the improvement of their English skills . Just give it a try and see by yourself how fast you are going to advance . 
