I really do not think that we should change physical books for electronic books because not all people have the opportunity to get a computer , tablet , or smartphone . Therefore , books are not as expensive as electronic devices , also books are repositories where you can get information very quickly and more importantly , that information that you 're getting was approved by professionals and people that really know about that topic . But the reality is we 're living in times where we need to be more ecological and unfortunately books are made principally from trees and looking at the future , we 're obliged to make a change from physical books to electronic books . There might be people that could think the same as me , and the question here is what opinion is correct ? In my opinion , I 'd like to keep physical books instead of using electronic books . That 's my opinion . 
I will always remember visiting the USA for the first time . That was the most exciting holiday I have ever had , for several reasons . And , in this writing , I am going to mention the reasons why I think so . To get started , it took place when I had just finished my degree . I was quite young and inexperienced then . Nevertheless , somehow I knew it was going to be one of the greatest experiences a person could ever have . A summer in New York just sounded as perfect as it truly was . Had it not been for the fact that I already had a friend living there , I would have never made the decision to go there that fast . But the truth was that having the support of a close friend who knew that enormous city well meant the world to me . Visiting New York , the city that never sleeps , simply made a dream come true for me . What I did first once I was there was find a job as a waitress , as I had plans to spend the whole summer there . I met some new friends at my job and they showed me some important and distinctive places in New York . I remember feeling tiny while I walked around the most famous skyscrapers . I also remember the crowded streets at every single moment , the lights , the singular cabs of the city . It all was magical to me . Nevertheless , there were some drawbacks that should be mentioned as well . Perhaps it was too much time for me to spend far from home for the first time in my life . It was three months missing my family , the food at home , my friends and , especially , my mother tongue . I was not very good at English at that moment , I have to admit . Last but not least , I would like to conclude by adding that , despite those downsides , I would certainly recommend this kind of adventure to everyone . Not only did I learn a lot about what living on your own means , but also I learned a lot about myself and how independent and responsible I can actually be . 
