November 2 , 2020 Dear Town Council , The freedom of free exercise is guaranteed to every American citizen by the First Amendment of the Constitution . However , this freedom is at odds with a recently proposed idea to ban mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants . I disagree with the banning of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants . Firstly , all citizens are guaranteed the freedom of free exercise . So , the town council cannot ban the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants unless people are doing something against the law . So , the town council cannot implement this ban because it goes against the First Amendment . This a major reason why I disagree with banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants . In addition , mobile phones make it easier for people to pay for items , food , and public transport . If the town council implements this ban , then people would have to carry lots of coins and paper currency whenever they want to buy something at a shop or when they are eating at a restaurant . This means that if this ban is carried out , it would make people 's life much harder . This is another reason why is disagree with this proposed ban . All in all , I disagree with this proposed ban both because it is unconstitutional , and that it makes people 's life harder . I hope that the town council rethinks it and does not implement this ban after reading this letter . Yours sincerely , Daniel 
Some people think that it is a good idea for people not to lie , while others say it is acceptable not to speak the truth . However , I believe that every individual should try to speak the truth always because it would help people to build a connection of trust between each other . I think it is acceptable to tell lies when it does not hurt other people . On the one hand , some think that it is necessary to always speak the truth . This is because people can build a strong relationship among each other by speaking the truth always and this type of connection mostly does not break . For instance , a 2015 report by the UK government found that the pupils aged between 5-12 share stronger bonds with other children than young and old people because children do not lie like young people do . So I agree it is very important to try not to lies to others , especially to loved ones . Other people would say that , sometimes , it is okay to tell lies rather than the truth . One reason for this is that in some situation where the truth hurts and separates people , so it is acceptable to lie . For example , according to extensive research , a couple sometimes lies to save their marriage , which according to me is also acceptable . To conclude , although views differ whether it is okay for people to lie sometimes , I would argue that every individual must try to speak the truth first which allows people to share a healthy bond . 
