The school of the future is going to be very different from nowadays . I am not sure if it will change to be better or worse , but the only thing I am hundred percent sure about is that it will be different . The main reason why I believe that is because technology has a big influence in all subjects in the world , and school is going to be influenced by technology , like other subjects . If we compare school now with school some years ago , we can see that it has changed a lot . For example , not many years ago , the teachers used to use a giz to write on a board , but now they normally use a pen or an electronic board where they do not use any pens at all . The most important thing is , is school going to be better ? Is the way used to teach going to be more effective than now ? These are questions that we ca not answer now . We will just be prepared to say if the changes were good or not when the future comes . 
Now is the start of a new school year . In the past year , I have finished several things from my to -do list . Firstly , I have started my master 's program at the University of Mannheim and I have done very well . Secondly , I submitted a seminar thesis in the Finance area and got quite a good grade at the end . Thirdly , I have learned the programming language Python , and done an empirical data analysis with Python . Therefore , I am very satisfied with my progress in the past year . However , there are still several things that I need to improve in the coming year . Firstly , although I have started to program with Python , I still need to continue the programming exercise to master this programming language . Furthermore , it is also very important to apply the financial basics in Python . Secondly , I still need to improve my English and my German to C1 level . Thirdly , I need to improve my skills with Microsoft software to be fit for the job . Last but not least , I need to train myself to get along well with others , since I am quite socially distant . To achieve my goals , I have made a daily and weekly schedule to remind me and track my progress . 
Nowadays , there are more options for studying and improving one 's own preparation than in the past . In spite of the evolution of school arrangements , there are always advantages and drawbacks as well . Thus , what are the advantages and disadvantages of studying abroad ? Firstly , a student who has studied abroad for at least some months has more job opportunities than other students . In fact , the most important businesses and industries of the world are always searching for a young graduate with this background . Secondly , studying abroad improves one 's own language skills , English in this case . This is verified by various research studies , which state that going abroad to study or work helps to learn a foreign language quickly . Moreover , it can make a person feel more self -confident , with an improvement in social relationships . However , there are also some possible drawbacks . For example , it comes at great costs , from an economic point of view . What 's more , a further issue might be the distance between the student and his family . It is not so easy leaving everything and going to another country , totally different and so far from home ! It corresponds to breaking all our habits and starting again . It takes a lot of time to get used to a new , different ( and sometimes strange ) lifestyle . In any case , it is an incredible experience that can change our own life and will remain in our mind forever . It is absolutely worth it . 
Dear Sophia , I am so excited and pleased to share with you my favourite movie . In fact , I think that you 'll love it too . The movie is called ' Clouds ' . It is a musical drama based on a true story . It tells the beginning musical career of a young man that has bone cancer . I do not want to spoil the movie for you . Indeed , I liked the movie a lot , because it draws a picture of the patience , strength and power of the weakest of us to prove his existence and shine brightly . You should definitely check it , because it will give you hope for life and show you the better side of the world . As a matter of fact , the movie is so influential and emotional , you 'd better watch it and not miss it . Eventually , I will be looking forward to hearing your opinion about the movie as soon as you check it out . Love , Saif 
I am writing this letter because I saw your article this morning about your idea to ban mobile phones from restaurants and other public places . I would like to share my opinion about this idea , so you hopefully change your mind . The first thing to mention is that all people in this country are free to choose where they want to use their mobile phone . Using a mobile phone in public places is not a crime and , therefore , it cannot be banned . Secondly , a lot of humans use their phone for functional purposes . For example , when an employee has a work meeting with an employer , they can meet each other at the workplace , but it is also possible that one of them works in a restaurant and the other one works from home . In this case , they need to call each other . So it would be very impractical if phones were not allowed anymore in restaurants . When I was reading your letter , I could understand what your intention was banning mobile phones . Everyone is nowadays only focused on their screen . This means that nobody makes new contacts anymore when they are , for example , on their way . Also the social aspect in a restaurant or shop disappears , because nobody talks to each other anymore . But in this case , I would like to suggest to make people aware of their actions instead of banning phones from public places . In conclusion , I have noticed your letter and I would be aware of my actions in the future , but I do not think it is a well taken decision to forbid mobile phones from public places . 
