Some prefer to live a longer , without being adventurous , life . Others , however , are concerned that once in a lifetime means there is no second chance . Thus , they would attempt to challenge everything they can and go on adventures when they are living in the world . As far as I am concerned , living an exciting and extraordinary life is more valuable than a long term but boring life . There are several points that will be addressed below . Firstly , life is irreversible . No one can predict whether the afterlife exists or not ; therefore , we should seize the moment and try to challenge the unknown when we are young . Eventually , those difficulties and challenges we have conquered and got over will turn into unforgettable memories in our life . Additionally , human beings are fickle . Some people choose a peaceful life at first . However , when they are dying , they start regretting countless things they did not do before . People desire to live in peace and quiet ; thus they should avoid having unpredictable behaviors which may bring unstable and risky factors into their life . However , health conditions should always be an inevitable issue once people get older . For instance , some old people may have dementia or they are out of action . It not only brings problems but also becomes a part of the burden on their families and offspring . Thus , it seems living too long still may not have a good quality of life even though the life is peaceful . To conclude , everyone will face the end of human life , thus the quality of life is more important than the quantity , and we should value quality . 
Most people watch interesting shows or movies on television to entertain themselves . The question is whether television can also be used for an educational purpose . Regarding this topic , opinions are mainly divided into two groups . Some of them think that we can use television for education . Others argue that television is dominantly used for entertainment and it is difficult to use it for education . The supporters state that we can use various types of television programs to educate our children , or to accelerate our knowledge about an unknown field . For instance , there are plenty of programs for English learning , or basic cognitive training programs for children . They are well designed for children , with many funny features , so that children can learn the new knowledge and will not be bored . Furthermore , there are also many different documentary videos for adults to extend their horizons . However , opponents argue that it is quite difficult to implement this ideal concept with television , since there are so many obstructions , especially when children watch television . For example , they pay much more attention to the funny scenarios than the content . Furthermore , there are also many advertisements during the program that will also disrupt the children from learning . Finally , most children , as well as most adults , are more likely to use televisions to watch shows or movies than learn new knowledge . As a result , television can be used for education . However , due to various drawbacks , it may not be the optimal tool for this purpose . 
