It may be a useful procedure , and in addition , highly interesting to observe , but I doubt you can charge someone for not going outside . That 's simply not feasible . Although I 'm fully aware of these " society diseases " and openly support a healthy lifestyle , even though I 'm no fanatic . You ca not expect people to just rise from wherever they 're sitting and go to play football , or something similar . We have something called personal rights , and the fact that we have free will is very well -written in there . And , of course , yes , I know we are discussing the schools , and other similar institutions , where this could be somehow possible to require , but think about that . It 's completely included in the capabilities of schools and universities to proceed with the standard P . E . Classes . In this case , I would simply augment the time - dotation . If the requirements are not satisfying , or the effect is not perceptible , the best thing to do is upgrade the system of lectures , simply innovate in this field , and bring some new procedures , techniques . If we 're talking directly about sports , then develop or involve some new games , etc . From my point of view , the most recognizable , acceptable and cheapest way should be starting a whole brand new campaign , with massive proportions , and range . I 'd make it effective , then , of course , effective in a friendly way ( we do not need any violence ) . It should appeal to people , give them new insights . You have to motivate the crowds ! For me , this is the most compromising way . I cannot agree with the introduced statement , we ca not directly force anyone . This could be acceptable , let 's say , maybe during the war , or other similar events , when the capable population is expected , and you can easily reshape young people . But it should not be done this way . It 's way too drastic and unnecessary . 
