Health or wealth ? With the development of new technology and society , the amount of consumer goods to meet the human demand is increasing dramatically . Meanwhile , more and more people are driven by their consumer desires and want to work harder to get richer . It is interesting to discuss whether health is more important than wealth . Some argue that it is more important to be healthy than to be rich . Others disagree with it . However , the answer to this question depends on various factors , such as the individual financial situation , the understanding of social security , value choice and personality . Since these factors vary for different people and countries , it is no wonder that people have different choices . For instance , most employees work round 72 hours per week in China , because they usually have high expenses and may also have mortgage debt to pay back each month . Furthermore , there is no effective social security . The Chinese must save money for themselves and for their parents , just in case . As a result , many people are already suffering from various health problems at a very young age . In a highly developing society , it is hard for people who are not driven by overwhelming consumer desire . Therefore , most Chinese decide to work harder to get richer . Nevertheless , many Germans choose another lifestyle than the Chinese . Many Germans choose to have a fun and relaxing job and have a better work -life balance . Most people in Germany work no more than 40 hours per week . Some of them even only work 20 hours weekly to have more free time for their family or their hobbies . Because the social security in Germany is relatively comprehensive and sufficient , people do not have so much uncertainty to worry about . 
Some people believe that health is more crucial than wealth . I also have the same concept as them . Money cannot buy health , despite having the ability to acquire the best medical system , however , money is earned through hard work . Nowadays there a rapid growth of competition in the market , as the world is constantly changing , thus people are fighting to keep their jobs and solve their bread and butter issues , forgetting how important their health is in a stressful environment . Being overworked can lead to health problems such as fatigue , increase the chances of having hypertension and other health problems . But there are some health problems that are incurable . Take Human Immunodeficiency Virus ( HIV ) . Despite nations pouring money into research , they have yet to find a cure . On the other hand , health can bring joy to our life . For example , if someone is on a trip enjoying parties and all sorts of crazy things while being healthy , but all of the sudden he falls ill , not being able to spend his last few days on a wonderful trip , everything will turn into anguish . Furthermore , if you were healthy , you would be able to gain wealth . The reverse is not possible . Health gives you the ability to enjoy what life has to offer and creates experiences that are often more cherished that physical goods . Therefore , I conclude that health is more important that money , although money can bring joy to some people 's lives , but greed will one day overcome them , turning them into a demon . 
