Write & Improve is an online platform provided by the Cambridge Language Assessment . It helps an English student ( or learner in general ) to improve their vocabulary and writing skill . In my opinion it is very helpful and stimulating , because , for example , it can check the written text and give some advice about it . This direct feedback is good for a self -taught and for every English learner . Moreover , W&I is characterized by many examples and models of a possible writing test . In fact , there is a so -called ' Test zone ' . Furthermore , there are W&I workbooks , in order to train daily with different topics , from sport to studies , from the environment to technologies and so on . These workbooks are divided by sections , which depend on the English level : Beginner , Intermediate or Advanced . For those who want to improve their business English , there is also a section called ' W&I Business ' . However , I do not like the restricted number of simulations of Writing Tests . Completing all the ' free ' topics , the others are blocked . If you want to unlock them , you should pay . If I were my classmates , I would start using Write & improve . I recommend it to everybody . 
Nowadays , video games are part of children 's lives . These days , kids grow up with technology and virtual games and their pros and cons . As a parent , our responsibility is to manage our children 's time on a computer and try to schedule it . Video games are actually a good way to develop motor skills and sometimes to learn languages . It is proved that playing video games helps to improve coordination , multitasking skills and enhances memory . For these reasons , video games are a good tool for distraction and to develop children 's brain speed . In contrast , the abuse of these games platforms is negative to children who spend their whole day playing video games , such as triggering violence , bad performance in school and health problems like anxiety , obesity or stress . Personally , I think that playing video games is a good resource to help kids improve their cognitive development , however we have to be conscious about the abuse of these games and we have to control the use of these video games consoles by kids . 
The Future of Travel Nowadays there are already various ways to travel , for instance buses , trains or planes . It is already much faster than the way to travel in the Middle Ages , as people usually travelled with carriages . And it was very slow and the journey was more likely limited to regional . Due to the dramatic development of technology and further travel demands of humans , the future of travel is expected to be faster , cheaper and more comfortable . For instance , it is not difficult to image that typical vehicles , such as self -driving cars that can fly , will actually be widely used in the future . This new vehicle can be used not only for a short -distance trip , but also for a long -distance journey . Correspondingly , international travel will be more personalized and flexible , since almost everyone could fly with their own car . And this new change may decrease the usage of large planes dramatically . Furthermore , outer space travel with spacecraft may also come true , and trips for humans will not be limited to the earth anymore . Finally , with the wide application of virtual reality technology in travelling and work , it is reasonable to imagine that people will do a real trip less and a virtual one more . 
