As a student , I like to live on my own to try my abilities and find my strength and weakness . I think when a young student lives with her/his parents , it is like a person has fish without any training in fishing . In my opinion , everyone has to be independent and learn how to do her/his responsibilities . In university dorms , you live with other people that come from different families with different cultures and there are a variety of ideas . In this condition , you learn how to behave with them . Another reason is that when a student lives on her / his own , she / he learns how to spend her / his money and not waste money . , . this condition makes a person stronger and sociable and independent . When you know you are responsible for your decisions , mistakes and behaviour , you will think about the results of your work . You learn to be a new person because your condition has changed . You are not a child for your parents to do your work . You are a member of society that grows up . 
Vehicles play a vital role in a human 's life , because we use vehicles for traveling . Today , many scientists are trying to fix the problem of road congestion , as there has been a large increase in the number of cars on the road . They are figuring out how to decrease traffic congestion and road congestion . According to Dr . Paul , they are innovating a flying car in order to reduce traffic congestion . In that case , we could travel from one place to another without delay in the future . As the world is progressing , in the future you can expect self -driving cars on the road . Besides these kinds of cars , they are planning to pave smart roads in order to decrease accidents and road deaths . I think that this is the future of the whole world . Nonetheless , I think airplanes will remain the same , although other ways of travelling could change , because travelling by planes is convenient . It is the best way to travel from one country to another . To sum up , even if flying cars and self -driving cars can be invented in the future , we cannot say if life will be convenient , because everything comes with ease and also drawbacks . 
I am an 18 -year -old student and studying English for almost 6 years now . For a long time , I was looking for a tool which may help me to improve my English writing skills because they are awful . But most of the programs or tools are expensive and , as a student , I cannot pay them . Some time ago , I found " Write and Improve . " It is a tool which is organised by Cambridge University and it is absolutely great . First of all , it is almost free . You can use most of the tools without paying anything . Depending on your English skills , you can choose among different difficulties . They are called workbooks in which you find , depending on your individual level , tasks for practising . After doing a task , you get immediately feedback from the program . It includes your English level and the mistakes you made . However , you can find a test zone for some exams Cambridge University offers . If you want , you also can create your own workbooks . In my opinion , this tool is really good if you want to improve your English or prepare yourself for an exam . It will not replace a real teacher because it is only a program , but in the beginning , it might be helpful . If you decide to sign up to the mailing list , you will also receive a lot of helpful tips . I can recommend Write and Improve , but I also have to say there might be better ones if you are ready to pay some money for a good program like Grammarly . 
Taking about whether television entertains , there are a variety of television programs broadcast on television , such as comedies , documentaries , reality shows , drama and so on . Regardless of gender and age , people like watching television programs . For me , I like dramas , reality shows and educational programs . Some people frown upon some kinds of programs , such as game shows and advertisements , because they think a lot of advertisements are a form of lying and they can make people feel depressed and discontent with their ordinary lives , especially those people who have only a small amount of money to spend on luxuries . And parents do not want their children to spend so much time watching game shows . On the other hand , I think we can benefit from watching programs like dramas , wildlife documentaries and educational content . Moreover , you can relax by watching a comedy or something like that when you are mentally tired . What 's more , people still get their news primarily from TV , and a few cartoons intended for kids can also teach a couple of things , some moral principles and some lessons . In conclusion , as far as I know , television can not only entertain but also educate us . It is a win -win situation . 
