Scientists have proved that exercise brings us many benefits . Doing frequent exercise makes our life a lot better , because it improves both our mental and physical health . However , there are still many things which are indispensable in life , such as relationships and knowledge , because these things play important roles in the success of a person . Firstly , a person cannot live without a network . Every one of us belongs to a certain group of people . Since we were born , we have lived with our families . We go to schools , we have friends and teachers . And , when we work , we belong to our companies . That makes humans different from animals , because we have societies and social interaction . The person we have become today is the result of all the interactions with the people we have met . For example , if a child lives with a good and wealthy family , there will be more chances for the child to become a good person in the future . Knowledge is also a powerful tool of humans . This helps us resolve our problems and develop into a valuable person . This factor is also crucial to the success of people . 
Personally , I think an office 's design is an important issue for the productivity and efficiency of collaborators , because I consider offices must have a more open design , with no walls separating employees from their co -workers . First of all , it is known that the most successful companies , which have won the awards for the best place to work , care about the design of the place where their collaborators perform their activities every day ; they do not have walls separating the peers , because they consider that walls can mean a line which restricts the collaboration and creativity inside the company , hence the rate of new strategies and new plans of action are reduced . Apart from that , when there are no walls in the offices , the people perceive more fairness and equality , and it implies a way to be more dynamic and adaptable about the coming changes , the latter is essential owing to the business world being full of uncertainty and complexity . Additionally , it is important to consider the health of workers , not only physically but also mentally , when designing the offices . So , according to some studies , the spaces where the people work must be wide enough to allow them walk and clear their minds so as to reduce the stress levels , increase the creativity and to promote the movement in their sedentary lives . On the top of that , it is claimed if offices have ergonomic designs , the productivity of the workers will improve due to the collaborators feeling more comfortable and satisfied . I would like to bring home this vital part , when workers do not have worries about the space where they have to work or they do not have negative feelings about the discomfort , they can focus on what they 're doing and have more energy for the activities as a result they leverage their synergy in teamwork . Finally , I think the spaces for offices should be wide and ergonomic for administrative employees , in order to promote efficiency , creativity and productivity . 
