Introduction The purpose of this report is to evaluate the Write and Improve website and to answer if it is a helpful tool for learning English . It will also consider possible future developments . I have been using this website for three months now and I have completed around twenty writing tasks . Advantages First of all , there are plenty of writing tasks available on the website . Starting from a basic level , the user can make progress completing more advanced tasks . The checking system works very fast . A user waits only a few minutes to check results . Disadvantages Although the checking system works very fast , it does not contain more precise information about the kind of mistakes made by users . Basically , it forces you to check what you did incorrectly outside of Write and Improve . In my opinion , the designers of the site should think about changing this solution . Recommendation . I would strongly recommend using the Write and Improve website . Not only does it help in developing writing skills , but also allows users to express their opinions on lots of different topics . 
I went to Panama when I was 10 years old . I saw lots of interesting things , like The Panama Canal . It is a famous landmark of human engineering which links the Atlantic and Pacific oceans to create an essential sea route . This gives the possibility of being a short and cheap transit route for ships responsible for transporting goods . I also went to an island called Chichime , that belongs to a region called Guna Yala . Guna Yala is an indigenous region in Panama , inhabited by the Guna ethnic group . There I spent two days . I swam in the sea and walked around the island . I went into the Biomuseum too . It is a natural history museum that is located in Panama City . Its intention is to change the way we see , understand and conserve nature and its biodiversity . It was my favourite trip because I learnt a lot of new and amazing things about the world . 
Before I decide what life I prefer , I want to clear up the definition of intense . Because what does intense exactly mean ? In my words , intense means a busy life . Not only a life full of adventures but also a life full of hard work and strict deadlines . Taking in consideration this definition , I would prefer a calm life until 100 years old . I choose this one because of personal events . A few years ago , my mother had a heart attack . This was a consequence of too much pressure . She wanted to move , wanted to achieve in her job and had too much to care about . It delivered stress and worse consequences . In order to enjoy my life , I want to relax . I do not want a lot of stress in my life . I think while having a calm life you can still have a lot to look out for . There are fun things to do and several occasions to celebrate life . Why would you rush your life if you could enjoy it for many more years ? I do have a sidenote to my statement . What I need most in my life is my family and friends . I want them by my side for those 100 years . So relax , do not stress and enjoy life . 
Should we free all animals ? In the XXIst century , a lot of eco -friendly movements have gained popularity . Some of them have been proposing closing zoos . They argue that all living creatures should be free and deserve better treatment . Are we supposed to open the gates and set the lions and other creatures free ? It 's an issue we should discuss . Eco movements claim that animals can be happy only when they live in their natural environment . Personally , I cannot agree with that . In my opinion , animals that live in a zoo are the lucky ones . They have safety and food and they do not worry that some predator may eat them tomorrow . Although sometimes it 's a pity to look at such a majestic animal , like a tiger , being kept behind bars , we should remember that by doing this , we help to preserve some kinds of animals . For example , pandas would not survive if we did not keep them in zoos . Moreover , I think that children can learn something going to zoos . In the future they may become nature lovers . In conclusion , I think that zoos should continue to exist . This is the solution I would recommend . 
I think students should have new teachers each year . Why ? There are a lot of reasons . I want to give you several examples . It does not matter which grade you are in . You can be a pupil or a university student . If you have the same teacher every year , you cannot learn a different perspective . On condition that students have a particular teacher , they can discover different things . Second , having the same teacher reduces their authority over them . Authority is essential for education . If the teacher does not have authority , they can be reckless . In other words , they cannot listen to the teacher . This situation is perilous . For example , if the teacher has lost control over them , he/she cannot teach them anything . On the other hand , sometimes the students face some risks if they have a different teacher each year . The new teacher could not be good like the old teacher . Finally , students should have a new teacher each year . 
