Video games are one of the most used mediums of entertainment at the moment . They are loved by children , who use them more and more . However , people are divided by different points . Some believe that video games are dangerous for health . On the other hand , some state how video games are useful and may have positive effects . What is the right choice ? Are there any other strategies ? Personally , I would argue that playing video games for many hours may involve issues , from eyesight to bad headaches . It is confirmed by the fact that more and more children and teenagers wear glasses nowadays . Concerning some positive effects of these games , I believe they are improbable . It depends on the genre of game which we are playing . Many war games and action ones have been available for years and often they are requested by children rather than adults or teenagers . It would be a problem from an educational point of view . A child who plays this kind of game could show more aggressive behaviour than one who does not play them . I think that children have to read books and be outside with others as well . It will be more fun than staying at home . I hope their parents will make the right choice for their children . 
Nowadays , our society teaches us to chase wealth , but is it really the key to happiness ? Personally , I believe that staying healthy is more valuable than living in luxury . First of all , unless we are healthy , we cannot make the most of our life and never achieve our full potential . Therefore , we should take better care of the aspects of our health that are in our control , such as exercise , food and sleep . But , in order to have a healthy lifestyle , we need enough money to cover our basic needs . Although it 's stressful when we are worried about little money , a huge amount of it wo not make us happier . For example , studies of lottery winners show that after a relatively short period of time , they are no happier than they were before their win . On the other hand , for a healthy body and mind , it is essential that we do as much physical activity as possible . But , the rich are supposed to have their luxury houses cleaned and their fancy cars repaired . As a result , they do less exercise than is required . In conclusion , from my point of view , health is the most important treasure in our life . 
My holidays in Norway : My grandparents and I , at the age of eleven , went on a trip to Norway to visit my aunt in the Easter holidays . This was a very special trip for me , as it was the first time travelling without my parents and siblings . We went by plane , embarking from the airport of Frankfurt and arriving in the capital of Norway , Oslo . I do not remember a lot about the journey , however I kept in mind the picturesque view of the Norwegian landscape , that I could see from the window shortly before the arrival . Having arrived , I became tremendously tired and fell asleep immediately . When I woke up , I thought that I had slept the whole night , but my aunt later told me that I had only slept two hours and that it was not morning , but evening . After that , my aunt and her husband fried some patties with vegetables and rice , which was the first dish I had on Norwegian land . 
