There were many discussions about which work environment is the most productive . In most offices I have visited , there was an open space where employees have their own desks . They can talk to each other , discuss something , but also hear each other on the phone . So there are some advantages and disadvantages about an open office . The advantages are that employees can see each other . They can know right away if you are available for questions or you 're busy . It is also a quite nice ambiance . However , there are some disadvantages . Most of the time , they are rumours . Different kinds of people are talking , to each other and on the phone . It 's also not possible to discuss something in private . However , there are some offices which have cubicles . This can be good for the productivity of the employees . Unfortunately , most employees find this very lonely . They like to talk to their colleagues . Talking to colleagues motivates employees . To conclude , I think working in cubicles is productive for a few hours . For the long term , I would recommend a more open design . 
Almost everyone associates the holiday season with fun , making new friends and having the time of their lives . I agree with those associations wholeheartedly . When it comes to describing my best holiday ever , one specific trip pops up in my head . It was two years ago . I was 18 and it was one of my first holidays with my friends . We went to Bulgaria as a group of 6 friends . Three of them were my best buddies , and there were 2 more girls . We had a great time there . We had a hotel within walking distance of the sea and there was a marvellous Vietnamese restaurant on the way . We stopped there very often . But it was not only due to this entertainment that it was my best holiday . During that trip , I got into a relationship with my old friend , Marta . That atmosphere of holiday carelessness surely made it easier . That was my best trip and holiday as well , ever . I found the love of my life , the one that I 'm engaged to now . We all have great memories from there and will be remembering that time probably for the rest of our lives . 
University represents a special moment in the life of a student . Their career and their future job depends on this kind of preparation . At that moment , students can decide to go away for studying or living at home with their parents . These two possibilities have advantages and drawbacks . Firstly , one advantage might be the possibility to be very close to the faculty . It will not be necessary to use transport , but it is possible to go there walking or riding a bike . Moreover , another advantage is to stay with your own without being stressed by old daily issues . Therefore , you might be more relaxed , paying attention to your studies and activities . In addition to that , you can meet new people and make new friends at university . What a stunning experience ! However , there are some drawbacks . For instance , your habits will change drastically : you will have to organize your routine differently , do housework and cook for yourself . In this sense , everything you neglected up to now . It is time to roll up your sleeves ! In spite of these difficulties , university life is an incredible experience . In my opinion , I would prefer to live on my own rather than staying at home with my family . 
