Enola Holmes is an adventure film . It tells a story about girl called Enola who lived in England in the 19th century . It was directed by Harry Bradbeer . Enola is 15 years old , she lives with her mother and servants in a big house , she has 2 brothers who live out of the town , and her father passed away long time ago . Suddenly , her mom left the house without telling her the reason and where she was going . Then she decided to go and find her in London , but her brothers came to the town and refused to let her to go to find their mother . She insisted on going , so she decided to run away from the house . The main character is Enola , played by Millie Bobby Brown and her performance is convenient and charming , and charming , and the other actors are amazing . It is a wonderful film , I give it 5 stars and of course , I recommend this film to you , and I am sure you will not regret watching it and you will repeat it more than once . 
Why do I learn English ? Is English necessary for me ? Well , they are the questions I have asked myself many times before . At first , I thought that I was wasting my time with this thing . But now I know the reasons why English is crucial to me . First of all , I 'm learning IT . As you know , this major needs English so much . The references , related documents ... are visually written in English . So how can I read them if I do not know English ? Secondly , promotion opportunities . Knowing English plays an important role in my future work . English is an international language . It 's considered as the second must -know language beside the mother one . Without English , it 's difficult for me to get promoted , because most of the companies require it . Finally , it helps me connect with people around the world . With English , I can travel anywhere I want and talk to people from other countries . Those are the reasons why I learn English . With it , my life has changed . 
Volunteer work is really important , from a social point of view . Considering how many poor people there are in the world , we cannot neglect the contribution given by volunteers . The biggest cities of the world ( and not only ) host several volunteer organizations and non - profit associations . Basically , the goal of these associations consists of providing food , a bed and whatever it is necessary . We have to be proud of them . Some high schools have a requirement which involves the achievement of a certain amount of volunteer work so that students can graduate . That is a good choice , by means of students are prepared to face the world and every kind of situation . Doing these social experiences , students are able to insert themselves in difficult social contexts and help unlucky people at the same time . Furthermore , volunteer work is not just this : there are several possible activities , which could be more or less suitable for each student . It depends on them , they have to choose carefully and cleverly . That is not a joke ! In light of these considerations , I would conclude by stating that organizations and activities like these must be sustained and preserved . We have to start focusing a bit more on the others than on ourselves . 
I am part of those who believe the quote saying : “ If you tell the truth , you do not have to remember anything . ” Even if we live a stressful and difficult life , I still think that telling the telling truth is the only way that can lead to reach a peaceful life . Our social environment is infected unhappily by this disease that called " lies . " Wherever you go , you meet a person who uses lies every time they speak without feeling wrong . I think this bad behavior is the unavoidable result of a lack of education either within families or in school . When you have parents lying continuously that lead their children to follow them towards this behavior . Parents and teachers have the responsibility to educate children not only by giving a good example but also by explaining how dangerous lying is for our community . Our children are growing currently in a difficult environment where lies are common behavior , so it 's hard for them to adopt a good way for their life . We should share with teenagers and the young generation the benefits of telling truth and lead them to increase their values and beliefs . Our laws also have to set new rules punishing those who use lies in their behavior . In addition , television programs could also communicate a spot about this issue . 
