Currently , there are many people who prefer to use computers and tablets to study . Thick and heavy books are no longer being used by students to study . Why do students opt to use computers and tablets to study instead of reading books ? This is in light of the fact that many students think that using computers or tablets to study is more convenient than reading books . Thus , a question starts to linger in all students ' minds , ' should computers and tablets completely replace books in schools and universities ? ' As a student , from my point of view , I think that schools and universities should replace books with computers and tablets . This is because books are very inconvenient . Books are very thick and heavy . There are a lot of newspaper articles alleging that many students suffer from back pain , injuries , bone deformation and growth disorders . Students have to carry heavy and bulky books to schools or universities every day . Thus , sooner or later they will suffer from these injuries . On the other hand , taking a computer or a tablet to school is much more convenient and students do not need to take a lot of school bags to school . They just need to take one backpack to keep the computer or tablet in . This is because all of the documents are stored on the computer or tablet . As all of us know that a computer or a tablet will not be heavier than a stack of books . Besides , one of my reasons for agreeing that computers and tablets should completely replace books in schools and universities is that when students need to search for some information , they do not need to flip through pages . With the click of a finger , students are able to look up the information using computers or tablets . Consequently , students are able to save some precious time and can reduce their strenuous study schedules , because they have more free time . From my perspective , I truly think that using a computer or tablet brings us a lot of perks and benefits . In conclusion , I agree that computers and tablets should completely replace books in schools and universities 
