I would like to study politics and economics as well . I am interested in being a part of the political discussion . I like to argue . I have a lot of free time . In this free time I could study politics and economics . Could you help me to find a place where I can study this ? 
Dear town council president , First , I would like to congratulate you for your excellent work during your current mandate . one can ignore your involvement and engagement . Our town is very proud to have a responsible like you , who pays attention to their citizens . I would like to thank you also for your good initiative that permits citizens to express their opinion in a free way . Concerning your new decision about banning the use mobile phones on public transport , I would inform you that I totally agree with it . It is a wise decision that could be considered an advanced form of citizenship . I highly appreciate this decision which will permit us to use public transport in a safe and efficient conditions . We suffered a lot from those who use their mobile phone on public transport . This bad behavior is annoying as well as disrespectful . This form of carelessness is behind many conflicts that lead innocent people to jail sometimes . Whether using a mobile phone on transport or in shops , this behavior must be banned . As you know , digitalization is swallowing up our lives . We use technology everywhere and it is unavoidably transforming our daily . Our mobile phone addiction is just increasing more and more . To summarize my letter , I would like to encourage you to maintain this courageous decision . All the people are ready to applaud this initiative . 
Everybody should travel at least one time in their life . Most people have already done it or have not yet . Concerning my own experience , I am going to write some lines about my best holiday ever . Two years ago , my friends and I booked a holiday , which lasted a week , three days in Praha and the other three in Budapest , Hungary . I admit we were so excited . Nothing went wrong , so we took off for Praha on 10th of August . After that , we went to the hostel in order to leave our luggage and start our adventure ! Despite having few days , we exploited them as well as we could and we visited many typical places of that fascinating city . In fact , we went to the Old Castle and we went into the historical centre , buying some souvenirs and taking many photos as memories . Then , we had lunch in a typical restaurant , where we tasted traditional dishes and drank a lot of beer ! However , the best was still to come . This was when we went to the spa . What a beautiful day ! Thanks to my friends , it was the best holiday ever . 
I do not agree with the first opinion . I think teachers should change each year . There are a lot of factors in this situation . Firstly , students need a different teacher 's opinion and view . For this reason , I think it is very important to improve children . If they see different kinds of opinions from their teacher , they can develop their thinking system and other brain systems . If they only have the same teacher for several years , it will never happen . Secondly , if students have the same teacher for several years , they can establish an emotional connection . This is a significant and dangerous part , in my opinion . I think this connection should never exist between teachers and students , because this type of emotional connection can be dangerous for teachers and students . Some teachers have a different kind of experience level , this is another significant point . Other teachers may be more experienced than some teachers . Consequently , teachers should change each year . 
Hello everyone , Thank you for your effort . I guess that video games are negative games and may affect very badly on children and youths ' health because of the bad design and the bad ideas which the video games usually have . I 'd like to discuss another issue . The biggest problem is that people use those tools and games for too long a time , so that they lose their own beautiful life and they might lose their own future ! I know many people who were successful at their school and were active family members . They suddenly lost their success due to video games . They had to break their apprenticeships or they had to change their amazing studying way ! I personally do not have any idea how to prevent this huge problem . It might be a good suggestion to prohibit video games for the youth and young people . Thank you . 
I believe in the all around personality development of students . For that , students should be engaged in extracurricular activities along with volunteer work . I feel this way for two reasons , which I wish to explore in this writeup . Every student has to go into society . For that , he has to be ready for social liabilities , like family responsibilities and job liabilities . Day by day , the environment is getting harder to survive in and competition is growing in every field , hence students should be ready for all dynamics . Many universities are encouraging students to do volunteer work with different courses , like NCC and NSS , which groom the personality of the student in every aspect , like physically , mentally , spiritually and with social parameters . Moral values is decaying in society , hence people are not interested to do a job for which they do not get asalary . In the wake of this scenario , offering the course with the requirement that students must complete a certain amount of volunteer work in order to graduate would be beneficial not only for students but also for society , to maintain the moral values of people . 
I agree with the opinion that learning to speak a foreign language is important these days . I have three opinions to support the idea . First of all , speaking a foreign language expands the world we can join . Our jobs cannot be dealt with domestically these days . In particular , the population in Japan has been decreasing for several years . At the same time , more foreign people who want to get jobs in Japan are coming to Japan . Japanese people have to work with foreign people recently . In addition , it is difficult to sell Japanese products only in Japan under this situation . Thus , Japanese companies should sell their products globally . If they can only deal in the Japanese language , they will miss the opportunities to get their products known in foreign countries . The situation is the same for people in other countries . Therefore , to enlarge people 's world , speaking multinational languages is an easier way and the job efficiency will be improved . Secondly , we can earn a lot of money if we can speak more than one language . In Japan , English speakers can get a well -paid job and have a rich life . Many Japanese do not have the skill of speaking English . The CEFR level for English speaking of most Japanese people is less than B1 . If a Japanese person has more than a B1 speaking level , he can get a chance to work with people in foreign countries and he can get a higher wage . In other countries , people who can speak foreign languages are elite and able to get a high salary . Thirdly , learning to speak a foreign language may help in the reading of a foreign document and the skill lets us save a lot of time . From the technological side , most reports are written in English . Thus , we should read these foreign documents to interpret what it is being described . If we can read English smoothly , we will save time and we can do any other things . If we can deal only in our mother tongue , we would get limited information . Learning a foreign language is effective for us to save a lot of time for doing many jobs . To sum up , speaking a foreign language such as English is able to expand our job capacities . 
It goes without saying that living on your own is one of the most crucial decisions a person has to make in their life . Moving away while you are studying is increasingly claimed to be the correct decision . My thoughts about that matter are going to be displayed in this writing . To get started , I would like to point out some of the advantages living on your own while studying has . No doubt , once you are at college , your life changes dramatically . NA , . you are not a teenager any longer and you are capable of making some important choices that have significant effects on your future . One of them could be to choose to live by yourself . To do so , it is undoubtedly needed to find a job which provides you with the economic resources necessary to afford your expenses , even if it is a part -time job . By undertaking a job , not only will you understand how hard life can be , but also you take some crucial responsibilities , such as working in a team or dealing with people . Nevertheless , some drawbacks should be mentioned . Living by yourself means that you are the one who is responsible for the chores at home . As a result of working and taking care of the chores , you do not get round to studying as much time as you wish , and that could be negative for you in the way that your academic results can be worse than you expected them to be . Last but by no means least , I would like to conclude by bringing focus to the fact that had it not been for those drawbacks , living on your own while studying would be the perfect moment in your life for you to find out who you are , who you want to be , and where you belong . 
In my opinion , a university student should live away from their family and live in a hostel . It would be better for his personality development . I feel this way for two reasons which I wish to explore in this essay . Firstly , I would like to say that personality growth is very important at this age . As we know , if a student lives with his family , he could not get such exposure which is needed for after to enter family life and professional life . Just after completing his university life , one enters his professional and family life , which is not easy and , for that , you need prior exposure and in my point that university indipendent life teach it well . Secondly , I would like to discuss the economic point of view because , in the higher education system , books are very costly and students have to read many point as self study and , for that , it 's a must that he has all the books , but if you are living in a group , you can share the books and study materials which are not available in the library . Further to this , as we know , discussion and group study is essential for the better understanding of subjects . 
Have you ever asked yourself : Is learning to speak a foreign language as important these days as it was in the past ? From my personal standpoint , learning to speak a foreign language is still important , maybe even more so . Why is that ? Knowing foreign languages helps you in everything , such as traveling , communication , etc . You can easily find places , ask for directions and even order food . Speaking a language gives you a better understanding of the country 's culture . You can interact with people more freely , which provides a greater scope for meeting new people , making new friends and having more fun and enjoyment . Next , language helps you in your work . According to the world 's development , companies ' requirements are higher . Most companies look for candidates who have foreign language skills . If you are already working , knowing a foreign language gives you promotion opportunities . In a nutshell , at any given time , knowing one or many foreign languages is important . The more languages you know , the better life you will have . 
Our life changes nonstop over time and the future of travel will also proceed to a new level . But I do not think everything will be altered at all . I 'm going to give you some demonstrations . Firstly , much more modern it surely will be , improved technology will give us a faster approach to taking a trip around the world . I believe that , in the future , people wo not need any travel agencies , they will be able to do it themselves . That means electronic advice and digital technology or social media will be used instead in serving our needs . Do you think that is the limit ? I know it is not . Most of you all know that we , as humans , are capable of travelling to outer space , even that 's just a glimmer of hope . We can extend the limits of possible travel . If you think it is too hard to solve , please look back at human history from prehistory to contemporary , everything has been done chronologically that started from just some imagination in our brain . Human imagination is crucial and time will prove it . As I mentioned in the outset , some things will change but some things will still remain . One of them is travel consultants or mentors . Agencies should be placed but some of them are really useful and I do not think people want them to disappear . We all have social media to research the travel sites which we have never been to , but we still need people , like mentors , who have practical experience , enough to help us out . I believe that verbal conversations give us more perspective of the places we want to visit . Not only more specific advances , but also more notified alerts about possible problems . Yet , we have so many things outside the imagination that will be done over a period of time . But some things still are in the state of remaining . 
Dear town council , I realise that there is a proposal of banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants . As a part of the town , I think it 's important to share my opinion . I think this is not a good idea . First of all , this will hinder the town 's prolonged effort to attract tourists . This is because tourists from other towns will find this idea bothering and will leave with a bad impression of our town . Other than that , this will bring inconvenience to us who utilise the short period of time on public transport and in shops and restaurants to do important things like reading the newspaper or hearing a podcast . The amount of time wasted in the long run is huge . Some of us will also have important calls that need to be made immediately . I conceive that this proposal has been brought to consideration due to the increase of accidents due to phone usage on public transport and long queues in restaurants and shops . For that , I would like to suggest a small immature suggestion that is to have a campaign to educate the residents to stop using phones excessively in unsuitable places or times . I hope that the town council will give serious thoughts to this matter . The advice that I shared is of my own opinion and I hope that it will contribute to this matter . 
Many people believe that it is important to always tell the truth . People often gain their trust by telling the truth to others . Telling the truth makes everyone believe in you and more people would like to be friends with you . As the saying goes , ' Honesty is the best policy ' , people often believe that people who tell the truth have a good personality . However , there are some times when we are unable to tell the truth because sometimes telling the truth to someone might hurt their feelings , make them feel sad or it might make them feel uncomfortable . Thus , as for me , I think it is acceptable to tell a lie sometimes . Telling a white lie maybe will make people feel better or less worried . For example , most parents often tell white lies to their beloved children so that their children do not get worried about them . Every parent in the universe does not want their children worried about them , they hope their children can live happily . On the other hand , there are also some people who really love and care about their parents . They will tell a white lie to their parents , telling their parents that they are living happily and there is no need to worry about them , but in reality , they are actually not happy about everything in their life or they are unable to get what they want , such as their jobs , their studies and their life . They just hope that their parents are happy and feel relieved that their children are doing well . Hence , I think sometimes it is acceptable to tell a lie . Furthermore , sometimes telling truth to someone might make you lose your friend and some quarrels might occur . For instance , one of your friends tries to look pretty today so she wears heavy makeup which does not look good in her then you tell the truth to her and say that she is very ugly today . This will make her very upset and also might lower her self -esteem . Instead , you should tell her that she looks good with the makeup and then you can give her some suggestions about the makeup . Consequently , you will not only not lose a friend , but your friend will also appreciate your help . Thus , once again , I feel that telling a lie is acceptable sometimes . 
Nowadays , people share the view that free time is vital to have great health because with it your mind puts off work . , . I am going to tell you what I do in my free time if you are highly interested in following my chill out routine . Firstly , it is crucial to tell you the activities that I usually do in my free time or for chilling out . , . I highly often read a lot of books . As I read so many books , I am able to have a grytificant experience because , I could have a grytificant experience because in spite of learning new things , I can also imagine a lot of astonishing settings . , . I absolutely love listening to music . As I listen to a variety of types of music , it me to relieve my mind from my work and also , it improves my mood . Last but not least , the schedule of my activities should be mentioned because if you are highly interested in keeping up my daily routine , the . , . I always start reading my books at 4:00 a.m . and overall , I always start reading my books at 4:00 am and overall , I accomplish it at 5:00 a.m . I am doing that at this moment because it is when I finish school and after that I need to chill out at once . I , . I usually start listening to music at 9:00 a.m . until 10:00 a.m . As I listen to music at this time , it music this time , supports me to fall asleep at once . To conclude this essay , I believe that free time should have the same importance as the other activities that we practise every day . If you have free time , you can cut down your levels of stress . So you must have free time , even if you do not have enough time . 
I 'm looking forward to going abroad for a master 's degree . I think there are a lot of advantages to studying abroad . Firstly , some foreign universities can provide better educational conditions for the student , especially Europe , the USA and Canada 's universities . I always thought about going to Canada for a master 's . But firstly , I need to improve my English very much . Another advantage is the people and conditions are different from my country . They have good living conditions and happiness . Who does not want to go to Canada ? In addition , if you live in Turkey , Canada has a lot of national parks . You can visit whenever you want . Definitely , there are disadvantages of studying abroad . I think one of the hardest is adapting , because you have come from a different country and culture . If you want to live there , you must adapt to them . You should learn about their culture and lifestyle . It can take time , but you will get used to their lifestyle . Then , you will miss your family very much , surely . That 's another difficult disadvantage . However , thanks to technology , it 's easier at this time , because you can video call them and see them every day . As a result , there are advantages and disadvantages , but if you live in Turkey , the advantages are more than the disadvantages . 
The new school year is beginning and I am eager to study this year . I want to improve myself . I want to learn new things from my teacher and friends . I always think we have a chance because we are young and we can learn so many things . I will improve myself and achieve my goals . Firstly , I want to improve in the field of communication , because I do not want to do any math , physics and chemistry lessons . I have not got any talent for science and I ca not do these . Therefore , communication is the best field for me . Everything is related to communication . Our life is communication . If I can improve myself in this field , I can be a success . I can do everything to achieve my goals , because these targets are considerable things in my life . If I have not got an aim , why am I on this earth ? I need some goals and I need to fulfil them . I must do everything . I can study all day long . It does not matter , morning or night . As a result , I will be a successful person . I know and believe in myself . 
It is almost half of year that I 've been using Write and Improve . It 's a really amazing program for my writing , because it makes it easier for me to write without thinking about what I should write . It provides many topics and we can choose them freely . There are some levels , from beginner to advanced . I started as a beginner for about 5 months and this is my first time joining the intermediate level . I hope I can follow this program better than before . How the program checks the writing and then gives feedback and a grade is clear enough . It helps me a lot to know my progress . The bad thing about this program is sometimes the feedback or corrections are unclear . I ca not find the best of it . I 'd like to recommend this program to all of the people who want to improve their writing . 
Last year , I went to Datça with my best friend and his family . It was a superb holiday . We had a car and we went wherever we wanted to go . We drank too much and talked about some significant subjects . We generally talked about work -life , religion and the universe . We had too much sun and walked to lose weight . It was tiring , but amusing . Datça was the best place for a holiday I 've ever seen , because there are not too many people there and it has beautiful views . I love it there . It has a clean and calm sea . If you want to swim there , it will be very pleasant . There is an island where you can go on foot . There are a lot of goats on this island . It was amusing to see and touch them . Then , we went to the Datça center all night . Sometimes we sat in some cafes . We were there for a month . I enjoyed it very much . I want to go next year . 
When I was child , I loved playing video games . I remember when I changed my dog because of a video game . It was a Nintendo 64 . It come with a Mario game . That time there was a place where you could rent some games . Usually , I rented some games on a Friday . Well , playing video games is not so bad , it depends on what games you play . For example , several games are educational , but other games are so very violent . So if you play a video game , but the game that you play is educational , I do not see any problem , but if you play some games that show our children violence , they show us violent behaviour . It might be a real problem for us parents . There is another example , but with cartoons . I have a cousin that watches Hulk a lot , but he shows us some negative behaviour . He shouts at his mother and other people . So , it depends on which game he plays . 
My favourite indoor activity is definitely going to the gym . Unfortunately , that is currently not possible because of the Corona virus . I like this activity because you have so many devices in the gym and options to be able to work out . The last time I went to the gym was two years ago . I miss it a lot , but I have found other ways to exercise outside . 
Everybody knows exercise is a significant thing to stay healthy . There are different factors , like food and sleep , of course . Firstly , all people need to do exercise . If our body does not move sufficiently , it does not work smoothly . We should not lay on the sofa all the time . Consequently , people need to do exercise 30 minutes daily . Secondly , food is another very important thing for our body . If we want to stay healthy , we should be careful about what we eat . We should not eat too many hamburgers , chips and other unhealthy food . Our body needs healthy fats , a sufficient amount of vitamins and minerals . If we do not have these beneficial things , our body does not work smoothly . We should not eat at night because our bodies need to recover at night . Another significant thing to stay healthy is sleep . Every person needs quality of sleep . If we did not have a sufficient amount of sleep , we would be like a zombie . A normal person needs to sleep 8 hours daily . As a result , we should do these things . They are simple and feasible to stay healthy . 
Of course , some things will change . There will be a massive change in travelling . For instance , the planes will be faster than now . We will arrive 1 or 2 hours later instead of 10 hours . They will be able to stay longer in the sky and wo not need fuel . What about the train ? The trains will faster than now , exactly . We know trains are not very fast , however they will be in the future . They will travel for longer and be powerful . They will pass through the cities . Trains are too loud in our times , however , in the future , they will be noiseless . What about cars ? Everyone dreams of flying cars . In my opinion , it 's not realistic . Cars wo not fly , but will be smarter and more powerful . We wo not need a driver in the future because cars will drive themselves . Car accidents will reduce , literally . People wo not die because of car accidents . As a result , future travel seems attractive , safe and fast . 
Hi Jack , Happy birthday again . We invite beloved people and friends to celebrate and to attend birthday parties in my country . It is normally the same as in your country . After the meal we all clap our hands and sing " Happy Birthday to you " and we have a cake with candles . We used to go to the monastery to donate money to the monks and nuns . Be happy ! Yoon 
Currently , television is globally known as one of the most needed things in a human 's life . What is the importance of having a television in our own house ? Is television that important ? If one day television disappeared from our life , would humans be able to live without it ? Thus , let 's take a look at the importance of what television brings us . First and foremost , television not only entertains us , it is also able to educate all ages of people , from young ones to old ones . Television creates a window on the world for us to understand and explore more about the four corners of the world . For example , we can widely acknowledge the things that happen around us by watching television . We do not even need to travel to get the latest news , we just need to sit on the couch and switch on the television to watch the latest news . Does not it sound so simple and convenient ? From that , we are able to get educated from the news that is reported on the television . Do you know why ? This is because there are a lot of people sharing their experience through television and we are able to learn some new stuff from their experience and avoid the same mistakes that they have made . As the saying goes , ' prevention is better than cure ' . We can prevent the occurrence of the same mistakes that others have made and this can reduce the troubles happening in our life . Besides , we are able to learn other languages by watching television . For example , there are a lot of people who would like to learn the Korean language so they watch Korean dramas on the television . I think this is quite a useful way to learn other languages and be educated . Apart from that , I have seen many parents allow their children to watch English movies on television . This is because children are able to develop their English language skills from a young age . From one of my own experiences , my niece is able to speak fluent English at the age of five , I am astonished by her . After asking her mother , I learned that my niece actually started to watch English movies on the television at the age of three . This really shows that television is able to educate children . In addition , children can also learn some moral values from movies . This can help to nurture good behavior in children . Currently , parents often allow their kids to watch documentary films on the television . This is in light of the fact that it helps them develop a vast cauldron of knowledge and know more about the world . Hence , television can educate people . 
I usually play games in my free time . In addition , I help my parents work until they finish . I go to the market with my mother to buy vegetables , meat and fish for our lunch . After that I go to the school to pick my young sister up . After all of that I start to play games with my friends . 
I 'm in the process of creating a blog in the English language to satisfy my passion for writing . After taking a look at Write and Improve , I jumped at the chance to practice and get my English writing to a new level . I was a bit confused at the beginning when I realised I would not be provided with any basic guidelines on how to write a correct paragraph , instead , I would not be provided with any basic guidelines a for how to write a correct pharagraph , in stead , I almost only had to cope with the tasks from which the scheme allowed me to choose my appropriate level to start with . Well , I think this is the place where you can totally improve your English yourself by writing and writing again . Our mission is to keep practising every single day , the program will check your spelling , show the mistakes and track your progress . Sounds great , right ? I feel like I 'm creating my own world of writing , I give my reasoning and opinion about each debate they provide . Do not worry , they do not score your presentation based on your persuadable sentences , so feel free to let things out from your sight and comprehension . Of course , there is always something which emerges to challenge your patience . When I had finished about five or six tasks , they frustrated me with the board on the left showing my levels going down , it made me feel that the more I wrote , the less progress I made . Bearing in mind this must 've been my first challenge , I put it to the back of my mind and headed towards to other tasks . And step by step , I could finally appreciate my effort when I figure out my English writing has been going so much farther than I had expected - less incorrect spelling , less silly sentences and in less time . The program will help your English writing skills , just like it 's done for me . But do not ever underestimate your patience in this case , trust me . 
I can agree with the opinion that always the truth is important to some extent . In general , being an honest and reliable person is very important and , nowadays , it can be a rare . That 's why these people are mostly very appreciated by others . In my opinion , when you are such a person , you are probably wise and intelligent . Therefore , you know that there are situations where telling a lie is almost necessary . I have in mind moments when telling a lie does not hurt a second person . Moreover , he or she might be thankful after he figures out what you did that . Sometimes , you need to tell a lie to avoid bothering another person . It can happen when you or somebody else is very seriously sick . When the person whom you told a lie cannot do anything maybe for him/her , it would be better because he/she does not change anything and only he/she would be furious or get mad . There is something like a lie with a good intention . In my opinion , telling a lie is in general a bad idea , but there are many exceptions when doing that is not bad and even though that person after time finds out about this , he will forgive you without a doubt . A lie is a bad thing when you use it as a way to achieve something . 
First of all , I have two computers . I use them both every day . I do my work with my computer , analysis , reports and presentations . During the Corona virus pandemic my computer became very important for me , because it was possible for me to work from home . You really have a lot of possibilities with computers . Currently I like to use my laptop for learning English . 
I really like and enjoy exercising . I was signed up in a gym . Unfortunately I do not have enough time to go to the gym regularly . Right now I have found out a new way to exercise outside . I am more flexible . I do not have to go to the gym , so I wo not waste time on it . My favourite exercise is lunges , because you can do them anywhere and they are so effective . 
I must definitely improve my English . I have to do a lot of things to improve it . It 's in a really bad shape . I try to read as much as possible . Then I try to use " Write&Improve " as much as possible . Last but not least , I talk with my language friends from all over the world . 
If I had to pick one kind of teacher , I would say that both teachers definitely need good quality in student education . A teacher doing lessons for the same students for several years could create a stronger relationship between students and between the students and him and deeper knowledge in specific topics . In biology , for example , the learning process is recommended to be guided by just one teacher . Importantly , the teacher must be a good one . Other classes would be better if they were taught by different teachers , such as art and politics , because the students can understand and learn with more diversity of points of view . To compare art with biology , the heart is to keep the blood flowing , is an opinion shared by any biologist , instead the origin of a political problem could change from one teacher to another to a huge extent , depending on who is teaching it . These are my reasons to respond that mixing both teachers is the better option . 
Having the same teacher offers a lot advantages . The same person can follow you , your development and results over a longer period of time . The relationship between you should be better and the teacher can evaluate the students even better . On the other hand , if the relationship is badly affected , then it 's difficult to repair . You ca not easily change the opinion of somebody . The conclusion is that the teacher may not want to help you because of a bad experience . The second proposal was having a new teacher each year . I like this idea because it 's not common and this is the first time I have heard of it . It would also give a lot of chances . As a student , you will meet a few teachers during your schooldays . Some will stimulate you more and some maybe less . You will have experienced more teacher skills and approaches . In the end , you will have a wide range and you can choose what you like most . I am always for changes and I would choose changing the teacher each year , to gain more experience with this approach . Some day you will be able to assess both approaches . 
Since I was born , I have been fat . My mom said to me that I used to eat so much . I was told that I could not behave like a thin person . Sometimes I used to fall side ou I always used to look at the food when I was baby . That 's interesting , is not it ? When I was growing up , I did not stop gaining weight or I did not lose weight . I used to try to go on a diet , but it never worked out . However , it did not work out because I did not use to follow the diet correctly . Today , I 'm 23 and I 've found out that doing some exercises can be good for us and for our mind . Yes , you read that correctly . I was reading an article and in it was written that when you do some exercise , it might help your mind to remember what you have seen or what you have read . Plus , it might help you to save more information in your mind , mainly if you are a student . Of course , you need to separate some time every day for working out . That 's all for now ! 
Hi Leyla , Firstly , I would like to apologize to you because I could not go to your birthday party . I was already prepared to go there but there was a case at my home . My mother got suddenly ill on that day . So , we went to the hospital immediately with my family to get treatment for her . We were worried about her and wanted her to get well soon . Fortunately , she became after two days later . Are you free the coming weekend ? If you are free , I want to invite you to go to a restaurant for dinner next weekend . See you soon ! Kai 
My favourite season is the summer . In this season , our long distance families come together . We celebrate the togetherness of our families and I love their company , especially Aunt Juliean . Aunt Julien has a lot of for me . She makes chocolate cookies for me . I eat most of the cookies during the summer . Apart from my aunt 's company , there is Christ who is of my age . We play most of the time throughout the summer and become so exhausted that we even sleep on floor . After one crazy month , our families go to a big farm house . This farm house belongs to our great -grandparents . In the farm house neighbourhood , there is a precious river . Sometimes , we go there and make a camp to spend night on the riverside . The view of the beautiful night is reflected on the river , which makes this whole movement unforgettable . Then we hit back to our home city with these special summer memories . This makes the summer season the most special for me , as well as for my loving family . 
Let us start by considering the facts : volunteer work is done by people who accept to do something themselves without any forcing . Just by reading the word ' volunteer " s meaning , we figure out that some schools might forget or ignore the consistency of what they require their students to do . Obviously , volunteer work benefits many things and people , it 's very respectful if you are a part of it , but it 's acceptable if you feel like refusing , that 's all your choice . One very important thing , you are not supposed to give anyone help , if you do , that 's just kind of you . There is not even just a minimum mistake here , you 'll simply not be able to receive a ' thank -you ' word . Everything would be better if schools encouraged students to apply for volunteer work fields , but never a requirement which breaks up the originally adorable meaning of that word . Especially , I would never agree with them classifying students for graduation by some work they have all their decisions to do , it should be something extra , like a useful back - up , to their graduating paths . That completely makes sense . 
Hello everyone , I thank you for your question . I think animals belong in nature , especially the forest , because they are creations and they have feelings like every human being . The fact is that some people like giving their opinions without any idea about the issue . An example of this is that some people think animals are a good learning subject ! I 'll try to explain some things with an example . When a student wants to learn , he goes to school , to the teacher , to the university and to the library . The teacher and the university wo not be taken to the student . The same thing should happen when people learn about animals . The animals should be visited by people , to be able to behave naturally . If you put a bird into a cage to cage him , you wo not learn about him , but rather you want persecute him , because you cannot force some animals to learn about them . In the end , I hope that people will feel one time that animals have feelings like people and maybe more than people . Thank you . Ahmad . 
It is said that 80 percent of a language is vocabulary and only 20 percent is grammar , so this is often overlooked , although it is equally important . Being supported by teachers in face -to -face lessons will help to clarify any issues and even push students beyond their limits because they can impart some personalised advice . Studying a language largely based on online lessons requires a high level of self -discipline and self -motivation . In terms of flexibility , it may be an advantage , as different time zones or suffering from illnesses do not matter . Owing to the fact that the easiest way of internalising a language is being surrounded by it , it is highly recommended to stay abroad to boost the progress of learning . This can also be a once -in -a -lifetime experience that students always like to reminisce about . To sum up , difficulties may arise no matter which method you choose , but drive and determination coupled with patience and perseverance will lead to success . Keeping this in mind , do not expect to run before you can walk . 
