Have you ever had a friend who is able to play at least one kind of musical instrument ? Yes , you might have . Did you find out that they tend to do everything which has to use brainstorming much faster and with better results ? Experts would say that studying music helps them . So , a yes from me . I totally agree that students should study music , it not only benefits their studying , but it also works for some certain situations in their daily lives . When we start to know more about music , it could be a little hard for some , but when you keep playing with it , you will no longer feel like doing homework , but like making friends . The point is that you will finish a thing you have never done before , there is no reason for the smarter brain you get after achieving another skill . You might not use music as your life -long job , but you should learn it as the right support : Firstly , it 's helpful for your concentration . When you 're studying to read a song or trying to remember the chords to play a song on the guitar , you 're required to completely focus on it because you wo not want to break up beautiful pieces of music into chaotic sections . Yes , you need to learn how to be wholy a part of the song you 're playing or creating . Next , I do not think you would say that you have never been stressed out by your job , even if you really love the job . Surely , you can listen to your favourite music to make a balance between work and living life , but if you can play a song for yourself instead , it works even better . Is it wrong when I 've just said it is the right support for your career path ? Besides , do you agree that working or studying with a very good memory is something you are quite jealous of when someone has it ? You would go from the attempt of getting each musical note into your head or each complex rhythm of some hard song to back up , which you can use whenever in your work with the aim to make things more convenient . Does it sound great ? Do you fancy applying to a music class today ? 
Nowadays , most people share the viewpoint that music is not a trustworthy choice when deciding a professional career , in spite of that , music lessons should not be forgotten or ignored , as music provides a great amount of benefits to people of any age . Firstly , it is undeniable that music may seem to be not as relevant as other subjects at school , which could be maths , history or biology , for example ; however , some research about music and learning how to play an instrument easy to handle , have asserted that it can help children to improve their bodily skills , memory , social habits ... Secondly , the amount of music lessons students have is an important point to consider since , given the irrefutable advantages of music , it is also true that music cannot be a prime subject . Therefore , it would be reasonable for students to enjoy from 1 to 3 music lectures per week . Last but not least , the obligation of studying that subject should be mentioned too , because music should not be a mandatory subject in every school year . Instead , students may study it mandatorily only one course so they have more general knowledge , and from then onwards , it is advised to give them the opportunity to choose if they want to continue their music studies or not . In conclusion , from my point of view , everybody should be enabled to know their study preferences in order to choose what subject pleases them more , and music , cannot be excluded from that list . 
Today 's generation is inclined towards the routine of indolence , which is hazardous for health . Being involved in sports might help students to be physically fit and active in any kind of performance , whether it is taking part in competitions or studies . Educational institutions are concerned about the physical fitness of students for their betterment and healthy lifestyle . I totally agree with the statement that schools must inculcate sports activities into young people . To commence with , it is true that sports help the young generation to build the strength to participate in various activities . It also leads them towards a healthy routine , which curbs sedentary behaviour in any field . Moreover , it can be seen that people who are involved in sports or do regular exercise are more active than those who only sit and enjoy food or stick to their phone . In addition to this , sports activities also build self -confidence in students , which helps them to achieve their goals . On the other hand , today 's generation is clinging to technology or mobile phones , due to which , they got possessive of their gadgets . Most of the study material is available on mobile phones . However , it restricts them from outdoor activities . Furthermore , this sedentary behaviour leads them towards health issues , such as obesity , anxiety , mental depression . As a result , adults get addicted to the consumption of alcohol , smoking or other substances . Thus , to deal with these situations and to make the youth more , active parents should encourage their children to take part in sports from an early age . And school plays a vital role in promoting these activities because it is the place from where we adopt habits . Having considered all the above points , I totally agree that educational institutions should impose exercise classes or sports events for the evasion of unhealthy diets and a sedentary lifestyle . It is difficult for most of the children to adopt these habits ; nevertheless , it is not impossible to obtain in our daily routine . 
Personally , I see that books should be replaced by technological devices in many fields , especially for educational purposes . First , technology provides us with easier access to information , with no limits . Indeed , search engines allow students to look for explanations , research and studies . Besides , schools and universities are using smart devices to facilitate teaching and education . Studies prove that teaching lessons with tablets and computers is more efficient than it is using books . Added to that , despite the fact that books are the roots of the internet , I believe that the web gives pupils the chance to discover the wide world of lessons , by learning new stuff in a shorter period than by using books and papers . Finally , I think that computers and tablets simplify education more than books do and therefore they should be replaced by technological devices in schools and universities . 
