Television is one of the most popular electronic devices used in the family . Obviously , the entertainment purpose is accountable for its popularity . Moreover , I believe television can be used as an educational tool which people can use to learn new things . There are a variety of programmes on TV , such as news , travel , food , etc ... and people could learn from them . For example , news programmes provide information about the world . By watching them , we are aware of what is happening around us . We know about the places , countries or the topics mentioned in the news . Some programmes are very beneficial , especially for children . Take animal programmes as an example . By watching them , children can learn about animals in the wild without actually going into the wild . This is a very convenient and safe way to learn . Sitting in front of the TV after a tiring day to relax is a very common activity , which might entertain and educate at the same time . 
Nowadays , unhealthy food and lazy lifestyles have become so popular among all the age groups , which is affecting the health and their next generation . It is argued that all students should be pushed forcefully to take part in sports games at least 3 times a week . I agree with this because those activities would help people to live a healthy life and are important for students to focus and concentrate . Even though it is true that sports activities take a lot of one 's time , I think these activities are very important for all the individuals , especially for students . One reason for this is that it would lead to them losing weight and leading a much healthier and happier life , so in the long run , they would enable them to be an active individual . To illustrate this , recently , Norway implemented strict rules and regulations for all high school students to play games on any three days a week . This has had a dramatic effect on keeping their weight under control . Another reason they are necessary is that students can achieve better results in exams . This is because exercise will make the students tired , so they can get some sound sleep at night . This would let them to focus on their classes and understand the subjects better . As a result , they can perform better in class tests and in final exams and , eventually , get a well -paid job . For example , there is some evidence to suggest that pupils aged between 10 and 15 who play any game do far better in exams than those who do not do any type of activity . To conclude , although students might not find sports games interesting , I think it is important because students can live a beautiful and happy life . Also , they can achieve better marks in schools and universities . 
