Hardly one week goes by without an article about an adventurous person who is trying or has managed to break a record in sports or in any other competitive area . Who is the best , the richest , the fastest or the most beautiful one ? It seems that these successes make the new standard which we should be able to achieve if we work hard enough and dream big enough . Characteristically for this approach , there is also the ongoing trend of self -help books and videos with catching titles , such as " how to be successful in one month " or " how to get rich in only one year . " Those titles attract a customer who has the self -impression of not being sufficient . Normal life has transformed into " the life you had before you lived the better life . " Personally , I would enjoy living a nice regular life and fill my 100 years with reading or walking through summery forests . Intensity should not be mistakenly seen as happiness . To live an enjoyable life is a myriad challenge , if not the greatest of all . During my 100 years , I will have to overcome many hurdles , which will make some days less brighter than others , but in the end , I will look back to my summery forest walks and the many books I will have read and the many inspiring conversations , and surely not think about how boring it was . 
Firstly , I think some university students decide to move away in order to be more independent and to start to live on their own . That is , these students want to have more privacy and more control of their own lives . According to much research , these students may be more prepared when they have to live without parental support . In other words , they might deal better with adulthood . However , it all depends on how the parents have raised their children and , consequently , how the students will deal with the university environment . Another key fact to remember is that the university environment is not always pleasant and , sometimes , it can be traumatic for some people due to prank calls , low support and other things . In conclusion , there is no universal answer for the question about students moving away when they go to the university . To put it more simply , there is no commonly better choice , because it must be decided in each situation . 
