I think it is better for students to have the same teacher for several years . Students and teachers all need time to be familiar to each other . There is a period for each to adapt . If students change teacher every year , they will always be spending time in the loop . For teachers , it 's important to know the ability , character and personality of every student . With this information , teachers can then use proper methods to teach different types of students . For students who lack confidence in their ability , the teacher might create attainable goals . For students who lack interest in studies , the teacher might use interesting ways to make it fun . There is a proverb , teach students according to their aptitude . For students , it takes time to adapt to the teaching style of a teacher . Some teachers focus on class communication , while others focus on homework . Students usually perform better after they are used to the schedule . That 's why I think it 's a better way for students to have the same teacher for several years . 
Nowadays , we have two groups of people . One group prefers to lead a calm life , in small cities . Mostly , they try not so stress too much , therefore they live longer . At the same time , the other one chooses to have an intense life , with loads of changes , it provides their lives with loads of fun and joy . Nevertheless , changes are related to stress , which might be one of the reasons for premature death . According to personal factors , everyone chooses which one he or she prefers . Living a long and calm life might be a dream for lots of people . Even though following businesses and careers is popular nowadays , some people prefer to lead their lives in a different way . They prefer to spend time with their families , have a non -stressing job and enjoy the little things they have . However , sometimes , those people might get bored and get into a routine with their lives . Living an intense life might make some people feel happy , but for some , it could be overwhelming . I think enjoying each of the days and not being bored is a domene of people who have an intense life . By doing something they love , they fulfill their passions and dreams . Nevertheless , in some cases , a high pace of life might lead to stress and disorders that might interfere with plans of living a long life . Taking everything into consideration , I think I would choose to live a longer without loads of stress , because I like being healthy . 
