Both choices have their own pros and cons . Moving away from family might seem like living in freedom , interesting and exciting , yet the reality is not like we expected . We have to manage ourselves to live healthily and organized . Otherwise , we will not be able to do well in university and it could cause our grades collapse . But as we usually know , the pro is we will have more freedom to explore anything we want . We can also use this opportunity to practice living alone for the future because we cannot live with our parents forever . Living with family while attending universities is great for those who want to focus on studying . Our family can keep our needs in control , so we do not need to worry about our economy nor our daily needs . But watch out , we cannot have such freedom like if we were living on our own . I prefer to move and live on my own because this whole life is about challenge and experiences . I think by moving and living on my own , I could explore more things and enjoy the transition of my life . I believe that I could manage things well and it will not cause any disruption to my academic studies . 
