What are my reasons for learning English ? I had to think about this question while I was studying English , because I felt that I was losing my motivation and not performing as I should . After thinking , I found that I study English for the following reasons . First , I want to learn English because I need to access the massive content written in that language . As we all know , English is the most spoken language in the world , and in it a large amount of content , such as books , movies , etc . , has been produced . By being able to read and understand English , I can easily consume the information and learn from it and that will greatly help me succeed in my life . Second , English has become the language of business , and anyone who wants to do business on a global scale has to learn it . Due to the development of transportation methods and communication , it became possible to trade with other organizations from different countries , and for successful interaction , there must be a common language between the two parties . English happened to be that language . In the end , people could learn English for various reasons . For me , I noticed that there are a lot of materials written in English that interest me . Additionally , I would like to be able to communicate with international businesses . 
An old Chinese curse states : I wish you to live in curious times . We all definitely live in curious times now . Everything changed in 2019 when the coronavirus pandemic started . We will face the consequences for a long time . How could it affect our ways of travelling ? One thing is certain , it will not be the same . First of all , in 2021 , we may still be forced to focus on domestic trips . Before the roll -out of the vaccine , there will be obstacles in crossing borders . I expect that the situation may go back to normality in early 2022 . Secondly , the costs of plane tickets may rise dramatically . A lot of airlines went bust and those that continue operating may be forced to cut their losses . Apart from that , even before the pandemic , some people claimed that we should not use planes because of the environmental issues . Does it mean that we will stay at home ? I do not think so . Maybe we will switch to electric cars and trains ? We 'll see soon . 
Poland is a country where we struggle to improve the health system . A lot of things have changed but there is still a lot to do . One of the most serious issues is the lack of medical doctors in rural areas . They usually prefer to work in big agglomerations or even go abroad to countries like Sweden , Germany and the United Kingdom . What is the reason for this situation ? In my opinion , the main cause is the salary . In rural areas , doctors usually earn less than those who work in big cities . Secondly , life in rural areas is less interesting . Doctors study at universities which are located in big cities and they are used to the hustle and bustle . Living in a small village may seem very boring at first glance . What can be done about this ? I believe there are several options possible . First of all , our government should raise the salary for the doctors who decided to move to remote areas of the country . Secondly , there should be investments made in the infrastructure . Fast trains and good roads would allow us to travel fast to all of the big cities . 
I have watched many films in the past , and I have a few that I like more that others . If I have to choose one to be my favorite , it would be Leon the Professional . It was filmed in the 90s in New York City and has an unusual and interesting story that made it to the top of the list of favorite movies . The movie begins in an apartment building in one of New York 's neighbourhoods , and in it there is a family that hardly can be called a family . There was frequent shouting and arguments , nobody got along with the others . It is not surprising when it becomes known that the father is involved in illegal activities with criminals and corrupt policemen . One day , the corrupt policemen invaded the building and broke into the apartment . They searched every room in the apartment looking for drugs that they had given to the father . As soon as they learned that he did not have the drugs , everyone was murdered without mercy , even a small child . Right before the policemen arrived in front of the building , a young girl , who was about 8 years old , had just left her troubled family to get a break from all the negative energy and also to get some milk . She was lucky , but she still needed to return to her family . She had no other place to go . While she was entering the building , she felt that something was wrong . She could hear a noise that was not familiar . She continued cautiously , and when she approached the door of her apartment , there was a well -built man carrying a machine gun . Frightened , she did not stop and continued walking straight on , passing her apartment door . She peeked and saw her father on the floor covered in blood . She knew what had happened , but tried her best not to show any emotion , or she would also be killed . While walking , a door blocked her way . It was a neighbour 's apartment door . After a moment of hesitation , she knocked on the door a few times and waited for rescue . As she was losing hope of escaping that tough situation , the door opened . She felt like it was the door of heaven . It was Leon who opened the door , a professional hit man . He was watching the whole event and knew what had happened to her family . He saved her , but he was now responsible for her as she had nobody . How could a hit man take care of a child whose entire family had just been murdered ? You need to watch the movie see what happens next . 
A great number of university students live far from home and live independently . However , other ones live at home with their family members . I am of the opinion that students who live far from home have a greater chance of developing their soft skills , and this essay will outline a couple of reasons . To begin with , living independently has been commonly regarded as an essential element in a person 's development because of its beneficial impact on other aspects of the person . A student living far from home must adopt their surroundings by expanding a wide range of relationships with other counterparts and getting used to a series of unexpected situations revolving mainly around financial burdens . Having multiple practical experiences helps the student become stronger and confident , not only in school life but also on a societal level . Besides , the university period offers students , especially those who live far from home , numerous wonderful opportunities , like either getting a part -time job or being involved in a voluntary campaign , to develop their soft skills including presentation and team -working , which are really essential after graduation . Without the time restriction from parents , a living far from home student in university could spend hours hanging out or studying in a group with other students , which helps bridge the gap between them and constitutes long -standing relationships not only in academic settings but also in the far -distant future . In conclusion , although university students living independently face numerous emerging situations due to the lack of their relatives , this also offers multiple amazing chances . Getting a part -time job and acquiring long -standing relationships helps the students become mature . 
Firstly , I think that volunteer work should be a requirement to graduate in all the schools because there are several benefits to this type of activity . For example , it 's an opportunity to learn about new subjects , including things outside of your social environment . In addition , some American research from Michingan University stated that people who do volunteer work live about four years more . Similarly , more research proved that volunteer workers have a better balance between their professional and personal lives and , consequently , less stress and more positive energy . Despite many people saying it 's a waste of time , volunteer work can change people 's minds in a good way by making them be more sensitive and , therefore , understand better the social problems . In conclusion , a certain amount of volunteer work can be very helpful in order to develop better the students as human beings , because that is also included in the school missions . 
Technological development is our present and it will be our future . For this reason , it will surely influence the way we travel nowadays , hoping that it will make it better . Over the years , experts and engineers have focused their knowledge and capabilities on artificial intelligence , that will lead the world 's logistics in the future . One of the most important examples is automatic drive ( or smart drive ) , which is the idea ( and actually the present ) of automatic cars and vehicles . This technology will not only change our own vehicles , but will change public transport too . In fact , in the next years , we will probably be able to find automatic cabs or buses that wo not need a driver , making the transport more efficient and quicker . On the other hand , also , private cars will have the possibility to be driven by a specific automatic system , which will make the streets safer than now and reduce the risks related to driving . 
The school of the future Have you ever thought about what schools in the future will be like ? As a teacher I ’ve always asked myself what the school in the future will be like . The world is in a constant change . Medicine , communication and education have changed as well . We know that the system of education needs to be innovated . Firstly , with the new technologies and the internet , everyone has easy access to information about everything . In consequence , teachers wo not be the only source of information , so they will become a guide . Secondly , abilities like public speaking will be more important than academic knowledge . However , abilities wo not supplant academic preparation and you ’ll still have to learn mathematics , science or history . So , professional certificates will be important , but they will never be as important as an academic qualifications . To sum up , the educational system needs to link to the needs of a changing society . We have more access to information and we can learn things on our own , but a professional degree and help from teachers will always be important and essential . 
