In my opinion , in the future , schools will follow the technological developments that are characterizing our world . I imagine a totally digital school , where books will be replaced by computers and everything will be faster than now . Schools may become smart facilities fit for the didactic aim , with digital features or digital functions which will be useful for students . For example , there could be digital courses mixed with normal courses , or a more specific didactic that will teach how to use robots or how to work with them . So , I think over the years , students will be smarter and more competent than now , so there will be a greater society . On the other hand , I think that some things will be the same as now . For example , school will still include the human contact between students and teachers wo not be completely replaced by computers or robots , in order to make schools still composed by a human aspect . 
To begin with , I am going to talk about if I believe that television can entertain and also educate . On the one hand , I consider that television should be more educational , because it is possible that some types of programmes can distort reality . Younger people believe that it is possible to earn money by doing anything . On the other hand , I consider that nowadays television is changing , especially the programmes . For example , there is a new show called " El Condesador de Fluzo " and I think it is perfect for understanding history or to discover new things . In addition , the people who go on the show explain things very well . In this show , there are writers , comedians and historians of all kinds . To sum up , I would like to say that I really think that television is changing for the better , especially for young people to not fall into stereotypes . 
In my opinion , television is a good vehicle to educate , but it is often bad in that aim . In fact , there are programs that could be very diseducative for young people , which could give a bad vision of the world , such as gossip programs or violent cartoons and series , but also with programs that include bad language that could influence people that watch them . On the other hand , television has great features that could make it great for education , such as the news , film channels , sport 's channels and so on . But I think that nowadays people are looking for something different from television . For example , people prefer using the internet and its features to search for something that they do not know , learn new languages or discover new things every day . In conclusion , I think that television is a valid educational vehicle , but it will be replaced by digitalization soon . 
