Is it important to always tell the truth ? I would say yes , but not in every situation . One thing for sure , how much we trust in one person depends on amount of believable presentation and the possibility they can give us . Each activity or relationship in our society is formed based on a platform of the belief we create for ourselves and for others . There might be some times we spend seeking somewhere we prefer to be part of and will never or be in little doubt about the people surrounding . Living in an environment of truth is the guarantee for always being clear about social systems and the transparency of any relationship . It 's definitely a view of life we all have been trying to build in . NA , . I know we had been taught to tell the truth since very early childhood , that was a basic installment for the awareness of any situations later . Growing up and whenever we refuse the truth with some certain situations , we are likely to feel apologetic and regrettable . On other hand , it is also important to sometimes not tell the truth . In some circumstances , we are required to lie to someone if this benefits them . I remember it is called a ' white lie ' , which is forgiven without guilt as you find it the most possible selection to apply . If your lie does not take a toll on anything or anybody , it is fine to use it then , but you should accept that one thing significant is that you may be less believable later in life . This is definitely a drawback . Taking all factors mentioned into account , telling the truth plays a key role in our lives and society . But it is completely acceptable to tell a lie depending on the circumstances and we need to assure that you have a positive reason to do it . 
I believe having different teachers can bring benefits to the students . First of all , each teacher transfers knowledge to the student using a unique methodology . So , if the student has only one teacher for several years , this student wo not learn different things in different ways . Second , different teachers are able to share many points of view or perspectives about one topic . It can help the students to develop critical sense and evolve their thoughts . If the student has only one teacher for several years , this student will begin , sooner or later , to mimic the thoughts of his teacher . Third , if the student has many teachers for several years , it can help the student set up his character , because the student can observe , analyze and then decide what is right and what is wrong and how each teacher handles different situations . Furthermore , having many teachers , you wo not become bored . To sum up , having many teachers has more pros than cons . 
I have heard that you , as town council , are thinking about banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants . I think this idea needs to be analyzed carefully . Firstly , due to the increasing use of mobile phones in public spaces , some American research stated that people are losing the ability to have a real conversation . As evidence , nowadays , it 's common to go to a restaurant and see people around the table , all of them just using their cell phones without talking to each other . In other words , people are becoming so increasingly addicted to mobile phones that they are not paying attention to the real world . Therefore , banning the use of cell phones in these places would force them to strike up a conversation with someone and be more aware of their surroundings . Despite this , the use of mobile phones has allowed people to contact someone quicker . For this reason , cell phones can be very helpful to get people in touch , especially in emergencies . These emergencies embrace all kinds , such as work and health emergencies . In sum , banning completely the use of mobile phones in public spaces , like restaurants , shops and on public transport , is not the right choice to make . In my opinion , the use should be permitted only in emergencies , because it 's impossible to ignore some of the benefits of cell phones in modern life . 
