I think both options are very good . I like it when I can experience different types of learning . When you have only one teacher , he knows you very well . When he likes you , he will probably give you good grades . The problem is when he does not like you , he will give you bad marks . I like when your teacher switches throughout the school years . You get to know different views about a topic . Moreover , you have a new chance every time to get good marks , because it is always a new start . The teacher gets to know you . I think the best length is for about three years . In this time , you can get to know your teacher and the other way round . Moreover , you know how the class tests are structured and you can prepare well . In the Abitur you get a test , which is not from your teacher . Therefore it is good when the teacher changes throughout the years . 
