In my opinion , everything should be digitalized in the next years . In fact , carrying only a computer or a tablet with every book and every note is much easier than carrying heavy books every day . Having digitalized books also makes you learn faster , because you can easily switch from the book to the notepad , or underline or delete when you want . On the other hand , having a computer or a tablet could be useful to be connected to the internet . For example , with digitalized books , you are able to search for a word whose meaning you did not understand and you will be able to do research to increase your knowledge in an easy way . I think that in the future , schools will be completely digitalized and also books will follow this path , making the school world faster and smarter than it is nowadays . 
My favorite indoor activity is reading . Reading for me is fun and interesting because I can learn about many things : stories , lives , cultures . I was reading yesterday . 
It is the start of a new school year at my school . And my English teacher asked me to write a report about what I want to achieve this new school year . So this is my report . At the start of a new school year at my school , I have a lot of things to achieve . There are so many things that I want to achieve this new school year , that I do not know where to start . The first thing I want to say is the areas of my learning I am pleased with , that is the good facilities that the school gives me , the library is also very good and very modern . Those are the areas of my learning I am pleased with . Next are the areas of my learning I want to improve . In these areas , I want to improve a lot of things . The most important thing that I want to improve is my studying . I want to be the best student in the major that I am studying in my school , but also the hardest thing that I have to do to make it come true , I gonna try my best to make it come true . To achieve those things , I am going to work hard every single day . 
Hi Matt , It was great to hear from you . We 'll see each other next week , great news . That 's right , I should improve my English . This year , I am determined to reach a new English level . For that reason , this summer I have developed a plan . If I wish to reach my goals , I 'll have to follow it . I 'm going to focus my studies on three different topics : talking , reading and writing . Firstly , I talk every day with Jenny , she 's my English teacher . Secondly , every Saturday I read an essay to acquire , therefore I am reaching a really good habilities with that issue . And thirdly , I watch movies in English without subtitles . In conclusion , I have decided to achieve my goals , therefore I should follow my plan . All the best , 
Recently , a lot of schools have been adopting new solutions in order to create possibilities for students to learn practical skills . Some of them allow pupils to do some voluntary work during class time . Is this a reasonable solution ? It has become a subject which is discussed by newspapers and on TV programs . I will try to present reasons for and against in the essay below . The main reason that supports students doing volunteer work is that they can actually help in places where this kind of help is needed . I mean places like hospitals , shelters and hospices . There is always something more that could be done there . Each additional helping hand counts . The next reason is that students can gain extra experience by helping other people . I honestly believe that one cannot learn such skills in school . In my opinion , these skills may be very useful after graduation . Also , having volunteer work in your CV may be a factor that will decide about getting a job . Employers usually prefer candidates who have such experience . What about the reasons against ? I find a very few indeed . But , you can always say that students should not be forced to do volunteer work if they do not want to . I guess this is supposed to be a free decision of each person . Somebody forced is never a good employee . To summarize , in my opinion , schools should allow students to help in hospitals , shelters , etc . But , it always has to be a free decision of each pupil and his parents . 
What do you think about learning other languages ? I remember the date when I felt a special interest in learning English and why it became one of my goals . I ’ve always had a special interest in learning English , but once , when I was on a school trip , some English people asked me for help and I was not able to help them , so because of my lack of knowledge of English , I could not make friends . In addition to that , I want to get a better job and English skills give you advantages to get one . One thing to consider is the fact that the English language is one of the most spoken languages in the world and if I could develop English skills , I ’d be able to travel , meet new people and also get work abroad . It has became one of my most important aims . To sum up , my strong interest in being able to travel abroad , to get to know the world , make lots of friends and get better employment opportunities , have taken me on this journey to learn English . 
Learning to speak a foreign language is not really important these days . If you speak an Arabic language and you go to France , you do not need to learn their language to understand . You can translate what they 're saying with your mobile phone . Everything has improved these days . Even if you want to learn a foreign language , it is way easier to learn than in the past . In the past , learning a foreign language was important because there were no mobile phones that translate quickly , so you needed to learn the language to understand . Even now , some foreign languages can be useful for you . If you want to live in France , you must learn the language , or you wo not be able to speak to people . Speaking to people is so useful as it helps your mental health to be better and to make new friends . 
I have had a lot of holidays with my family since I was a kid , but the holiday that I think was the best holiday ever with my family was maybe 9 years ago and now I ca not remember the details of that holiday out . So I think I am going to tell you about a holiday when me and my whole family went to an island . It was such a beautiful island , the beach and the scenery were so fantastic . Everyone in my family had a lot of memorable memories that they ca not forget . Me and my family spend seven days on the island , enjoying and sharing moments together . The food was also very good too . Everything seemed to be really fun and also unforgettable . I do not have anything more to say , because there is nothing more to tell you , because I do not know how to tell you . The feeling on that holiday with my family was so fantastic , that I do not know how to express the feeling to you . It is very hard to express feelings for others to understand , and I am bad at this . But I hope you can understand that feeling . 
I have had a class discussion on the importance of exercise . Now my teacher has asked me to write a composition answering whether it is good or not for our health to do exercise every day . In my opinion , doing exercise every day is very good for our health . But everything has two sides , the good one and the bad one . On the good side , doing exercise every single day is very good for our health . Doing exercise can give us good health and mental alertness , that can help us have more concentration in our life . It can also give us a better life if we can do exercise every single day . Doing exercise every day can make us better at our job and our things . In this way , we can see the benefits of daily exercise are numerous . On the bad side , if you do not do exercise in a scientific way , it will be bad for your health and maybe it will endanger your life . So before beginning to do daily exercise , we should research the suitable way for us to do exercise effectively without any danger . 
In my vision , it is most effective to work in an open space that has no walls to separate workers from their colleagues . Some people say that they can concentrate on their job by working alone . But , I think that it is not efficient for both them or their co -workers . I have two points about this . First of all , talking to each other while working is important , more than working quietly . I do not mean that they can talk about anything without job like their hobbies . I want to say that people working in open spaces are able to help one another . Then , helping each other with working leads not only to efficiency , but also to making relationships between them . So , it is the best way to work in an open space . Secondly , workers can be eager to work by seeing their colleague working . If they work in separated rooms , they are possibly focusing on their job but cannot see other workers working . On the other hand , in open spaces , there are people working arduously wherever and whenever they see around them . So , individuals in the office will want to work with their co -workers and it generates a multiplier effect . Lastly , all in all , I described two points about my idea why it is better to work in open design offices than in separated offices . Recently , we have been able to see many changes about how to work . Then , there is diversity working in present society . So , we will have to adapt to working styles in the future . 
Hi , I 'm very sorry to hear that you had an accident last week . Are you okay ? I can bring you some interesting books when I visit the hospital . Do you like history books or comics ? I will probably visit you this weekend . If there is anything I can do for you , please let me know . See you then . 
Dear Matt , Hi my friend , I was glad to receive your email . I have found some methods that help me improve my English . I read an English book every Saturday and also collect new vocabulary every day . It was really hard at first , but now I feel comfortable with it . I hope I can communicate with you better and you can understand me : ) I ca not wait to see you on Monday . Xoxo , Tan 
