Everybody loves to travel . It does not matter if you go to either surrounding cities or travel abroad . Most things will continue the same , like if you do not make your list about where you 'd like to go , you will end up hiring a service for the trip that you 'd like to go on . Well , according to specialists , we will have faster transport than we have nowadays , it will be more spacious and more comfortable . Besides than , hiring this transport might be easier . If you schedule a trip on time , you might hire that transport in that moment . Or even cancel any trip on time . And you will receive your money back with no problem . Besides all of that , what 's your opinion about the environment ? What about hiring a means of transport that uses electricity rather than gasoline ? You 're not reading another thing ! All transport could be more sustainable . Those are incredible things , are not they ? And so , are you prepared for the future and to contribute the development of the world ? See you in 2050 ! 
Both ways to sleep work for me , but if I have to choose one I 'd take the first one since you get to sleep faster and you do not need any help to fall asleep . And , the second way to sleep you 'd need more time to fall asleep due to the noise . But , when you have had a tough day at work or school you do not mind if there are any noises , lights or whatever , when you lie down , instantly you fall asleep . 
English has become a must -know language for most people who want to have a better life , a decent job , etc . Therefore , many people have tried to learn it . Some people choose to learn by going to English Centers , others choose to learn through the Internet . When you use the second method , you may be confused because there are too many platforms for you to choose from . Today , I will recommend you a new platform , which has just been released recently , Write and Improve . The name says everything . The main feature of this tool is to improve your writing skills . That 's right . There are many lessons divided into specific levels : Beginner , Intermediate and Advanced . It also has the lessons to help you in your IELTS exam . That 's cool , right ? When you finish any task , click check and then wait for the error checking system to check your result . It will tell you what should be changed , what is necessary or not ... And then , you can check again to see if the changes you made are good or not . But , nothing is perfect . This tool is not an exception . I have tried using it for a week and , sometimes , I had a problem with the error checking system . Sometimes , it did not work well . For example , in a task , I used the word " Complain " and it recognized that one was not correct (???) Another thing I think is a drawback of this tool is that some of the tasks are not necessary . For example , it has a task that tells you to write about the experience you got after helping at a pop concert . I do not think many people did that thing . In a nutshell , this tool has its pros and cons . The cons may make you confused sometimes but , in general , this is a good tool for people who want to improve their writing skills . 
It goes without saying that living a long and successful life is a craving every individual has . However , when it comes to choosing between having a long but calm life and a shorter but more intense one , no doubt I would stand for the second option . My thoughts about that matter are going to be displayed as follows . To begin with , I would like to point out some of the reasons why I would undoubtedly choose having a shorter but more exciting life instead of a long and calm one . Should there be something remarkable about our mere existence , it would be surely the fact that we all have just one life . Owing to that situation , life itself is unique and genuine for every single person , making it the most valuable treasure one has . We all are well aware that , at some point , our lives will get to an end . Perhaps because of that statement , I consider that , in terms of time , quality prevails over quantity , in the sense of the more experiences you have , the higher sensation of happiness you will feel . Nevertheless , some drawbacks should be mentioned concerning a shorter existence . By living less , not only will you miss the opportunity of witnessing how your children grow , but also you will not able to get to know how the future gets developed . Last but by no means least , I would like to conclude by bringing focus to the fact that no matter what your choice may be , the most pivotal thing is that you have to be who you want to be during your lifetime , whether you are understood or not , because that is how you will find the sense of belonging . 
Dear town council , I am writing to you regarding the issue of banning mobile phones on public transport , in shops , and restaurants . Although mobile phones have a lot of disadvantages , such as social disintegration , awful effects on health , and trespassing others ' privacy by taking pictures of them or recording their voices without getting their permission , we need to consider that phones are essential and cannot be disposed of or banned for several reasons . To begin with , phones are important to report any accident that may occur in public areas , like a car crash , a fire , a crime , and a severe health condition . In those situations , it is critical to contact the police or special forces to deal with the circumstances at once . Secondly , there are a lot of people that need to take calls at all times , like doctors , salesmen , policemen , parents ( in case their children need them ) , and in general , everybody . Prohibiting people from receiving urgent can result either in people not going to shops and restaurants , or causing protests to dwell in order to stop this ban . In addition , a lot of students use phones to listen to their recorded lectures or read a novel on their way to their destination on public transport . Preventing them from seizing their time and using it wisely will affect them badly . In the end , I believe that allowing mobile phones is the right decision for the comfort and safety of the people . Sincerely , Batool 
" Sitting on a chair , holding a book in my hands , I hear the rustling of leaves in the trees on a breezy night . Everything around me is calm as it used to be and as it is going to be until I die . " When imagining this scenario , I pray to god not to let my days be weary , and let me live enthusiastic , fierce , savage and delightful days that will render me in a thunderstorm of feelings and events , even if I had to pay a portion of my life in order to achieve that . How long we live is determined by how much we accomplish , and the amount of knowledge we leave to the generations that are going to follow us . If you asked me how much did Einstein , Disney and Edison live , I 'd tell you that they never died since their memory is going to live for ever . Such leading eminent figures have really lived their lives through every intense detail in it . Routine kills people , it makes them no better than animals that spend their lives doing the same things all over again . God granted humans with a brain to think , innovate , discover and change their lives to the better . For those reasons , I much prefer to live a whimsical life full of ups and downs , because thence I can consider myself alive . 
As you can see , nowadays , more and more medical doctors want to work in cities , where they will make a lot of money , instead of rural areas . This leads to the phenomenon of a lack of doctors in those places . So , what are the reasons for this problem ? How can it be solved ? This essay will examine the main reasons and suggest some solutions to solve them . One of the main culprits resulting in this common trend is the fact that the salary and benefit packages in urban hospitals are more attractive than in rural areas . People might have the tendency to choose a generously -paid job after working several years , medical doctors are not exception . They would prefer to contribute to city hospitals , where the amount of patients is enormous , which means they could get a higher salary . Another factor adding to this issue would be related to the disparity in living standards between cities and rural areas . Being a doctor is a heavy profession , hence those working in this field desire a deluxe lifestyle . They think they deserve to have it . So , how to solve this problem ? There are some solutions for this issue . One of them is that the government should enhance the fringe benefits for doctors who work in rural hospitals . In detail , bonuses could be rewarded to freshly graduated medical students if they chose to devote themselves to those institutes . In addition , workforce distribution should be taken into consideration . This means not all the doctors graduating from medical schools can work in their favorable places . It depends on their academic . In a nutshell , there are 2 reasons which have lead to the lack of medical doctors in the countryside : One , the disparity in living standards , salary , benefits between cities and rural areas . Two , their desire of having a deluxe lifestyle . If the government and individuals share collective responsibilities , it 's possible to solve this problem . 
It goes without saying that zoos have always been significant places where people get to know about animals , their habitats and the way they live . In this writing I am going to express my thoughts about that matter . To begin with , had it not been for zoos , we would not have been able to contemplate some animal species face -to -face . I cannot deny that this is definitely one of the main reasons why some people would agree that zoos are proper knowledge sources when it comes to understanding how animals live and behave . It is actually an interesting way to watch them and learn from them . Nevertheless , all that glitters is not gold . Lately , there has been an increase in the amount of people who claim zoos are not a fair method of analyzing animals , and I am in favor of this thought . In that spirit , it is often argued that , in places like zoos , not only is freedom taken from the animals , but also they live in terrible conditions . We should not allow that to happen . They are taken away from their natural environment , parted from their family members and used as entertainment , instead of living creatures with feelings . Last but by no means least , I would like to end by mentioning that there is actually a more respectful manner of enjoying animals , combining both , watching them face -to -face and respecting their lives , and these places are none other than safaris . 
Recently , I have tested a new tool called Write and Improve , which is a helpful tool developed by Cambridge English where we can practice and improve our writing capabilities . There are so many options for you to choose from , separated by some standard levels , which are beginner , intermediate and advanced . Moreover , you can write about business English and write just for fun , which is one of my favorite options . In addition , you can test yourself for IELTS , using Test Zone tab where you will find three options , which are IELTS Academic , IELTS General Training and B2 First . All of them are full of content to help you to get your certificate . If you access as a learner , you can see and track your tasks , and if you are a teacher , you can create some exercises for your students and check all of them . This shows how Write&Improve can be a helper for both sides of the learning process . Now you do not have any excuse to improve your writing and your speaking skills at the same time because if you live in a country where English speakers are not easy to find , this tool can give you the opportunity to work on your speaking by writing . And this is powerful . I highly recommend this . 
It 's true that the working area plays an important role for workers , especially the ones working in an office . Open office or closed office , which is better ? It 's hard to answer . So , let 's take a look at them . Firstly , open office . An open office is an open work environment where there are no enclosed office rooms or walled cubicles for employees . Usually , employees work in the same room , beside each other , while sitting along a huge desk or workstations positioned close together . Many workers prefer this design because they can easily communicate with their own team -mates or even different teams . It 's more likely for them to establish relationships among each other . But , this design has some disadvantages . First , noise . You ca not definitely avoid noise when working in an open area . If you and your teammates are working on a task that requires quietness to concentrate , this design will make it a lot harder . Secondly , conflicts . When a group of people with different personalities and beliefs are crammed into a prison -like room to work for 8 hours a day , there is a high possibility of misunderstandings and conflicts . Finally , spreading illness . When someone is sick with a communicable disease , they can easily transfer and spread the virus to the rest of department . That 's about an open office . How about a closed one , a traditional design one ? With this design , workers have more safety , privacy and stability . Moreover , many workers tend to more concentrate on their work while sitting in an area surrounded by something . But , just like the open design , this one also has some disadvantages . Firstly , cost . A closed office is more expensive to build and maintain than an open one . Since each employee has his own workplace or cubicle , you will need more area to fit every member of your team . Secondly , low supervision . Each employee has his own workplace , so it 's hard to supervise what he is doing . Is he working or playing games ? In a nutshell , each design has its own advantages and disadvantages . It 's hard to say which one is better . 
Dear Peter , Just let me explain to you that we have two meals a day in Spain . I always have breakfast at 10 AM , and after that I have lunch at 14.00 PM . Furthermore , I always have about two snacks and then I have dinner at home or try to go out for dinner with my family or some friends . To answer your question , my favourite food is ' Cargols a la llauna ' which is grilled snails which are made in a special pan . This dish is often eaten out in Catalan restaurants and it 's better to eat it for lunch . I suppose that it sounds disgusting to eat snails , but it 's quite common in Catalonia . Have you ever eaten grilled snails ? 
If you live in a big and vibrant city , you have to agree that it is not so difficult to find many facilities around you , but if you live in or visit small towns and villages , you probably have lived some situations where it is almost impossible to find some essential facilities . It is completely dreadful when you need some facilities and it is so rare , even more if we are talking about health needs . Health assistance can become a great problem when you are far from the big cities , so in some small cities , it is impossible to find a doctor and even if one exists , you take days or months to make an appointment . One of the reasons for this problem is because doctors wo not work in small cities , they always prefer to work in medium or big cities so they can make more money in theses cities . Besides if they work in small cities , they have to get used living in a quiet place and most of them cannot settle in small cities . This problem has no easy way to be solved because the government cannot force doctors to work in smalls cities so some other alternative needs to be thought . The governments of some countries offers many types of incentives to try to attract doctors to live and work in small cities . The government pays a really good salary , provides home and car and countless other types of perks for the doctors that are available to work in some far away cities . Regardless of this great effort , there are still many cities needing doctors with the desire to work there . Perhaps one alternative is for the government to give support for the local students so they achieve their medical graduation with the condition that they cannot leave their cities after graduating . 
Eating is a very special time for me . It 's like therapy and helps me to feel good . In Brazil there are a lot of different kinds of food . The typical food came here from African , European and native people . I love Italian food , especially pizzas and spaghetti . I try to eat it once a week . I love this food because I like cheese a lot , this ingredient is comun in this cuisine . 
From my point of view , I think it is important to be able to speak a foreign language . In the last years , I have noticed people choose English as a foreign language , because it is the most used in the world and it is the easiest to learn . Firstly , Universities in Europe are teaching foreign students from the Asian and African continents in English and French , but if they choose to stay in the country they are studying , it is required for them to learn the language which is spoken in that country . Secondly , it is good to study the country 's history and see what is the most attractive for you , then start and learn their language , because you never know when you will have that feeling of making a change and moving to another country . Although people are born in nice countries , they are rejected by their own leaders and forced to move by corruption to foreign countries , in spite of leaving their families and their homeland , which makes a big contribution to their spiritual life . In conclusion , I would like to say that learning a foreign language is important and required . 
I like to sleep in complete darkness because any kind of light can disturb my sleep . However , my curtains are not the best and some light from the streetlamps slips in through the gaps . That is why I bought an eye -mask to allay the light input . I have read a lot about the circadian rhythms , sleep , and light . Having digested all of the information I can no longer stand insufficient protection from light and noise during the night hours . To deal with the sound , I bought ear plugs . Unfortunately , they 're not the most comfortable solution . I used to spend a lot of time on my smartphone just before bed time . But I have changed my habits after learning about the circadian rhythms . Fortunately , common sense prevailed . 
The School of the Future Have you ever given a thought to the matter concerning what the school of the future will be like ? It goes without saying that every time we think of the future , technology has a significant role in it . Distant though it may seem , the future is closer than ever , in the way that in the recent years there has been a sharp increase in the usage of technological devices among the population , as well as in schools . I cannot help but mention that , when it comes to picturing the school of the future , I always imagine a robot taking the teacher 's place and computer screens everywhere . Nevertheless , replacing a human teacher with a robot one would be a big mistake , in my humble opinion , due to the fact that human contact cannot be replaced by any gadgets . Each and every student has a different personality and distinct needs , and only a real person is capable of adapting the study method to every individual . On the contrary , I find that the rest of the technological devices that could be introduced in the school system would have a positive impact on the students ' learning , as their principal aim is to make our lives easier . So next time you stop and wonder what the future will be like , you should have under consideration that human beings will have to be part of it and nothing will ever substitute real feelings . 
Thank you for recommending Write and Improve . I have found this tool to be quite useful . I will start my description with the positive aspects and then move on to the flaws . What I like the most about it is its levels of advancement . It seems that the developers thought about all English learners . There are variety of writing tasks for each level , which are related to everyday situations . Another interesting feature is the progress scale , which helps you monitor your improvement rate . However , the feedback is the most confusing part . Sentences with errors are highlighted and you receive a short , written explanation . On the one hand it 's very detailed , as even the lack of a comma highlights the whole sentence . On the other hand , the written explanation is useless and you have to figure out for yourself what you have done wrong . I think that Write and Improve could improve a little . Then it would be superior to all other learning methods . 
I believe it depends on the teacher and I will be happy to justify my answer . Learning is like a journey and a teacher is a student 's guide . As long as the teacher can take the student where he wants to go , it 's fine . There is of course more to it . The aspect of integrity is of paramount importance . For example , some teachers are only there for the money , just doing their jobs , whilst others are true teachers , who care about the student and his progress . Some teachers are also disorganised and inordinate . They seem to get lost in the lecture and often forget about the time . It 's like walking a long distance without taking a break . It can be exhausting for the students and cause them to lose enthusiasm . On the other hand , I have met teachers who are willing to go the extra mile . They have remained a student in a sense , are not afraid of questions and are keen to investigate issues . These are the teachers I like the most . 
Nowadays people tend to present totaly totally different tastes in sleeping habits . Some prefer a totally dark room with ear plugs because otherwise they could not fall asleep or even if they did , they would for sure toss and turn all night long . Others are more fortunate and are able to sleep no matter the setting or sound . They even proved to drop off holding a smartphone or watching TV . Why is it so , that we differ from each other when it comes to sleeping ? 
In my opinion , if we want to have good quality sleep , we should sleep in a dark and quiet room . Light negatively impacts our sleep ; it reduces our sleep quality . Noise is the same . They both impact negatively on our sleep . On the other hand , some people are heavy sleepers and they do not get disturbed by light or noise . I know some people who are heavy sleepers and they can sleep wherever they want . However , some people are sensitive sleepers and they are disturbed by light and a bit of noise , like me . I do not want to sleep with light or noise as they disturb me effectively . 
Both have their pros and cons , then I think that a company should design its layout appropriately according to its purpose . What I mean is that a marketing department cannot be so enclosed or strict because of its purpose , which is creation and coming up with creative ideas , and when your are inside an enclosed place , you feel enclosed , which will not help to achieve the department 's purpose . Whereas a legal department will ask for a more strict layout because of its purpose . Another thing to take into account is how the workplace affects employees ' mental health , it can seem like an empty discussion but it 's more important than we think . The longer you 're in there , the more affected you are . 
English is one of the most spoken languages in the world . I wonder if there is someone who cannot speak at least an English word . It is impossible . Because of globalization and the mixture of traditions and culture , in addition to a rising request for more and more language skills , English has become the basis . With regards to my personal experience , I love using English . I am learning the idiomatic expressions of this amazing language more and more , as well as its culture and literature . From Byron to Blake , from Shakespeare to Milton , I read their masterpieces , trying to understand their thoughts and feelings . Of course , a language must be spoken . Writing , listening and English grammar are surely important , but they are not enough . This is the reason why I am talking in English more and more every day . One friend of mine is helping me to do that . Moreover , I am used to watching movies and TV series in the original language , so that I can improve my listening and spelling skills . A foreign language is a " strange world , " which is waiting to be discovered ! I love English ! 
These days , some high schools consider volunteer work a requirement for their students in order to graduate . Is that necessary or not ? To my way of thinking , I think it 's crucial . There are several reasons why I say that . Firstly , it is proved that volunteer work gives pupils essential skills and practical experiences for their future lives . Through volunteer work , pupils can get social knowledge and skills such as public speaking , fast reflective skills , interpersonal skills , etc . Life has different stages . Pupils should not only just focus on their school life but also their social life . They should know how the world goes on outside school . Having expertise but lacking social knowledge , that 's really bad for their future . Secondly , it also shows that pupils have the ability to contribute to their countries . Almost all volunteer work is related to resolving unemployment , gender inequalities , crimes , . . . In addition , participating in those activities shows that pupils have concern and have capabilities of giving solutions and improvements to bad social problems . Finally , social relationships . Participating in those activities helps pupils improve their social relationships , extending them . They can meet other people , make friends with them . That really helps them with their future lives . In a nutshell , volunteer work is crucial for pupils . " Without community service , we would not have a strong quality of life . It 's important to the person who serves as well as the recipient . It 's the way in which we , ourselves , grow and develop , " said Dr . Dorothy Height . 
My personal opinion is that with noise we would have a way to deal with it . But we cannot deal with brightness . The solution for dealing with noise which I came up with immediately is ear plugs . You can shut out the noise only putting ear plugs in . It is easy ! But about brightness , can you cover yourself up with a blanket ? Soon you will feel too warm to hide there . Can you use eye masks ? No , I do not think it would be the best way , how do you know it is the morning , if you are in the dark , unless you take your eye mask off ? 
In my opinion , I prefer to sleep in a dark and quiet room , maybe after reading a book or watching television on my cellphone . For me , sleeping in a noisy or light room is an unpleasant experience . I do not like noise , including relaxing music or classical music , neither do I like light bright or a small light , because the light activates the ideas of my duties . In another observation , neither do I believe in using a mask or odors like incense , in this case the incense makes me cough . I also do not think eating a lot before bed time is a good idea to induce a sleep , in fact it makes me have nightmares . I notice when I do exercise , I feel a little more relaxed and it makes it much easier to induce me to sleep well . Finally , if a quiet and dark room is not enough , drinking a glass of milk always helps me . 
Dear Sir , I hereby write this letter to address my concern about your thoughts of banning the use of mobile phones at various spots . I strongly disagree with your idea to forbade phones on public transport . Usually people use them as a form of entertainment while they travel from one place to another . The use of their mobiles enables them to see the time pass a little bit faster . A further point is that there are a lot of people who , for instance , read the newspaper on the train because it is the only moment in their tight schedule they have the time to do it . Nonetheless , I agree with you that phones in shops and restaurants do not have a particular and useful utilisation . Banning them would give customers the opportunity to socialise more with their environment . I find it really distressing seeing a group of friends sitting around a table and only talking to their phones , instead of each other . However , even if I strongly believe that there are some advantages to banning mobile phones in shops and restaurants , it would infringe everyone 's privacy . Banning the use of cigarettes in restaurants was considerable because it was harmful for your surroundings , whereas mobile phones do not cause health issues . I strongly recommend reconsidering the ban of mobile phones . I hope you take my letter into consideration . Yours faithfully , 
It goes without saying that telling the truth is commonly believed to be the best option whenever we are asked about anything . My thoughts about that matter are going to be displayed below . To begin with , I would like to point out the reasons why people who are in favour of telling the truth permanently give support to that idea . Needless to say , we contribute to our credibility by giving a neat and honest answer . People find it easier to trust us if we do not hide the information we possess and explain the facts that lead us to certain positions with regard to a topic . Nevertheless , some drawbacks should be mentioned concerning telling the truth as it is the case of bad news . When it comes to giving information that could be harmful or delicate for a person , we ought to take into account the other person 's feelings . For that reason , I consider that , every now and then , it is understandable to tell a lie instead . Especially when we talk about information rated overwhelming . Last but by no means least , I would like to conclude by bringing focus to the fact that we should evaluate previously if the information we own is worth being given to the other person . If we cause a problem by telling the truth , then it would be preferable to keep that truth to yourself , otherwise , we would regret making a person unhappy . 
My favourite season of the year is spring and I would like to explain my reason . First of all , I will describe the way I see the other seasons . Summer is great . There are long days and short nights , it is a warm and relaxing time . However , you know that autumn is coming , the worst season of them all . Why is it the worst ? Because I know that here comes the darkness , here come the long nights and short cold days . Do not get me wrong , I do not avoid suffering and I am glad that I am able to live outside of my comfort zone , but what is the best time in life ? The best time is not the suffering and it is not the end of the suffering either . The best time is the last minute before the light . And that 's why I love spring . It symbolises the end of the misery and a new beginning . 
We live in an age when many of us are interested in learning a foreign language for many reasons . Nowadays , it is a fundamental part of people ’s lives . To start with it , learning a foreign language has become an important part of each person ’s development . Currently , if you want to get a better job , it is essential that you ’re able to speak other languages , such an English or Italian . In the past it was not important , you could be a success without the knowledge of other languages . Moreover , today we live in an age in which everyone has contact with different cultures around the world , consequently more people are interested in learning new languages . In conclusion , learning foreign languages has more relevance these days . The necessity of getting a better job and the increased interest in travelling abroad , these and other aspects have made it more important to learn a new language than years ago . 
Dear Sir or Madam , I have recently apprehended that the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants may soon be banned in our town . For that reason , I would like to give my opinion on that matter . From my perspective , the use of smartphones today is inalienable as they are a pervasive part of our lives . Due to globalisation and the increasing importance of fast communication , our society is adapted to the use of smartphones . Nevertheless , there are cases in which smartphones are not necessarily needed to use : My impression is that . 
College is the biggest step in a student 's life due to the fact they will be treated as adults . Therefore , I think it 's probably better for students to live on their own , that will teach them responsibility . In addition , it will help them to be independent and they will develop a strong character . Being responsible is one of the goals that parents try to teach their children . Students that decide to live on their own will learn to rely on themselves as well as take full responsibility for their actions . My sister was a very reckless person so we encouraged her to live on her own when she got accepted to university . All of a sudden , she became a different individual . She started to take control of her life and organized her time as well as her to -do list . For that reason , my parents were massively proud and happy for her . As it has been mentioned before , going to university may be a huge step in an individual 's life . It will help in forming their characters and building their personality . I was a shy person that always got nervous when talking to others . Since I was scared of trying different things , I decided to break my comfort zone by living away from home . It was a hard decision , but when the time passed , it got easier . I developed great communication skills as well as learnt to be comfortable around others . To sum up everything that has been stated , living on your own while attending school will probably be more beneficial than living with your family from my point of view . 
I wish I could live forever , never grow up , always have a good time . I wish my life never ended , but if I had to choose between a long , calm life or a shorter and more intense one , I would definitely pick the shorter one . One reason why I would do such a thing is my love for adrenaline . Ever since I was little , I have been a fan of extreme things ; I used to love roller coasters and scary movies , and I have not changed at all . I see life as a video game where you 're the hero and if you want to finish it , you have to pass some difficult levels . Another reason why I would not choose the long life is my tendency to get bored with things very quickly . No matter how much I enjoy something , I always feel like I need to change something . A calm life could never been enough for me . I want something memorable ; I want to experience love , heartbreak , loss , happiness , sadness ; I want all the things that make us human . I understand why some people would prefer to live longer : more time with your loved ones , more time figuring things out and a lot of other things that take time . Even though I would want those things too , I ca not imagine myself choosing a quiet and peaceful life . All in all , this is not the first time I 've spoken about this topic and , after giving it much thought , I realised what my choice is . I want an intense life , even though it might be short . 
I used to sleep in a dark and quiet room far from the noisy street . But everything changed when my son was born . We moved to the first room , which is bigger and more comfortable , however that means that we usually hear the noise from the street . Also , we adopted the habit of sleeping with a small light on because we used to get up many times to care for him when he was a baby . Nowadays we continue with the habits that we took some years ago . Nevertheless , I can sleep in darkness or with a light , in a quiet or noisy room , it does not matter . 
One of the best ways to expand our horizons and our brain connections is travelling . It is a mix of a new place , new food , new people and a new way to see the world . In the past , journeys were very long and people usually spent weeks and months on one journey . Nowadays we only have to spend hours on a journey because of an invention called the airplane . Therefore I believe that time spent on journeys will be shorter in the future . Even though we 've invented a large amount of transportation , some more will be invented or they are being invented . 
Nowadays , many schools require students to learn and play a musical instrument . Some people say it 's not necessary , students do not need to learn it . Others say the opposite . To my way of thinking , I think music should be taught at schools . Why ? Music is a subject to help students relax after heavy studying hours . As you can see , students must learn many subjects at the same time . Math , literature , physical education , . . . everything . The classes go on continuously . One class is finished , the next one is going to start in a few minutes or even immediately . It means that , except the break time , students do not have much time to relax after finishing a class . Music will help them with that problem . In addition , the curriculum of this subject is not heavy . Students just need to know some basic knowledge such as some chords , notes , etc . They do not have to learn like they 're going to take an entrance exam to a conservatory . Finally , music classes can make an opportunity to detect musical talents at school . This contributes partly to develop the art of a nation . For example , many historical stories in the world recorded the famous musicians who were educated by normal schools before . If there had not been musical classes at school , the world would not have had any famous musicians and singers . In a nutshell , music should be taught at school . It not only helps students relax but also makes an opportunity to find musical talents . 
The school of the future is an interesting subject to discuss together . I think school in the future will be really different from the present . I think school in the future will be better than school in the present . But at any time , everything still has a good side and a bad side . On the good side , I think the money for studying in school will decrease and will be cheaper than school in the present , so everybody can study in their favorite school without worrying about money . The school facilities are going to improve very well , so the school can educate their students effectively . I also think in the future everyone will be able to study online . That will make it easier for us to study in the future than study in the present . The conclusion is , in the future , everyone will be able to study more effectively , easily and cheaply than studying in school in the present . On the bad side , school in the future could be more expensive than school in the present . That will be really awful for our children and our future . 
Televisions are devices only to entertain and at least here in Brazil they are not used to educate , which is really sad , because TVs are powerful tools . I will tell you what you will see if you turn on a TV in Brazil . First off , the bad news , here television programs talk about death , violence , robberies and other bad things . Second , serials , which are something similar to series , but they are a lot more boring and full of violence , arguments , death , robberies and bad things . Third , sexuality , this is something very acceptable in the country where I live and you will see things related to sex frequently on TV . So , yes , TVs can be used to educate , but they do not . Those who have this kind of power use it to manipulate and to influence people 's lives and their political opinions . 
Most people in the world say that they could not endure lies and they always tell the truth . More than half of these people lie in their daily lives . The way I see it , it does not hurt to tell little lies every now and then . Of course , I am totally against big lies , people should not tell lies which could affect other people 's lives deeply . In the first place , if everyone told the truth , it could hurt people . For example , if you ask a friend how it was after changing your hair , you would expect to hear a positive comment . Especially if this friend is not very close , you may not be prepared to hear a bad comment from her/him . In such cases , your acquaintances and friends generally do not want to offend you , so they do not hit the negative side of the situation in your face . Our close friends and family usually take on this role in our lives . Another major reason is that sometimes the occasions are not your business . So you lie when the interlocutor asks you something because you do not want to mingle in others ' things . This behaviour is actually really great . I am concerned that when you mingle in other people 's situations , they may accuse you after they resolve the situation . In the end , you could be the culpable and they will go about their lives as if nothing had happened . All things considered , sometimes lying is necessary for the good of people . If you are not in a position to tell them the harsh truth of people 's lives , it is much better not to interfere in their affairs at all . In my opinion , it is a great mistake for people to lie to their immediate surroundings , other people are not that important . 
A lot of people think that they do not need to learn English because they do not travel abroad . They even think that they can get everything translated , so why bother with learning a new language . The opposite is the truth ! First of all I would like to mention books . I agree that there are subtitles for more or less every movie and TV show , however there are so many books which you ca not even buy in your country . My life is so much better because I can read all of these foreign books and there is an infinite number of them . And aside from books , what about all of the podcasts ? No one will translate more than five hundred hours of the Jocko podcast , but it is so great to listen to . So you do not need to travel at all to benefit from your language skills . 
My favorite food is rice with fried fish and Coca Cola . I eat this meal every time I can . Let me tell you why , in my country the weather is hot , for this reason drinking a cool Coca Cola is very pleasant . Also , my work requires me to make a physical effort , for that I need carbohydrates which are in the rice , and I have to read more than usual , so for that eating fish is good for me . 
