I like to sleep in a dark and quiet room . I cannot stand any noise , because I wake up . My sleep gets interrupted very easily . If I sleep in a room with a lot of background noise I use earplugs . That happens especially on holiday trips . You never know , which room you will get . But noise is for my sleep more disturbing than light ; I can sleep in a room with a little bit of light coming through the windows . 
My best holiday ever was ten years ago when I visited an exhibition about archaeology . This exhibition happened in my city . It was important because I could see evidence that dinosaurs had been living near my house thousands of years ago . I could see a couple of archaeological sites with many digs and in one of these digs there were a few bones of dinosaurs . These bones can be named fossils and they are important to describe how the dinosaurs became extinct , or what the base of their nutrition was , or even if these animals had some diseases . This holiday was important to me , because I could spend time with friends and relatives that I had not seen in a long time . They were living in another state far away from here , but they came to visit the exhibition . So , in summary , that day was great . My friends , relatives and I had an excellent and fun day . 
What can be more important than exercise ? One needs energy to be able to run , jump or do yoga . Therefore , there are at least two more valuable components to our health : food and sleep . In 2017 , the Noble prize in medicine was granted to a team led by professor Rosbach . The team researched the circadian rhythm . Their discoveries revolved around the sleep -wake cycle that is embedded into our cells . The research denotes that our bodies function better when we adhere to these patterns . Furthermore , it revealed that each and every organ of our body functions according to a slightly different pattern . Therefore , it 's not only important that we go to bed at a certain time , but also that we eat at a certain time . Generally speaking , people who sleep well tend to be more relaxed and less spiteful . By the same token , an appropriate amount of sleep precludes the need for an inordinate daily coffee intake . Then there is exercise , the third component of the circadian rhythm . To be healthy means to feel tired in the evening and refreshed in the morning . Therefore , we should exercise at least 30 minutes a day to avert the effects of our sedentary lifestyle . 
For many years , television has been used for entertainment . Now television is used as more than only a tool of entertainment . Television entertains , but can it also educate ? Schools now use television as part of the tools to help teachers in their education process . In addition to that , there are many channels helping students at home to gain knowledge and learn . Kids at home can play and learn at the same time from channels dedicated to and suitable for their ages . Television has helped many sectors , like health and civil defence and others , to raise and create orientation in people . Television brings us what is happening around the world and enriches our knowledge and discovery of other cultures . Television educates people about the weather , in order to help them decide when they should travel , go fishing and other things they might do . Television is always educating all people all the time . 
Hello everyone , I have the opportunity to write about the schools of the future . It is a complex topic , because it has many viewpoints . Well , it is time to write about my opinion . Let 's begin : 1 . It is necessary to keep in mind that I am from Colombia , a totally underdeveloped country . Sadly , it is a country with many economic problems , where most people are poor or extremely poor . The children face a lot of difficulties to go to school , while the other part of the population cannot go to school and the minority can go to school without any issue . 2 . The pandemic has been the reason for change . Now , the children take their classes in their houses . They use the virtual way to study , but you should think , if they are poor , many do not have a computer , wifi , desk or elements to study . The government of Colombia wants to implement virtual classes , but the question is what is going to happen with the children ? In conclusion , I think schools should keep their essence . They are places to study , share , learn , teach and play , but it is possible in the future , these places will give us some virtual classes and relationships with schools in other countries , improving the vision of the world . 
Phuc Tan Phu District Nguyen Son Street Las Noches City March 3rd , 2021 Dear Town Council , My name is Phuc . I heard that you are thinking about banning the use of mobile phones on public transport , in shops and restaurants . Allow me to demonstrate my viewpoint on this . First of all , I do not think this is a good idea . The ban on mobile phone use can be disapproved of by many citizens , who find it very convenient and essential in their daily lives . Mobile phones make it easier to communicate , find information , to contact people . Basically , they are essential tools in a vast and dynamic society these days . The prohibition on using them should not be implemented . This can result in many problems . On the contrary , there is a serious problem when people freely use mobile phones : noise . There are a variety of complaints about this problem . Many people use their mobile phones with high volume in public . However , as I mentioned before , the banning of mobile phone use can result in many problems . So , to prohibit this issue , instead of banning them from using mobile phones , the town authorities should impose some laws and rules . This may reduce the amount of noise in public and wo not cause much discomfort for the surrounding people . In conclusion , banning mobile phone use in public is not a good idea . Instead , it can be controlled by imposing some laws and rules . Sincerely , Phuc 
