Obviously , the second one , open design offices are the most effective type of arrangement , from a visual point of view , but also from a work point of view . If there are not walls that separate employees , I think employees can work better and more quickly because there is cooperation between employees . There are also disadvantages to no walls offices , there is not privacy and if you have to focus on a task , there can be a lot of noise that can be not given you the good concentration to do that . The type of arrangements of offices officies although must be chosen for the aim of the office . For example , if the office is in a bank , the type of arrangement better being a closed office to preserve the privacy of the customers . On the contrary , if the office , for example , is a social media office , the type of arrangement can be a no walls office . In the end , no walls offices are better , but for the right employment sectors . 
