Well , it depends on how these volunteer jobs are led because when you impose something , the development of important skills and perception can be jeopardized and the learning process affected . Let me explain , when a youngster is forced to do something they do not want to do , they normally do it in a sloppy way , which means that the tasks or job will be done jeopardizing both sides , the worker and the work . The worker will not absorb the learning from that task or job and the work will be not so good . On the other hand , when you force a youngster to do something when they are not encouraged by anything , this can help them to discover new things and to learn during the process . So , in my opinion , this is something good to be done , however , an experienced advisor is highly recommended to guide them through this journey . 
I would like to say that learning to speak a foreign language is more important these days than it was in the past . More and more , people around the world live in the global world . We may meet more and more foreigners in our daily life than we could in the past . We should be able to speak another language , especially English , so that we can talk to people from around the world . It is a very important thing to be able to speak with people from other countries . Communication itself is always needed in general . Some people would say that we could communicate with translation software . However , I would say that it is not real communication . We should speak to someone with our mouth at any time , so that we could communicate our emotions to them . Moreover , we cannot expect other people to use translation software in all situations . This is why I insist on my opinion that we have to learn foreign languages . Hopefully , it is not only English , but also another language too . 
