Television has a short history . It was invented in the 20th century by an Englishman . I actually do not know his purpose . Why did he invent such a device ? This is not important for the vast majority of society anymore , I guess . No one asks why or when anymore , we just enjoy what was invented . We do not even ask if it is harmful , beneficial or anything else . Firstly , I think television is far from educational . It is distraction for children and maybe young adults . We ca not deny that there are a few educational channels , but how many of us really move away from TV series and watch them ? The answer is distinctly stands here , almost none of us . Old ladies are fond of soap operas , young adults love TV series like GOT or The Big Bang Theory and children mostly watch cartoons . Maybe cartoons have a little benefit for children , but their parents should choose carefully among all of them . They could include violence , sexuality or vulgarity . Secondly , besides what I wrote in the first paragraph , there are also benefits . There is the news , documentaries and economy channels , but I still insist that most of us do not watch those channels or programs . While most people do not like to watch documentaries , since computers and phones became common , nobody uses television for news and stock markets . Phones are more preferred in this regard , because they are much more practical . But for people who do not know how to use a phone or computer or do not have them , they still use television for this purpose . As a result , in my opinion , television is not a necessity in our age and it does more harm than good . I think it is far from being educational . We cannot ignore the benefits only during the pandemic period . Children who do not have access to computers and phones in our country attended their classes on television . Other than that , I do not think it has any benefit to education . 
