Nowadays , people can read books on their computers or tablets , or even their smartphones . So , students in general could use those devices to study in schools or universities . Should they replace books in those situations ? In my opinion , computers and tablets should completely replace books in schools and universities . They are simply convenient . Books take up significant space . Books are also damaged as time passes . On the other hand , computers and tablets do not take up so much space . Also , they can contain considerably many books . More importantly , the students do not need to carry such heavy textbooks . There would be less trouble if they did not have to carry their textbooks all the time . Of course , computers and tablets inevitably need electricity , while books do not . However , the advantages of computers and tablets outweigh their disadvantages . On balance , basically , schools and universities should use computers and tablets to get the students to study . If there are problems with them , then they should use books in those cases . It is inevitable that new technology replaces traditional stuff . 
