My reasons for learning English Learning English is so important nowadays , because English is an international language . There are many reasons to support my ideas . Firstly , as I mentioned before , English is an international language , so it is spoken in most countries , such as China , France , Italy and the Middle East . Secondly , I am really keen on learning languages , especially English , because I enjoy watching movies in English , so that ' s why I started learning English . As far as I know , a lot of jobs require English skills these days . In the education part , if you would like to continue a master 's and Ph . D , you need to get an ILETS , which is an English international exam . It is also a great idea to learn English in your free time . This will help you to get knowledge and finally , if you are thinking of emigrating to another country , like the United Kingdom , you need to learn English and start preparing for the UKNI exam . So , what are your reasons for learning English ? It depends on you . Thank you for reading my article . Written by , Sam 
My reasons for learning English I think learning English is very important nowadays , because everyone speaks the English language . There are many reasons for learning English . For example , if you want to study abroad , you need to have an IELTS exam , so you need to learn English and develop yourself . Also , if you want to apply to a big company , you need to know English and other languages , etc . For people who like going to shops or need something professional , such as a beautiful dress or a present , like a box that has many things , makeup , a bookmark , money and perfume . In general , to learn English , firstly you need to write a specific goal . Secondly , do a level test to see your level , if it is beginner , intermediate or advanced . After that , find websites or books to help you learn the English language . Then create it as a habit , like studying English for 20 minutes . Finally , enjoy your learning experience in English . 
Vietnam is a country that is famous for many delicious dishes . And the food I like most is spring roll , an indispensable part of our cuisine on special occasions like the Tet holiday , or the Mid -autumn festival . There are many ingredients mixed to create the rich flavor for this dish : rice -paper , shrimps , meat , green onion , carrots , wood -ear mushrooms , salt , pepper , fish sauce ... And the recipe for spring roll is also easy . You just need to stir up all the ingredients , with a reasonable amount , and then put them in the rice paper and roll it up . The last step is deep frying them and that 's why it is called a spring roll . I extremely like this dish because the aroma and the taste is so good . Moreover , when I make spring rolls , all my family members will gather to make them together . So , this dish is not only mouth -watering , but also full of love . 
