Dear Johnna , You have no idea where I went last Monday . To tell you the truth , I went to a music concert in Baoli Giant Theatre actually ! March had witnessed a dramatic improvement in my career . The greatest of all was that I got promoted in my firm this term ! Given that the former HR manager had resigned for good , I sought the opportunity just in time . You understand that people 're likely to relax themselves when they 've just gone through a tough period , do not you ? That accounted for why I was heading to the music concert . Frankly speaking , my knowledge of music is rather limited . To be honest , it was not until I got to the spot that I eventually learned whose concert it was , since the tickets were booked by my boyfriend in advance . Have you ever heard Alicia Frankle 's name ? Representing one of the most distinguished divas in Britain , she is performing around the world this year . Overall , I regarded this concert as a more -than -fascinating one ! Alicia Frankle was not only a professional , but also gifted in engaging people during the two -hour concert . I was on the edge of bursting into tears when she sang the bridge of Shassas . It was so amazing ! You would never forget about it once you hear her singing live . The concert is going to be a lifelong memory for me , definitely . Yours , Iris 
Nowadays , it is well -known that many people are emigrating from small towns in rural areas to big cities . Therefore , we need more hospitals and doctors in the big cities for the reason that they have many patients to attend . However , the citizens who live in rural areas are old people and they need more health care . Owing to that fact , I believe that we should invest in those areas and , as a result , some citizens who have emigrated to big cities will have a chance to come back to their town . As a result , the population in rural areas will increase and this will lead to the creation of new hospitals . In conclusion , there are not enough doctors in rural areas due to the lack of population in those zones . For this reason , I suggest that one of the best solutions could be to invest in those areas , so we can create new jobs and this will bring more citizens to those areas and , eventually , they will need more doctors . 
