Dear Jason , Glad to hear from you so soon ! Exciting that a movie festival is to be held on your campus . I literally have a fascinating one to suggest - The Social Network . As is widely known , the movie was adapted from the storyline of Mark Zuckerburg and the process of how he and his friends created Facebook . Just like other adapted films , TSN did a good job in keeping the balance between drama and reality . That is to say , you can see the traditional American style of films , which are filled with sex and conflicts , as well as a strict plot . At the same time , there are also reflections of what happened to the characters in reality . What I found most thrilling when watching the movie was the engrossing acting by two male actors , Jesse and Andrew . As for Jesse , who acted as Mark in TSN , he never failed to attract the whole audience with his high -speed lines , as well as delicate facial expressions . I almost cried out , " That 's Zuckerburg live " when he typed at an incredibly fast rhythm on the keyboard . Needless to say , Andrew was the one who dedicated his heart and soul to his character Edurado . Playing Mark 's best friend , Edurado went through a series of tough times when they started their career . Notwithstanding , Andrew 's Edurado was a " sweetheart " from head to toe , as he was always there for his mate . Released almost ten years ago , TSN was a phenomenal blockbuster , as well as a box -office hit . It 's the kind of film that you surely do not want to miss . That is why I highly recommend it to you . I sincerely hope you can enjoy it . Yours , Iris 
