Hi Jack ! It has been a really long time since you last wrote to me . Anyway , happy birthday Jack . In my country , we celebrate birthdays almost like you do . In my last birthday , my family brought me 50 KFC chicken wings so that I could have a feast with my friend . I do not like cake , so we never bought one . 
It 's a common belief that learning to speak a foreign language has a positive impact on our life . And I think that it 's more crucial in the 4.0 industry than it was in the past . Firstly , learning foreign languages will meet the great demand for communicating with people . We are living in the modern world , where people easily interact with others over the continents , thanks to the invention of the Internet in 1969 . Besides , the need for travelling and trading is one of the reasons bringing people together . So , learning new languages helps people whose culture is different easily understand each other . By that way , it has become more and more necessary than in the past , when people could not afford to travel or exchange things with foreigners . Moreover , today we have a new notion - global citizens . It is the idea that one 's identity transcends geography or political borders and that responsibilities or rights are derived from membership of a broader class , " humanity . " Therefore , the priority is that they have the ability to speak more than two languages . Then , they can do their work and make a contribution to the development of their countries . 
Nowadays , it is well known that computers and tablets are winning popularity with students and teachers . However , I 'm one of those who believe that we should not remove books . I agree that computers have many perks . For instance , with them we can search for information with just a few clicks and the sources of information we have on the internet are almost endless . Nevertheless , these perks can be disadvantages at the same time . It has been demonstrated that computers and tablets can reduce our capacity for attention . For example , many students usually spend most of their time on social applications such as Facebook and Instagram . Due to this , I think that books are still useful for students , because with them we are normally more concentrated and therefore we can learn more . I have to say that in some lessons the In conclusion , even though I believe that computers are vital for schools and universities , we should keep using books for some lessons . 
Studying abroad has advantages as well as disadvantages . The main advantage is that students have the opportunity to explore other cultures while pursing their studies abroad . Learning about other cultures is a real plus in nowadays ' multicultural society . This will no doubt be a big advantage during their future careers . They will learn about the cultural background and differences , will learn how to relate to other cultures , certainly skills they would not have been able to develop while studying in their own country . Another advantage is that if a student decides that studying abroad is an option , then that student is able to choose from multiple qualified universities and available degree programmes . Studying in a foreign country will also be a big asset on their resumes . The biggest disadvantage is , while focussing on their studies , the students will also have to take care of their own household , while at the same time live in a foreign country , not aware of the cultural differences , which might cause problems and probably , being able to make themselves understood , because they will have not mastered the foreign language yet . Studying abroad will , if you are not eligible for a grant , be far more expensive than studying at home . Several types of grants are available for students and it might be worthwhile exploring the possibilities before deciding in which country you want to pursue your studies . Living in another country also makes it more difficult to find a suitable part -time job to support yourself during your studies . 
My favorite food is pizza because we can put everything that we want on it . Pizza is so diverse , there are so many flavors of pizza and my favorite is cheese with calabresa . I usually eat pizza on the weekends because my mom does not like me eating junk food during the week . I like this food because it is so consistent and so tasty . 
First of all , studying is one of the most important things if you go to a country that has a good education . Let me talk about the advantages that you will get , a wonderful education and you will choose what you want to study . I mean there is not a degree that will limit your college or high school studies . You will see a new country , place , culture and things that you have never seen before . New friends , you will meet your mates and you will have new friendships . I think with all these , you will get some of freedom away from your parents , friends , the whole family and that will not make you shy to do anything , but I mean good things . The disadvantages will be that you are in a different country and there are a lot of things new to you and maybe you will not like it , but you have to deal with it . If you are sick one day , you will be alone , without anyone in your family and that is the worst one . The fee for studying maybe will be expensive , so you have to decide before you travel to a country and make your plan . The bottom line that is studying abroad is good if you have the money and plan on where you will choose . 
Many workplaces are enormous and they do not have any kind of barrier in them . Others offices instead are small places to work , with barriers and without communication with workers . In my opinion , big offices are more effective than small offices because you have more possibility to communicate with other people . Workplaces with an open design are better for coworking as you can communicate with your team . Instead , you can ask advice to someone and you can share your point of view about the work you are doing with your colleagues . For instance , if you are wondering about a thing in your work , you can ask someone for help . In addition , big workrooms are places where you can know more people that are inspirational to you , and they could help you giving some advice . Big workplaces are better because you have more possibility with other people to work and to exchange ideas . 
Some students , to obtain their degree , have to do a certain number of hours of volunteer work . I think that this requirement is crucial for students , as for them , it is a first approach to the world of work . Indeed , volunteer work brings them to understand which job is better for them . For instance , if a student is confused about his future , with volunteer work , he can understand which is the best way for him . In addition , volunteer work is an important experience to do because post -graduates show and demonstrate if they are ready to do a real job . Indeed , with these hours of practice , schools understand if they are ready for graduating or not . For example , if a student does not complete the hours of volunteer work , the school know that he is not ready for the degree . Volunteer work is important for students as a first approach to a real job and it is also a good experience to do to clarify ideas about work . 
Yes , I exercise daily and I rest once a week . Exercising is very important in my work , because I spend more than 8 hours sitting down . I 've never gone to a gym , since the beginning I 've always worked out outside or at home because I do not have enough money for a gym subscription or I am away for a gym . Exercising by yourself is very hard and risky , especially at the beginning when I did not know the routines well . I would like to go to a gym in the near future . I go for a run three days a week and I do strength exercises on the other three days and I rest on Sundays . 
I do many activities in my free time such as watching TV series , reading or going out for a walk . But my favourite activity is to go for a walk . I try to go out daily when I leave my work office , now it is harder due to the fact that I 'm working at home . When I walk I feel less anxious and forget the problems in my work , I think about all that things that make me happy , like my next trip or visiting a friend or a TV show or any special dish or restaurant . All those things relax me and when I get home , I am ready for the rest of the day . 
