Dear Matt , As to improving my English in this new school year , I will increase my opportunities to speak English , to write English , and to listen to English . I think that if someone wants to improve their language level , it is necessary to use the language . So I would like to increase my opportunities to speak English through a website class , to write English through writing emails to Matt , and to listen to English through You Tube . Best regards , Shusuke 
Nowadays , some things have already been changing . The way to teach is different to the way when I was a child . We are living in a multicultural society , so everybody has the same opportunities to learn everything about their original religion . This is the reason why we can hear people talking in different languages . It wo not be a problem in the future . We may use a small device fit in our ear to translate all the conversations . Furthermore , we will have a microchip inside our skin and our parents or teachers will be able to know where we are . In the future , the most popular language will be Chinese . Therefore , if you want to learn a new language , you should start with that . I 'm sure the classes in the future will be mainly online . Nowadays we are living a lockdown period and we are learning how we can work from our house . The way to teach in the future will also change . Pupils will study at home , watching videos and video -conferences and giving their opinions about them . I do not know if we will be better . 
It depends . Television entertains viewers , but sometimes it does not educate them . There are many programs which require some knowledge about different skills , for instance , " Pasapalabra . " It is a competition to win lots of money . However , the participants must study a lot if they want to win the quiz . They have to discover what a word is with a definition of it and a clue : the first letter of it . I think it is so useful and educational , like The Wheel of Fortune . You can also learn to cook or to sew a garment . Nevertheless , there are some programs which , in my opinion , are rubbish . These kinds of programs show how a couple play with their relationship . Many people watch them . However , I think these types of programs are not educational . You may watch a film or series about the history of a country , so you can learn a lot , or you are able to watch a crime film with a lot of violence and blood . We need to look after our children . Television could educate , but sometimes it does not . 
My favorite film is " Kureyon -Sintyan . " It 's an animation movie . It 's the story of a kindergarten student . He has many personal friends . For example , Kazama - Kun is the smart boy , Nene - Chan is the light girl , and Masao - Kun looks like a rice ball and is always crying . His parents and neighbor are a little strange too . For example , Hiroshi 's feet smell really bad , and Gin -San likes beautiful women . This film is supported by many people for many years . It has the power to attract the viewer . Maybe you would like it . 
So , you probably remember that my favourite Disney movie is the Hunchback of the Notredame , since I might have repeated that way too much the last time we spoke . I think you should really watch it , because it is extremely awesome . For one , the songs just hit you right in the feels . I almost cry every time I hear Heaven 's Light and I get overly dramatic when I hear and sing along to Hell 's Fire . Another point is that the characters are very well rounded . They show real human emotions , such as love , lust and envy . And even though Quasi might be in love with Esmeralda , he also sees that she is in love with Phebus and he with her , so he lets them be , even though it breaks his heart to see them together . 
Last Summer , I had the distinct pleasure of spending time in Italy and looking back , I recognise it turned out to be the best holiday ever . Since Italy is a 1600 km drive , we always spend the night near Lugano Lake . Luckily for us , there was still a room available at one of our favorite hotels , where we enjoyed the top quality service of this very charming , yet very traditional hotel , commonly known for its famous visitors , like Audrey Hepburn . The second day , we arrived at the campsite in Tuscany . The sun was shining and the temperature had already risen to a very comfortable 30 degrees . Unpacking was done very quickly , so that we could settle in the sun and start planning our sightseeing tours in the surroundings . One of the highlights was the visit to the waterfall in the beautiful rural neighbourhood of Florence . We walked alongside the waterfall and were very impressed by the amazing nature . All kinds of plants were flourishing and the colours of the flowers were brilliant for taking photos . The other unforgettable moment was the visit to Cita del la Pieva , an ancient village with small alleyways , stunning views from the top of the village , small squares with beautiful little shops , tiny little restaurants where we enjoyed local food and of course the best espresso ever . 
A very special food in Romania is fried bacon . But it 's a different kind of fried bacon . We cut it into a square or rectangular shape , we put it on a stick/fork and we fry it on top of a fire . We make a small fire outdoors . We put it on a slice of bread so that the grease can cover the bread . We serve it with green onions and tomatoes . We usually make this kind of bacon on a camping trip or when we go to our country house . 
