Dear Mollet del Valles council , I write you regarding the news about banning the use of mobile phones in some spaces . I disagree with this new proposal . First of all , for the reason that I believe we should have the freedom to decide if we want to use our mobile phones in shops or restaurants , therefore it is not a matter that the council can decide for us . Secondly , due to the fact that nowadays many people need their mobile phones for their work . For instance , let 's imagine that someone who works as a stock broker goes out to have lunch at a restaurant , however he is not allowed to use his mobile phone while he is eating and suddenly one of his stocks goes abruptly down . He could not notice it because he did not have his phone and now he has lost a lot of money . Therefore , I would like to give a suggestion : The council could create advertisements in order to warn the citizens about the damages of mobile addiction . As I see it , it is a less aggressive action , which gives the freedom to the citizens to choose . In conclusion , it is true that we spend too much time in front of our electronic devices , nevertheless we should have the liberty to choose if that is how we want to spend our time or not . Even though , I the council could . 
