Dear Makenzie , How are you ? I went to a music concert last week and it was so great , so I could not wait to share my experience with you . You know me well , so you know that I love music , because music can make me feel relaxed . I had a really hard time last week , due to the many exams I had to take . As a consequence , I decided to go to a music concert to relax . A pianist from Germany was performing . I could not spell his name because it was too long and complicated . Nevertheless , I could recognize him among the people , because he looked very handsome and tall and he was very elegant . Perhaps it was the classical music that made him so gorgeous . I really enjoyed the music during the concert , but there was something annoying . Many people were late for the concert , so there were many figures moving to find seats while I was listening to the first piece of music . What 's more , there were some kids in the theater . Maybe this was because their parents wanted them to get to know more about classical music . Nevertheless , kids hardly know about classical music and they could not understand the meaning of the music . It was really tough for them to sit on the chair for over two hours without screaming and crying . This made the experience not so comfortable . I do not really think we should allow children below 10 years old to enter the concert , because they may ruin a precious journey with music . I also think we should not allow people who are late to enter the concert . They have to take responsibility for not being punctual . What do you think about my thoughts ? I hope everything is going well with you . I think we may go to a concert together when I go to the USA . I am looking forward to hearing from you . Yours , Joany 
I think the school of the future will be fairly different from the schools we have today . Most the time , students will take their own track to learn something new . The teachers will work to show the pathway to the students and make sure they do not get lost . Maybe the students will work with specific topics . For instance , if a student has a gift to work with exact sciences , he will focus on it . And over time , that student will get specific knowledge on a specific topic . I think some courses would disappear and others will emerge , like coding and other topics related to computers and artificial intelligence as well . Some things wo not change , for example , interaction among kids . They need to develop their social skills or soft skills . And human contact is essential for the children to develop . I hope kids in the future become better humans beings than we are now . 
