Studying abroad during high school or university is a good idea , because it will help in your career , to learn a new language , new culture , new mores , studying new things in another country that 's awesome for your curriculum . The advantage for those who study abroad is meeting new people that have a different culture than you . That helps you a lot , depending on the career you will follow . If you want be a flight attendant , it is good for you . The disadvantage of studying abroad is because it will hinder the progress of your academic life in your country of origin . When you go back , sometimes you need to study more to arrive at the level of your other colleagues or not . The most important thing in your life is to study abroad . It is so expensive , but it 's really worth it . The experience is the best in the world and everyone could have the opportunity to study abroad . 
I firmly believe that living in a separate house during the university days changes their life in a good way . This idea is held up by my past experiences . In the adolescent period , to be emotionally stable , young college students build a firm network they want to belong to instead of relying on their parents all the time . This sense of belonging accelerates their mental growth because they play a role in the community aside from a child . They will be mentally independent and responsible for not only their lives but also their communities . This whole experience makes him who he will be in the future . Having said so , some people still stress that living at home is cost -efficient and comfortable to focus on the academics . I would oppose this idea for two reasons . One is that it is true you save your money if you can go to university from your parents ' house , but is the cost -effectiveness the true reason why you wanted to attend university ? Apparently , you may go though more hardships than you imagined , yet these challenges you encounter would be a medicine to intensify your growth . The younger you are , the better it is to go through a variety of experiences . The second reason is that if you cannot manage your time by yourself without seeking any family support , you will suffer a new life after working in a company . To grow , you should stand your own two feet even from the college days . 
Hi , Thank you for your interesting email . There are a lot of ways to celebrate someone 's birthday in Japan . But when it was my birthday , my parents and I went to a shop to buy some pieces of cake . Then , we ate them at home . I think it 's the same way to celebrate . I want to know more which is other countries . Sincerely , yours 
The Future of Travel changed with the arrival of the COVID19 virus and the challenges facing us with regard to the climate . More than ever , people were faced with the most challenging and only question regarding travelling ever , is it a luxury just for the rich people or a common thing which ordinary people can enjoy as well . COVID19 prohibited people from travelling beyond the borders , all belts and braces in place were directed to having people stay at home . Crossing borders was not allowed during the outbreak of the virus , moreover it was forbidden by national governments , to prevent the virus from spreading unnecessarily any further than it already had . Travelling was only possible within the borders of the country . So maybe , the future of travel is not getting onto a plane for a far -away vacation , experiencing other cultures and nature , but staying close to home , exploring the neighbourhood and revisiting all the little gems in the local area surrounding us . The future will tell if people will ever be able to travel long distances again or that it will be forbidden forever . Ultimately , less travelling will have a beneficial effect on the climate , because travelling in itself will burden the climate . So maybe the limitations set by the virus will in the end have a positive effect on people as well as the climate . 
Nowadays , it takes a lot of effort and money to successfully run a medical practice , especially in these competitive times . Since insurance companies play an important role in setting rules for medical practices , it is more and more difficult for a medical doctor to run his business at a profit . The strictly set rules prohibit medical doctors of being creative while treating their patients to the utmost of their capabilities . Each treatment has its own set of limitations as to what a medical doctor can offer and can declare afterwards . And in the end , it is all about business . Rural areas represent a low number of inhabitants , whereas medical practices need as many patients as possible , enforcing medical doctors to set up their practice in large cities instead of small villages . Moreover , a small village , however charmingly picturesque and attractive , does not offer enough patients and is in such a way extremely challenging for entrepreneurs , who in general want to develop a successful business . Once in a while , you will still find a lonesome medical doctor , stuck away in a little village , using old -fashioned ways to accommodate his patients , thus taking all the time needed to comfort the patient , but these are becoming more and more of a rarity in today 's society and are becoming distinct . 
Young medical doctors who are starting in the profession prefer working in the big cities to make a lot of money , as long as starting and they want won money , when these doctors grow in the profession and stay are stabilized , they come to rural areas . It is easier to find a job in the big cities than in the rural areas , that is the reason why young doctors prefer cities . Old doctors prefer working in the rural areas because they are stabilized , they have a good career . Young doctors need to network with other doctors , and the big cities are the best place to do it . In rural areas , they have more difficulties to network with doctors . It is a big problem that some doctors have in rural areas because the hospital needs so many doctors in all the places , and not concentrated in the big cities . We need doctors , sometimes have an emergency and we need doctors . 
Dear Cristina , I was so surprised to hear about your accident and also I felt so sorry for you . I also heard that you must stay in your home for two weeks . So I would like to help you so please let me know whatever you want me to help you with . And I would like to visit you as soon as possible if you can accept visitors . Best regards , 
My favorite season of the year . If there was a possibility , I would create a new season , a season of fun ! Well , maybe next time . Exquisite things happen during the year . However , there is one season I find particular , Autumn . Why , you may ask ? Autumn represents a new academic year . I am always excited about it . My life is all about learning new things . Equally relevant to this is that chill weather allows me to easily focus . As you may notice during the hot peaks during summer , studying is not the best option . I loathe warm countries . Sweating and stinking is definitely unpleasant for me . Autumn is best time to travel . Flight tickets are much cheaper . The weather makes it easier to walk a long distance on an adventure . And last but not least . Autumn is particular to me because of my birthday on 17th November . All I do that day is be with the people I love the most . 
I usually play video games in my free time . I have got a lot of stress in my life as usual . So , we need to take a break . Video games give me a less stressful life and I can live comfortably because of them . I usually play them when I finish eating dinner . It 's an important part of the life cycle . 
My favorite indoor activity is painting . I like to draw different painting styles on my i Pad . I love drawing because I cannot sing , I cannot play every video game or I cannot make a structure . I like to draw also to create new things that cannot happen on the earth . I drew an old man who says " skadoosh " and I put a toy weapon in his hand in the next hour . 
Dear Lily , It 's a long time since I wrote a letter to you . I hope you are doing well and are having a nice weekend . Firstly , I am so sorry I did not contact you , because for the last 2 weeks , I have had a mid -exam , so I have been really busy . As you know , I am a final year student , so I need to try my best to keep and achieve good results to prepare for my future . I want to find a good job after I graduate from the University . So I hope you can forgive me . Today is Saturday , so I am free after the stressful exam time . I went to the cinema and watched the movie " KONG Island . " Do you know or have you watched the film ? I think you like this type of film . It is a movie about KONG , with many modern techniques . I know that the movie was filmed in Ninh Binh , Vietnam . And Ninh Binh is my hometown . It is a very beautiful place and one of the famous travel places in Vietnam . Most foreign tourists go to Ninh Binh when they come to Vietnam . I also hope after the Covid pandemic ends , you can come to Vietnam and Ninh Binh . I will be very happy when I can meet you . The film is about the survival of Kong on Skull Island , how Kong fights against human intrusion . The content is quite simple , but it is extremely meaningful . I think you should go to see it if you have any time . In the end , I miss you so much and am looking forward to hearing from you about your internship at Columbia University . I hope you have a good time and experience at this time . And please take good care of yourself during the Covid pandemic . Best of luck to you and see you in your next letter . Sincerely , 
In recent years , there has been a heated debate on whether college students should be forced to do physical activity due to the fact that , because of the heavy effects of modernization and industrialization , it is plausibly hard for students in universities to keep a reasonable balance between stressful schoolwork and physical and psychological health . While I hold the firm belief that it is doubtless for school children , who may probably be too busy to distribute some of their time and energy in order to satisfy their basic requirements , I , to a large extent , maintain that only by doing regular exercise , be it jogging or swimming , can we , students , have a prime opportunity to pursue more rounded personalities as well as enhanced academic performances . In this essay , I would like quote a few examples to support my opinion . To begin with , generally speaking , exercising can absolutely release us from feeling stressed and suffocated , which is remarkably catering to our physical needs and psychological pursuits . What I mean by this is that under so many fierce competitions in schools and institutions , it is rather important to keep fit to ensure the success of our academic grades , which any benefit us undoubtedly and offer us valuable chances toenlarge our merits and edges over other candidates of further would - be competitions . Therefore , it is of great necessity to guarantee our exercise on a daily basis , as a consequence , starting now ! In addition , in many cases , as it is known to everyone , making ends meet has been increasingly difficult for adults , especially when during an extended period of time the whole world is suffering from a financial recession due to COVID -19 , it seems more essential to every individual , school children in particular , to have a healthy condition not only physically but also mentally to prevent them from being bombared by the bills of different operational costs and daily consumption accordingly . Simply put , as an old saying goes , a healthy body ensures the success of the revolution , which exactly proves my mentioned point . To sum up , while schools are allowed to enact and enforce a number of specific regulations about exercising , which might seem to be too cruel somehow , I am still convinced that it is our capability and responsibility to follow them , as they could make us effective and efficient somehow . Ideally , change your against mind and start to move , instead . 
