My favourite is Red Thai Curry . The food comes from Thailand . It is really spicy and special in taste . It is not common for us and we do not eat it every day . I like to eat it with rice . I think the rice is called Jasmin rice . It smells really good . In addition , we add mushrooms , carrots and tofu . This way you can have a meal without meat , i . e . a vegetarian meal . That means it is really healthy and tasty food . 
Dear M . S . Nada , First of all , thank you for your discussion , it was really helpful . Taking care about yourself is very important , because if you have any health problems , you will not able to eat or drink well and live your life to the fullest . In my opinion , it is more important to be healthy than to be rich , because if you have bad health , you cannot work or study or develop yourself . About becoming rich , it is not impossible , but it needs a good effort and to keep peactine about your progress . I am going to tell you the steps to be healthy . Firstly , eat healthy food . This means eating good food , including the triangle of carbohydrates , vitamins , fats , minerals and meat . Secondly , make sure to sleep well , between 6 to 8 hours . After that , do exercise . Finally , to be healthy , it is really important to become rich . 
Taking care of your health is so important . Our health is precious and no one can help you with that if you do not look after yourself , I mean having a balanced diet and eating sensibly and doing exercise . Listen to your body , because it leads you to have the best results in your life . I totally agree with the statement it is more important to be healthy than rich , because I believe that it does not matter being rich in life , there are many things more necessary than being rich . If you have good health , you are one of the luckiest people in the world , that does not need someone to pay for them to have surgery , like their eyes , or for their hearts . Also , think about your life , how it would be if you were rich but ill . You would not be happy , right ? Yes , in fact , all happiness comes from good health . In conclusion , remember that your health is weart and you need to save and keep it . Always be grateful for every moment that you are healthy and have a good income . 
The question if it is better to be healthy or to be rich is certain . It is very important to be healthy . When you are healthy , money is very important , because you need a life , a nice house or flat , you may want to have children , etc . Money is the only device for a better life . The natural or original thing in our life is our health . Two years ago , I had a moment when I found out that only one thing and everything is away . We have to protect our health . We can try to suggest that we have money , but we do not have health . What is this ? I think that we are feeling bad . I have had everything and I have to still take it . We have done everything to be healthy and now we are doing it too . I would like to say that we have to hold our life in a healthy mood . It is the only thing that we have to do . We will have a lot of things like money . There is only one life . I want to be rich and healthy too . Then my life will be the best . 
I use the computer every day from the morning till the evening . What I used to do on the computer was to see videos and play games , now I usually use it for learning English and seeking work . Right now what I most enjoy is to listen to music and study English , also I like to speak with my friends and play with them . 
I think Write and Improve is great , because this site has four big characteristics . First , this site can check the sentence I wrote . If I make mistakes , the site suggests corrections for the word . Then , changing the word or sentence over and over makes my English skill improve . And this site has three ways to convey the mistake . Because of that , I can understand the mistake clearly and it makes me improve my English skill fast . Second , the site has a variety of tasks and has 5 different levels , beginner , intermediate , advanced , business and just for fun . Therefore , I can select the task which is close to my English skill and can do English writing comfortably . Third , the site has a test zone . Most people want to test their own English skill when people get a good deal of English skills . If I become like that , I can take a test and if I pass , I 'll get a great feeling , like achieving the aim . Last , this site is equipped with many programs . So the detail of this site is good . The site is nice and I 'll recommend it to my classmates . 
It is quite well known that television entertains , but there are some doubts about whether television educates or not . On the one hand , we use television to have fun , relax and entertain ourselves in different ways and we spend a lot of time in front of it . On the other hand , education experts have been trying to solve this question for so long , does television educate ? I 'm not totally sure about it , but I know I have been watching television to learn things for a long time . There are lots of educational channels available for a wide range of ages , from 1 to 99 years . The major problem is most of the time people do not use television as they should do . Mostly children and teenagers need to be supervised while they are watching television as part of an educational program . Even adults need to deal with the desire to watch entertaining shows on television instead of an educational show . In short , I think people can use television for an educational purpose . 
Nowadays , a lot of students are getting unhealthy because of their inactive lifestyles . That makes some people say all students at school or university should be forced to do sports activities at least 3 times per week . In my opinion , I agree with their thought and encourage the government to make some policy about it . There are several reasons for my opinion . To begin with the most important one , from some research of Cambridge University , those students who do sports activities daily can actually have a brighter future than the others . The reason for this is simple , those people who do daily sports not only have a healthy body , but also have a spirit of never giving up . Which means they will have more chances in their future than others . Secondly , there are two kinds of students , those people who like sports and those people who do not like sports . For the first type , their schools or universities do not need to force them to do weekly sports activities . But for the other type , it is necessary for their schools and universities to force them to do weekly sports activities . Because if their schools or universities do not force them , they will never do any sports activities , which can have a bad influence on their health . Last but not least , doing sports activities can bring us a lot of positive effects . On the one hand , doing daily sports activities can make us healthier . On the other hand , it can also make us have a wonderful social life . For example , you can make a lot of new friends when you are doing sports activities , which can give you a better personality . By the way , when you are doing sports activities , you can gain lots of precious memories that you can recall someday in the future . To summarize , students should do daily sports activities . Our schools or universities should force their students if it is necessary . 
There is a question about our behavior towards our own life , would you prefer a long calm life or a short intense life ? Everyone has their own answer to this question . In my opinion , a short intense life is way better than a long and calm life . There are several reasons for my opinion . To begin with the most important one , from some research by Cambridge University , those people who have intense lives actually can have a better life than the others . They explain it with a theory , the personality of those people who have an intense life are more positive , they know what to do when something suddenly happen . Secondly , from my point of view , a long calm life means a boring life . But life should be exciting , which means people are wasting their lives if they spend every day doing the same thing . By the way , although those people who have a calm life can live a long life , when they 're old , they wo not have anything to recall . Last but not least , an intense life maybe is short , but it will make you feel refreshed every day . For example , you can make new friends every day or experience new adventures normally . If you have an intense life , on the one hand , you can fill your own life with a lot of valuable memories . On the other hand , when you are old , there will be lots of things for you to recall . To summarize , an intense life is better than a calm life , even though intense lives are always short . 
On holidays or at the weekend , an outing to a zoo is always welcomed , especially among the youngest . But are zoos suitable places for the animals kept inside ? Would not it be smarter and wiser to leave them in nature ? I would say it depends . Indeed , nowadays wildlife is increasingly threatened . Poaching , mass breeding , trafficking and the destruction of ecosystems are the main reasons for the dramatic plummeting of the different types of animals on Earth . But the list is far from being complete and wildlife today has nothing to do with the variety we could have observed 50 to 100 years ago . And that 's where the zoos can act in a good way . By providing the animals with a living environment , obviously much smaller than the one they would have had in wild , but much safer for them and their offspring , zoos are helping to preserve a wide variety of fauna . Therefore , zoos can be an excellent way to preserve wildlife . Besides , by showing them to the public , everyone can learn about them and be sensitized to their protection . As long as the world stays as it is currently , there 's no way we could return those animals to nature . It is true that they belong in it , but nature is no longer safe enough for them , whatever the ecologists who would like them released say , and therefore they will be delivered to human madness and to death . 
In this modern society , the rate of chronic patients gradually increases every year , which represents that there are more and more unhealthy humans . Why does this situation happen ? It can be attributed to an irregular daily routine and sleep schedule . According to the investigation , the data demonstrated that office workers are under a lot of pressure at work , and in their leisure time , they prefer to veg out in front of the TV rather than do exercise . It is a malignant cycle ; therefore , there are more and more scientists promoting exercise , which can help you be in shape and healthy . From my viewpoint , I concur with forcing students to participate in PE class . First , healthy habits should be cultivated in childhood . Schools can teach students correct concepts about diet and sport . This type of knowledge can be applied to their whole life . Consequently , when growing up , they understand how to take care of themselves and maintain a regular daily routine . When entering in the elder , they can prevent severe diseases and enjoy a jubilant retirement . Second , the purpose of having sports activities is not only healthy but is also sound development of the body . When doing exercise , individuals ought to acquire how to control perfectly their bodies to meet the standard . This is extremely significant for children , for they are supposed to learn the rules of each item , which can enhance the development of the brain . Finally , having PE class can make students experience a diversity of sports . These kinds of encounters ca not be obtained from a book . Besides , when playing games , they enroll in how to coordinate with others , how to confront failure , and how to make use of strategy , and so forth . These advantages are useful in their whole life . To sum up , forcing students to do sports activities is all benefits without harm . It cannot only reduce diseases but also increase longevity . 
Hi guys , I am Xinh and I come from Viet Nam . I am a student at Hanoi University . My major is languages and I chose English as the main language to study and for essay writing for my topic . Because English is a global language , I want to learn and follow it to find new and attractive opportunities in the future . I can hunt for scholarships or work in foreign countries . Of course , to do that you must study hard and try your best . Another reason why I like learning English is I want to make friends from all over the world . Because Vietnam is a quite small country and developing , many people do not know Vietnam . I want to introduce the history and the beauty of Vietnam to everybody in the world . I hope I can contribute a part of myself to promote the culture and cuisine to international friends . I can create a volunteer club to do this in the future . If you like this , you can absolutely join me next time . 
To whom it may concern , I am writing this letter to tell you my ideas and my opinion about banning mobile phones in shops , restaurants and public transport , and why I think that it is not a good idea . The banning of the use of mobile phones in shops , restaurants and public transport is a tremendous disadvantage for the people who work with smartphones , such as : social media managers , vloggers and influencers . Indeed , without a mobile device , they cannot do their job and I think that this is disrespectful to them . The second reason for which banning mobile devices in public places is not a good idea is because mobile phones are one of the most useful things to communicate with people , especially when you are alone in a place that you do not know , or if you have to meet a friend and you do not know where it is . Finally , I would say that mobile devices , and especially smartphones , are very helpful in dangerous and emergency situations , as with them , you can call immediately someone to help you , like the police or hospital . I hope that you will read this letter , and you will change your mind about banning mobile phones and other devices from public places . Best regards , Paride 
In general , I like to draw random things which seem good to me or I play video games after school and I prefer to listen to music in my free time . Actually I listen to music every day , however I need free time for drawing . I like to do art or science things in my free time and if you try these , you will understand why I like to do them . I drew a little cat with his fish two hours ago . 
This notifies that I agree with your decision to implement a new municipal rule to prohibit using mobile phones in public places as a part of the amendments approved by the council in this month . Some people may cast a doubt on why suddenly this restriction on using mobile phones is put in place . However , after observing immoral behavior in so many public places , I am on your side . It is because immoral behavior , in turn , causes friction or a lawsuit among the people in our town . This trend was surprising to me , to be honest , because I believed that our people living in this town could live a life without a specific rule on mobile phone usage . Yet , the reality was in contrast . I found a lot of cases last year just to argue some offensive behavior triggered by mobile phone usage . To protect our life , this implementation should be welcomed by all of us . Said that , one suggestion from my side is to launch a new educational programme for everyone to digest what is moral behavior in a public space and what is not as an example via a video streaming service . While it takes time to penetrate this common understanding on how to use a mobile phone in a public place , I strongly consent that educational contents will prevent our future conflicts in mobile usage , for sure . 
Hi , I hope you 're doing well ! Last Friday , I went to a music concert with my dad to attend the first -ever performance of Rossini 's Barber of Seville in our town . I was keen to go to that concert , because I love Rossini 's music . Besides , it was the first time that opera had been played in the music hall we went to ! For this special event , we had first class musicians and singers performing in front of us : the London Symphony orchestra and famous singers from all around the world . The actor performing Figaro was excellent and he had a wonderful voice . The hall was already overcrowded when we arrived . Luckily we had booked tickets previously , so we managed to get good seats . The show lasted for 2 hours . Although it was long , I really enjoyed being there ! Therefore , I strongly recommend you to go and see one of their performances . I 'm sure you would enjoy it as much as I did ! Have a nice day . 
