Report about my experience with Write and Improve I started to use Write and Improve a week ago . Till now I have found it very useful . I like that it is very easy to use , the menu is very clear , with tasks ordered by difficulty . It has different kinds of subjects with all kinds of tasks and that is very good , because it makes you think and improve your vocabulary . I like that it gives you feedback , corrects your spelling and you have the option to change your work and make it better . I also like that it shows your progress . This is very good , because it makes you do better next time . What I do not like is that in the feedback , in the answer , the question it does not show correctly . Even if I answer all the questions , it shows me that I did not . I will definitely recommend it to my friends . It has helped me improve my writing and spelling . 
I discovered Write and Improve during my English learning course , and I found it an excellent tool to improve my skills to write about different topics . They are interesting for everyone , but prior to all I appreciated to see the feedbacks on my reports in few seconds , I appreciated to see the feedback on my reports in a few seconds , with the highlighted mistakes and an hypothetical result of the exam . Then , you can choose your level from beginner , intermediate and advanced , but it 's possible to switch it each time you want . And , important information , it 's free of charge , you have just to register on the platform , without any ads if you do not want , nor request of information about your credit cards . With an account , you collect the results of your reports for each level on a graph which evidences your improvement or less . In my opinion , this is the best instrument to check your ability to write about something quickly if you do not have a physical teacher or a classroom ; knowing that it 's very hard to have them today , due to measures against the spread of the coronavirus , I recommend everyone this useful tool to stimulate your mind to develop arguments in English properly . Enjoy your course and write , then write again ! 
What do you do in your free time ? In my free time I prefer to sleep . How often do you do it ? When I have a job only in the night , and when I 'm unemployed all the time . What do you like about that activity and why ? Maybe because I do not have to think , and in this way I forget about my financial problems and strong anxiety . I like living in the oblivion . Tell us about the last time you did this . Sure , thank God I do not remember anything about my dreams or nightmares , who knows . 
Learning English is very important and I will tell you why . All around the world people can speak English . English is the most famous language in the world . I have been learning English for 20 years . I studied at school as a small boy . I do not know when , I think I was 8 years old . We had a great teacher for English . At the grammar school we had a lot of teachers and our level went down . One year we had four teachers , yes , a lot of changes . Then I learnt alone . I taught myself . Everyone should learn English for their life . My reason was for a better job . Everyone can study what they want . I would prefer English than another language . Therefore , I will pass an exam in the English language in July . I hope I will do it . I am learning English every day and I am happy . You can do it . Let us get to B2 First level . It is a degree for each of us . We have to learn a lot . I will have done it by 12 July 2021 . Have a nice day . Tom . 
Good morning Miss Town , I heard a few days ago that you and your council were thinking about a new law that was to ban phones and all digital devices on public transport , in restaurants and in shops . I think it can be , at first , a good idea if the people in the city wrote a letter about that law to see their opinions , so I will begin with my idea . I do not think that banning digital devices in those public places is a good idea because these digital devices are important for the life of today . If people do not have their phones on public transport , they cannot receive the message that says that their mother is dead ( for example ) , they wo not know that , and when they get off the bus , they will see that there is a problem . If people cannot use their MP3 , they will be obligated to hear the cries of babies , the discussions of people that they do not want to hear . Secondly , if people do not use digital devices in public places , what will they do ? They wo not speak with anyone , they wo not do anything , even if it is being bored by life in public places . I see a lot of people that work on their phones , that do important things on their phones , so I think that banning digital devices is not a good idea . I hope you will read my letter , and I hope you will like it . Thank you for your attention . Sincerely . 
Hi there Max ! Are you doing well ? Anyway , you are right . I really want to improve my English and I am trying my best to practise as much as I can . In my free time , I read English books and answer the questions in an online class , but I am still weak on grammar . I have just bought a grammar book too , so that I can learn more about it . Roux 
Welfare states like mine provide free health assistance for basic cures : but if you need something more serious , and you live in a small town surrounded by mountains or away from a big city , it can be hard to find the doctors who you need , or a hospital with the right tools for you . This is the result of a transition of the funds that was increased to build a few efficient hospitals , against the reduction of the resources for small first aid centers . About private medical doctors , the argument is the same : an office in a town with a few thousand inhabitants is not as profitable as one in a big city , so if from one the side , it is necessary to have health assistance everywhere you live , on the other side , a doctor prefers to work where there is increased earning potential . The government , in my opinion , has to find a way to keep enough doctors and tools equally divided in his territory because the entire population has the same right to receive assistance properly . 
In the last years , there has been an increasing number of cubicles , with just space for a desk , personal computer and phone : this solution was thought to guarantee more privacy for every worker , and probably was a good idea by the engineers . Some research made by a group that observes workers ' conditions , in fact , discovered that an open space reduces effectively the interaction with each other , maybe because the mind finds it difficult to exchange information with a colleague when all the others can see and hear your discussion . I think that an open design office is more indicated just for particular jobs , such as architects , or events like meetings and courses . In a daily routine , when each employee has their task to develop , a cubicle is the best solution , with right breaks and a time to socialize personally with the other colleagues . This is my opinion , even if there could be examples against my theory . 
Hi friend , My favourite film is The Big Short . The Big Short is a comedy drama film . This film is about the financial crisis of 2008 . The film tells us how the financial crisis of the housing bubble happened , from the causes to the consequences of the recklessness of the financial markets and their agents . The story is told through four characters that invested against the housing market in season . I believe that the film will please my friend , and also incentivize him to know about the financial markets . 
When I was younger I used to sleep in a dark bedroom with the window opened , the twelve months of the year ( I know , it sounds a bit strange , but I like the sensation of fresh air on my face ) . Since I was engaged , and now married , my partner 's opinion is the opposite to mine : every window and shutter must be completely closed , so I had to change my habits . But it was not difficult , when I am tired , I am able to sleep under the high lights in a disco ! 
I belong to the group of people who are not able to play any instrument , unfortunately : having said that , I agree that all students could have a chance to study music and play a musical instrument . In my opinion , if a student has a talent in this field , they must have the tools to develop it , like a talent in some sport or computer science , for example : music is an important part in almost every life , and school is the exact time when you can discover if you will be just a listener , of the radio or similar , or a music -maker , like singer or player in a group . School has an important role for everyone : if it is possible , they must guide each teenager to his best future , according to his skills , and where it is not possible , it has at least to have tried it . Summarizing , every student should have to study music . 
At my green age , it was to join mandatory the army for about one year ( the so -called compulsory conscription ) . Obviously , it is an imperfect comparison , but this old rule often resulted in more sense of responsibility in the behaviour of a young boy . In the same way , I absolutely agree with volunteer work during high school , because it can improve social relations , physical skills and the sense of belonging to a community , physical skills and the sense of belonging at a community , as classroom as the town where the student is . There are already some teenagers that do volunteer work themselves , often following the example of their parents . But I think school plays a better role in giving a civic sense to the future generation : and according to my personal experience , this is an age where you accept some rules only if they are necessary for your target to achieve , like a degree or simply to finish earlier the school period . 
My country is authentic of landmarks , we have pyramids , museums , and temples . Some pharaohs governed my country in the past ; my country is the past my country is the mister of ancient history . When talking about shopping , we have many malls , and we have parks , and rivers . We have hundreds of restaurants and all of them are different . At night you can talk a chill at the river or in the whole country . 
Doing volunteering work is an amazing way for students to learn skills on the ground and have a first experience in a work environment . It shows the university that the candidate is motivated and has a desire to work in a specific field . For example , if you wish to build a career in the organization/volunteering/donation , you 'll need many years of volunteering to get access to the position you 're looking for . It will give the student an understanding of the job and the ability to work and understand the task asked . Volunteering may lead to an internship and a job offer , so it should be taken seriously . I have not volunteered in my life , but thinking about it now , it would have been a good idea . Sometimes , you feel lost in your life , and you do not know what you want to do . Having a try of volunteering may give you some ideas about a career you 'd like to have . I always thought about giving my time to food donations , but maybe next time . I wonder if my English is good . For example , if tomorrow you ask me to write an essay for a test , will I pass the exam ? 
In general , it is important to tell the truth because it is morally right . But it is not always good to tell the truth . As I see it , I am a really honest person , I hardly ever tell a lie . But sometimes , a lie could disappoint the person you are speaking with . So sometimes , it is good to tell a little harmless lie . Of course , it is not right to lie in an investigation or when you did something really wrong . That is because the first lie makes you tell more lies to cover the first one . And that is the real issue . On the other hand , I believe that it is not bad to tell a little lie to make some people feel better . For instance , if someone had a dreadfully cut haircut , you would tell him the lie that the haircut does not look too bad . And that could make him feel better . Some lies also could encourage people to do something . For example , if someone is scared of doing something that looks dangerous , you could tell them that it does not look too dangerous . And that little lie could make them more confident . So as I see it , it is not always important to be honest . So in conclusion , we should think about it before we tell a lie . But we should also think about the consequences of telling the truth . Because the truth can be something that you do not want to hear . 
Hi John , It has been a while since I received a letter from you . You asked me about my favourite film , so here is my answer . My favourite film is Mamma Mia ! Have you seen it ? I think that almost everyone has seen it or at least has heard of it . Actually , I like all musicals , but I absolutely love this one . It is full of lovely and enjoyable songs written by the Swedish pop group ABBA . It is about a girl who is getting married and wants to have her father there . But the problem is she does not know who her father is . I wo not tell you more in case you have not seen it . It is full of joy and it is really fun . I enjoy it every time I watch it . What is your favourite film ? Write to me soon . William 
Dear Billal , Last week , we went to Croatia for a school trip . We visited several museums in Zagreb and saw the culture of the city . Besides these , we visited some shops and restaurants . We toured the city for 7 days and did the homework on the one hand . Therefore we were very tired and spent time in the parks on the last day . We spoke English because we were outside our country and we met new friends there . So we had fun in Croatia . See you soon . 
Some people since their childhood are considered to be extremely gifted due to their inborn ability to produce a beautiful sound while they are singing or they can learn how to play an instrument in no time at all while others find it hard to play the flute while carrying out compulsory tasks in music classes . Most people claim that music talent is inherent and you ca not do anything to change that . For some , it comes easily while , for others , it means punishing training to master their skills . But is it really true that some of us are cut out to be musicians and others simply are not and that there is nothing to do about that ? ' 
