For a lot of reasons , my most important holiday was my honeymoon . Prior to that I had already been to fascinating places , but the experience in Madagascar was absolutely the best I 've ever had ! We started from the capital , Antananarivo , and in sixteen days , with the help of a wonderful local guide with a car , we were able to see the most characteristics places in all of the country , like forests , typical animals and trees , the lifestyle of a normal person and his very poor house . We were impressed by his genuine kindness , without expecting money or goods from us . The idea was he was happy even if he had not almost nothing . In a few days , we saw a lot of landscapes , from mountains to the beaches along the ocean , from cities to very rural farms . We came back with our minds lighter and with our hearts full of love . Today we still speak about this gorgeous life experience . 
I think it is a great idea of high schools . The children experience some real life experiences . Moreover , they can help in the community . You could , for example , volunteer in a home for the elderly and support the nursing staff . Moreover , you could talk with the old people . I am sure that they would be very happy when they can talk to someone . Furthermore , I think you could volunteer for the environment . Maybe you can pick up some garbage or you could plant some trees . I think the nearby cities have some things that also children/teens can do . You could also engage politically . Maybe you can have a youth advisory council or something like this . Then you could enforce your ideas on your city . So you have a say how your city should look . In conclusion , I think it is a great idea that students have to complete a certain amount of volunteer work in order to graduate because in order that students have a lot of free time , which they should use for a good cause . 
Television is communication equipment , therefore it can entertain and also educate . Like any other tool , it all depends on the way it is used . One must be myopic to see only the entertainment applications of television . Yes , it is the most common use by far and we can tell by the number and the quality of shows that are available for common individuals . There are plenty of sports channels , competitions and TV series . Every tired soul will find something to consol and rest after a long day at work . However , if you are willing to educate yourself , you will find programs with meaningful discussions and content . There are specific channels dedicated just to make their audience more knowledgeable in the chosen topic . They usually do not display so much detail , but it is certainly enough to raise the interest in the particular discipline . 
I believe that it is really important to learn foreign languages . If you want to be connected with the world , it is necessary to speak a foreign language . Of course nowadays we have online translators , where you can find almost all languages in a bit . So it is not necessary to learn a foreign language when you can use the internet . In the past there were not any online translators . People had to learn a language or look in a dictionary . The issue is that using dictionaries takes a really long time . But if you want to travel a lot or to live in a different country , you have to learn a foreign language . Currently , many people or at least the young generation , are learning English . Almost every child has English lessons at school . But the problem is that if they do not use the language , the language will be forgotten . That is quite a big issue . Many people learnt a foreign language and now they remember no words . In conclusion , from my point of view , it is important if you will use it . If not , it is just a waste of time . 
I think having new teachers each year is better than having the same teacher for several years , since it is unhealthy for students ' learning . Having the same teacher must be difficult in upgrading the class . We learn new things in every new grade and if the same teacher is teaching for four years , he can be insufficient with new subjects . If you want to hear a specific reason from me , our primary school teacher was the same person in first grade to fourth grade and my middle school teachers were different each year . I learned more and harder subjects than the primary school . In my opinion , teachers should have test lessons and students should choose them . Beside this , I do not think everything is about teachers , sometimes the students should do more practice themselves . Finally , I can say that having new teachers each year is better than having the same teacher for several years . 
The best tool for improving your English What would you say if I told you that there is an excellent tool to improve your English ? There are lots of tools to practice any language , but " Write and Improve " offers free payment options , furthermore it 's backed by Cambridge University . Firstly , W&I is a free tool and almost all of its features are free as well . You can find exercises for any level such as beginner , intermediate and advanced , the tool gives you opportunities to check your mistakes and correct them . I would say that , as you know , there are many tools to practice and improve your skills and W&I is an excellent option because you do not have to spend lots of money and time , however , it has extra features and if you want to use them , you have to pay for them . What I like most about the tool is the ease and assistance to avoid and correct mistakes , moreover , it has a large number of exercises to do . I sugest that if you really want to improve your writing skills , W&I is one of the best options that you could pick up . You only need a couple of minutes every day to practice and I can assure you that , as soon as you notice , your writing will have improved . 
I like to do exercise . I usually do exercise almost every day during the period of the afternoon . When I do exercise , I prefer exercising outside , practicing soccer with my friends . I like to exercise outside due to the climate and the fresh air , both are motivators to continue exercising for me . Doing exercise outside provides me with tranquility and energy . The kinds of activities I like to do are playing soccer , cycling , and walking . 
In my opinion , in these days , learning to speak a foreign language is more important than it was in the past . In this age of a global world , people can move easily , without high costs , around the world , either for work or for leisure , so it is important to learn another language beyond their native one . I personally feel that to know another foreign language helps to understand other cultures . Nowadays , people can take advantage of more opportunities in this world , where borders are wider and wider . Secondly it is the age of computers . Thanks to the internet , every day , people are connected to other people from all the countries . Not only other people , but everyone can access information , thoughts and knowledge written in other languages . In this way , a person could improve himself , his skills and also his way of living . To sum up , learning to speak a foreign language is more and more important , because in the modern world , there are a lot of opportunities to meet foreign people , to get to know other cultures and even to live in other countries . 
Dear council , Are you sure your decision could be a good idea ? I would want to switch your attention to the central role communication has in our life . You can be a mother , a manager , a doctor , and at any moment , someone can call you for something extremely urgent , and the same could be with a message : I agree that a bus full of passengers with their heads down in their smartphones can give a feeling of sadness , but I do not think a ban could be the best solution . Nobody prohibits speaking with each other , so everyone is free to choose their behaviour , within the limits of the civil roles : about this , I could suggest a useful role about the use of mobile phones in public areas . Can you make a law that can oblige people to speak on their mobile in public spaces only with a headset ? I , and a lot of citizens like me , ca not stand hearing the noise from phone calls , sometimes made with a loud volume : so , if it 's your goal to put a rule about using a mobile phone in public areas , please pay attention before banning such an important tool in our daily life , and consider the way to limit its use in a less noises way than now . I would be grateful if you could reply to my observations . Your citizen , Holly 
Hi Matt , This school year , I will try to speak with English friends , take English exams , and I will read in English ... But I do not think it 's a good idea to pass English exams instead of passing school exams . If you have English or someone who speaks English well , that will be easier . Take care . John Smith 
As requested , this report is to assess English learning goals for the new school term . 1 . Reading skills are at an acceptable level . 2 . I have good knowledge of grammar in my level . 1 . Speaking should be more natural . 2 . There are some difficulties in writing reports and articles . 2 . Vocabulary level is too low . 3 . Pronunciation is problematic and needs to be improved . 1 . It is necessary to develop a reading habit for vocabulary building . 2 . Usage of a good dictionary to expand vocabulary . 2 . Make friends from different countries and communicate with them in English to improve speech fluency . 3 . " Shadowing " technique for pronunciation , as listening to a model and repeating what they say in real time helps to sound more natural . 4 . Listening to podcasts , as listening to the language you 're learning is in itself useful . It can introduce us to a range of different accents . Moreover , it brings us closer to the real language . 5 . Usage of the " Write and Improve " app to practice writing reports and articles , with an emphasis on organization , length and spelling . 6 . Watching movies and reading books in English to immerse in the language . Immersion is the fastest and the most effective method to learn a foreign language . 
Nowadays , many young people lead a sedentary lifestyle that means they rarely get involved in sports activities , and therefore , it is suggested they should be required to do sports at least 3 times every week . I completely agree with this method . First and foremost , an inactive lifestyle has affected the physical health of young students . Without adequate physical exercise , they are more likely to suffer from some illnesses , such as obesity , diabetes and heart disease , which would do harm to their personal lives and studies in the long term . Thus , if they are able to participate in sports activities , these problems could be solved because their immune system and body circulation would be enhanced by doing sports . In addition , young people who appreciate a healthy lifestyle with more opportunities of taking part in sport activities may develop their interpersonal skills more easily than those people who always stay indoors . In particular , through doing a team sports , they could have more chances to communicate and cooperate with others , which would be a key ability for their future life and career . Therefore , at school , sports clubs are perfect places where people can develop their social skills by meeting new friends and interacting with their peers , and learning sports in PE classes is also beneficial for them to learn how to work in a team and solve problems with others ' assistance . Admittedly , many opponents may disagree that young students should be forced to do sports at certain times as they ought to have the right to make plans for their leisure time . If they are persuaded to take part in those sports activities , they may hardly be interested in those sports and build a more negative attitude to physical exercise . However , one fact that needs to be highlighted is that the physical problems caused by the lack of sports activities are a huge concern around the world , which should be solved immediately . Besides , the addiction to computer games and social network websites has impeded the enthusiasm of doing sports for many young people , and therefore , this solution should be valuable and effective . In conclusion , from my own perspective , young students in universities as well as school children should be forced to do sports regularly . 
" There is one thing in common among successful people which is that they do exercise " - Galway I love to exercise and I believe that it is a must for anyone seeking success . For me , I have exercised almost every day for at least the last 2 years in which I lost 10 kg of my weight . Exercising at a gym or outside both have pros and cons , for example exercising outside the gym is more economical and has no limiting rules regarding the time you wish to exercise . On the other hand , exercising in the gym is more intense and you get a mentor . 
Nowadays , medical doctors prefer to work in cities because they find better opportunities to be successful than if they work in rural areas . However , this can be changed and will improve the healthcare in remote zones . Firstly , the problems in health services need to be improved in both areas . The main problem about rural zones lies in a lack of growth opportunities , low salaries and lack of necessary equipment . Due to these problems , medical doctors prefer to work in urban areas rather than rural ones . Nevertheless , the solution could being implemented by the government if they offered better conditions of work for medical personnel , such as fair wages and growth opportunities . In conclusion , our healthcare services and medical staff need to be improved . People who live in remote areas suffer the lack of these services more than people in the cities , I believe that this problem can be solved if the government works to improve the working conditions for medical staff . 
At first impact with the question , it 's too easy to answer that the truth is always the only thing to say and to hear . Sure , this is a utopian reality , and a world without lies will not ever exist for the main reason that human beings are imperfect . This obvious statement drives me along the line of thought that is a skill of some people telling lies that seem truthful for a personal aim , and who does not have this skill is forced to have at least the ability to listen carefully to the sound of the true statements . I do not think that one person can be able to tell always the truth , but there are very important differences about the way and the reasons why we tell a lie : sometimes we have to defend our bad behaviour , often it 's necessary for a " politically correct " speech , in other cases , it could be just to avoid that our listener could know our business or plans . But , such as I said firstly , this is a dangerous joke : if you are not able to cover your lies , your risk is to damage your public opinion and to seem like a liar , even if you tell the truth . However , the best way should be to choose the moments that need a sane lie , and in all the others , it 's better to be sincere and truthful . 
