Playing is a natural way of interacting and practicing different skills . Video games , in my opinion , have a similar role in young people , therefore I have a positive feeling about children using video games . I am going to explain it now . There is a lot of research about the beneficial effects of gaming on children . One of those has found that boys and girls develop and improve important social skills , as such team -working and fast strategy decisions , which are highly valued by multinational companies . Another very important ability to be developed during games is understanding and practicing the English language , like reading , listening and speaking mostly . The last paper I read focused on the improvement that youngsters have in their performance -solving problems too . Parents ' negative thinking about video games comes from their ignorance and bad relationships with their children . Basically , many of them grew up without experiencing video games and they are scared of them . If parents balance the permission to play games and socializing in real life for their children , it could be beneficial . They only need to take care of the type of games and the amount of time they allow their children to play . 
