I think that it is impossible for computers and tablets to replace books in schools and universities completely . Along with the improvement of technologies , I also think that to some extent , computers and tablets can replace books in schools and universities . To replace them completely , I think there are two problems to solve . I think the first problem is how to digitize historical documents . A lot of historical documents are not digitized , so that you have to go to a library to read them if you need to . I think it is difficult to digitize such historical documents and it will take so much time to do . I think the second problem is how to keep the security of the IT network system . If the IT network is down because of some trouble , it is impossible to use computers and tablets . Recently , it has often happened that IT networks in the world have shut down because of a computer virus . So I think it will take for a long time for computers and tablets to replace books completely . 
