Nowadays , it is undeniable that playing video games is the most common current teenagers ' fondness , moreover it has given a lot of employment to workers . However , this activity is equally undervalued by adults , since the games are a big source of distraction . Firstly , most video games show players different useful skills , such as creativity , following instructions against the clock and coordination . Furthermore , there are some games available in a foreign language , therefore you might be forced to understand the words and , consequently , your brain will think more . Secondly , adults are searching every day for an alternative to screens . One of them is doing exercise . An advantage of this activity against bits world is natural light radiation , moreover muscle movements . Finally , getting a job in the video games industry is actually very easy . In our days , young people can have a degree in Graphic Design and create their own computer games , and even a graduate in Translation could write the script of a Nintendo video game . As a conclusion , I argue that video games are really important in our lives , since they have had a huge impact on our society . So , dear parents , you should not try to hide this art from your children . 
Even though a lack of exercising brings negative effects to our bodies , it is not appropriate to force students to play sports . Indeed , there are several reports and research about the negative effect caused by the lack of exercise . Therefore , there are many articles advocating the advantages of frequent exercises and sports in magazines , newspaper and the Internet . However , when it comes to forcing students to do exercises and play sports , it is another story . The following contains other feasible ways to prevent students ' health from getting worse , better ways to encourage students to exercise more , and the reason for my disagreement . First , playing sports is not the only way to maintain our health in a fair condition . In other words , having well -organized eating habits can also have an impressive effect on keeping good health . For example , calculate the calories in meals and make sure the nutrition you take in meets the daily requirements , avoid having meals at midnight , and do not touch fried meals . Second , instead of setting rules about the time they need to exercise , it is more rewarding for them if there are related events , contests , or even championships . By holding a variety of sport events , the students will be interested in sport rather than being forced . Last but not least , since there are different kinds of sports , it is possible for them that some certain way of playing sport does not make them exercise enough . For instance , defensive positions in basketball and baseball . Not to mention , those who have no interest in these sports try to find a cozy spot for themselves and watch the whole game without moving much . In conclusion , I do agree that one refusing to have a proper exercising habit will eventually lead him or her to have a body with deteriorating health . But it is also necessary to find a flexible way for students to let them enjoy sports , instead of forcing them to do so for their own good . 
