I think being healthy is more important than being rich . I was sick for the last two years . All the money in the whole world does not matter when you 're in unbearable pain . First , I had a benign brain tumor . Before surgery , it had hurt so badly I wanted to cut off my head . After surgery , half of my face was paralysed . Actually , it 's over two years since the tumor was cut out of my brain and I 'm still not in the shape I used to be . When I was visiting my doctor , he said that I still had something in my head . Something else . It turned out that I needed another surgery . This time it was a malignant tumor , a glaucoma . After I left the neurosurgery department , my condition required radiotherapy and after that chemotherapy . I was lucky that my insurance covered all the bills . Some people are not so lucky and then they need a huge amount of money for their treatment . That is the reason for spending your money . So yes , money is also important , but health is the most important . 
Music is an important part of everybody 's life . For sure , everyone has contact with music every day - on TV , on the radio , on the Internet , on our phones . We even learn about music at every school level from kindergarten to high school . However , in some schools , learning music is not required . For me , it 's good , because not everybody has to learn music . At the beginning , I want to say that not everyone has a talent for music - to play an instrument or sing . Obviously , it 's normal . We all are different , we know and do things in other ways , so not everyone has to know music well . What 's more , a lot of people are shy . In that case , they may have problems with learning music because they are ashamed that they have to play or sing publicly . To be honest , I am an excellent example of that . I learnt music at primary school and it was really challenging for me . I was incredibly shy - I sang very quietly and I was nervous when I had to play something . Because of that , I was scared before every music class . And that 's not the point ! Music classes should be calm and stress -free . So you see , not everybody must learn music at school . I truly believe that even if we do not learn it , all of us has enormous contact with music . And I 'm sure it teaches us more than normal classes at schools . 
Someone might argue that exercise is important for our health . I hear what they are saying . However , I believe that there are more important things . I will describe three things below . First , it is important to sleep enough . Based on some research , if there is not enough sleep , the positive effect for health decreases . That is because growth hormones occur a lot during sleep . Second , it is important to have good ingredients too . After exercising , the muscles need to recover . Then good ingredients are required , for example , protein , vitamins and minerals . Moreover , we need to have good ingredients for a good health and mind . Third , it is important to be relaxed . I believe that it is the most important compared to the other things above . A little stress might be good for our health . However , generally speaking , stress is bad for our health . And relaxing is good to get rid of stress . So it is better to have a good situation in which we are able to be relaxed . To summarize , it is important for our health to exercise . In addition , it is important to sleep enough , have good ingredients and be relaxed too . 
When I was child , I saw my grandparents , who are French people , and admired how they could , even if they were poor , live in deep happiness . I asked my grandfather all the time in order to discover the key of his happiness . He explained to me that the reason was very simple : enjoy what you do . Even though this advice was very simple , I was highly convinced that was the secret of living good and happy . Due to that statement , I think it is interesting to live in harmony within our community , it leads us not only to live longer but to live also happily and proudly . I know the fact that life is hard and very exhausting , but enjoying what we do in our life must help us to live in peace with our own life and leads us to reach easily our goals and dreams . I saw may cases in my family as well in my relatives who lived a shorter life but much more intense . It was their choice to live like this , but I am highly convinced that they have never enjoyed their life because they lost peace and happiness . To summarize my opinion , I could say that I hope I will be able to live a long and calm life until 100 years old or even 120 years old , but I insist that the secret to success is happiness . 
Computers and tablets should take over the role of books in academic institutes . Electronic devices provide a much greater use than printed materials . For instance , they update information faster , store greater quantities of data and permit access to the Internet for further online research , which are the essential limitations of traditional means of storing information . It is also observable that for such convenience , in modern times , books no longer retain their appeal to readers as they used to , which is witnessed by the drastic decrease in book sales . Therefore , computers and tablets are bound to replace the hard copies of words in schools and universities . Replacing manuals with high -tech devices in education facilities is a risky choice , for the fact that it requires exhaustive financial resources to purchase these devices . In Vietnam , a similar proposition was introduced to the National Congress , but was denied because of costing half of the national development budget to initiate such a transformation , without any definite guarantee for its results . In conclusion , modern technological devices such as tablets and computers should not be encouraged to be present as the main storage of information in schools and universities . 
For years , schools have designed different methods of study . Many of them have included extra classes like dancing and music lessons . There is research which shows that these kinds of lessons are beneficial for students . However , not all schools offer these classes to their student population . The advantages that learning or playing music have been exposed by much research . For instance , it is known that if children do dancing or learn how to play any musical instrument , they improve their academic performance . In addition , for children in their early ages , a musical education stimulates brain zones which allows the development of some areas : cognitive , emotional , motor , affective and linguistic . Some institutions have included musical education as a compulsory subject due to all its benefits , however , not all schools have the infrastructure to give this kind of education . In conclusion , the advantage of having a musical education is obvious , there is research and evidence to support the results . That is why governments should invest in improving the infrastructure and be able to offer a better education . 
Television was originally invented to serve an entertainment purpose for people in the industry . However , the content on television is gradually changing and offering various choices to serve the distinctive needs of individuals . Nowadays , the content is designed to support a learning purpose , especially for children , which accounts for 20 percent . Many channels embark on childhood development by intervening knowledge with entertainment that is displayed through cartoon characters , to attract the children 's attention . To reap the full benefit from television , child psychologists advise parents to spend time with their kids on television , to mark the imperative knowledge and observe their learning curve . National Geographic is the other educational program which is available on television for free . This program broadens the biology perspective , compresses it in an uncomplicated way , to consume and open a whole new world for adults and children . Television also assembles ubiquitous vocabulary and evokes linguistic development in the early childhood stage . Some research has disclosed that television is the first source of English learning for students in countries which speak the least English around the world . In conclusion , television entertains , but it also educates people in an effective way . 
