I am learning English because I want to have the opportunity to work in a good job , to travel to foreign countries , to be able to read books in English , to watch movies in English and to talk with people with different cultures and likes . At the moment , my main goal is to learn English to get a job with a good wage . From the moment that I have an intermediate level , my chance of getting a job is much more . Companies require candidates to have an intermediate level of English at least . After achieving the goal of getting a job , I will focus on improving my networking with people around the world . This will be important for me to build relationships with people who can add to my life , both professional and personal . Lastly , with English proficiency , I aim to study in a university in the United States , Canada , or a country in Europe . 
As far as I 'm concerned , I think students benefit more from having different teachers throughout the years . First of all , having the same teacher for several years makes the students get used to this teacher . It can be an advantage : the students know their teacher better , the teacher gets more acceptance and respect all through the years , for instance . However , such a familiarity can have a negative impact on teaching . Indeed , as the students are used to their teacher , they can get distracted or irreverent more easily . Besides , it depends on how the teacher works with their students . If it 's a cool , enjoyable , but still instructive lesson , then maybe having this teacher for a few years can be great . Otherwise , if the teacher is boring and their lessons uninteresting , having new teachers each year enables them to avoid the problem of having a boring teacher . Furthermore , having different teachers each year helps the student to familiarize himself with different ways of teaching , which can help a lot when he gets into higher education , for instance . To conclude , each teacher teaches differently , therefore a student could enjoy several types of instruction , all beneficial to the mind then . 
Mankind found solutions for most of the problems which make our lives hard , however these solutions sometimes bring some issues with them . An inactive lifestyle is one of the problems that modern life brings to our lives . A large number of university students are suffering from an inactive lifestyle , and their lives are becoming more vulnerable constantly . I believe that every university student should do sport during university . First of all , doing sports improves students learning skills . Most studies that have been done on university students indicate that students who do sports have more developed brain cells than those who do not do any sports . Having strong cells is essential to learn more quickly and effectively . Furthermore , doing sports provides relief and it reduces stress . Less stress means more efficient learning . Secondly , doing sports gives students another important opportunity : team work . Students can learn to work with each other if they do sport . There are 2 students , one of whom is doing team sport and the other is not . According to most statistics , the former student tends to work with others more than the second student . Those who say that doing sport is only waste of time and it only makes you tired are wrong . Because doing sport has various kinds of opportunities , it is essential for students . It is not a waste of time . While students do sport , they learn and share . because when people do sport , certain hormones make you more energetic and also happy . Therefore , doing sports has more beneficial features than we thought To sum up , modern life is forcing us to an inactive lifestyle . Doing sport is the most logical solution to solve inactivity . And it is also essential for university students . Thus , every university student should do sport if they do not want to , then they should be encouraged to do sport . 
There are different reasons why medical doctors do not want to work in rural areas . I could just list a bunch of them right here , but I 'll try to show the ones I think are the main reasons for this phenomenon . In my point of view , poor wages can be seen as the main reason , as all the process to become a doctor involves a lot of money and effort , so it 's normal that someone who goes through all these challenges expects a life with the benefit of money in a good place to live . Another important point that sometimes is neglected is that , like all of us , medical doctors are also humans , they have the right to have this sense of belonging to a community , and to just expect they have to go to a remote place because that place needs a doctor is a naive thought . These people have families , friends , relatives , relationships that are entangled in the cities they live . These problems can be seen in different countries , poor or rich , but I believe there 're some ways to help solve it . A short term solution could be more incentives so doctors can be attracted to work in these places . Another idea that comes to mind is a rotation among doctors , so some of them would spend some time in these areas and return home after that . However , the main and lasting solution would be an education system that gives everyone the same opportunities , so these rural areas could have doctors of their own , professionals attached to their communities receiving what a doctor deserves for the work of caring for lives . 
Nowadays , it is well known that learning to speak a foreign language is more important than it was in the past and I absolutely agree with that , for these reasons . Firstly , learning to speak a foreign language could support you in finding a great job abroad . As a result of that , you might earn a vast amount of money and you will have the opportunity to live in another country , so it could be awesome . Furthermore , speaking a foreign language could provide you with a lot of money , as you can work in different places . As a consequence of earning a great amount of money , you are allowed to spend it on outstanding things , such as blissful trips , an astonishing house and chill holidays . Last but not least , learning to speak a foreign language has other advantages , such as living better , getting to know impressive cultures and meeting superb people . Therefore , it is very profitable for you . In conclusion , I really consider that learning to speak a foreign language is more important than it was in the past , as it makes it easier for you to find work abroad , it allows you to earn a lot of money to spend on great things and it gives you the opportunity to live better , get to know wonderful cultures and meet stunning people . 
I think students should not have to study music , it can be a student 's choice but not an obligation imposed by the school . I appreciate that , in world , there are schools where studying how to play a musical instrument is a subject on the high of their business , but I think learning to play a musical instrument is not an important quality in a student , to find a job or to be a good citizen in the society . In high school , I learnt to play the guitar , but when I grew up , I did not play the guitar anymore because I was not good . In my opinion , it is wrong to force students to play a musical instrument if they do not want to play some musical instruments . Not everyone has to become a music start or the best musician in the world , and also , to learn to play a musical instrument linked to buy the instrument by family and maybe some families are not able to buy a guitar or some other musical instrument . On the other hand , I agree with schools where students must study music because music is an art and it is correct to teach students the power of music on people , but I want to say : " Stop learning to play a musical instrument , no one is becoming Ringo Star or John Lennon ! ! ! " 
Dear Mr . Stark , I am writing this letter to the council of our town because I want to give my opinion about banning phones in some places . In my honest opinion , banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants is both not good and not wise . At least from my point of view . As you know , we are living in a free country , also in a free city . You , as the government of our town , should not ban mobile phones . By doing this , you are taking part of our freedom in places such as public transport , shops and restaurants . Going further , I think that most citizens of our town would not enjoy the ban , neither would I . In those places , people should be allowed to do whatever they want to . Some people work remotely from our restaurants . No one would enjoy losing their job , you or I would not either . It will , for sure , be a big hit for those people . There are more reasons why this decision is not correct and optimal for the town . One of them is that a lot of people are learning or even surfing the web when they are traveling by public transport . They can learn a new language , read books , messages their friends , etc . Summarising all the things which I have mentioned , I strongly believe that you will change your opinion about this ban . Your sincerely , XYZ . 
In my opinion , for students it is better to have the same teacher for several years , especially for foreign languages . The reason is very simple , changing teachers each year also changes the study mode , the teacher 's pronunciation and so on . Another reason is , especially in primary school , the relationship between the teacher and child is the first step of a student 's growth , and if every year the teacher changes , the children do not make a strong relationship with the teacher . If a child has the same teacher every year , he feels less in awe if he needs help . Now , the teacher 's situation is more complex than in the past , because schools have not got the equipment to start a school year with teachers for all subjects , and not quite all teachers have a regular job contract . Every year , 50 % of teachers do not teach in the school where they taught the previous year , maybe because they prefer to do lessons in a school closer to the long where they live . 
My favourite season of the year is winter , due to it being the season of my birthday . I was born on Christmas Day in 1995 . I also love winter because I can go to ski with Andrew , my boyfriend . I think few people love winter like me . I love also the summer , but I think that winter is the best season of the year . We can go to the beach and sunbathe all day , but complete happiness is sitting down around a table with a hot chocolate , singing Christmas songs and waiting to open the presents under the Cristmas tree . My friends disagree with my opinion . They love summer ! I appreciate the summer , but it 's too impossible to love it . It 's so hot , you ca not sleep well , you have more than 2 showers a day . It 's impossible to love the summer ! ! ! ! 
Nowadays , young people prefer having a short but intense life to a long and quiet life . I am a person who tries to live every day like it was the last , a life full of risks is more exciting than a boring life . Personally speaking , a lot of old people have had long lives because they were hardly able to follow their dreams . During their childhood , they grew up with the idea that a good life was getting married , having a job and having children . In fact , currently , there are people who still have that idea of an ideal life , even if they would like to try different things . Some people still have fears and they prefer following a predetermined routine to following their own aspirations . I grew up with people who told me that I should get a man beside me , I should have children before I am 30 and I should serve my husband all my life . However , my idea of living is pretty different . I enjoy doing outdoors activities , which makes me feel adrenaline , activities such as climbing , parachuting , skating , etcetera . I am aware that some activities could be dangerous , but it is something that is worthwhile . Traveling around the world is fascinating as well , visiting amazing places in remote areas , tasting exotic food are things that everyone should try once . In conclusion , each person has different ways of seeing life and has different aspirations . We should do whatever makes us happy , from my point of view , I would choose a short but intense life . 
I like sleeping in the dark and I do not mind noise . I hate noise . I do not sleep with a small light because it is terrible . I really like silence , because I can sleep . If I sleep with a small light , I ca not sleep because I ca not concentrate . I think a lot of people sleep in the dark and do not mind noise . I also sleep in the dark and do not mind noise . Sleeping in the dark helps me concentrate . 
I feel better after a good night 's sleep . I ca not sleep if my room or the next room has any noise . I take a bath before I sleep sometimes . I like to sleep on the left side of my bed . I always have covers all over me . Having a milky drink before bed helps me sleep . I sleep like a dog if I do all of these . I can never sleep if the lights are turned on . Unfortunately , I lived in a dorm for 2 years and we could not agree about the light with my roommate . I could not get a night of sleep . I was so angry the next day . But we never solved this problem ... 
