The design of an office has for result it . The indoor design of every place has as principle that is a need to achieve the best regardless of who is inside . NA , . It 's important to think about the routine in the office , a customer service place , a customer service place , a meeting room and ergonomic quality for workers . For a company which needs a lot of concentration and an individual works on projects , an enclosed workstation or cubicles are more effective . They help employees emproyees following to focus on and following to focus on and this to find more easily the solutions and conclusions for individual demands . In some companies , however , the task needs more team work , creativity and freedom for discussion and reflection as a group . In this case , offices where open designs happen , the flow of the ideas , communications and collaboration process is more effective . In addition , some that this place can put some space for interaction moments as a team . the projects ' demands , like a room with a sofa and games or to promote a happy hour . The draw for spaces where the people need to spend a lot of time requests a specific design to achieve good comfort and to contribute to the best result . So , the design of an office is a model which does not have walls or with workstations depending on the company needs for results from the employees . It 's important look to build the place pleasantly and that it helps everybody to get the best result from their personal development . 
Nowadays , it is well known that computers and tablets should not replace books in schools and universities , but I firmly believe that they should , for these reasons . Firstly , it is really essential to say that computers and tablets provide students with more knowledge than books , as tablets and computers have the Internet , so pupils could have access to various sources of information . As a result of that , they can learn more things than reading books . Furthermore , computers and tablets have videos , in which information is better explained than it is in books . As a consequence of that , children could learn new things in astonishing ways , thus they will have better marks . Last but not least , the information which computers and tablets provide to students is always being updated , so pupils are not going to study the same things all the time . Therefore , they will find studying a rewarding activity . In conclusion , I really believe that computers and tablets should replace books in schools and universities , as they bring more knowledge to students than books , they have stunning videos in which the information is explained better to the students and the information on computers and tablets is always being updated , thus students will find studying a pleasurable activity . 
Dear Sir or Madam , I am writing this letter in response to the ban of the use of mobile phones in public places which the town council is considering . I believe that it must not be implemented , but some rules or laws would be necessary . It is common knowledge that mobile devices are an essential component of people 's lives in this modern world and they use them almost everywhere . It is indisputable that some of them use them with a lack of morality and show disrespectful behaviour . One of the major issues is noise , which is caused by people who talk on the phone loudly on the bus or train , and other passengers are bothered and frustrated . Although these kinds of drawbacks are paramount and should be addressed , using gadgets in public spaces has some advantageous aspects . For instance , people can do their work , check up on their children , read emails and study , which can people people 's daily lives better and productive . For this reason , in my opinion , texting , reading and other functions that do not make any sound should be allowed . In other situations , such as in a public library , shops and restaurants , it should also be considered . In conclusion , I object to the total ban of using mobile phones in public places . However , it would be acceptable to control the use of them with some restrictions in order to maintain public morals . Yours faithfully , A citizen 
What I love most in Turkey is sarma . Sarma is unique to Turkey . Actually , there are three standard ingredients and these are : grape leaves , rice and onion . I think you would love the taste of sarma ; it is so delicious . Unfortunately , it is very difficult to wrap sarma . We eat yoghurt with sarma . 
In the nineties , people around the world mostly used to communicate by writing letters . Today , mobile phones have completely changed the way people communicate . Mobile phones are taking more and more importance in our life . If we look around us , regardless of what part of the world we are , we notice that the majority of people have a mobile phone in their hand . Mobile phones are extremely convenient and useful . Not only do they allow us to speak in real time with our families and friends , but they also allow us to rapidly get any information we need on many different topics . Today , we could even say that people are addicted to mobile phones . Nobody would agree to be separated from their mobile phone . In addition to that , people are inclined to excessively use their phones , which is now becoming very inconvenient and highly disturbing , especially on public transport and in shops and restaurants . Sometimes , pedestrians cross the roads without paying attention to the traffic lights , which might be dangerous for them and for the drivers . Obviously , the use of mobile phones is rising safety and security issues , therefore banning the use of mobiles would be somewhat unfair because it 's a matter of freedom . Nevertheless , the authorities have to undertake actions to tackle some abusive uses of mobile phones . Maybe by implementing some simple rules for the use of mobile phone on public transport . 
The doctor 's residence Many doctors prefer to live in big cities where they can find more opportunities to make money , whereas rural areas suffer from a lack of doctors . This problem has many crucial consequences . However , there are a number of beneficial solutions to address this problem . First , the government should support these rural areas with sufficient medical supplies and build big hospitals . For example , they can build one hospital in every region . Secondly , the government should provide suitable accommodation for doctors in these areas . They can build a huge compound for doctors and their families , for instance . Third , the government can develop transportation means to aid commuting doctors . Forth , because doctors are going to live there with their families , the government should pay close attention to other services , such as schools , restaurants , and shops . Moreover , the government can offer a high -wage for doctors who voluntarily decide to work in rural area hospitals . These solutions can help limit the significant consequences caused by insufficient medical staff in the countryside . 
As we all know , nowadays , it 's not common for people to do sports activities . It 's terrifying that very few people are living in a healthy way . It 's more common to lead an inactive lifestyle , which is obviously unhealthy for them . Some people say that children should be forced to do sport activities at least 3 times per week during their university and school terms . I believe that this approach is correct . But , it 's far from optimal . Do you want to know why ? Let 's begin ! First of all , doing sports is healthy . I 'm not talking about a sports career or something , which is obviously less healthy ( maybe even less healthier than not doing sports at all ) , but running a few times a week or even every day is , without any doubt , beneficial for our body and mental health . It 's also important for our well -being . I understand that not everyone is talented , muscular or has good genetics . But , I believe that swimming or just simply doing some sport activities , like running mentioned above , a few times a week is very necessary . As long as you have the motivation to change your life , you should do sports . Of course , there are some downsides to this idea too . I think that forcing everyone is just simply not good . There are people who are really talented and take sports activities seriously . We should not make them attend those classes . It 's pointless . We would simply waste their valuable time . Further going , at some age , you realise how important your health is . You discover that it may affect your life in the future . I think that we should not force students . They have a lot of stuff going on in their lives and I believe that they understand at this point how important it is . At the end , I just want to summarise all the things I have mentioned above . I believe that this idea is great . It 's very important to do sports activities , but we should not force everyone to do them . 
My favourite season of the year is the winter . In the city where I live , the winter begins in November and it ends in May . I like the winter because I feel more productive and comfortable day to day . Because of the cold weather , going to work or university is more pleasant for me , due to the fact that I do not sweat on the way and when I am working or studying . I can sleep better in the winter and it is very important for me to keep productive throughout the day . The disadvantage of the winter in my city and state is that it causes flooding in many areas , pushing people affected to move to other areas , leaving their houses that are flooded . The winter is very special for me . It 's the season when I feel happier and more peaceful , getting positive results at work and in my studies , despite the disadvantage cited above . 
