Dear Sir or Madam , I am writing with regard to the possibility that the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops , and restaurants will be banned by the town council . As a citizen of this town , I would like to give my opinion on this matter and give my arguments against this regulation . First of all , banning the use of mobile phones on public transport is not such a good idea . Some people have time to talk only when they commute . What is more , our town is a really popular place for tourists . I am afraid that this ban will negatively affect our town 's economy . As I have been talking with other citizens , they all agree that banning the use of mobile phones in shops is a very bad idea . Some people are very indecisive and they need help to choose the right products . Usually , there is not enough staff in the shop so , as a result , they phone their relatives or friends . Banning the use of phones in shops will also negatively affect the economy . Finally , I do not agree on banning the usage of phones in restaurants as recently there has been a massive interest in food blogging . More and more people film their food and earn money because of it . Our town is famous for its restaurants that are friendly for bloggers , You Tubers , and other influencers . I strongly believe that banning the use of mobile phones is not a good idea . Overall , it will not only badly affect our economy , but it will also have a negative impact on the citizens ' happiness . Yours faithfully , XYZ 
Nowadays , more and more medical doctors desire to work in some cities for a handsome salary instead of working in the countryside . That leads to a medical employee deficiency in many rural areas , which is a significant issue that need interferencing by the government . To solve the problem radically , we need to know about the reasons . From my perspective , many doctors are inclined to give priority to big cities as their workplace by virtue of the financial benefits that rural areas ca not provide them with . It is undeniable that doctors in urban areas could be paid three times as much as those in rural places . It means that they have handsome incomes to pay their cost of living and meet their entertainment needs as well . Moreover , working in these cities brings them many opportunities to develop their careers . Many experts , prestigious hospitals and medical research centres all gather in the big cities all over the world , so it facilitates medical doctors to develop themselves and take advantage of these benefit conditions . Another reason is that there are not many up -to -date devices in the medical facilities in the countryside . However talented the doctors are , it is hard for them to cure their patients in these poor conditions . So , what is the solution to that issue ? I think there is always need of government interference . They should bring in new laws that encourage medical doctors to work in rural areas . Maybe better compensation and benefits packages will work in those cases . It secures them more stable lives and makes them loyal to their jobs . Moreover , the government should provide cutting -edge machines for the medical facilities in the countryside . It will be a shot in the arm that helps doctors in their jobs . Besides , clever advertisement campaigns to stimulate the sense of responsibility and love for medical work will be effective in attracting in attract labour in the rural areas . 
