Young People and sports . Doing exercise is really important for our health . In addition , there are lots of sports , such as walking , swimming and dancing . In this essay , I am going to give my point of view about university and school children doing sports . In my opinion , I believe that doing exercise is necessary for having a better lifestyle , which is great . I know sometimes it is very difficult for students to manage their time because they have lots of assignments to do and complete their quizzes on time to get high scores , but if you want the best lifestyle , you need to think about yourself living the amazing life that you want . Firstly , you need to organise your time by using apps or notebooks , etc . Secondly , prepare all the things that help to be organised , like your statinorties notebook , file , pen and pencil , etc . Thirdly , prepare your sports clothes to do exercise , like going to walk in the garden to walk 20 minutes , after that , going home to have a shower . I feel your will feel relaxed . After that , study hard for all your exams and be patient . Try when you have a busy day as a student to have some leisure time to relax , like having a beautiful cup of tea with wonderful classical music and switching off the light during that time you take a breath so you do not feel so much stress and you enjoy your time . I will sum up with a fasstinc advice by love yourself and take care , be positive , work hard , have ambition to become the best version of yourself . Do not forget you have a bright future , just care for your life and take care of your family . 
Doing exercise is something necessary for our bodies , it helps us to focus and be healthy . In this essay , I am going to write the importance of exercise for children and teachers at school . Doing exercise is the best way to improve your physical health , your memory and your psychology . The reason why is that we need children to do some working out in school , even if they are forced because nowadays there are a lot of opocslity that affect children 's education . For example , sitting around the computer for more than two hours a day harms their body , they ca not move and they will have problems with illnesses like obesity , eye problems and psychological problems , like depression , etc . On the other hand , not doing exercise will give them a lot of illnesses , like they will have low energy , as a result of that , they will have low spirits . Another thing that children might have is insloution so without exercise , they will not be able to make relationships , such as with their classmates and their teachers . As an adult , it is important to do exercise everyday at least ten minutes because the more you do not do exercise , the worse health you might have . Especially when they reach thirty years old , believe me if you do not do exercise , you will have a large bag of medicine that you will need to carry out with you every day . With regards to doing exercise , according to much research , I found out that people who do exercise every day become stronger , happier and they lived long years because they looked after themselves and listened to their bodies . To sum up , I will end with this quote " healthy body in healthy mind , " so always take care of yourself . 
As a student who has learnt for 12 years , this includes living at home with my family for 9 years and living on my own for 3 years . I think that living independently is hard but the best choice . When we move away and live by ourselves , there are various problems that will appear , such as money , time management , balancing learning and working and security . Money is a first and biggest issue when we live without family . We have to pay for everything , even something we did not think about when we were living at home like toiletries , ingredients , cleaners , etc . In fact , some little needed things in a house for a normal life cost very much in total . And when you have more things you have to do than just studying and working , since you still lived with your family like going for groceries , cooking , cleaning , etc . , it takes so much time for you and one important thing is that you have to learn how to manage your time and balance your studying at school and working for a living . Living independently is really hard and challenging , but if you can do it well , you will realise that you are more mature , independent , confident , responsible than an old version of you when you lived with your parents . You know how to order your life , and be a reliable and decisive person . No one can live with us forever , even our parents . Instead of trying to live with family as long as possible , live on your own to develop yourself and make your parents believe in you . 
I think that the requirement that students must complete a certain amount of volunteer work is not a correct thing because volunteer work is an important thing and needs a lot of responsibility , so the people need to do because they want to help someone , not because they have to do it . I already did volunteer work in some hospitals and asylums , and it is a serious thing , there are a lot of rules and we need to be kind and empathetic . I choose do it , no one forced me . So it was a very good experience , but I wanted to do , I think that volunteer work could be encouraged , like showing a video like the movie Patch Adams that is a very beautiful story and my inspiration . The people need to help to make a difference , not only for graduation . These people that only do things to receive an award could be rude and a bad idea for someone that needs help . 
