There are two main types of office design nowadays : separating employee 's workstations into different cubicles and putting no divider between them . From my perspective , I would prefer the first one rather than the latter due to its prominent advantages . First of all , an enclosed workstation tends to enhance focus abilities of white -collar workers . They cannot be distracted by externalities , such as a coworker 's action , when there is a divider between them from other employees . As a result , their work quality will increase and improve a lot . Moreover , workers can be ensured about their privacy in the office . The walls separating employees from their co -workers play the role of wardens for their own houses . There , they can freely do anything that comforts them without being afraid of anyone else . A real life example , a man who is forgetful can stick some sticky notes on one side of the wall although his colleague likes them or not . That also helps them avoid some embarrassing situations . So , workers can work in a good mood , which has a positive effect on their work performances . Another reason is that walls make the office look more tidy and aesthetic . They keep employee 's workstations in the right order and lessen the risk of taking the wrong stuff from other people . Bottom line , enclosed workstations facilitate employee comprehensive . Making them more concentrated on their work , ensuring their privacy , keeping the workplace formal is the thing that makes this type superior to others . 
