Nowadays , it is well -known that high schools and universities are implementing more and more requirements in order to graduate . And despite most students ' disagreement , I would rather see them as great opportunities to challenge them and help them improve and gain a wide variety of skills . Firstly , it is undeniable that students ' schedules are usually really occupied , so volunteering could be quite a wished experience for them , although they might not get round to doing it . As a result , making that activity mandatory may be something positive and enjoyable for them while it is academically necessary . Secondly , the fact that volunteer work fosters better people and the bounty is also an important point to consider because they will be feeling great doing some charity work or giving their help , which at the same time will help their mental health and calmness as much research has shown . Last but not least , the job experience they will be acquiring throughout that time should be mentioned since it will be something very useful and remarkable that they will not forget about it . For instance , communication skills , social interactions , team work abilities ... In conclusion , from my point of view , requiring students to complete volunteer work in order to graduate is a great way to help them to become more professional , better people and gain regarded skills . 
I think playing can have both positive and negative impacts , it depends on how the children use them . It is not wrong if children play video games . Many people in my country use video games for learning a language and it definitely works . You can play a video game and learn a language at the same time . Now , we can consider playing video games like a sport , since we have an r - sport and it gets bigger and bigger . If you consider it as practice until you are a good player , you can do it it terms of sport . But many people ca not make it to that position and not all video games that are considered like a sport , so I think it is also important that you have to arrange what time you play and what time you do not . There are many types of video games out there . Some of them have more benefits than others and I think no game is absolutely bad , it depends on how you use it . 
When I have free time , I like walking through towns to look at the monuments and beautiful landscapes . Generally two times a week I walk in a town . At the same time it 's good for your health to walk regularly . The last time , I discovered the magnificent view from the Basilica Frourrvier of Lyon . 
Essentially , what you are asking is if one would choose a short life of intimacy , home and family versus a fast paced life of sensation , never forming long -lasting intimate relationships and fluttering from one thing to the next in search of adventure and excitement . The choice is crystal clear . A slow , short , boring life but one filled with the real intimacy of a true partner ; the love and nurturing of a family , pets and causes and developments of real and loyal friendships beats the fast life of loneliness , ships that pass in the night , quick trust and quicker betrayals ; the excitement of adventure , shared alone or with strangers , the duplicity and fickleness of the limelight . The answer is clear , just as George Bailey learned in " It 's a Wonderful Life . " You can never put a price on real love , trustful intimacy or the knowledge that there are friends who will be there when you call . It 's boring sometimes , and duty is often tedious , but when you go to bed at night , you are not alone , in your soul . The other way leads to alcoholism and extreme experience , drug abuse , divorces , loneliness and suicide . Just look at the lives of the stars and famous people , all seeking that trust and intimacy and finding only betrayal and loneliness . No wonder they turn to hard drugs - they are committing slow suicide , passing the time oblivious to their aloneness while they are nodding off , waiting to die , wishing for someone to love them , truly love them , for who they are , not what they represent or can do to advance the careers of other ambitious wannabees . Oh , the answer is quite clear . Seneca said it 2000 years ago and it is as true today -- " It is the quality of life that counts , not the quantity . " 
My favorite indoor activity is watching movies , series and documentaries with my family on the weekend . I usually use Netflix 's streaming platform to watch movies , series and documentaries . I like this activity because it is relaxing , fun and a source of learning about various subjects . For example , in the last few days I saw a documentary about the historical advance of cell phone technology and I was able to understand the emergence of the smartphone . The last time I watched a movie on Netflix was yesterday , because it was the weekend . 
As to all university students and school children being forced to do sports activities at least 3 times per week , I personally agree with this idea . I think that one of the merits of doing sports is to make people healthy . And I also think that it is no problem that you choose from the sports what kind of sport you want to do . For example , you can choose walking , jogging , swimming and do such sports at least 3 times per week , it will make you healthy . From my point of view , when I was a high school student , I belonged to the Judo club in our high school . At that time , I did it 5 times per week , from Monday to Friday . Sometimes we had a test match with other high school students on Saturday and Sunday . With this experience , I could improve my Judo skills and train my body . At the same time , I could understand how important it is to continue to train everyday both in sports and in studies . So I think that it is important for young people to do sports at least 3 times per week . l think that one of the merits of doing sports is to be able to make friends by doing sports . Some sports are team playing sports , such as football , baseball , etc . And some sports are individual playing sports , such as swimming , jogging , etc . Even with such individual sports , by doing such sports , I think we can make friends who like the sports . From my point of view , when I was a university student , I joined a ski club in our university . In the ski club , there were a lot of people both who are very good at skiing and who are just novices at skiing . Furthermore , there were some foreigners in the ski club . So I could make a lot of friends in the club so that I could communicate with many members who had a different cultural background , so that I could understand the importance of diversity . 
I agree with the second opinion . I think it is wrong to keep the animal in zoos . All animals belong in nature and no one has the right to keep them in zoos . I think zoos have many problems . First , I think no one wants to live in a cage or a small room . If you ca not imagine it , then try to imagine that you are in a prison and you did nothing wrong . I think it is not fair to keep any animal in a place they do not want to be and do not belong . There are many ways that you can learn about animals , such as you can go and find them in nature . I think if you see animal living in nature , you will never want to go to zoos again . Second , many zoos have a problem with hygiene . It is bad to let animals live in a terrible place . If you think it is right to keep animals in zoos to study them , I think it is best if you study them in real nature . 
