Books vs . Technology Should computers and tablets completely replace books in schools and universities ? That question has been asked for so long and so far nobody has a specific answer to give . My personal opinion is no , computers and tablets and books should be complementary to each other . I believe people need to handle books and flip through the pages . I think it is part of the learning process . When people handle a book , they can feel closer to the book than when they only touch a cold and black screen . Although some researchers have said that computers and tablets should replace books at school , I disagree with them . But I know children need to face new technology to be accustomed to it , because certainly they 'll use it at some time of their lives . However , using computers and tablets may be good for the environment . Think about how many sheets of paper you will avoid printing when you use any sort of technology to read something , mostly not important things . In short , I 'd say there are lots of pros and cons about this idea . 
