My best holiday was when I went to the museum by myself last year . It was a museum I had really wanted to go to for a long time . The night before that day I was really excited about the trip . It almost made me stay in bed all night . I think that night I slept just 5 hours . In the morning , I woke up earlier than usual and left the house earlier that usual too , because I needed all of my time to stay there as long as I could . I went and visited every room and every exhibition that I could . The one that impressed me the most was the show where the artist came to show his skills in painting . I have always wanted to paint an enormous piece of work that could live forever . Also , the artist that came was my most favorite artist . That is why I chose to go on this specific day . I think I wo not forget that day for all my life . 
In my free time I do different activities . On some weekends I watch anime and movies , on others I visit different places , like a restaurant , bar and mall . Sometimes I also do physical activities , like street running . I usually do it on the weekend because I do not have to work . Earlier today I ran a street race in my district . I ran about 5km in 40 minutes . 
When I was a child , my relatives used to ask me what I wanted to be when I was older . My answer was not what they wanted to listen to . As I said " biologist " or " volleyball player , " my cousins answered " a medical doctor . " It is obvious which one had the most attention later . I think this episode might help us to understand the first question . A lot of medical doctors do not do what they do because they love it . The truth is : they love the money that working as a medical doctor can offer them . From this logic , although we found the key to the problem , another question is formed , such as " how can it be solved ? " Sometimes , I think what kind of society we would have if every career earned the same salary . Would we have a lot of people wishing to become medical doctors ? I 'm sure we would not . On the other hand , inside this same logic , I 'm also sure that all medical doctors who have still chosen this career would be the ones who would work everywhere , because they love what they do . Although this problem seems easy to be solved , it 's not . Changing society 's thought so we could finally have a fairer world where we might work doing what we like , makes us change our way of life ( which means our perception about money and happiness ) . The medical doctor 's problem is just a piece of the whole problem in modern society . 
The school of the future The school system is significantly rigid in comparison with the development of our world . We can think for example about the means of transportation . It developed from bare feet to shoes , horses , trains , automobiles and the automobiles developed from steam cars to today 's hybrid cars . And what has changed in school so far ? When I was studying , it looked like this . I was sitting with my class in a classroom and in front of me was our teacher , standing beside a blackboard from where he was lecturing us . To my knowledge , it is not much different from the memories of my parents and I think that it is no different from the memories of their grandparents . They were sitting in a classroom and in front of them their teacher was lecturing . Of course there are some differences . Teachers can use projectors and televisions and maybe students can type their notes on their laptops . But the principle is the same . So I do not expect many differences , I am afraid , just about the content of the subjects . I fear today 's cancel culture because it leads to totalitarianism . 
