It would not be a holiday to me if I just lay on the beach and do nothing other than eat , drink and sleep . I need to be active , even on my holiday . So one of the best holidays I have ever had took place a few years ago in southern Czechia . I went there with a great group of friends . We spent a few days at Dam Lipno . Then we borrowed bikes and during the day we cycled through the beautiful Šumava mountains . After a few days , we replaced the bikes with canoes and went down the river Vltava for the rest of the week . So , after a few grueling days of cycling , we switched to more relaxing canoes in time for the sunny weather . The best thing about going down a river like Vltava is that it is not a boring activity , but it is not much in demand either , so you can afford to have a great time and drink a little . In the end , it is one of the best weeks I can remember . 
I am writing you regarding your question about general practitioners who would rather work in the cities . I guess that one of the major reasons is that those doctors would prefer to get much money for their efforts . The second reason , about which I usually think , is that they are people who could study hard to get certificates , however they could not yet learn enough about good manners , which everyone , especially a GP , must have . General practitioners are rarely not kind , but some of them need to be brought up by their parents well , because neither do schools teach personal personality nor do universities . I think the quickest solution for this matter is that universities should have school subjects that encourage students to be good guys , who can do some good deeds for no reason but for being good doctors . I thank you for giving me this opportunity . 
Hello everyone , I am writing you concerning your question about workstation types . I think there is no need for any employee in any career to have noise during his work . In other words , if the employee has noise , he will have a disadvantage in his work and he wo not be able to do his work properly , as well as if he had a quiet working environment . but it is such a tiny advantage in comparison to the disadvantage of having noise at work . In this case , having independence from others ' desire to listen to the radio or speak with each other . It can be devoided by having walls between the rooms or between the workstations . If the fabric has walls between the sections , the doors can be open or closed . However , if there are no walls , the space must always be open and the noise can easily be heard by the co -workers , who work relatively far away from the noise sources . I thank you for giving me a chance to express my opinion . 
Hello everyone , I am writing to you concerning your question about volunteer work . Some careers are highly dependent on society . The employees and the workers , who have to work with people , should be tested in many , if they are nice enough to deal with people . Sometimes employees are harsh . Those kinds of people are not suitable to work in some careers . The beauty of a society can be shined by testing those people before graduating . Otherwise , harsh people can be employed by an institute , school , university or an organisation , which need nice people more than engineers and well -graduated people . Nowadays , some graduated students do not have anything to do with their families , their friends , their neighbours or their colleagues . In this case , they live like robots and do not have enough emotions to show the consumers or the clients a smile . They just do their tasks like a machine . In some cases , employers are not able to test the employees during the interview , that is why preparing a good generation of kind and nice employees is upon the shoulders of the university and the institute . Otherwise , some countries could be beyond modern in comparison to others , not because of the newest technologies but because of the kind and suitable people who work in suitable places . Those people can lead organisations to help people , not to damage them . Thank you for giving me this opportunity to express my opinion about this matter . This issue is not easy to think about , but it is so important to discuss . 
Hello everyone , I am writing to you concerning your interesting question about the music class . I have asked myself several times , what the music class gave me during the primary and the secondary school . I unfortunately always answer the same answer . NOTHING . Really , nothing . If I were allowed to go home and rest , it would have been an encouragement for me to learn more or to finish my homework early . If the music class were a class during which the student could utter questions , the student would not have wasted a long time asking their parents to solve some complicated issues in the evening . Someone may say , what if a student is an artist ? Well , every single young student was bothered by teaching him music due to one or two students and he was not able to recognize that he was losing months and years of his most important time ever . Otherwise , if the school taught the students everything they need in their future , the school would have many more classes every day to fulfill their desires . If someone says that the music is fun , the response to this expression is that sport is more fun for the students and it is healthy . The students who dislike music are much more than the students who dislike music . If someone says that we have to change every class the students do not like , we would change more classes . The reply to this expression is that there is a big difference between teaching the kids to brush their teeth despite hating it and it being healthy for them and teaching the kids how to kiss dogs and cats and it is not healthy at all to do it . I thank you for giving me this opportunity . 
Hello everyone , I am writing you regarding your question about students ' living places . I think every choice had pros and cons . It is difficult to say that one option is definitely better than the other one . Living on one 's own has some advantages . For example , the students are more free and independent from their families . They can organize what they want to do during their days . However , they have to manage everything they need at home . For example , washing , cleaning and buying the necessary things . If the students can live with other students and they can learn from each other , it will be not too difficult to pass their examinations . Living with the family may be a good thing to do if the student likes communicating with people after uttering his tasks . But if the family does not have time to speak with him , the situation will be the same as if he lived alone . It depends on the studies the student is doing . It will take a long time if every study section has to be explained . At the end of the day , every student must find the best way to make his studies easy to be graduated . I thank you very much for giving me this opportunity to utter my opinion on this issue . 
When I go to sleep , I like to be in a dark and quiet room because if there is any noise I cannot sleep well and the next day I feel very bad . I know there are many people that have different ways to sleep , but in my case there must be silence . To sleep well we all should sleep between 7 hours or 8 hours a night and in this way we can recover our energy . So we should all sleep well , with a light or no light . 
One of my favourite activities is sleeping since in almost every sleep I will get a dream . Dreaming is like my second world , I can do everything I ca not do in my dreams . Every day I sleep for around 8-10 hours . I like sleeping in a dark room . I always turn off my lamp when I sleep , except when I feel afraid of something like a ghost or a robber , then I 'll turn on my small light . Or if I sleep with other people who ca not sleep in a dark room , I 'll get some fabric , usually my scarf , to close my eyes so it reduces the light . Noise , mostly I do not have any problem with it . I can sleep even among crowds . Nevertheless , sometimes I ca not sleep even because of a small disturption but it happens rarely . I remember I enjoyed my sleep while listening to children who were singing through the mosque 's speaker . They sang in a bad way . When they stopped , I woke up and it was hard for me to go back to sleep . Despite all of that , generally I like a dark and quiet room . 
