Dear Daphne , Thank you for sharing with me about your country . I hope I can visit your beautiful country one day . I have something to tell you that I believe will make you want to visit my country . It 's about food , as I know you 're a big fan of a variety of food , especially Asian spicy food , right ? I do not think you will have ever tried this food . The name of it is Seblak . It 's not a main food , it 's more like a snack , but a heavy one . The main ingredients of Seblak are : kerupuk , chilli and aromatic ginger . Kerupuk is like a chip made with tapioca flour , we use the raw one . Usually I add onion and garlic to level up the taste . I like Seblak because it 's spicy . Obviously , I use many chillies because I love the spiciest of spicy food . The other thing is that there is a unique taste from the aromatic ginger . For your information , I use the same seasoning to make other menu as I like the taste of Seblak . I usually eat this food almost every day in my rest time from my class . There is a Seblak cafe near my university . Nevertheless , the university is off these days , so I cook it by myself at home almost every day . 
Do you know about bun cha ? Bun cha is a delicious dish which president Obama ate for 5 years and bun cha is my favourite food . I usually eat it in the morning every day . I really love it because it 's delicious and the taste is good . I believe that you will not regret it , if you eat bun cha in Hanoi . 
The phenomenon of globalization and the recent improvement of public transport have increased people 's desire to start learning new foreign languages . Compared to the past , learning new foreign languages ​​is now more important than before , because today 's world is much more competitive and faster than in the past . The current market is no longer local but global and today requires highly specialized workers with a good knowledge of foreign languages . Nowadays , workers should know at least two or more foreign languages ​​if they want to make a career and be competitive . In the past it was only true for a small circle of workers , such as scientists or those who wanted to work in the academic field in general . Learning new foreign languages ​​nowadays is also more important than in the past for the improvement of transport . Nowadays , getting from point a to point b is easy and cheap , and people are encouraged to do so . Foreign languages ​​are useful in this situation and prevent you from falling into unpleasant situations . 
