I think that students do not need to complete a certain amount of volunteer work in order to graduate . Being a volunteer , you have to do it voluntarily , no one should force you to do that . Maybe there are some students who disagree with that opinion , but they have to do it because they want to graduate . In high schools , students have to study a lot , teachers give them lots of homework . They do not have time to rest , so when could they go volunteering ? If you want them to be a volunteer , first you do not give them the requirement : " Students must complete a certain amount of volunteer work in order to graduate . " Just tell them that : " Being a volunteer is optional . If you want to , do it . If you do not , no problem . " Secondly , you have to pay a certain amount of money , appropriate for their volunteer work . They will have energy to be a volunteer . Because , no one in the world will do anything without something being paid back . Third is decrease their homework , therefore , they will have time for volunteering . Make the time they are volunteering become happier and meaningful , like organizing games . The person who completes this work the fastest will get extra money . They will be interested in their jobs and volunteers will increase suddenly . 
The transport sector has started to radically change the way people move from point a to b . Analysing the last decade , the automotive sector has started to push electric engines and all the infrastructure to support it forward . We can expect in the near future a ban on vehicles powered by carbon fossil fuels and the circulation of cars powered only by electric motors . We should not expect drastic changes , such as flying vehicles for everyone as shown in science fiction movies , but we can expect a more affordable means of transportation between planets instead . Nowadays , transport between planets using space shuttles is only for astronauts and meant only for space exploration . In the near future , we will also be able to use space transportation for vacation and work purposes , but probably it still wo not be affordable for almost everyone , but we should expect a reduction in prices year after year . 
In my free time I usually watch videos on You Tube about economics , politics and technology . I also like to watch movies with my family , they like romantic comedy and adventure movies . During the week I do physical activities such as street running and weight lifting exercises . I watch movies and videos on the weekend , while the activities I do during the week . 
