In my opinion , television can entertain and also educate , because I think it can do these two methods together . But if we need to do them together , I think it is harder than just one , entertain or educate . It needs to be thought about very carefully . When you go to use something with the purpose of educating , you need to careful in every aspect of what you use . If you are not careful , what you represent can be the worst mistake and it can also cause you enormous trouble . There are many ways to combine them together , such as using it in the way of animation if you want to make children understand the animation more . It is a good way to catch the attention of children . A game show is more interesting if the listener is a grown person . It is fun and easy to give useful information to them . 
To avoid the harmful influence of an inflexible and lazy lifestyle on health , it is said that all university students and school children should be obliged to do sports activities three times per week or more . From my perspective , I back up this idea for many benefits in the long term . People could easily see many health benefits when the plan is applied in school in just two weeks . It does not matter what sports activities they do , they will get fit in many ways . University students can play some sports which require strength like football , basketball or swimming . In that way , their stamina will be enhanced and their muscles will be tightened , which might facilitate their schoolwork . School students can do lighter sports like aerobics , badminton and tennis . There are also mental sports such as playing chess , sodoku or meditation , which will relieve study stress and anxiety effectively . So , doing sports activities will provide them with physical and mental strength so that they can have better a performance at school . Other benefits of being active are that students can build up their relationships and enhance their teamwork skills . When they take part in sports activities , they have a chance to make friends and cooperate with other students to practice . As a result , their relationships will be broadened , which may bring them many opportunities in the future . Moreover , in the playing sports process , students will learn how to deal with problems arisen with other people . That means their teamwork skills can be improved a lot . Moreover , playing sports frequently can lessen students ' time on surfing the Internet and increase their time outdoors . These days , students tend to be indoors and play video games more than they did in the past , which can lead to bad habits . But when they do sports instead of wasting time on social networks , they can experience many things and be closer to reality . In conclusion , doing sports activities can lead to many benefits in the future and make people 's time more worthwhile . Students can gain more experience and become healthier in their lifestyles . 
I have recently discovered the fail in the English exam I took in the last exam session and , after the sorrow lasted a few days , I started to search online how to address the issue . I was mainly focused on finding a method for improving my English writing skills without spending too much money , and in the search engine 's top results , I found a platform called " Write & Improve . " It is a platform provided by Cambridge in recent years to provide to the user a trustworthy method for testing your English writing skill for free . The platform has several sections based on the English level or the certificate the user would like to do , and each section has thousands of examples including emails , essays , and reviews . The key feature of " Write & Improve " is the possibility to check the text whenever the user wants , multiple times , and without human interaction . This is a plus that similar platforms do not have or it is normally provided as a premium feature . The check of the text is done in a few seconds and gives you an insight into what can be improved and the current level of the text . The tips given by the platform do not contain many details and this could be a downside of the platform because , for beginners , it is important to understand well what the mistakes are and how they can be overcome efficiently . I consider " Write & Improve " a good starting point for learning English , but since it is meant for testing only one of the English skills and I recommend using additional tools when learning . 
Nowadays , it is quite common for students to live on their own while attending university , especially in prestigious universities where the selection requests come from all parts of the world . For most of the students , it is the first experience in their life where they have to look after themselves and do tasks normally done by their parents such as cooking , cleaning the room , and paying bills . The interesting idea of living on their own while attending university is an experience you may have with the students who live with you . It is common for university students to live in structures such as dorms or shared houses , and for many students , it is one of the best parts of their academic experience for the great memories they make . Living with the family is a good option when you would like to save money since living alone is expensive , especially in big cities . It is affordable for many people , but still not for all of them . I personally have experienced both experiences and I recommend all the university students to move away and live on their own , because you may have unforgettable moments that are difficult to live after . 
Volunteer work is an aspect of everyday life really well -appreciated by many people that can be done in many different ways . The activities normally done in volunteer work could consist in working for some local institutions normally involved in helping people in a difficult situation or in working for the municipality , but the goal is always to involve the volunteer to work on the social side . It is mostly an extracurricular activity not recognised by schools , but some high schools have started to propose volunteer work as a requirement for graduating . This proposal recalls what is normally done for some degrees in university , where university students have to do some internship hours for graduating . I personally approve the proposal of these high schools because volunteer work is essential in this selfish and fast world dominated by the idea of thinking only about ourselves . It is an opportunity to start to understand for real the everyday problems of our city and start to understand how we can help others . Plenty of times , people live in a place for years without noticing some of the details , sometimes even by convincing ourselves that these details are not problems . Volunteer work , meant as the experience in public life , should open people 's eyes to bring them back to reality . These experiences are really important for personal growth and enrich and influence us for better choices in the future . 
Life is the most important thing in the world . While some creatures live very short , some can live a long peaceful life . Most people prefer a long life . Even though most people prefer to live over 100 years , I prefer a shorter but more energetic and fascinating life . First of all , if people live a very long life without any beautiful experiences , then this life is just a pain . Some prisoners , for instance , must live in a small and dark room until they die . A study shows that those prisoners would choose to live only one day with their family than live in a prison until they die . They did not choose to live in prison until they die , but they chose only one day with their family . This study proves that people tend to choose a short but intense life . Secondly , when people get older , problems begin to get bigger . Elderly people cannot do the things they used to do . That is why I prefer to live everything when I can do it . If I do not live life now , I will not be able to live it when I get older . To sum up , I prefer to live a shorter but much more intense life when I can do it . Because I believe that the most important thing in the world is life . And if we wait to live life until we get older , we will miss lots of amazing and unique experiences . 
When I was in high school , I had the dream to move away and live a life on my own . Of course , I did not have any idea about how difficult it would be to live away from your parents , but I had the most important thing : the wish to know new places and new people . Because of that , I studied a lot and could start college in another city called Campinas . It 's a city near my hometown , so I thought this location would be the best for me , because I would have the freedom I 've always wanted and my parents would not be so far if I had troubles and needed them fast . While I was living in Campinas , I noticed I needed to learn a lot of things to survive , such as cooking , cleaning the house on the weekends , paying the bills , etc . In the first moment , it scared me , because I have not been prepared for this moments . But as time passed , I could handle that and find time to enjoy my new life . I made new friendships , traveled a lot , self -accepted my sexuality , etc . Actually , when I look back at this moment of my life and compare it with friends of mine who stayed in their hometowns to study , I see how much I 've grown and how it was important to make who I 'm today . Thus , if someday someone asking me which choice is the best , I 'm going to say : the harder one . 
As the technology is getting more and more advanced , people nowadays live easier and sedentary lifestyles . Hence , I agree on forcing university students and school children to do sports at least three times per week . First of all , society is educated that exercising is beneficial , but we do not see the impact on the students and children . They need to be obliged to exercise in order to realise the importance of exercising regularly , which is three times a week . This is because when they start exercising , they will feel more accomplished and healthy , and finally understand the gain of exercising and being active . There is also scientific research that proves the effectiveness of forcing someone to carry out certain activities in order to realise and understand the positive consequences that will be brought . Secondly , not everyone is disciplined . Hence , by implementing this act , they will be compelled to exercise , which will achieve the goal of wanting more children to be active . The neglect of activity in youngsters will only engender more unhealthy issues to arise . I understand that we should allow them to exercise willingly to reduce the resistance towards it , but pampering students and children , such as obeying their needs and wants , will only impact them negatively , for example , they may be obese if they are sedentary . So , if we truly care for them , we should take actions to hinder the unhealthy problems from arising . In my opinion , I think that we must not only force them to exercise . We can also reward them to keep the children motivated to continue exercising . As an example , we can give them healthy and delicious snacks , such as fruits and yoghurt , to alleviate their mood from feeling blue and weary after exercising . We must treat them well as we need to respect the children at the same time . In a nutshell , I pen down writing that we must strike for a balance in implementing this act of forcing the students and children to exercise . I recommend that encouragement and obligation to exercise be done at the same time . 
Hi neighbour , How are you ? I 'm traveling to Portugal and I would like you to take care of my house for a few days . Below are some daily instructions and recommendations : 1 ) My keys are inside the mail box , please do not tell anyone about it . 2 ) The garden plants need to be watered at least twice a day . 3 ) My dog and cat need to be fed every morning . The dog food is in the kitchen cupboard . Do not forget to go out with them every afternoon . 4 ) I will email you every day , do not forget to check your email inbox . Sincerely , thanks . 
