Everyone in this world is good and interested in different areas . This person loves art but that person loves playing video games . Why do we have that difference ? Because each of us is a different individual . No one can force anyone to love this or that . We have different opinions , thoughts , hobbies . So that 's why we have to respect others 's opinion . Back to our problem . Like I 've said , we are completely different individuals , no one is exactly the same as the other . So I think that studying music or learning about musical instruments must depend on the students . We ca not force them to do the thing we want . What do you think about students who do not like music having to spend 2 or 3 hours of their time doing the thing that they super hate ? Meanwhile they can do homework for 2 or 3 hours . If you are in that position , do you agree ? If schools do not have enough money to open a music class , therefore we can recommend students to go to the other music class . I think we have to create a survey . Then we 'll base on the percentage of students who love music . If the students who love music are more , we will create a music class , if the percentage is less than the students who do not love music , if we wo not open a class . When you want to do something , do not just do it because you like it , you have to ask everyone 's opinion . 
