In recent years , the number of doctors has started to decline due to the limitation imposed by universities on the inclusion of new doctors in the medical field and the large number of doctors who have started to retire . The few doctors who are still in service prefer to work and live in cities where they can earn a lot of money and where there are services that nowadays are considered essential . Rural areas are the most damaged in this situation because there are not enough doctors in most of them and the medical service may disappear in future . We will in a world where most of the doctors work only for monetary purposes and the passion for helping people is in few of them . Governments should work in the direction of changing and improving rural areas to facilitate and tempt the transfer of new doctors . An additional thing the governments could do is apply tax reductions to doctors who want to work in rural areas since most of them move to places where they can earn as much as possible . The tax reductions could also involve the reimbursement of expenses in some fields , such as gas , in case the doctors live far from the medical centre , or a public transport subscription in case they use public transport . 
In the past , sports activities were the only way to have fun for most university students and school children . The recent improvement of technology has introduced a new way to have fun besides sports activities , but at the same time , the number of people who have started to be inactive has increased . Recent studies have shown the correlation between technology and inactive lifestyles , and have highlighted a bad trend among younger people . Governments have started to handle the critical situation and have proposed forcing university students and school children to do sports activities at least three times per week . For many of the schools and universities , the proposal is affordable and can be applied with minimal effort since the required structures already exist and the management does not require a lot of effort . The government 's proposal is interesting and I consider it the best way to counteract the bad habits and lifestyles of many students . At the same time , I disagree with the number of times they should do such activities . It is important to let students develop their hobbies and interests by allowing them enough spare time , and the proposal does not consider this idea . Doing sports activities at least three times per week would force students to spend too much time at school without letting students think more about themselves and their real interests . The students ' engagements and interests should be more respected , and I have always thought that the imposition of rules by force only produces the opposite result . I would suggest governments rethink their proposal and start being more realistic . The corrections I would make take into account the reduction in the number of times students should perform their sporting activities and the voluntary basis for carrying out the activities . I know that forcing people to do sports is the only way to stimulate them to counteract their bad habits , but less active activities are also important and sport should be more of an addition to our life and not a real obsession . 
