As people , we have different behaviours and attitudes , so when you are going to talk about the truth , in my opinion , the truth is always hard , but we need to believe that the truth is best . In addition , there are lots of situations when you need to be honest and accept your destiny , like when you finish high school and you want to decide what you want to do . Do you want to study at university or do you want to work ? The decision needs to be thought about carefully and , after you decide , you have to tell your parents your decision so you need to be honest with your family about your desire . Also you need to show them that your are responsible for your life . Sometimes , you need to lie for some reason , for example , if you want to visit your friend and your mother she has accepted that , so your friend tells you I miss you , shall we meet on Sunday , please ? Just for one hour . In that case , you need to lie to your mother saying that you want to study for your exam , so you need to go for the library and it is actually that you want to meet your friend . From my point of view , in that case , I have a mission , you can lie but not always because if you keep lying , I swear you will become a bad person and you Do not that . At the end , I prefer to tell the truth because it is the best thing . 
Telling the truth In our life , we have a lot if things that we need to say , especially in our daily conversations with our families , friends and so on . Many people when they have problems in their work or even personal problems lie to other people to avoid another but the thing is lying to people could create other problems , such as losing money or having problems in your life . As a result of that , telling lies to people can make you lose important relationships or lose a marriage and the problem could get worse if your lies affect other people and it might make them lose their life , or sometimes even end up going to jail . From my point of view , I believe that we always need to tell the truth . I know sometimes it hurts , but on the other side , at least you will not lose someone truth or you wo not break someone 's heart , and telling the truth will always keep you on the safe side . You will more confident , honest and brave . Being brave is not saving someone 's life only , also if you tell the truth , you will be a hero . For example , if you are a student at university and you had a difficult exam , and when the result is posted , you get a D grade and your parents have spoken to you and said , " Honey , what did you get in your subject ? " Of course , if you tell them the truth , surely they will be mad , but at least , they will trust you . 
