As far as I 'm concerned , somebody telling a lie is really terrible . There are many reasons that can give this answer to me . First , a person who often tells a lie will lead to his or her friends finding it hard to believe him or her . A classic example is the fable of the boy taking care of sheep and a wolf . The naughty boy thought that it was very funny to say there was a wolf coming to eat the sheep . Because of that , all the residents living in the village would come out to protect the sheep from the attack of the wolf . After the boy pranked the residents many times , the residents heard the boy calling for help again , but all them considered it a joke and nobody went out to give him a hand . In the end , the sheep were attacked and the residents were very angry . So the trust between people will be exhausted by the lies . Second , when a person tells a lie , the person usually has to tell you more to make the first one reasonable . For instance , my friend , David , hung out with me but he did not get his mom 's consent . He also had a class at school he needed to go to at the same time . Therefore he made a phone call to school and took a day off . Unfortunately , the school called his mom and his mom knew that too . Then he received a phone call from his mom , so he told more lies to convince his mom . But the truth will emerge some day . And he got a guite scolding . To sum up , being honest will be the best way to live in the world . 
