It 's really hard for me to make a decision between the 2 things , to my consideration are both are effective . But , maybe they 're not . Let 's analyze the benefits and drawbacks of each one . The advantage of working in enclosed workstations is you can have your own workspace . You 'd feel more comfortable if you work alone . Let 's imagine that you 're thinking of a problem and how to solve it , but then when you look up and you see a bunch of people in front of you , maybe they are not doing anything but that could cause your thoughts to be interrupted . So if you 're a boss , why do not you separate walls ? Therefore , your employees would have 100 % focus on their jobs . But , everything in this world has 2 sides , including this one . The disadvantage of working with walls separating are is that some people do not like this . They got used to working as a team . The most preventable is separating walls . They want , when they 're working , to be able to easily talk with their colleagues . We ca not force them to like what we like because each person has different opinions . The benefit of working without walls separating is like the drawback of working in cubicles . That will be applied successfully if people in the offices are extroverted . It depends on the purposes offices want to achieve , so we have different solutions . The reason why I did not talk about the drawbacks of working without walls separating is because that 's the advantage of working in cubicles . Me , I have my own decision . I know that some will disagree with me because we 're not the same . I 'd prefer working in enclosed work stations . I do not know what type of human am I , extroverted or introverted . But I do not care . The thing I assure is that my thoughts will be not interrupted if I choose to work in cubicles . 
It is often said that having a peaceful , long -lasting life and gaining lots of achievements are the things that many people desire . But we all know that it is not easy to get both of them or balance our lives in that way , so we have to strap something . From my perspective , I would like to live a long , tranquil life rather than a shorter , prosperous one . That does not deny the fact that no one is successful without trying hard and the reason behind that effort mostly is money , which has highly power for paying all the bills and securing a bright future for everyone . But all lives will end someday and people cannot be buried with their money . And the older people are , the less expectations they have . Their final purpose is happiness and calmness with their loved ones . So why do not we enjoy this while we are alive ? Many people did not spend much time with their family members , close friends or their partners when they pursued their wildest dreams , which is the thing that they most regretted , whether their dreams came true or not . We only live once and we rarely live as we should . So , learning to be pleasant with everything we have and enjoying each minute passed by is the key for happy life , not rushing for unreachable things . Moreover , if you live a long and peaceful life , there are a lot of interesting things ahead of you to go through . But if you live a short and intense life , you are likely to miss many things . On the other hand , living a calm life does not mean that you can have a decent life without doing anything . You still have to work to make enough money to meet your family 's demands . 
