Telling the truth is a favourable thing , it is the value and moral system of all communities around the world . In addition , telling the truth is an important element in all religious scriptures in which people believe . Telling the truth is the centre on which all other human values are based on . We teach our children to always tell the truth no matter what ; because the contrary , which is telling lies , has very damaging consequences . Telling the truth can sometimes save the lives of others as well as achieve justice for people who are oppressed by the criminal justice . Nevertheless , telling the truth is always a good thing because it allows us to respect others ' rights and maintain their dignity . In medical practice , it is part of the medical ethics to always say the truth no matter what consequences might arise from it . For example , if a surgeon makes medical mistake while performing the surgery , he or she must disclose the truth of what happened during the surgery with complete honesty , even if it will pose them worse consequences . Similarly , telling the truth is part of every other career environment . People sometimes find themselves in a situation in which they have to tell a small lie ; such as making a friend happy by telling a good little lie . I think that may be acceptable as long as it does not hurt anyone or affect anyone 's dignity and well -being . 
