In my opinion , there are some wondering about imposing volunteer work for high school students to graduate school . First , volunteer work should be done with their consciousness . If it is requirement , it will lose its innate meaning . Some students may hesitate to act as volunteers . This is a vicious matter . Second , there are no opportunities for students not to learn why some people need volunteer work . Students may think the action is just a duty . In other words , this program deprives students of the ability to think about their action 's meaning . If the school curriculum wants that students to notice their environment and local people who need support , they should not only impose the activity itself but also give an opportunity to study the importance of the activity . , . I think that high school should not handle volunteer work as as credit . Teachers should set the learning opportunity for students and also act with them on site . 
After graduating high school , students usually apply for university . Some of them decide to stay in their childhood houses , others move out to start on their own , alone . Which option is the best one ? Firstly , students who choose to stay with their parents are faced with less responsibilities . This can be really helpful , considering the amount of time one spends studying . Usually , parents pay for a living . The student does not have to work , therefore has more time to study . What is more , parents usually guarantee healthy food to eat . They cook , bake and make food with healthy calories , which improves one 's overall well -being and condition . This way , the student 's nourished brain works better and the student ends up with better grades . On the other hand , one 's abilities to manage money or to learn responsibility drastically go down . That is because constantly living in comfort only leads to discomfort in future life . Young people benefit from moving by learning a lot of practical skills , which are later needed in adulthood . Students who move after graduating become independent much faster . To sum up , opinions diverge . I personally believe people should learn independence as fast as they can - it will make their future life easier . 
There are many programs that are broadcast on television , It could be educational programs , or it could be programs that are not available for children , but it will depend on us to decide , as parents , to allow our children to see something good . I think it is our responsibility as parents and we need to have control over what our children are watching . We cannot avoid that a television channel broadcasts a program in particular , but we can control what our children can watch . I think that it is something of an education and education starts in the house , with all the examples that we give to our children . Many times we can blame other people for all bad things that our children are doing , but the main responsibility is ours as parents and we need to show them the right way . If we teach them the good things that television gives us , I think that we will not have a problem with that , because you should show them that television can show us documentaries , or several things that we need to learn and not all is bad 
In my opinion , it is more comfortable for office workers to spend their time in an enclosed space . First of all , in an enclosed space , they can easily concentrate on their desk tasks . Companies must achieve their missions and earn money to pay the salary to their employees . For this reason , it is necessary for companies to provide their staff with a comfortable work place . Some people think it is not good to communicate with other members if employees stay in their shared desk . But I can override this point , because there are many opportunities to share ideas by using emails or business meetings . Staff can communicate by using these tools or they can plan meetings . I think that is more effective for people who do not have enough time . Sometimes , people spend invalid time with chatting with other members in an open space . Moreover , they can consider their ideas and present them to prepare staff meetings beforehand . For all of these reasons , I think it is more effective to provide an enclosed space to employees . 
