Dear town council , Although we all know about the downsides that the use of mobile phones in public places or even in shops and restaurants can cause , such as distraction and accidents . The use of theses objects in my opinion should not be prohibited . In spite of the facts stated above , there are many advantages to using mobile phones . Let 's take the use on public transport as an example , we can take a long journey on some transport , and with the help of a mobile , we can work on things on the way . Taking now one example in a restaurant , imagine that you are a very occupied person , as I can imagine you guys from town council must be , if you did not have the help of these mobiles phones , how many dinners and lunches would you have to cancel to attend an appointment ? These technologies are here to help us to live better and more efficiently , so there is no doubt , in my opinion , that mobile phones should stay allowed in theses places . Even more , we can see in our rights about being free to do whenever we want , since do not do bad or disturb other people . To summarise , I believe this thinking of yours is completely wrong , and should be revised before you make it public . 
I think the most important is to be healthy , but I think you ca not be healthy if you are not rich . If you want to be healthy , there are many ways to achieve this , such as exercise , eating healthy food or following an influencer on social media who can teach you to be healthy . I think all these ways need a lot of money and time , that you ca not achieve if you do not have money . I do not think we can view these two in a separate way . As I said before , the two terms need to come together . If I can choose one of these , I will choose to be healthy , because if I am healthy , it is because I am rich . In old age , we will face a lot of diseases and in this world , money is the most important thing . You need it to pay to cure your disease . That is why you ca not be healthy if you are not rich . 
The teacher is a critical factor in the process of education . If we have a bad teacher , we may be hurt by him , and if we have a good teacher , he will help us , but if we have a great teacher , then we will be inspired by him . The question of what do you prefer , a teacher for several years or having a teacher every year , is complicated . We ca not just answer yes or no , it is not that simple . My opinion is that it depends on two things . First and foremost , is he inspiring and compatible with the students ? If so , we can move to the second question , is he able to teach one class for several years ? If the answer to the question is yes too , then I think he can teach the class for several yeas . But to be honest , I believe that having one teacher every year is the best choice . Why ? Because I had many great teachers over the years . If one of them had taught me for several years , then I would not have been able to know the others , which would have been a disaster , because I learned something from each and every one of them . Their words are still in my mind , I can still hear them . To summarize , no , I do not think that having one teacher for several years is a good idea . 
Hi , my name is Vinicius . I 'm a mechanical engineering student , I 'm 26 years old and I live in Brazil . My profession requires fluency in the English language . I use the website " Write and Improve " to improve my English . The program has many questions that are divided between beginner , intermediate and advanced . The user must answer the question by writing on the topic suggested . Once completed , his answer is automatically corrected with feedback . My study strategy is to answer at least one question every day . I have been using the platform for almost four months . I started with beginner level questions and answered about 80 questions . During the time I have been using the tool , I have noticed incredible advances in my writing . Today is my first day at the intermediate level and I 'm very happy . I highly recommend " Write and Improve . " It 's an excellent tool to improve your English . But , in order to be efficient , the user must have discipline to answer the questions during the week and not procrastinate . That 's why I recommend the user to organize their time and do the tasks according to their language level . Hugs ! 
