Studying abroad is a beneficial opportunity for any student and it is an experience that should be had at least once in a lifetime . And like any experience in the world , it has advantages and disadvantages too . The most important advantage will be seeing other cultures and interacting with them . This interaction might be helpful , especially for people who come from poor countries , because it helps them see another world and other people , which may be a motivation for one to help one 's country more . The other advantage will be the trip itself . Travelling lets us see other people , other cultures and other heritages . It is always great to see for yourself rather than hearing about it . But there are always disadvantages too . First of all , it may be hard for some students to travel and be in another country with other people . This change in the environment may have a negative effect on some students , especially introverts . Not everyone can handle this kind of change . As I said earlier , studying abroad is a great experience that should be had at least once in a lifetime . It may be one of the most beneficial experiences the one can have in one 's life . 
