Music is always in my daily life , such as waking up , eating lunch or dinner , having a good sleep . So , I think that music is important for our daily life . Even if my mood is so down , the right pop music played is a cheering sound for me . Also , music makes us relax and is a cure for daily tiredness . When we work or study in the daytime , we are always forced to listen to uncomfortable sounds , mechanical noise , people 's voices , etc . But listening to music can cure our tired heart and remove our stress too . For example , when we eat lunch listening to classical music , we felt so relaxed and happy . For these reasons , I recommend listening to music in our daily life . Also , we sing along with our favorite song . It is a very popular and cheap stress release , like Karaoke , with which we can communicate with other people . I think that music must be our life . 
Today , music is omnipresent . Never has it been it easier to tune into your favourite song , whether you are working , playing it in the background while dining , or during our daily commute . However , this begs the question whether one can listen to too much music ? We all know the first signs of hearing a song too often , the inner playback in our head . The more serious symptoms can have significant effects on our daily lives , in forms of productivity loss or demotivation . To answer the question of too much , we may first reckon with the query of function . For some , the main intention is to get into a mood or emphasize current emotions . Others see in music an efficient memory assistance , reliving the past . However , these functions seem to lose efficiency and effect if one listens to the same song too often . Instead of being associated with that one specific memory , it becomes a song playing in the background at all times . That is why I am an advocate of a more active and memorable listening to music and songs which get passively picked up in our daily lives , for example in the gym , on the radio or at a party . 
