Music and the sensations associated with experiencing it are deeply rooted in western culture . How big is the impact that these mysterious sounds have on us ? Do we necessarily need them for our well -being ? Presumably , all of us have experienced the healing power of music , at least once in a lifetime . When you feel under the weather , depressed or really anxious , it could be tremendously curative . It has been scientifically proven that music can cause an immense increase in our mood and , mixed with exercising , can help us avoid depression . For God only knows how long , music has been used to sanctify human life . Ancient people , just like modern ones , used music for rituals to make an impression of the divine . At first glance , it may seem quite alien , although just think about what people experience during a concert of their favourite music band , it 's kind of mystical , is not it ? Music has been part of human culture since the dawn of time . I reckon everybody would agree that it has a tremendous impact on our life and makes the pain associated with awareness of our finitude much more bearable . 
I think that music is very important in our life , because music can play a lot of roles , like just making us have fun , making our mind positive , healing humans ' minds , making people get together , etc . Especially , the role of healing humans ' mind is very important . There are many things that could happen and sometimes we could have a hard time . Even though it is a hard time , we can go forward if there is music . The role of making people get together is also an important role in our life . Singing a song or dancing with music with other people is not only fun , but also gets people together . Even though people cannot communicate with each other , people can enjoy singing a song . These are the reasons why I think music is important in our life . And I also think that with no music in your life , the enjoyment of your life will be halved . 
Hi Jack , In my country , the way we celebrate birthdays is a little bit different from your country . The day before our birthday , we invite some close friends to come to a birthday party at our home . Then , on the birthday , we have dinner with family at home . After that , we have a cake with candles , snacks and drinks . And when the friends come , they sing " Happy Birthday " and give me the presents they have prepared . I think each country has different ways to cheer someone up on their birthday , but all of them are so good . Do you agree ? Hany 
Can you imagine our lives without music ? I ca not remember a time when I did not listen to music . I need it all the time to do my tasks . Music makes me feel motivated and happy . Music plays a part in the lives of everyone . We listen to music with different purposes . It 's important for us to do any activity . For instance , some people use music to concentrate when they work or study , music could help you to be relaxed and there is research which shows that music can help ill people to recover . It 's difficult to imagine our lives without music . Probably , life would be sad and boring . Our world would be less beautiful , music gives happiness and color to our lives . We can enjoy the music that nature gives us , such as birds ' songs , the sound of water , rain or wind , these are examples that music is all around us all the time . Music plays a part in our day -to -day life , wherever we go music will be there . It 's necessary for us , we need it because it helps us to feel a certain way or to express our feelings . 
