I think no walls separating employees from their co -workers is more effective for work than enclosed stations . I think this because , in the office , we need to work together and if we are separated from each other , it will make employees think they need to work by themselves , not work together . And , I also think there will need to be more space than usual because if you provide more space , it will make employees think they have enough space to think that they are not imprisoned in the office , which will make them work better . No walls separating will make employees work together and not need to walk to reach each other . I think both employees and employers need to work in the same room if it is a small business . No one in the company needs to have a room to separate themselves from each other . If you have a separate room , it will make you think you are more important than the others , which will lead to bad for the business . 
