Music appeared a very long time ago . Music is like when we say something with very high or very low voice . Music is important in our life . It can make you feel less stressed , or make you feel happy . It makes our life better . There are lots of kinds of music : rock , jazz , blues ... Each kind of music gives you a different feeling . Rock and jazz make you feel excited . Blues music makes you feel comfortable . Country and folk mix exciting and light music together . People listen to music when they need to relax . Life will be boring without music . Without music , there 's no high point or low point in our life . A big part of relaxing activities will disappear ! You wo not have many things to do . I listen to music every day , so music has become my friend . Life will become smooth , boring and not interesting . Music has become a friend of all of us and you must not decry anyone 's music ! 
A long calm life or a short intense one . I think that living a life that is worth it is the principal goal of any human being . So , I would prefer a short intense life that is worth it instead of a long nonsensical life . The principal reason is that I want to travel to a lot of different places and know the culture and life there . I also want to learn as much as I can and create precious moments during my lifetime and if these reasons mean to live a short life but an intense one , I prefer to create memories and live the day , every day . I have always wanted to know different parts of the world because I am really interested in cultures and customs from different parts of the world and the behaviour or way of living from one city to another or one country to another change is fascinating for me . Thus , I would love to live travelling and living experiences in my life . Another reason why I prefer an intense short life is because I like to learn and know a lot . So , I would like to learn as much as I can in different fields of science or life . I do not mean how longer I can learn , I just want to learn and try to comprehend the world around us . In summary , I definitively prefer living a worthy life than a long life . I want to live a life that can be an inspiration to everybody or at least to the people around me . 
University life is different when you live alone or you live with your family . Both cases have pros and cons , but to me , the best option is living with family . In my experience , university could be stressful and you , most of the time , do not have enough time to do many activities so , if you live with your family , it facilitates a lot of things such as you not having to pay attention to expensive bills or making food . Above that when you live with your family , you have more time to focus on your studies and you do not have to pay much attention to other things . When you live with someone who cares about you , university life is easier to deal with . In conclusion , if you have the opportunity to choose between going or staying with your parents during your university degree , you definitively should choose the second option because your university life will become easier . 
Hello Chris , I 'm so glad you are all coming next Saturday . Well , we are going to take a bus to the train station , so that we can go to the museum . It 's a little bit far away from my home , so we 'll have to do this , but I promise you , it will be worth it . At the museum , you will get to see a lot of paintings and sculptures , also there 's a part where you can interact with the art and have an experience of a lifetime , it 's so wonderful . So for this adventure , you 'll have to bring some money to buy the tickets for the bus , the train and to get into the museum , for food , in case you feel hungry , and your camera to be able to take as many pictures as you want to . 
As members of society , we are sometimes asked to step up and help other people or the community around us . In some institutions , like our high schools , it 's done by mandated volunteer work . Is it right ? Must students be obliged to do volunteer work to graduate ? The problems of our society surround us in our everyday lives . When we turn on our TVs or connect to the internet , we see a lot of people struggling to have something to eat , places devastated by storms and flooding , the famine in Africa , etc . Seeing everything that is happening , it 's obvious that something must be done , so it 's our responsibility to give support to those in need and sometimes the best way to do it is through volunteer work . We have to find ways to encourage volunteer work and our educational system has places where we can nurture our individuals to care for the problems of our society . Since kindergarten , our children must be aware of it 's complexity , respecting their ages and understanding capability , of course , in order to be ready to take action when it 's needed . Conversely , of course , we need citizens willing to help our society , but this involvement must be achieved with education and not obligation . The obligation is in the hands of our institutions that can encourage students using win -win solutions that connect those in need with those with the resources and responsibility to help . 
Music is the most important thing in our lives . Music is good to do a lot of things , such as running , cleaning , cooking ... I ca not imagine my life without my favourite music . I am sure that it would be boring and uninteresting . Depending on the day , my body needs different kinds of music , there is always the perfect music for each moment . A life without music is the same as a rainbow without colours , I ca not imagine this . As long as there is music , there will be life . If you want to do something interesting , you will need to listen to music . I can imagine a life without cars , but without music it is very difficult to understand . I believe that there will always be music in every corner in this world . Moreover , if one day we are living on another planet , there will be music too . I 'm sure about this affirmation . 
Hello Ana ! How are you today ? I hope you are well . My mother tells everyone that I am learning English , she is very excited about that because she wants me to study in the UK for my Master 's degree in a few years ' time . Anyway , I am studying English with some online courses that are free , the sites with teachers for studying English are very expensive for me and I do not have any money now . I use many applications to study like : Duolingo , You Tube videos , podcasts and I am studying the three hundred and sixty most common verbs . I need to work in a few months ' time and the jobs with the best salaries require English as a second language . It is very important for me to learn English . Tell me , how did you learn English ? I need some advice . 
It 's astonishing how the combination of the main seven notes can create different kind of melodies , which at the same time fit in our different life stages , such as when we are feeling under the weather or having a really difficult time , there are some songs which either make us feel a little bit more relaxed or even motivate us to keep going . Apart from that , music is always our company when we need to dance or sing in order to find a way to convey our thoughts and feelings when the situations become too difficult . Besides , music is vital to make memories with those who we love and care for . We make bonds through music and every time we listen to that melody , we can remember a special moment , such as a birthday , a date , a wedding , a dance , or just a loved person 's smile . On the other side , a long time ago , Nietzsche said , " Without music , life would be a mistake , " and I completely agree with him . If we did not have music , we would miss a way to express our feelings , we would not be able to fully enjoy a great moment or we would not be able to put into words and notes our sorrow . After all , music is so kindhearted with us to allow us to create memorable times and to liberate us from such overflowing emotions . 
Music was invented a long time ago and music has played a really important role in our life from the past to nowadays . Nowadays , music is important for our lives . You can see , music is everywhere , in the supermarket , in the coffee shop , on the street when you go to school or go to work . On a farm in Japan , you can see the cows also listen to music , because they believe when cows listen to music , the cows become more relaxed and they will grow effectively . Those are some examples of music in our lives . You can see , somehow music has become a part of our lives . Music can also help us feel more relaxed and comfortable . That is why music is very popular and there are some studies which prove music can impact children in a good way and help improve their brains effectively . Music can also help adults and old people improve their mental and physical health , help them go through hard times and gain more strength . In my opinion , without music , our lives would be very boring and stressful , because music is a part of our lives . 
In today 's world , studying at university is becoming more and more important for the young generation and it seems to be a most efficient way to learn about life . To my way thinking , studying abroad is much more preferable in as much as it contributes to younger being wise adults in three ways , as follow : The first and foremost reasons for my choice is that many students do not have the chance to learn how to manage money . For instance , they do not get used to paying bills for electricity or distributing money for other necessary items . However , a university student has to pay attention to making compulsory payments , otherwise he or she has to burn the midnight oil in real terms . Another reason which absolutely deserves some words here is that staying at home during university years means beating a dead horse . I mean , studying at university teaches young brains something about life , not only for landing jobs but also for becoming a social , conscious person . And it paves the way for taking these opportunities and having fun taking decisions without any interference of their parents . On the other hand , sitting next to a lovely dad and mom provides the same lifestyle as being a student at high school . Lastly , it will be worthwhile studying away from home since it accustoms both children and parents to live separately . For parents , this milestone causes them to be able to travel without any responsibility , i . e . freely . For students , they can find good jobs in other big cities while studying and Interning in big companies . In a nutshell , it is the time to live freely and take their own decisions even though they might be wrong . With the aim of learning about life easily , students should study abroad . Otherwise , they will miss the boat . 
