Although many people say their best holidays were in a foreign country , I prefer to be in a quiet calm place where you can enjoy nature . As well as that , I had a beautiful holiday during the summer time , when I stayed for two months in the south of France in my birth village . Each morning , I got up early to take advantage of the cool temperature just before the sun came up . I went to the baker 's to buy the fresh bread just out of the oven . That was delicious , to walk in my village so early . Before breakfast , I had time to be in the garden , listening to the birds sing and other noises of nature waking up . At 8 o 'clock , breakfast was ready and often the table was set outside on the terrace and in addition , the sun was just beginning to shine . During the day , we stayed in the shade inside of the house , alternating reading books and refreshment in the swimming pool . The days finished at midnight with the cool temperature and the songs of the cicadas 
Time flies . You can see the changes it brings , not only in people , but in nature as well . One season starts and another ends very quickly . But have you ever thought about which one of them is your favourite ? Mine is definitely spring , and let me explain to you why . In summer it 's too hot and during the winter and autumn it 's too cold , so spring is somewhere in the middle , with optimum conditions . Of course I 'm simplifying now . Spring is my favourite season , not only because of the weather . But at this point I have to add it 's really appealing to me . It 's a beautiful time of the year . Everything is waking up from the winter sleep . Plants are growing and painting the world in green , with all those leaves and grass . Birds return from Africa and every morning sing to you their outstanding songs . It feels like the whole world is joyful and this happy excitement can be infectious . To cut a long story short , I love spring in my country . You should spend some time outdoors during that period and if you enjoy being close to nature as much as I do , you will fall in love with that season . 
I think sometimes music is important , because it makes us feel better and to concentrate . I think music makes us feel all sorts of things , depending on what type of music we 're listening to . For example , if we 're listening to pop music , it can make us feel happy and full of energy , or , if we are listening to classical music , like Mozart , it can make us feel very relaxed . I think life without music would be very boring and sad , because music makes us feel different and happier . I also think music plays a very big part in the world , because music and making music is a way for us human beings to express ourselves in a creative and fun way . Also , a life without music would be a life without fun , because you can dance to music and sing songs , and all of these activities are really fun and without music , it would not be the same . 
I would like to live a shorter life but much more intense because I think it would make me feel more alive . I have a long , calm life and I do not think that 's enough for me and just the thought of living 100 years like this does not make me happy at all . I believe life should be challenging , overwhelming , thrilling and full of adventures . I should be able to have the biggest heartbreak ever , to experience an unforgettable breathtaking kiss every day and to have moments that will be with me forever . The best people in life are free to live like this , in an intense way . I would love to achieve all my dreams , do all I ever wanted at once because I think that 's what life 's about , the love , being intense , dramatic , romantic , challenging and to be more realistic . It would be pretty boring to live quietly , just doing tedious stuff , that would kill me inside . I am an intense person and I love to feel emotions , that makes me feel alive . I would love to go to a concert of one of my favorite artists and sing all my favorite songs and dance , scream to all the potential of my lungs and dance until I feel like I 'm going to break my bones . That 's what I would love to do ! 
Sometime people do not like physical exercise and prefer to stay at home and watch TV . I think exercise is important for your emotional and physical balance . First , physical sport is important to maintain your dynamism and ability to move . If you do not sport , your body will become heavy and fat and step by step you will have health problems , like a heart attack or difficulty to walk because you heart will not have enough blood pressure to send it around your body . Second , exercise must be part of your life to maintain good mental health . Your spirit needs to be solicited to interact with your body . If you do not do this , your brain can degenerate . In conclusion , human life is moving , because the cells of your body must develop . That is the main reason why you must do physical and mental exercise . If you do not exercise , you may degenerate and die . 
Firstly , the music is essential in human beings ' lives . Even a child in a mother 's womb before it has been born is able to react to a melody . There are studies which prove that playing a Mozart melody to these children may help evolve their brains and these kids will have brilliant minds . Although we do not put a higher focus on the music itself , a background tune may have significant benefits for our ability to concentrate on a certain problem . Plenty of surgeons listen to relaxing music while they are in the operating theatre , since it has a flourishing effect on their work . To add more , a lot of people are prone to evaluating others according to the kind of music they listen to . Only a style of a music may connect people with the same feelings . We may see huge groups of people visiting metal gigs . They all share the same enthusiasm for this kind of music , while a different group of people see metal music just as a discordant tune without any sense . 
