The truth is considered a virtue in many cultures and religions . And I believe it is a virtue too , but each rule has an exception , therefore , there are some specific situations , in which , lying would be a viable option . The first situation is war . Imagine yourself taken hostage by your country 's enemies during war time , and they investigate you , and ask you to tell them about your country 's weapons , number of soldiers , and secret matters . It is a foregone conclusion that telling the truth here is wrong , it is deemed as betrayal . Lying at war time is necessary in order to protect your country , your family , and yourself . The second situation would be in marriage , and I do not want to be on the wrong foot here . So , I do not mean big lies or twisted lies like cheating on your wife and lying about it . Instead , I mean lies that would make her happy . For instance , if your wife was not attractive during pregnancy , and she probably was not , it would be really wrong to tell the truth to her face , even if she asked . Lying in these kinds of situations is also crucial , because the truth will not be beneficial for anyone . Instead , it will hurt her feelings and make her feel less confident about herself and her body . In my book , I believe that these two situations are the only ones when a person should lie in . Other than that , it is wrong . 
There have been some rumours about a legislation that bans the use of mobile phones in public transport , shops , and restaurants , basically , any public closed place . I am writing you today to express my thoughts about the matter , and to give you some suggestions . I believe that your idea is good , but it is a little bit extreme , and it is not a viable option . It is true that individuals are using their mobile phones non -stop theses days , and it is also true that this excessive use is causing a lot of issues and accidents , but banning them that way is going to cause another problem , because someone may need to use his or her phone for an emergency , thus , a complete ban is not the best solution . However , we can all agree that the use of social media in public places is not necessary most of the time . The same logic applies to games . Therefore , we should ban these kinds of apps which are not helpful at all . In this way , we can have a suitable solution , which is not so radical . At the same time as we achieve the desired outcome . I really want to thank you for giving me the time to read my suggestion . I hope that it was helpful for you , and I think that you are doing a great job . 
This essay involves a delicate issue that I have been thinking about a lot before answering , after having heard other people 's experiences . It seems a very easy issue and I doubt that people would prefer being rich , but in a bad state of health . What I mean is that being healthy should be our main priority and all of us should take care , not only of our personal state of health , but should also think about others ' health . Being rich and wealthy is not as important as many people think , and all the cases of rich people s illnesses are a clue that making a lot of money does not mean you are happy . What people do not understand is that they should not push their luck , because they run the risk of losing what the most precious thing is : their health . It is true that people have no control over what life brings to them , but they cannot spend all their life looking for riches and wealth . We know very well how we risk being down on our luck . If our destiny is to be rich and wealthy , we must just let nature take its course . 
