Dear participants in the town council , I would like to express my opinion regarding the last idea of banning the use of cell phones in common areas , such as restaurants and shops , as well as on public transport . I am actually aware of the environmental as well as biological risks of pollution due to electromagnetic waves , and the very little worry of the people about that . First of all , people do not ' feel ' electromagnetic waves , in the sense that it is pollution that does not make noise , or have a bad smell , nor even is ' seen ' as wasted material . Nevertheless , it is with no doubt acting on our ear warming , as the cell phone electromagnetic waves are of the same kind as microwaves , thus enabling our water molecules to ' twist ' , producing warming as a secondary effect . Unfortunately , this kind of molecular movement sometimes creates headaches or even tumors ( most of the times benign ) . Especially in young people , as they are made of much more water than adults . For all of these reasons , I would agree with the council 's initiative , for the ' precautionary principle ' that would induce us not to use intensively cell phones before a clear scientific statistics are made by our health organization . Anyway , before such a decision , I would encourage them to take initiatives in order to make people discuss with competent doctors the problem . In fact , I think that you need , first of all , to give the knowledge , then you can convince people to accept the rule . 
Currently , few high schools presume students to proof a some voluntary work in order to graduate . But is this just a waste of time or does it promote the personality development of its students ? At first , undeniably , most students experience schools as too theoretical rather than practical . It seems to them that they learn something with low impact for their future . Or do you have to acquire broad skills - think about arts or sports - for applying to a maths degree ? Therefore , volunteers could gain real life experience , which would top the dry school material off . Additionally , students had to choose from a range of voluntary work that suits their interests best and learn essential life lessons such as communicating with others or to be empathetic . Lastly and not less relevant is that students with a voluntary background set themselves out from other peers . This enables them to gain benefits in an application process for university or a job . To sum up , I personally think that more schools should assume students to conduct work on a voluntary basis . In my view , this work would certainly broaden the horizon of the students academically and personally . 
These paragraphs contain the question whether university students should live on their own while they are attending school or whether they should live at home . I personally think that it is less laborious to stay at home because you do not need to look for another affordable accommodation and you can spare your money due to seek for another affordable accomodation and you can spare your money due to a missing rent you do not need to pay . To sum up , this is a great choice if your degree course is taught at your home university . Despite that , it is obvious that some prospective students move away because of their interest in a specific field of study . Furthermore , you will mature more quickly by managing your own life , that covers the daily shopping in a supermarket or to arrange a doctor 's appointment , and you will feel more confident and successful . Moreover , it could be beneficial to study even abroad in order to learn a foreign language and to represent yourself as person with international attributes . That would ease your job search after graduation enormously if you preferred to study in an international working environment . 
Since a well -known magazine for English language learners has asked for reviews about useful resources for learning English , I recommend Write & Improve with Cambridge , whose function is to improve your writing skills step by step . If you open this writing tool , you can choose between various tasks which require a different level of English . After that , you start to write a text and hand it in after you finished . Subsequently , a review of your written text appears and you can see what you have done correctly and where you can improve . Then , you correct your mistakes and hand in your revised text to check whether it is right . On the one hand , this method requires a highly responsible and motivated student who seeks his mistakes over a long time , but on the other hand , it can be extremely unsatisfying when you can not fix some mistakes . So this tool is quite a good way to self -study . But it is even better when you can ask someone for help sometimes to improve your writings a lot . In my view , every English student should use this tool or a similar one to enhance their individual writing skills . More in particular , you can learn at your own speed and focus on your developing fields . Nevertheless , it can be frustrating to seek mistakes for a long time , but then you need to go on . 
People around the world plan their life differently based on their wishes . Two possible life plans are a long calm life and a short intense life . Firstly , it is crucial for everybody to live as long as possible in order to be able of fulfill every wish . Referring to this , it is out of doubt that a long life suits best to this life 's goal , because the elderly spend more time on Earth and can look back on a long life span . If anyone pursues reaching that , he needs to live healthily and to stand out of any danger . Another life plan is to act less calmly and to do more exciting as well as dangerous things . Moreover , they wish to do more dangerous activities because of the adrenaline rush . , . some people feel more vital during these nasty situations and can relax from the monotony of their routine lives . In addition , these people think that they should do anything that they want before they get too old to do it . While both of these life plans are imaginable for me , in my opinion , a calmer life would fit better with my expectations . In more detail , I am not a person that seeks exciting situations and I feel more comfortable in a structured daily routine . But most important is that I want to live as long as possible , because I have several plans for my future . 
Young people and sports Should sport be obligatory for young people ? Many would argue no . Others could see this from a different perspective . Let 's try to take a look at both opinions . According to statistics , every fifth child is overweight in UK schools . " Just do more sport and eat less " some people could say . But it 's not that simple . It 's not easy to " just do sport . " Young people can be disgusted by sport because of their early childhood memories . For example , Harry was forced to do at least five sport activities a week , and none of them were neither interesting nor enjoyable for him . Because of this , now , when he can take some responsibility into his hands , he does not do any sport , because he thinks all of them are alike . On the other hand , there are people like Sarah , who found their passion in early childhood . Nowadays , she is a basketball player in the national league , playing at least five times a week . Although she was not forced to choose exceptionally this sport , she found it thanks to PE in school , where sports changed almost every lesson . This had fortunately led her to outstanding success . Without a doubt , she is a role model for many young ones . To summarize , this question is not as easy to answer as it may seem . Seldom do we see such ambitious young people like Sarah . But still , her story tells us something . She was able to try all the sport in her childhood and nobody forced her to do any of them . Therefore , she has been doing sport until now without planning to stop . Other people do not have to be as active as her but finding any hobby in sports helps them in their healthy lifestyle . All in all , I 'm certain that young people should try as much sport as possible , but forcing them to do what they do not like wo not help the cause . 
