In my opinion , it depends on the kind of job because if , in the offices , there are no walls separating employees , it 's very loud if you need to make a call . On the other hand , if , for the job , it 's necessary to talk with your partners , it 's better that no there are walls in the office . Always , in your office , you need your own space to do your job as best as possible . Without walls , creativity and communication will be better than if you have a wall and you ca not see your partners . If for your job , you need to be concentrated , such as a designing , it 's more useful to have walls to do better your job without distractions . Another reason , it depends on your boss because if he wants to look at his employees without walls , it 's easier to do . I hope it 's a group decision and I 'm afraid that not always all the employees will agree with the same solution . 
Dear members of the town council , With this letter , I want to remind you of our constitution . According to article two of our constitution , a human being has the right to act as they please . Therefore , your intention to ban mobile phones from public transportation , shops and restaurants is illegal , as long as you are not able to provide any good reason for doing so . Restrictions to our right to act as we like are only feasible if you have a profound reason for it . Despite that , you have not provided such a reason or given any explanation on why you plan on banning mobile phones in the already mentioned locations . As far as I can tell , there is no danger involved in the activities you consider banning . Also , I ca not see any other good reason to enforce your idea . I can only guess that your intention is to patronize your citizens . To me , it seems like an idea that aims to hinder people from using mobile phones in situations where a well -behaved person would not use these devices . But , while this cause is understandable , it still is an illegal constraint of our constitutional rights . Social norms should , by no means , be legally forced on people . In the long term , such overregulation will lead to unsatisfied citizens and riots . Therefore , I believe , you should abstain from your idea to regulate the use of mobile phones in public transportation , restaurants or shops . 
The reasons for many doctors to choose the big city is because they will receive more money and there are more doctors in that place , so it 's more difficult pass to work in a hospital located in a big city . On the other hand , it 's easier to pass in a small city , but their salary is not good . In a small city , the local people do not have good salaries and the government does not pay a fair price to live there . The solution is simple , the government needs to invest more in small villages to solve the inequality problem . If they do that , the doctors will be more interested in changing places and their health will be better , solve the problem of the bigs competions in bigs cities and in the small wo not miss goods doctors . Here , in Brazil , we have the same problem , in part , for a time , it was solved with a government program when Dilma Roussef was president , because they started to pay for Cuban doctors . Nowadays , we do not have this program any more because the new president fired everybody . 
Between the two possibilities , I would like to have a long calm life until 100 years old . I 'm opting for this option because of my personality . I 'm a quiet person , who does not like to do things hastily because acting like this can make you commit a lot of errors . Other than that , I see the point of doing intense activity , but I do not feel like I could afford and maintain this lifestyle . My body would not be able to resist such conditions and , with aging , it will become more and more difficult to maintain an intense life . In the end , why do I choose a long calm life ? Highlighting different motivations , other than what my temperament is like , another reason for liking this type of life is that you can have the possibility to see the little things of life . What I mean is that , in this way , one has time to appreciate and feels the little gestures of the person you love and gives back these gestures to him/her , one can deeply think about nature and how complex , beautiful and amazing it is . I think it 's essential to take our time to understand better and deeply nature and creation . I feel like I can understand a bit more the complexity and the depth of creation . The most important discoveries were made by analyzing nature and trying to copy its mechanisms . In the end , these are the reasons why I prefer a long , calm life . 
I often play badminton , read Harry Potter and other books , sometimes I watch the television , too . I read books when I have time , including in the morning , afternoon and at night . I play badminton on Saturdays and Sundays in the afternoon at about 3 P.M . I watch the television at night when I finish my homework and study . Sometimes when I am bored , I play with Lego or go to my friend 's house . 
Dear Sir or Madam , I am writing this letter in response to the recently published proposal of banning the use of mobile phones in public settings and I would like to express my disapproval of the above proposal . It came to my attention that public transport , shops and restaurants will be mainly affected by this newly created idea . To begin with , I would massively appreciate it if the council would like to cast a bit more light for us on why you think this would be a good move . A far as I am concerned , none of the reasons we have been presented with were supported by any scientific evidence . Therefore , I am demanding the town council to present the public with their backed up by science arguments . Moreover , neither I nor anyone in my family has been ever approached and asked to give our own opinion about the topic . Should our local representatives not be more in touch with their people when it comes to making such drastic changes in our lives ? Do you think this is the right way to treat your citizens ? Well , I must strongly disagree with you , then . And finally , to sum it up , I would like to propose to organize another meeting where everyone who might be affected by those changes is able to express their views . 
Although people think being rich is the most important thing of your life , I am definitely sure heath is my first priority . The first report is when people have lost their heath definitively or just temporarily , they become much more sensitive than people who do not have health problems . It is always a good to reflect on this priority when you have a small heath problem , like you break your arm or just have the flu , when you are obliged to stop all of your activities and you must stay at home . At this moment , you can say at yourself , even if I am very rich , I can become as healthy as I want . Nature is stronger than you and you need to be patient . These situations improve your humility and are the best way to understand the better value of life compared to only being focused on money . Life is a balance between your health and the need for money to live . It is important to take time to care for yourself . That is the first step for heath and good mental heath . 
Music . Not a thousand words could portray its inner essence . Music has played and always will play a tremendous role in our society . It is the backbone of our modern civilisation . Moreover , it enables us to communicate with people around the world . Its beauty has brought us together and unites us all over the world . Could you imagine a world without music ? I certainly cannot . Whether we are having a bad day or we are desperately seeking some alternation in our life , music is always the right answer to it . It enhances our emotional state and combats stress . Additionally , it makes us feel worthy and unique . We just live in the moment . So , as I already mentioned in the beginning , I would not want to live in a world without music . We should be grateful for music and be cheered by it every day of our life . 
MY NEW SCHOOL YEAR The aim of this report is to plan my new English school year by specifying the most important objectives I would like to achieve by the end of the year . MY STRENGTHS When it comes to studying English , I cannot help but mention that my biggest strength is none other than my writing skill , and so I want it to continue being this way . In that spirit , my intention is to keep on practising it . MY DRAWBACKS With regard to my weaknesses , not only do I find it difficult to express myself speaking in English , but also I am aware of my difficulties in understanding some different accents , such as Irish or Scottish . Should there be any way to make it easier for me , I would be delighted to explore it . REACHING MY GOALS It goes without saying that once I overcome my drawbacks concerning English , I will be more confident when using that language whenever I find it appropriate and it will also encourage me more to continue studying it for good , as we never stop learning . Last but by no means least , I would like to conclude by bringing focus to the fact that English is the most universal language on earth , therefore it is essential for us to learn it . 
Although the majority of people like to watch police films , I prefer films with adventure and that initiate people with know -how . That is the reason my favourite movie is Wind . The subject of this film is sailing to win the America Cup . The story of the movie is very interesting , because you follow all the different steps before the win . The first step is when America lose the cup to New Zealand . You can analyse why they lost and the interesting tactics of their competitor . The second step is the reconquest of this title by the American team . That is a great maritime adventure and I suppose my penfriend will like it . 
