Generally , music is very important in our lives . Music is a cure . When I was a boy , I listened to rock a lot . Now I listen to pop , because it is better for my good mood . Every person needs to listen to some music , for example the radio or a concert . Without music , I cannot imagine my life . Yesterday I was listening to my favourite singer , Lucie Vondráčková . I had worked a lot and I needed to change my mind to be happy . Now I am listening to the radio . Tomorrow I will be listening to the second ACDC record and I think that tomorrow evening , I will have listened to all of the best songs . I should listen to music with the volume down , because my ears are very painful from noisy music . I like the volume up very much and then it is a problem . I will try to change it . I have been listening to music a lot and I will not change that , because music is my whole life . I would like to say that music makes people happier than other areas or department , for example , TV or movies . Let 's have some music in our ears . Best regards . 
Although in France few people speak English fluently , I would like to be fluent in this language , because I am planning to travel and live in different countries of the world . The language of the world is English . Today , the planet is extremely connected and to be able to work or simply exchanges ideas with other people , you must have a good level in speaking and writing English . After this trip around the world , I would like to be writer of novels . First , I have to read a lot of novels to learn the English style . Second , I will learn to write English with a famous English writer , J . K . Rowling , author of Harry Potter . I hope to be as successful as her . Third , I will isolate myself for 6 months on Gozo Island to find inspiration . Learning English is a big project for me and my lifestyle . 
In the last decades , the health of students has started to decline . An inactive lifestyle , accelerated by the negative impacts of video games and streaming platforms , has resulted in higher obesity rates . One burning question has emerged : Should we force school children and even university students to participate in sport activities at least three times per week ? This essay intends to make it abundantly clear that strict regulation is not a solution at all . There can be no doubt that the physical state of myriads of children has worsened due to the rise of globalization and digitisation . With thousands and thousands of children addicted to video games and social media , the allure of going outside is comparatively small . This has certainly changed over time . The leisure time our parents and grandparents spent in their childhood seems to be worlds apart from ours . Few people would dispute the fact that exploring the wild is not an integral part of growing up . There are those who argue that kids should not be put in a risky situation . Helicopter parents are instantly watching every single step of their beloved offspring . However , in that way , they are indirectly hindering their child 's development . Kids need to spend time outside . It is widely believed that children need to make decisions on their own , to make independent decisions , which thus enhances personality development . The proposal of forcing children to do sport activities is quite similar to the approach of the autocratic regime in China . In order to counteract the " feminisation " of society , which refers to the up -bringing of a generation full of spoiled only children , the government has implemented a sports scheme . However , we - as members of a democratic society - should set a good example . In conclusion , children should not be forced to do sports involuntarily . These initiatives would not improve the overall situation . We have to counteract these recent developments by supporting children not to use their smartphones all the time and instead taking a walk outside . All our problems would diminish within a second . 
Dear town council , I am writing in reference to your idea of forbidding the use of mobile phones in public . I disagree with your opinion and will state my arguments with the help of examples . Firstly , mobile phones are used by most people for keeping in touch with each other , for working activities outside the office and to inform themselves about the daily news . You will probably reply to this in the following way : Everybody is distracted because there is so much activity on their mobile phones , and social communication decreases in public . Thus , new technologies , like mobile phones , computers or headphones , to name just a few , are part of our today 's culture and too relevant to ban them . Furthermore , you are forgetting another important aspect : social network use is increasing , especially among younger people . Whose advantage is that people across the world - even in the most distance between each other - can interact with each other . It is known by most that this is a relevant factor to globalisation , which enables us to act together for the first time in human history . But the winning argument is that the use of mobile phones spare much time . If you needed to search for some information for ages , you would get a result in a much shorter time span now . Time that could be used to go outside or to do engage voluntarily . Therefore , I strongly recommend to decline your idea of banning mobile phones in public . Yours faithfully , Jan 
Hi Éric , I was at the jazz concert at the Hot Club of Lyon , where Richard Galliano played accordion . That was brilliant and energetic . I am glad to share with you all of my enthusiasm and this enjoyable moment . First , I wanted to hear Richard Galliano , because he is a famous French accordion player . He played all the different accordion types in the jazz concert . Second , I was lucky to have a ticket , because the Hot Club of Lyon is a small place . That was fantastic too because the public was near the player . You could see and speak with him . I remember one of the pieces of music : Tango . Marvellous . 
Music - A part of your world The majority of people have different opinions about music and its forms . Some do not actually relish music at all . The question is though , are there times when music is significant and vital , for instance for our psychohygiene ? Is it sometimes required and necessary to listen to music ? Certain people believe that the shapes of voices and sounds are highly calming to our ears . The sounds may make us feel better and pleased , even when we listen to them passively and do not really give attention to details , such as the words of the songs . Owning to that being said , it is clear that music may reduce , for example , stress , depressive thoughts , wrath , sloth and many other wrong emotions . What would life be like without music though ? It depends on what type of a person you are . If you do not fancy music much , then you 'd probably be just fine , but if the case is the opposite , you might be in trouble . In conclusion , it is highly considered within humanity that music is an inseparable , necessary , essential and fundamental part of it and makes us feel great . 
First of all , nowadays , listening to music is becoming a habit for every human living on this earth . Also , there are different times that everyone listens to music . For example , there are some people who like listening to music before going to bed , because they are feeling relaxed at this time . Furthermore , there are some human beings who like listening to music while they are studying , because they feel more concentrated on their studying . Besides that , there are some other folk who prefer listening to music while they are working on housework , because listening to music gives them more energy to work . For this reason , listening to music is gaining more and more space in everyone 's lives , and attracts more people to depend on listening to music . For instance , there are some people who listen to music when they are sad or anxious , to release this pain . However , there are some people who listen to music when they are in a good mood . Indeed , everyone living on this earth has a specific goal for listening to music , such as listening to music while studying , working on housework and in bad moments . Moreover , there are different feelings that people have when they are listening to music . Finally , listening to music brings more benefits to this earth . 
I know that some need music in their lives , while I also think that not all people need music in their life . First of all , music is not the only way to make life better . For example , my hobby is running . Thus , when I have time or need to feel relaxed , I usually go to a gym and run using a treadmill . While , I do not listen to music if I have time . In addition , my husband also has other hobbies without music . He is a person who feels happy when he makes new programs . Additionally , music is not necessary for all to live life . There are many indispensable things for our life , such as sleep and food . However , we can live life without music . In fact , a long long time ago , people lived life without music . Thus , I believe that music is not needed for our lives . 
I just discovered the tool named " Write and Improve " recently a month ago . Whatever device you use , you can easily access this tool . You can use this tool from your computer , mobile phone and tablet . This tool will encourage you to use their program for improving your writing . You can start with an easy one that is not difficult enough for many people to surrender . I think that is why they need to start with something easy . there are a lot of tools that can help people with writing skills , then if you start with the hardest one , many people will turn that software away . If you are familiar with the easy one , then they will recommend you to go to the next level that is a little bit harder than the previous one , but this level is not that hard . I think this tool provides a lot of different levels so that you will find the level that suit you . And they have other modes such as Ielts , toeic and other tests that are well -known to a lot of people . This is the best feature that a lot of people use . I have tried around ten practices and I think they are quite similar to the real tests . If you find a tool that can help your writing skills , I think " Write and Improve " is the best choice you looking for . You will find what level suits you and then practice and then go to the next level . And they also have a test mode that is like the real one . 
Living an unhealthy lifestyle leads to unhealthy people and being inactive is a main reason for health issues . Nevertheless , should we really force university students and school children to do sport activities three times a week ? Nowadays , students are already stressed out at school and university and , often , while writing exams , there is not much free time left to include sports into their daily life . It would be really stressful for some students to start forcing them to do sports because it does not fit into their life . When forced to do something , the activity becomes less fun and can sometimes not be enjoyed , which leads to demotivation . Furthermore , what would the consequences be if someone does not do sports activities three times a week ? I think it would be unfair to punish someone because they were studying instead of working out . On the other hand , sport is great to help with physical issues and mental health problems and , considering the current state some of the students and children are in physically and mentally , sports activities would be a great way to help them out and to decrease obesity and depression . On the whole , sports activities are excellent to create a work life balance , which is often missed by a lot of students , especially when they study a lot . In addition , to stay healthy in the future , you need some sort of activity during the week if you do not want to become ill when you are old . In recent years , the amount of obese children has increased , which is also caused by a lack of movement because today most children play video games , which is why motivating them to do more activities would be a good idea . Last but not least , if one finds the right sports activity , it is often a lot of fun and , afterwards , you are more likely to be happy because your body sends out endorphines . In conclusion , I think forcing students and children to do sport activities three times a week is not the right way , but changing something is necessary . Sport needs to be more integrated in school and university , which would also make it more comfortable for students to integrate sport into their everyday life . For example , there could be more sports lessons in school , more free activities and maybe a whole new subject concerning a healthy lifestyle . In college , taking part in a sports course could be obligatory and there could also be more options . Often , at least as problematic as the lack of movement are the eating habits some folks have , which is why working on that would also be a great improvement for young people 's health and providing a subject in school about it would be the best way to do it . Still , the sports activities should be fun and not forced , but it is important to consider making it obligatory and including it more in school and university . 
From my point of view , all of us need music in our lives . Music can be important in a lot of different situations with different goals . For instance , some of us are used to listening to music on public transport . In this case , that 's entertainment and the music makes the journey shorter . For other people , it 's a way to put some words to their thoughts and to express them . Hither , music has a cathartic function , whether joy , sadness or any feeling which the music highlights . It can also be used to celebrate , in clubs or in more intimate events , like a party between friends . We can definitely see that music has a lot of different uses . Personally , I ca not even imagine life without music . Evidently , I know that some people do not need to listen to music daily and feel very good with that . But globally , music is one of the seven major arts , which humans and their culture rely on . 
When you start learning a language , you are going to find that each language has a certain volume of resources on the internet . Some of them have a small number of resources because it is not that popular , whereas others have a huge number of them , because it is an important language . English is a great example of the second type . If you try to learn English on your own , you will be confused at first , but I believe that I can help you a little . Writing is considered to be one of the most difficult skills in any language , since it needs correct grammar , punctuation , and good vocabulary . Another problem would face you is the need for someone to correct your writing , and most of the times that is not available . Write and Improve solved many of my writing problems . The website contains a huge number of writing tasks , divided into three main categories : beginner , intermediate , advanced . After finishing the task , the site will refer to your vocabulary mistakes and major grammar mistakes . The best thing about Write and Imporve would be that it gives English learners a chance to write every day for free . I have been using Write and Improve for months now , I started practicing through the intermediate tasks , but I Improved , and now I am writing advanced ones . 
The world has changed and it is becoming more open to all countries . Inexpensive flights allow us to fly all around the world . Tourists and businesspeople have this opportunity , but when you are in different foreign countries , you must be able to interact with people . The mastering of a foreign language like English is essential . Now we have a lot of possibilities for learning a foreign language . You can watch TV to improve your language and also a lot of foreign websites teaching languages are available . Learning a language allows you to have access to the culture of the country . That is an important point , because culture is the base of all good relationships between people . You learn history , literature and economics . The world being so interconnected , you must have this ability to interact with foreign people on these base subjects . As you can see , it is essential to have the mastering of at least one foreign language . 
Dear town council , I received the information about your idea of banning mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants . You are willing to hear our opinion regarding that statement , so here you will hear mine considering different aspects . , . banning mobile phones in public spaces would have such a positive impact in relation to the human capability of socializing with each other . Especially in public transportation , why do I think that ? Well , nowadays , everybody who is travelling alone spends most of their time looking at their screen or listening to music in order to avoid conversation with anybody around . It 's appalling to see how addicted we are to our technological devices , with this idea in mind , we could undoubtedly see a change in our behaviour within a short time But if we think about it , banning mobile phones can be an outstanding concept for extroverts , which are likely to begin a conversation with others . Nonetheless , for introverts , it could sound like the most dreadful idea , some already find it terrifying to get on public transportation , but they are able to accomplish it thanks to the phone . On the other hand , banning mobile phones in restaurants will be easier to implement owing to the fact that most of the time you go accompanied . It goes without saying that reducing time on our phones will not only make us realize how nice it is to have a simple conversation with a stranger but also remember what life was like before technology . I hope to hear from you soon . Laura Manuela 
TV is undoubtedly the way that has brought together different parts of our society , and it has made people more conscious about the world in which we live . The TV 's structure has been the same since it appeared over five or six decades ago . This structure has been criticised a lot , because many people have doubts about the truth of what TV tells us . TV should entertain the audience and all those people that watch it , for example when they are having lunch and dinner . This is the reason why it is easy to watch some programmes , like a " talk show " and " quiz show , " where the guests are invited to give their opinions . The power of TV education is something that has been already discussed over the last decades by well - educated opinionists , and as I see it , TV can be useful to educate the wider audience that follows its programmes . However , we must point out that the relevance of TV does not depend on only the subject , but also the manners and education of the manners and education of the opinionists . The most important thing is to pay attention to the cultural level of the cultural level of the opininists , irrespective of the subjects dealt with . 
