To talk about the volunteer work that has to be done to graduate from some high schools , we have to figure out what volunteer work is first . In my opinion , volunteering is to work but not for pay . Maybe for leaning some experiences or just because of their passion . No matter what the point of departure is , volunteering should be good for everyone . But actually , something has gone wrong now . Volunteering should be done because they want to do it , but some schools made up rules that require students to do volunteering compulsorily . In that case , students will do volunteering with a different attitude . They are not really there to help , and they just want finish their job as fast as they can . Absolutely , most of the quality of their work will not be as well as we expected . It is a difficult question to solve . If we change the compulsory rules to some rewards , the quality will not get higher because most of the students will still finish their work at the lowest requirement . And if we make the lowest requirement higher , their parents will start to argue that it took too much time to do some meaningless things that their kids cannot study well or anything else . The best way , I think , to solve this problem is to cancel the rule that requires students to do volunteering . The students who really want to help will still go by themselves and the others who do not have that kind of passion will not have to waste their time . There are lots of things that cannot be done well by setting up rules . Many factors have to be considered , no matter the psychological problems or anything else . If we make everything compulsory , nothing is going to go well . 
