Motivating children to do regular exercise Today ’s biggest challenge in child education and parenting is how to motivate children to do regular exercise . In recent years , the number of doctors reporting children with health problems such as obesity has skyrocketed . The amount of youngsters doing sports is also always decreasing . So , schools should give their students sport classes three times a week . Firstly , parents most of the time are not able to bring their offspring to the soccer club or tennis club . They are too busy with their work and come home after diner has already been served . Undoubtedly , schools are the perfect solution for this , their students could simply stay at school three extra hours a week and follow sport classes . This will help enable children to exercise regularly . Furthermore , it will not cost any extra effort from school or the parents ; the students are already at school , so they do not have to be brought or anything . Secondly , as already mentioned in the introduction , there is an increasing number of teenagers who suffer from health problems because of their lack of exercise . They may not be motivated or empowered by their parents , but this is the part where college comes into play . Similarly to the first argument , schools should just force and motivate their pupils . This could simply be done by doing gymnastics three times a week . In conclusion , schools should enable their students to participate in sports activities , since there is an ever increasing amount of young people who suffer from health issues , because they do too little sport . Furthermore , not every child is able to do exercise regularly . Schools could simply help these youngsters by giving sport classes three times a week . Students should not be stupid and doop it . 
As an actual pediatrician who looks after the health of all the kids , I could not agree more . During these last years , junk food and gummies have become the most crucial food for kids , and because of the big amount of restaurants of fast food , this habit of eating unhealthy food has became bigger . Now that there 's more technology that surrounds us , and that a lot of kids are into video games all the time , the best we can do for the children is put sports activities at least 3 times per week , because if they keep having an inactive lifestyle and still eat junk food , the amount of problems and illnesses they can have at present or carry to the future are extensive . I think that the parents of these kids are not very aware of the type of life their kids are living with such bad habits in health and food . If the parents are worried about their children , they can do some things to avoid the problems where a younger kid can have a heart problem once he 's older . One of the things that I recommend is putting the kid into an extracurricular sport , or if you have the possibility to do a sport that you can do at school after classes , you could choose that option . Doing an extracurricular sport helps the kid to have a more active lifestyle - in addition to the sports activities 3 times per week - and to become more healthy . Although we want children to start having a more active lifestyle , I would also recommend for them to change the type of food they 're constantly eating and that is not healthy for their body . Food , like juice , that has a lot of preservatives and sugar , chocolate that is in almost every cookie you find , etc . 
