Human always keep developing every second , that 's our instinct since our ancestor 's era , we 've already possessed that feature . Our ancestors had an intense life because that 's the survival instinct , they had to forage , find place to sleep and hunt or would be hunted . Today , some people presume that we do not need to do so anymore as we have everything we need already ( foods , stable accommodation and even places to entertain ourselves ) but I do not think so . We 're human and humans always want more in a positive way . Personally , it 's not wrong as curiosity is good , learning new things is good ... I love an intense life more than anything else . That 's why if you ask me , I will definitely choose a shorter but much more intense life rather than a long , calm one until 100 years old . As I have said , to keep moving forward is our instinct , I believe that 's a special feature that God makes specially for humans . Furthermore , I love the intensity of our life , I always think it 's the gift which life gives to us . Every time I come up against a challenge or sticky situation , maybe I would feel sad or some other negative feelings at first , but after that , I know it was a positive experience and felt very proud of myself . After all , challenges help us grow , I learn a lot from those hard moments . In summary , I could not live even a day with a life that is so calm or monotonous , every day is the same , I prefer an intense but short one . 
