MY REASON FOR LEARNING ENGLISH The number of reasons why I want to learn English are endless , but there is one that makes me totally absorbed . English is the most common language in the world , and despite the unrest around the world , I think that a good knowledge of English will let me to have a conversation with a large number of people . Although I do not like its grammar and the different ways to do the structure sentences , I must acknowledge that English is an interesting language and it is useful to reinforce our ability in thinking in an alternative way . As well , English has been singled out as the first language for international trade , and all those who take over the control of a company or a firm have a deep knowledge of it . As I see it , when your level of English is high , you have the authority to manage all the international sides of an issue , like politics , economics or psychological problems . We must not bury our head in the sand . English is the language of the future . 
There are four seasons in a year and each season has different weather and different characteristics . So , because of that , people will like different seasons to some others . For me , I like summer the most . Why ? The first reason is I love swimming , especially in hot weather , and summer is the hottest season in the year , which is a convenience . Second , my favourite food is cold and sweet junk food , and it is best to eat cold food in hot weather that makes you sweat . One more very special thing is I do not need to go to school in summer , which makes sense to all students ! As I have a summer holiday , of course , in summer , I can go swimming and eat ice cream . I can also visit my grandparents and meet my cousins too , which is really fun . I do not know if other people like spring , or fall , or winter , but I like summer the most . 
Many people believe that the best holiday is to go to a beach near some good shade , but there are many destinations to go on holidays . According to tourist offices , more than 80 % of people prefer to go close to the beach in summer , in order to look for relaxation and good food . The problem is that a lot people think the same , therefore the beaches are crowded . My wife and I prefer to be in contact with nature , far from any crowds . For this reason , on our honeymoon , we decided to go to Costa Rica . It was the best holiday we have ever had in our lives . It was amazing walking through the jungle to look at wild animals . In spite of the dangerous animals , you can see them if you stay quiet . To sum up , it does not matter what the place is where you go , the most important thing is who are you going with . 
If you asked me two years ago what the meaning of music was in my life , I certainly would not have given it the importance that it deserves . Nowadays , two years later ( and a Covid -19 pandemic in the middle ) , I can say that music saved me . When the Covid -19 pandemic started , I needed to move back to living with my parents and stay locked inside our home for safety . It was a really difficult time for me , because I was used to living alone and there was a lot fear in the air . This episode took more than one year and I needed psychological help to keep me strong until the end . In several moments , music was my only company and distraction . Because of this , I developed a rich taste in music , especially different musical styles from around the world , such as reggaeton , pop culture , R&B , Indian music , etc . Now , I 'm sure I ca not live without music and I 'm looking forward to the next Doja Cat album ! 
There are uncountable reasons for this problem . And perhaps it can be very hard to find solutions for it . Why do so many doctors prefer to work in cities where it is possible to earn much money ? The answer : There are several reasons , and one can tell some of them : First : Those cities with many people are places where there are many more opportunities . If there are many possibilities , there will be much more money , too . Second : With more money in your pocket , it is possible to choose the best conditions of life . And the things are an unstoppable circle . Third : Perhaps doctors want to work in the richest cities because there are more advanced technologies , more research , more qualified people to work beside the health professionals . These are only some of the reasons why I see that preference . But , what can we say about the real situation of those people who live in rural areas ? In these places , there are not enough medical professionals in the area . So , why do not those doctors want to work there ? Well , poverty is a huge reality ... the places where those people have to work are simple and small , and they almost do not receive enough research or support to continue doing their activities . In these smaller cities ( or districts ! ) , this or that doctor used to be the only professional to work during the weekends . This means an extra load of work for several doctors , and for these reasons too , they choose not to work in places too far from great urban cities . How can it be solved ? It is difficult to say that there is only one solution to solve this problem . In reality , there are several points to be analysed . It is necessary to give the best remuneration to those professionals that work in little cities . And so , the governments have to look with more attention at those people that live outside of the capitals . It is also necessary to improve the structures and conditions of those work places . Perhaps , after all these improvements , doctors can change their points of view and they want to change the largest cities for the calmness of the smallest villages ! 
Olomouc can be considered to be one of our most beautiful cities . The reason is that it was destroyed during the Thirty Year War and then rebuilt by Maria Theresa as a modern fortress . That is why there are beautiful city walls and , in the former bunkers , there are museums and restaurants . 
