Is learning to speak a foreign language as important these days as it was in the past ? In my opinion , yes , today it is more important to speak another language , especially English , than have a professional degree . It ’s probably because of many causes , for instance , a ) the size of the American economy , b ) the international relations between United States of America with the Commonwealth and c ) several free trade agreements or treaties subscribed with many countries around the world . Another reason may be the American culture . It is fascinating how they have captured the imagination of millions of people of thousands of different cultures , through their music , television programs , movies and video games . Of course , globalization has an influence on the economic relationships between countries , but it all depends on the important leadership of the United States of America and the United Kingdom . This leadership includes advanced technology and military forces . 
Medical doctors and cities A great issue faced by many cities is the absence of health care staff , mostly medical doctors , in rural areas . This problem affects both underdeveloped and developed countries . Medical doctors do not want to live in the countryside . But why does it happen ? Which reason drives to that situation in several countries , being these countries rich or poor . I guess there are several things that can influence it . One of them is when a highly qualified professional , like a doctor , lives in a big city , they can make more money . In addition , doctors living in big cities can easily get educational updates such as MBAs , courses and conferences rather than those living in rural areas . Living in main cities can help these doctors make professional connections and that is very important for their careers . Maybe they would not be able to get these opportunities if they lived in the countryside . Despite the difficulties of setting medical doctors in the countryside , there are some possible strategies that towns can adopt in order to attract these professionals . One is to give to them tax exemptions to set up a new medical office . Another possibility is to offer advantages to just graduated medical students . I have seen an interesting alternative here in my country . Medical schools are being set up in medium size cities , known as regional centers , and it has been helping to fix young doctors in those areas . Regional retention surveys have shown that it works . 
