Dear town council , I am a normal citizen in this town and I respect your opinion about banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants . But I have revesial oponion opinion about this law . I have been a worker in this town for 10 years , I often have to go a long way to the work , so I think that I need to buy a phone for necessary situations , but the security on public transport is very low and I must be alert about pickpockets whenever I want to make a call . Therefore , I see calling by public mobile phones to be a better choice , I can move to the place where there are the driver and bus attendant , it is quite safe . Another reason for my opinion is that a public mobile phone on transport and in restaurants can support me in an emergency . I sometimes forget my phone at home and I cannot borrow another phone , so public mobile phones are my salvation . Finally , the cost of public mobile phone 's time is cheaper than private phones , so I can save some money on it . As a labor worker , I need to accumulate as much money as I can , because the company only hires young men under 40 and will fire all the old workers when they are not efficient . As you can see , I strongly protest your law . Although there are some problems with public mobile phones like the installation fees because we must put the phone on many roads , and the nuisance of being bothered by children , but we can solve it easily by encouraging people to use it more , and we can teach children not to do this . I think that is more beneficial than banning public phones . In conclusion , a public mobile phone is more convenient , safe and economic than other choice . Sincerely , Hang . 
MUSIC FOR LIFE Today , there are a lot of music types in the world and the latest polls show us music is indispensable for people , because it is the best option for making people happier . Life is miserable and depressing , because everybody has problems in their life and they want to feel happier . Music makes people 's lives less depressing . because when they feel the music , they go to a completely different world which is far away their problems and they feel happier and less depressed . A life without music is unthinkable , because if there is no music in the world , people will always be depressed and sad , because there is no option to feel happier or far away from their concerns . On the other hand , life with music is better than without music . I think music is a necessity for people 's lives , because there are a lot of concerns in people 's lives and music helps people to be far away from their concerns for a moment . Moreover , there are a lot of social media platforms which use music on their platforms for fun . In conclusion , music is life and life is music . 
Choosing a university and the course to enroll in is one of the most important decisions in life . Students have to decide it taking into consideration a lot of reasons , among them whether to live on their own or with their parents . I personally believe that living by yourself is one of the best choices for a student . I feel this way for two reasons , which I will explore in the following paragraphs . To begin with , I think it is crucial for students to pursue their own independence in this period of life . For a long time before , college students live in their comfort zone in their parents ' house with food , housing , and clean clothes available . It can make them used to a lifestyle that is not real , and for that reason , a period living alone far from home can be really helpful for their development . I am a compelling example of this , the best decision that I made in life was to leave my mother 's house to go to college in another state . It helped a lot to develop skills and habits that come in handy nowadays . Secondly , living alone provides an opportunity to connect with other people and build lifelong relationships . Moreover , it can also lead to building a powerful network that will be important at a professional level in the future . For instance , when I was living alone in college , I made a lot of good friends , they helped me a lot to pass through that new phase and we became really close . Furthermore , for being with me everyday , they became my second family and I can rely on them until this day , which definitely comes in hand on a personal and professional level . To conclude , I strongly believe that living on their own is good thing for students . It will help them to grow personally and to build great relationships . 
I think music is necessary for everyone . Even if you do not like some styles , I bet that you have a song in your mind that helps or has helped you somehow . When you are sad or happy , your playlist can tell , I am sure . And this is the thing , music has a great impact on our lives . The best romantic song was written because of someone , the person put all his feelings in a way to express how they felt . And , somehow , when we listen to that song , we think about someone too . Or at least feel something . But why ? Because music carries more than lyrics , it carries feelings . Another interesting thing , some studies have reported the effects of music on neurological and mental diseases , showing that songs could affect our nervous system and memory . This is an amazing thing to search for more about diseases like Alzheimer and dementia . So , somehow , the songs that you like and listen to have a permanent effect on your brain , even though you think about music as a random way to pass the time . And because of that , I am sure that our lives would be harder without the feelings expressed through beautiful lyrics . It would be harder to charge ourselves with the beauty of melody and composition . Music makes us feel alive . 
When talk about university life , the first thing we will think of is being independent . Most of the students are of age and it is just the time to face some problems by themselves . But , is moving away and living on their own a good choice ? Here are some points . The most simple problem is about money , there has to be a place for them to live , and a place might make some money . So where should the money come from ? Some families can afford another expenditure like this , but what about the others that cannot afford it ? Of course , students can have a part -time job , but college life is very busy , and I think it will affect their studying or their socializing . And that might be putting the cart before the horse . And another problem is about time . When we are in college , there are lots of things to do , no matter the studies or the clubs or the relationships . They are all very important for college students and will take a lot of time . So , do they actually have time to do all the housework and do some dishes ? In my opinion , they have to learn how to control the use of their time and it is possible to handle everything . So if the family can afford the expense of living outside , maybe we should give it a try . Actually , there are many other things to worry about in college life , because it is a big break of life . We start to learn things not only for tests but we start to plan our future , maybe start to feel stress out but that is just what we have to face . 
My favourite season of the year could not be any other than winter . Yeah , the winter makes me smile all the time . I will explain better . I do not like hot weather . In the summer , my body feels uncomfortable . I ca not have good food , I need to drink a lot of water ... When the weather is hot , I cannot sleep very well and doing sports is a great sacrifice . That 's why I prefer winter . Low temperatures make my body feel better . When the winter comes , I sleep very well . I can eat several delicious things , I do not feel thirsty and doing sports outside is amazing . While in the summer I have difficulties to wear some clothes , in the winter I can easily use several of them . So , I have all the motives in the world to love the winter . During the winter , it is possible to travel to those places where the snow falls . And the scenery becomes awesome ! When the winter arrives , and one is close to a loved person , there is a sensation of love in the air . In the winter , staying close to a loved person is simply amazing . I only appreciate the summer if I can walk along the beach . Then , if there 's no beach where I am , I hate the summer . On the other side , I prefer winter in all occasions . 
Most medical doctors want to work in cities where they will make a lot of money , yet in many rural areas , there are not enough doctors . I believe medical practice is based on humanitarian values ; and medicine is always on the front line in the fight against health catastrophes such as pandemics . However , doctors often want to work in cities where wages are higher than in rural areas , and the reason is that doctors may have spent several years studying medicine ; so they want to compensate the years wasted with financial profit from their work . Furthermore , nowadays , studying medicine is quite expensive , challenging and takes a long time ; so all of these factors contribute to why doctors want to earn a lot of money for compensation . In my opinion , this problem can be solved by strengthening the healthcare sector through enhancing the healthcare facilities in rural areas , and increasing the salaries for doctors who wish to practise medicine in rural areas . In addition , we can also encourage doctors to work in rural areas by promoting living conditions in rural areas where doctors can find a suitable environment to live and work so that they can feel satisfied . On the other side , in advanced countries , rural areas are well -equipped with hospitals and medical centres ; making little difference from big cities . However , in developing countries , rural areas have a very bad healthcare system compared to cities ; and that is what makes most doctors in developing countries prefer working in cities instead . Finally , strengthening the healthcare system and promoting the living conditions in rural areas can bring about a hope for many doctors to practise medicine in rural areas . 
