Hi Leyla , How was the party ? I am so sorry that I could not make it . It is becoming notorious that I have to be at my office instead of home . So please tell me what happened . I believe you had such a great time . Supposing I would like to compensate for it a little , would you go hiking next weekend ? Nothing terrible just some nearby peak , just to make the blood flow . 
I live at home with my family and I commute to school every day . I actually like this . You can learn while travelling , listen to music - it is quite relaxing , before or after the whole day . It 's just a 20 -minute long journey , so not too far . I like living with my family as there is always someone at home , and you are not alone for all the household stuff and you have time to study and so on . But I am also happy when nobody is at home as well . Then I can relax or study without being bothered . However , I am an adult and I can handle all my studies alone . But some students are not responsible and self -disciplined enough to look after themselves and their studies . Then it is definitely not convenient for them to live alone while studying . I think that those students tend to be more rebellious and less responsible with their studies . But it is not always possible for students to live at home while studying because they might not live close to their school and they would have to commute far away to their school . Then students should be very self -disciplined and keep touch with their parents to be controlled . I personally prefer living with my family , but I think I could handle living on my own as well . 
When I was in elementary school , I used to have music classes once a week . Honestly , I was not the most dedicated student in class nor the best one . It might say that I did not like this class , but even though it was not on my favorite class list , I 'm a pretty defensor defender of musical education in schools . Like physical education , musical education provides a complex group of skills that can be developed along the years , like keeping concentration , motor coordination and patience . Furthermore , this kind of class shows the students the cultural variety of rhythms around the word . Knowing this , the student can get to know about other subjects , such as history , geography and literature . When the students grow up , they become more independent and their social lives require contact . Music classes might help them to make a band with their friends or people who they have never met before . In addition , at difficult moments , like the end of high school , the capacity of playing an instrument can bed them and make that moment easier to go through . Thus , I only see pros when the subject is having music classes at school or not . Even not being a musician nowadays , I ca not live without music and I 'm grateful to my musical classes for showing me this adorable world . 
Hi Billal , How are you doing ? I could not write to you because I have been on a trip with some classmates . It was great but I had no time and no connection , so I was not able to correspond . We were in Germany . To be honest , I am not sure about the purpose of our trip . It seems to me that they had invited us just to show off . However , we were introduced to their newest pieces of technology , for which I am glad . 
I 'm a fan of animated action films , which is a combination of an animated film and action film . This kind of film is interesting and we can watch it at all ages . So , my favourite film is " Wreck It Ralph 2 . " It 's about a man called Ralph and a little girl named Vanellope , who travel in the world of the Internet . Both of them are game characters in an arcade . This film is very long , so I ca not tell you it all . This film is very interesting and meaningful . You should watch it , so you can imagine the Internet world and understand the meaning of friendships . 
Dear Sam , I ca not wait to see you tomorrow evening in my house . I hope you can be here at around 6 p.m . and bring with you a tennis racket for our session at the local tennis club . Just in case you do not know how to find my house - after you exit the train station , turn left and walk along the main street for about 5 minutes . My house is number 16 on the left with a big rose bush and blue doors . Best wishes , 
Hi Sam , You may come to my house after six p.m . I 'd appreciate it if you could bring your own drinks . My house is about ten minutes ' walk from the Maikore station . When you get out of the station , turn left , and go straight on for two blocks . Then you will find the building on your right . I 'm looking forward to seeing you tomorrow . 
My favourite season of the year is winter . I think it is quite obvious , if you live in a country that is hot as hell like mine , you will love the winter season . However , in this country , the winter that not as cold as I thought the winter should be , but it will be good to have some cold out there on the street . But I think the weather is hotter that before and I think maybe in 50 years , the temperature in the winter season of that year will be equal to the temperature in the summer of this year . I think all around the world the temperature is getting hotter . This is a serious situation . We all need to solve this problem quickly if we do not want to destroy our world . We need to reduce our temperature as fast as possible . I want to encourage all of you to reconsider when you do something that harms our world , such as establishing a company that exploits workers and does harm to our world . 
Hi , I would like to wish you happy birthday , too . And I think that we celebrate it in a more or less similar pattern but the part about singing is probably a little bit different . We do sing our birthday song at home , however , it is unusual to sing it in public . 
Hi Jack , My birthday in Vietnam is a bit similar to yours in your country . We also have a meal in a restaurant or sometimes we decorate our home , buy some food and have a party there . But it is a little bit different , we will sing " Happy Birthday " and eat the birthday cake first , then we have a meal . After the party , we play some fun games and then say goodbye before going home . Write soon ! 
Dear Sam , As we discussed on the phone last weekend , I am going to hold a small party at my home tomorrow evening , to which I have invited all of my close friends , including you . The party will start at 7:00 pm . You should come a bit earlier so that we can prepare everything together . In case you have forgotten , my apartment is on the thirteenth floor of the Sunview apartment block , which is located on Go Dua Street . You can get there by car . There is a large parking lot so you do not need to worry about parking . After you arrive , you should call me because I have a key to activate the elevator . I will pick you up on the ground floor . The elevator is next to the parking lot . Since we are having a BBQ party , you should bring a bottle of wine . That will be a perfect combination with my grilled pork ribs . Apart from that , you do not need to prepare anything as I will buy all of the ingredients . See you tomorrow . Best wishes , 
In my opinion , nobody has to be forced to do nothing they do not want to . It is very important for each person to develop their awareness of having a healthy life . Nowadays , it 's obvious that so many people are not afraid of their health . A considerable part of the people have acquired bad habits , which include fast food , processed foods , not going to the gym , low quantity of water ... and all this is enough to make people have a bad life quality . This is absolutely necessary : To put inside the head of each human being that it is very important to care about their body . Mental , psychological and physical health . I think that it will not be a recommendable thing to force all university students and school children to do sports activities 3 or more times per week . More than forcing them to act this way , it is important to show them how a good lifestyle can contribute to raising the level of productivity of everything in daily life . Not only the professional or school sides will get better . Maintaining good daily habits will improve several areas in the life of the people . When we put together good food , sports , inter relationships , smoking abstinence , alcohol consumption control and many other things we must do to have a pleasant life , it 's possible to live during much more time with good health . So , I think that it is not necessary ( and it is not pleasant , too ) to force somebody to do something that they do not want to . Life always show us that , on many occasions , when we try to apply some habits in people when they do not like them , the results are not too good . When time passes by , some of these people go back to old bad habits , and all the work will have been lost . It 's better to bring solid , good argumentation , which will make people re -think their habits , and so , they will be able to to change themselves in a voluntary way . 
They say music and mathematics are the languages of the universe . Everyone in the universe is supposed to understand the languages of mathematics and music . Despite them having the same root , they have some differences . Math is essentially reason , whereas music has poetry , inspiration and is art . We need poetry and beauty in our , sometimes , grey life . Music is essential for our leisure , concentration , for remembering good moments , for inspiration for work and to forget , for instance , some problems . It can recharge our energy with hope and inspiration to search for solutions for many problems . Music is important for our lives , for children , adolescents , adults and the elderly . Without music , it would be impossible to dance , to provide action and feelings in films . I think life would be impossible without music . Even primitive civilizations composed music to celebrate peace , victory , leisure time and to give gifts to God . 
Hi Rie , Thanks for inviting me , I 'll be there right on time . I 'd like to have some sushi , it is a traditional food in Japan and it is really delicious . Or we can have some pizza , it is a traditional food in Italy , and many people like it . Looking forward to that day . 
Although most people like the summer season when all the people can go to the southern French coast , for me , I prefer the winter season , when the weather is bad and you can fly to exotic countries where the temperature of the water is cool , with a beautiful sun . I like this season because it is quite calm in the foreign countries . I prefer working during the summer season in France when there are a lot of people to buy my products in the south of France . I think that it is a better solution for me , because I do not want to be on holidays surrounded by a lot of people and have a lot of traffic jams . For me , holidays must be in a quiet place where there are few people . For example , this year I will fly to Venezuela during the month of February . 
Dear town council , I am writing to express my disagreement with the current idea that is being thought to be implemented regarding the usage of mobile devices on public transport and more facilities . In the first place and above all , using electronic devices in the previously mentioned places does not affect anyone in a negative way . In fact , people that take public transport for work or education displacement often use it for helpful purposes or entertainment , which should be taken into consideration as well since some trips are long and dull . Furthermore , regarding shops and restaurants , people using electronic devices can be anything but harmful or disrespectful . For instance , people taking pictures of their meals or clothes could attract customers or advertise these places in some way , which in light of the shop and restaurant owners will not be seen as something needed to be banned . Last but not least , I would like to mention too that the attempt of preventing people from using theses devices , might only make the situation well worse due to the fact that people may rebel against it , new regulations and punishments would need to be implemented ... And if we balance the consequences , and knowing that it is not one of the pressing issues in our city , it 's efficiency may be sparse at best . I just desired to express my opinion and foremost help with the problem . Please do not hesitate to contact me if I can offer aid with anything . I hope it was relevant information . Yours sincerely . 
Some activities requested by schools to their students in order to graduate are very important because they introduce some values to students . And what 's more , depending where these students are studying , they would have a chance to interact with their community or do anything relevant to contribute with their cycle . However , the way that it is presented and requested to students is not the best way to do that . Broadly speaking , I guess schools that apply this philosophy to their education system should think in another approach to justify and motivate students to create and develop this feeling of responsibility to their community . Although it is considered a requirement in some schools , in other words , that activity is mandatory , there are other ways to teach these values ' importance . A great example of that are extra curricular activities where students immerse in aspects that are proposed to them . I could list some of them here . To begin with , students live with another family , for instance , in a farm or in a fishing area , and them help these families with their daily tasks . Second , students could spend some days helping in parks that are designated to preserve natural wildlife and forests . It is possible to enumerate lots of different activities , whereas it is not necessary , because the idea here is the same , it only shows that there are other possibilities to show students that volunteer in work matters , even when it is not a requirement . So , to wrap it all up , I strongly recommend students and people in general do volunteer work . As a result of that effort , we can experience a better environment . 
Hi , I am glad to hear from you . You are right I need to work on my English . I am going to continue in what I have been doing for now and I am going to add some new methods . So I am really passionate about reading books in English and I know that I am going to read as long as I can still see . Really important is listening to podcasts , too . However I would like to add something new . I am thinking about moving abroad for a while to get some real world practise to improve my speaking abilities . What you are going to do about maths and history ? 
Nowadays , video games are very popular among children . These games are very interesting . As a result , children are addicted to them . However , some parents believe that these games can have negative impacts on their children . On the other hand , other parents think that they may have some positive effects . As for me , I do not think they may have good effects . There are many reasons why I say this . If children play the games , they have to sit for the whole day , because these games are interesting . So , they do not want to stop anymore . It is not good for their eyes and their health . In addition , when they are playing games , they forget everything , like to eat , to drink and to sleep regularly . In the long run , there may be many bad things for them . Moreover , if they play games all the time , they do not want to do anything else , for example , help their parents , do their lessons regularly , communicate with other friends . Therefore , I agree that playing games can have a lot of negative impacts on children . 
Some people think that zoos are good places for people to learn about animals . On the other hand , other people think that animals should live according to their nature . So , it is not good to keep them in zoos . However , different people have different points of view . I do not want to judge exactly which one is right or wrong . However , to be honest , I think that it is better to keep animals in zoos . There are many reasons why I say this . In doing so , the animals do not need to worry about their meals , because people feed them regularly . Moreover , they can stay for their whole life without any danger . In addition , they do not need to worry about their health , because doctors come and take care of them very often . And then , the people who come to the zoo feed them too because they love them . Maybe some people will say it is not their nature and they should live freely in forests . It might be true , but it is not safe for them because of hunters . Thus , zoos are the best place for animals . 
There are many advantages of studying abroad . The students can learn new experiences , new cultures and can make a lot of friends from different countries . Moreover , it is exciting and challenging , because they keep in touch with different people . So , they can share their experience with their peers and they learn different things from them . In addition , they can improve communication skills by studying in foreign countries . And then , they are away from their parents , so they have to do everything by themselves . It helps to improve their skills . However , living in other countries might cost a lot in comparison with your native town . And they can have difficulties to communicate with the other people with different cultures . Another thing is that they may be homesick when they are away from their home . If they are ill , there is not anyone besides them . So they might be lonely . To sum up , there are both good points and bad points of studying in other countries . 
Sport is , with no doubt , essential to everyone , both to young and older people . Especially to students , doing a sports activity is very important because it allows them to distract themselves from the long hours of studying and to free their body from the accumulated stress . Students spend lots of time sitting in a class listening to teachers or sitting in their own rooms or libraries studying or writing . Therefore , they need to move , not only in order to stay fit but also to recharge themselves and gain the necessary energy to face the day . Many high -school and university students may think that training makes them lose time they could use to study or to relax , by hanging out with friends or watching television . Anyway , watching a TV series , for example , does not help them to disconnect their mind and recharge their energy , it simply gives them the impression of relaxing , which is important but not as beneficial as training . Regarding younger students , such as those who attend primary or middle school , I think parents should make them understand the importance of sport , but without imposing on them something they like . Every child should be free to choose the sport he or she most likes and feels comfortable with . Going to the gym , attending fitness courses , doing a team or an individual sport , instead , helps them to stay fit while having fun and in many cases also making friends . Despite the temporary fatigue , both the body and the mind will benefit from that . They will sleep better , they will study better , they will have , in short , the necessary energy to face a normal weekday . For this reason , many schools and universities are thinking of forcing students to do sports activities . Even though it might seem too much , I think it is the right choice . Students , however , have to be free to choose the kind of activity that most suits them in order not to feel discomfort . 
Really , music is not important in our lives . In the first place , just to take this more seriously , we do not need music to eat , to think , to drive to our jobs , but all the daily chores would be more pleasant with that . Moreover , music can change our perception of time and it builds the connections that we have made in the past . For example , have you ever had a random thought with some music and suddenly you remember a situation very clearly ? If the answer for that question is yes , you must thank the music . On top of that , music can change our feelings . Recently , research discovered that music can affect behavior and society . This explanation is given due to harmony , because anyone could sense that harmony and understand that in different ways , being able to turn more aggressive or calmer , it depends on the person . 
This is the start of a new school year . Therefore , I have decided to do my best in all the subjects . I had to learn three subjects last semester . They are Maths , Science and English . I think that I am good at Maths and Science . So , I appreciate that . However , I am weak in English , although I try hard . Thus , I want to improve in this subject . Moreover , I have a lot of difficulties when I learn it , because it is not my mother tongue . So , I decided to take an online class to improve my skills . And I hope that the online instructor will give me the best and most appropriate advice . Besides that , I will ask for feedback from my teachers and I will take some suggestions from my peers . In doing so , I think that I will be better than before and it will help me to improve my English . 
In my country there are just two seasons , summer and winter , and my favorite season is summer , because the weather is so hot and you can go anywhere without being concerned by the rain . The other reason is because I like to go to the beach and enjoy the sunny days . When it is winter in my country , the people must use their umbrella and it is a little uncomfortable to go anywhere with this kind of thing . Another thing that I do not like about winter is that you can feel the days are boring and sad , because the clouds are grey and you can feel a little depressed . We just have two seasons , but I would like to have the experience of knowing what spring is like . I would like to see how the trees change color and how the trees lose their leaves . Another thing that I would like to see is the snow and I would like to do some sports , like snowboarding or another kind of sport . Maybe I can go to another country and have this experience , I believe that it could be really great . In this moment , my favorite season is summer , since it is all that I know . 
Hi Matt ! I have been improving my English by watching You Tube videos , writing and reading English texts . I hope , with this method , that I can improve my English and become an English speaker in the near future . Since a few weeks ago my English understanding has been growing , so now I can write more complex texts and now I want to apply for a customer service position . 
My favorite film is about two lovers who had to find a way to stay together against the adversities of the world and how , in the end , they find a way to stay together and be happy for the rest of their lives . That movie made me cry like a child , and it had a lot of feelings . I think you will enjoy this movie because it tries about a similar story . 
In my spare time , I often practice my English and try to improve my skill in the hope of finding a good job . When I practice my English , I always try to practice my pronunciation , my grammar and listening skills . I am doing it right now , writing this answer to you . 
It is not about the exercise in itself , but about the results . I exercise every single day and the results are , at least for fifty percent of the time , psychological ; it is about staying on my path . I prefer to exercise as soon as possible , so on Sundays I work out right away in the morning and during weekdays I exercise at work or right after it . I do not need fancy gyms . Most of the time I exercise at my place with a bare minimum of equipment . I usually work out outdoors , even during winter . I do anything that I assume is a demanding workout . 
I went on a holiday last summer . I went there by coach . I went there with my friends . We went to Myintkyina , which is situated in Kachin State . I 'd never been there before . So , I was really excited . We visited Mayka -Malika , which was pleasant and beautiful . The scenery was breathtaking . In addition , we visited Zalon Pagoda , which is very famous . And then we saw pine trees , vineyards and ice mountains along the way . These were very pleasant . In the evening , we went to the night market to try local dishes . The food was very delicious . I took a lot of photos with my friends . I think that this place was really amazing to visit and it was one of the best places . Moreover , the weather was really cool . I appreciated it . Therefore , I will never forget this place . I had a great time too . It was the best holiday I have ever had . 
Using mobiles phones is very important in our day -to -day life , and we use them very often to communicate with our family , friends and co -workers at work . I cannot imagine if people can give up using mobile phones one day , because every aspect of our lives has become connected to the use of phones . In spite of that , phone calls on public transport and in shops and restaurants can be very disturbing to the people around us , especially in these places , people need some quietness . I guess banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants may not be the solution and it could be quite a strict decision if the town council plans to enforce it ; because simply people find it hard to comply with such laws . What I claim to be the solution is to raise awareness about how much disturbance and harm could be caused if we use mobile phones on public transport , shops and restaurants . Awareness programmes could include attention sign board and maybe even TV programs or videos on the internet to educate people about the proper way to use phone calls in public . People sometimes have to make phone calls to ask for help or opinions over what to buy in shops or what to eat in a restaurant . Finally , the technology in phones has made life easier , more than ever before , through instant communication with our beloved ones , so it is very difficult to ban using them in public places , but we can always encourage people to keep quite when using phones in public places . 
Since it was created , music has became an indispensable part of our daily lives . People sing when they are happy , exhausted or even when they are being hurt by someone . We listen to music when we feel lonely or want to have a new idea for a project . Music is being used as a way to convey our emotions , it boosts our confidence , removes tension , brings everyone closer and removes the gaps between people . A long time ago , it appeared in some tribes to enjoy the harvest time , celebrate special occasions and make chances for youngsters to make friends with each other and now it represents a custom of a country . Furthermore , music makes me concentrate more on my work and releases stress , as well as anxiety , when you have to face a difficulty in your life . It is unimaginable what the earth would be like without music . Humans would suffer from mental illness , reduced efficiency to create or make innovations , the world would become monotonous without melodies , people might be less sympathetic and hate to communicate . So we need to protect and develop music . 
Exercise is important for our health , of course . Without doing exercise , we ca not be healthy . Therefore , we should make time , at least 5 or 6 hours a week . There are many advantages of doing exercise . It keeps our body fit and healthy . Moreover , it is good for the circulation system . So , people should do exercise regularly , because there are many good things , as I mentioned . If we are unhealthy , our life will not be valuable . For example , we ca not do things such as work , ca not give time for the family and we will be unhappy too . However , if we are healthy , we can do everything that we wish . So , health is very important for all . And we should take care of ourselves . I think that there is nothing more important than health . To sum up , people should do exercise daily , even though they are busy , because it is very important . 
Although people like to talk with their co -workers , I prefer working in a room alone . I find working in a cubicle convenient because you do not have the noise of your neighbour that distracts you when you need to reflect or you are on the phone with a customer . Also you can manage your privacy when you must phone for a private subject . Today , there are a lot of open spaces to be able to manage easily your employees . That is between the management and the control of your employees . There are already problems between managers and employees because of this type of work organization . More and more employees ask to have a private area to be able to phone for a private subject , but also to manage a small meeting on a web conference or with co -workers . That is also important for the quality of life and the need to concentrate on your work . Teleworking shows the necessity to have a dedicated place to work at home and at the office . Today , with digital work , control of the work is easier and do not need to be in the same area . All of these reasons are in favor of the privacy of each co -worker and , when it is possible , having each their own office . 
In my free time , I play video games , read a book , the name of which is ' Your Parachute Color ' , and watch TV . The thing I like doing most is playing video games on Friday . It is important to me . In this time I forget about all the things . I go inside the game . The time goes so fast . On weekends I have a lot of time to do other things , but I ca not do that thing . 
I ca not deny that I use a computer quite often , however , the only thing I need on it is a browser . I prefer to use the browser on a computer rather than on my phone . The most enjoyable activities for me are listening to music and sometimes watching something funny to let some steam off some preassure . I used to play a lot until I was fifteen . Back then something happened and I have not played games ever since . 
Travel will be more and more different in the future , because technology is developing with time . It helps people to save time too . Technology impacts on our daily life , including travelling . Long long ago , people used to cycle , ride carts and so on when they were travelling . Therefore , they had to take time when they travelled from one place to another . In the Middle Ages , people used cars , buses and bikes when they travelled . Nowadays , there are many choices to travel , such as subways , planes and public transportation . So , it is easy and saves time too . Maybe there will be more development in the future . I do not know exactly how it will improve quickly . But I think it will be better than today . Moreover , I think that using public transportation will be the same as usual , because most people ca not afford to buy their own . So , they will still use it . 
In my opinion , music is one of the most important things in our lives . Music can connect people . We see its power in history , for example in the First World War , when the enemy soldiers had a short time of peace during Christmas Eve . Generally , music can be used for treatment and as an assistance with psychical problems , etc . Music is able to change our mood . It can bring joy to our lives . I think that without music , our lives would be sad , dark and without hope . Music can help us to discover or find our limits . The limits are in our mind , but it can help us to overcome our physical limits . Music is a very important part of our lives , because it is the way we can show our feelings , sadness and last but not least , our joy . We have to support our children to express their feelings through music . 
Hello Sam ! I am so glad to see you again and I hope you are too . You can come to my house when you want , my parents come home at 11 pm and my sister is out of town , so , there is no problem if you want to come early . You must bring some clothes and video games . Do not worry about the food , in my house there is . See you tomorrow and have a nice trip . Call me if you want . 
Hi Sam , I am excited about your visit , we will spend a great evening together . I am going to be home at six minutes past five . Could you come one hour later please ? Could you bring your computer ? I have prepared an exciting virtual game . My home is near Lane Street , just walk five minutes from the bus station , it is number thirty two . See you soon . 
Most of the time I listen to music while driving a car . I turn the radio on any time I am in the car . When I listen to pop songs , I feel like information is updated . I did not listen to music for a while when I was occupied with life things , especially buying a home or preparing taxes . I caught up with collecting information from the internet . I could not afford to listen to music . Even though I was listening to music all the time , it was as if I did not recognize my colleague who talked to me when I worked for the game developer . This was totally opposite before . At that time I was toasted , stressed , wanted to forget everything , I wanted to fill my brain with music . Come to think of it , I had pretty much afford to listen to music when I was young . 
If someone could choose and plan their life , I think many would . Choosing between a short intense or a long relaxed life would be a hard decision . Living a short but intense life would be a good choice for many people because you could do activities like sky diving or climbing the Mouth Everest . You would not experience getting old or probably sick , which often happens when people get old . Nevertheless , living a long life would mean you have a lot of time . You can plan your life just like your upcoming years and what you want to achieve . Personally , I would live a long relaxed life . I would like to spend a lot of my time with my family , finding the love of my life and spending many years with them would be my life time goal . I would want to study , find a good place to work and build my own house , which often takes a lot of time . I would want to watch my children grow up and see them find love , struggle with life and develop a career if they want to . I would love to meet my grandchildren and see how they cope with life . I am a very calm person and I like to chill on the couch watching a good film . If I had the chance , I would do this my whole long life . 
I think music is important in our lives , because we can relax with it . I think music moves a frequency of our mind and that helps us to relax or be good in our day . There are a variety of sounds or types of music . For example , there is classical music . This music is very beautiful , because it uses different instruments and with it we feel very relaxed and we can focus on our work . There is also rock and heavy rock . This type of music uses different rhythms and scientists have said that rock music can help us to be in a good mood . However , if there was not any music , maybe we 'd be frustrated and maybe I could not be good with other people . I think music has always existed , since our ancestors . They did music to give thanks to their gods , besides , they danced because they were happy . So music has always been very important throughout history . 
Volunteer work is the base of our society . It 's part of the human attitude to be able to help other people . For this reason , it is very important to teach students to improve their ability to help somebody by becoming a volunteer worker . That is so important for young people because , in general , they do not pay attention to one another . They are young and often self -centered . That project helps students to meet people without interest and they must take time to listen to people who have perhaps another vision or character . They learn how to negotiate and also to talk with the people around them . This exercise is essential to practice soft skills . This skill is the most important part in your work . At their future work , they must have the ability to interact with other people without aggressiveness . You must try to understand the people in front of you . In this case , you will be able to build together a project for their future company . Volunteer work is essential for a student . 
Music is very important when we are sad or when we have had some troubles , because our favorite music can change our state of mind . A second could be at parties , because music can make you dance with your friends , or we can enjoy more placeful the time . The third option is that music can transmit feelings to other people and because the beautiful sounds are international and we can communicate the others through them Music is very important for everyone , because we can influence our lives , when we are happy , or when we have broken up with our lover . l usually listen music when I have a lot of work , or when I have had some big trouble , I relax listening to music . I have listened to music while I work or when I want to be happy , even if I have had trouble with my wife and I sometimes like to learn about some themes , because I know there are many types of music . Some were very famous and beautiful and others have been horrible . 
MUSIC : ONE OF THE MOST EXCITING THINGS IN LIFE If you have ever thought that we do not need music in our lives , I cannot help but say that you are absolutely wrong . For better or worse , we all need some artistic means of expression to let our feelings go , and music is one of the most powerful ones , without doubt whatsoever . Unbelievable though it may seem , music is something extremely pivotal for me . I would even assure you that I could not feel free without it , as I am a singer and through music , I manage to express my feelings . Had it not been for the fact that I became a mother very early , I would have dedicated my entire career to music . Nowadays it is just a job that I do from time to time , but not a full -time job , as I wanted it to be . I would also like to mention some other benefits music has , especially concerning mental health . Somehow , music connects with some parts of our brain , making us experiment with sensations . Maybe it is that connecting power that makes music be used as a mental therapy as well . In a nutshell , artistic expressions are significant and pivotal for us as individuals , as they play an extremely significant role in our existence . 
The main reason behind is capitalism . People often want to work in places where they earn more money to support a better standard of life . This is what the economists name as externalities and is one of the reason for the justification of government intervention . To solve the problem , the government could provide an incentive for working in these areas . A better salary or social benefits could be a good response . This could bring more doctors to rural areas and maybe make a call effect . Developing good services and cultural life in rural areas may be a good idea as well . Sometimes , doctors do not want to live far from the city because they do not find big opportunities for developing a professional career or maybe it is difficult to find great work -life balance . There is no magic response but the key could be in the incentives . After all , people 's responses are conditioned by their interest . 
