Before answering this question , we have to look at the reason why university students and schoolchildren do not do sports anymore . There are two main reasons , either they do not have time for sports or are too lazy . However , the difference in the conditions of countries can be an influencing factor too because children have different school times in different countries . In some countries , like China , Chinese students have no time and energy for sports . They live under huge learning pressure that learning hours and homework time already take most of their time . According to analyses , the average sleeping time for Chinese students is 6 hours , which means they wo not be able to have any free time for sports . If the government insists on asking school children to do sports at least 3 times per week , it will bring nothing but pain and stress to students . But school children in the western world have plenty of free time after school . At this point , I would suggest the government set up some PE lessons , so kids can do sports at school . I personally think that all university students should at least do some sports 1 or 2 times per week . Because they are already adults , which means they could manage the time between studying and workouts . And in the adult world , I believe that a muscular body can enhance your sex appeal and makes you look more attractive , regardless of gender . Nevertheless , although doing sports cannot only build a prettier body figure , it can also lead people to a healthy life . But it does not mean students should be forced to do something ; doing sports should be spontaneous . Because if the government forces students to do sports , then they probably wo not enjoy it , on the contrary , they might start hating it . In conclusion , although doing sports is brilliant , it ca not be forced . 
