The moment young people have to choose a university , they balance their qualities and skills with what they would like most to work as . To my mind , it depends on the type of person students are what influences most of their decision regarding whether to live on their own or with their family . It is a well -known fact that moving away requires a broad sense of independence . Young people who live alone must single -handedly manage their finances and learn how to better plan their schedule in order for them to cope with every day challenges . Moreover , they need to cook and do the laundry individually without the help of a relative . On the other hand , deciding to remain at home during their college years has its benefits . Students can be supported by their families , who help young people with the house chores while they have more time socialise and a higher level of energy to put into their studies . What is more , it is less likely for students who live with their relatives to get homesick . All things considered , young people have to make an important decision when choosing where to continue their studies , thus they need every bit of support they can get from their loved ones . 
Talking about university is complex , since your future gets an important place . You become an adult and , as a result , more independent . I met some people who , despite the distance , study in other places of Spain , like Madrid or Barcelona . As a consequence , they have to live alone or in student communities . However , they are overjoyed with that lifestyle . I agree that living without parents prepares for the future life , if you want to get married or if you want to have children , but it 's true that you have to have in your wallet , at least , a considerable amount of money . Moreover , the student must be a mature person , therefore he has other responsibilities besides getting a superb degree . Looking at the other option , although it is great to have a bed , food and water completely free , and so on , you do not miss your family . I think independence is a crucial part of people 's lives , so the sooner you leave home , the earlier you get independence and responsibilities . Anyway , I would choose the first option because , in spite of the amount of money , you can always get a temporary job to earn money . 
Music is an immaterial element part of human culture and society . Living with songs at different moments , for example , in school class or at home , helps improve emotional intelligence and social skills , beyond that mathematics ability and concentration . However , for some families , there is not this acknowledgement , than music active or learning play an instrument is essential to the whole formation of a person . Based on scientific indication , music contributes to the development of a lot of important skill in children and young people . Learning a musical instrument or taking class is a strong tool to achieve concentration and better results in math tasks , for example . The music classes present in every school can try to deliver the basic foundations of education and help those who are interested to shine . The learning process sometimes focuses on " scientific subjects . " This sidelines things related to culture . In this way , music is only seen as fun , and the science behind music is ignored . Because of this , some families do not care about music classes and some schools do not have this kind of class available . Instead they study science and develop other skills . Music is more or less important for some parents or curricular projects of schools , what a lot of people agree on is that music is an interesting art for everyone to learn to develop more completely . Then , music classes must be present in every basic school although some school or families do not worry about this discipline . 
