In general , it is not a good solution to ban something or the behaviour of people by using legal rules . I prefer convincing people of the right behaviour . In this case , the town council would like to ban mobile phones on public transport , shops and restaurants . The difficulty of this rule is for it to be applied and controlled . The town council must create a police squad to check if the rule is effectively applied ! This squad will be a source of tension between citizens and owners of restaurants . That will also cause stress between citizens . They will provoke fighting between us where the police squad will be obliged to intervene . All this situation risks degenerating ! It will be better for the town council to promote a preventive action . Each citizen will be an actor of this change . It will be an occasion to promote new values of conviviality in public areas . The town council will also promote places where you will use your phone . For example , telephone booths where nobody will be disturbed . In fact , this is a problem of education and well -being . The town council must introduce in a college class information about a good attitude in the area with your phone or other technology . The goal of these classes will be to learn how to live with other public in a public area . This policy will be useful for other areas of living well together . 
When the magazine contacted to me to write an article about music , suddenly I thought of all the positive things that it has . Under no circumstances can we live without music . Listening to music has different relationships . For example , there is a special link between music and mood . In this way , we listen to sad music when we get sad or the opposite , happy music when we feel over the moon . Needless to say , there is also angry music , such as a Beethoven symphony that we listen to when we get angry . I would add how important music is in our lives . All of us have different styles of music , depending on the stages of life . Have you ever found changes in your music ? I 'm sure that the music that you used to listen to when you were young is very different to now . In conclusion , I think that we have different genres of music in every moment in our life . 
