I consider that learning a foreign luggage is quite important these days . Actually , we are living in a multicultural society , that is to say , a society in which different people from distinct countries live together . When people have to change their usual home and have to emigrate to other countries for work , personal problems , or war conflict , it 's important to know a foreign language . The knowledge of another language opens our minds , we are more tolerant and we learn to appreciate our own mother tongue . Learning a new language is an opportunity to communicate with other people in order to establish different kinds of relationships . Nowadays , we have many options to learn a new language and we have to do it . Technology and the use of social media is an excellent way to start . Also , listening to the radio , watching TV and reading in the language which you are learning . 
Rising levels of obesity have been labeled one of , if not the most , severe public health crises of today . Other illnesses caused by an inactive lifestyle are on the rise as well , although they do not reach the same levels of publicity . To combat these emergent problems , we should put renewed effort into the physical education of our children , instigating mandatory physical exercise as a promising approach in this regard . However , forcing such measures on adults is a different story entirely . It is without question that children need to be taught about the benefits of an active lifestyle . The health problems we as a society are facing are a direct result of neglecting this kind of education and failing to prepare becoming adults because of the challenges of increasingly sedentary jobs . Likewise , it is apparent that such a programme must not be based on pure theory . School children need to experience the benefits of physical exercise first hand , which means they have to do sports activities on a regular basis . To achieve this , schools should expand PE classes and complement them with other measures such as mandatory participation in a sports club , compelling students to do sports at least 3 times a week . On the contrary , all adults - including university students - should be regarded as self -determined members of our society and have the right to refuse any physical exercise if they so desire . To encourage an active lifestyle among these groups incentives can be employed . As an example , insurance companies may adapt policy rates to benefit those who regularly exercise and universities could reward participation in college sports . In essence , our primary resources to tackle public health crises will always remain the education of our children . We should make it a goal to have them leave school fit for the challenges of modern work environments . We may extend incentives for physical activity to adult life but should refrain from compulsory measures . 
I am a doctor , I work in a rural hospital , and I 'm tired because I have a lot of work , the medical service is scarce here . There is only a small hospital for all the people of the town . There are two doctors and seven nurses . It is really impossible to attend many people . In fact , some patients need special medical treatments such as surgery , but we do not give them . The main reasons for this issue is that the place is not near the city , and many doctors do not want to change their home , and leave their families . , life is not easy here because there are not places for fun , such as parks , museums , supermarkets etc . On another hand , the afternoons are very beautiful , you can breathe clean air , and look at the mountains . I think that the solution is complicated , but maybe , the doctors could be to visit our hospital for some weeks , and to know the town , the nice and friendly people . I 'm not sure that they would like your place of residence . But they will have a great experience . 
Could you imagine a world without music ? It is a fact that music is a really important part of our lives . Music is with you at many different moments . For instance , when you are studying , doing exercise , having a shower , cooking , etc . Furthermore , it is present in movies , on the radio , on TV , the Internet ... In short , we listen to music at all times . Music is a form of expression as well as a way to feel different emotions . I strongly believe that all the problems are like a piece of cake if you face it with music . In my case , when I am sad and depressed or , on the other hand , when I am happy , excited and cheerful about something , I always listen to music . Music always helps you in all situations . This is the reason why I think that music is so important and as necessary as other subjects at school , such maths or science . In my opinion , all students should have the opportunity to study music when they are at school . Music lessons may be a creative way which allow the students to express their emotions . Furthermore , a way to learn about music history as well as instruments . We need to raise awareness about the importance of art and music subjects in schools . Due to this , it is really necessary that our governments make laws in order to implement these subjects . I hope , in the future , music will be as important as learning maths . 
A rural area can be a big problem because it does not give us enough comfort to work or live there . Mainly if you grew up in a big city where this place offers many benefits such as electricity , watering water , you can buy anything either in shops or e -commerce with no problem to find a shop close to you . Besides having a great control of wild animals . Firstly , the electricity suppliers should spread the electricity and offer enough comfort to live on a hot day or not . Secondly , the spread of the shops around a area rural is important to increase access the goods and services . I do not want to mean they must create too many shops in order to remove the view pf the rural area . But , offering specific point shops along the way . And last but not least , urge the people to use the medical service in order to increase the amount of patients to be attended . People who live in rural area tend not to use this service for lack of information . 
