I believe that all students should learn about music and , I 'm not saying this because I 'm a musician and play the saxophone . I believe that learning to play an instrument , to read a score , has a huge benefit . First of all , music can develop a child 's talent , how do you know if you are good or bad at something if you do not try ? Also , studies indicate that playing an instrument is correlated with academic success because music is another language . At the same time , music is fun , enjoyable , relieves stress in children , and teaches little ones to concentrate , great benefits to consider . Another reason I wanted to point out , which personally surprised me a lot , is that music helps to understand mathematics . Although they may seem different , music and mathematics have a lot in common . Aspects such as rhythm , proportions and fractions appear in the scores . To learn music , one must understand mathematics . Finally , music and self -expression go hand in hand . We do not go to school just to learn traditional tasks , we also go to school to know ourselves , to know how far we can go , what our limits are , and music can serve to achieve that important kind of knowledge . 
Nowadays , we are living in an era in which technology is developing very rapidly . Video games are very popular , especially among children . However , they clearly have an impact on their lives , both positive and sometimes negative . 
What kind of life would you like to live ? The answer to this question depend on the personal goal of each people . There is no great or bad choice , there is just a personal choice . Another difficulty is life cannot be excepted and , for this reason , there are alternately periods of quiet and intense time . For this reason , it is very difficult to describe a quiet or intense life because that wo not be possible . But if I must make a theoretical choice , I would prefer a long calm life until 100 years old . Because I like to be quiet and have time to reflect on myself and the best situation to think about yourself is to be in a calm and safe area . It is also possible to set a different rhythm for your life : learn how to meditate and take care of your body . This is a choice of well -being . This lifestyle will give you a strong character and capacity to think thoughts . For me , I will be a more balanced person because I like a quiet environment without excitation surrounding you . With this lifestyle , we will live a very long time and I could see all the new technologies and innovations . I will see also many generations of people and I will be very quiet because I will have a vision of life with my experience . 
I think it is a positive requirement . Schools should teach not only traditional homework , but also educate and show students other realities . Volunteering has many benefits and if a sixteen or seventeen -year -old student has the opportunity to do it , I think it is a great privilege that we cannot let pass . Volunteering not only looks good on your curriculum , but it is an activity that can give you a sense of purpose because you become part of something bigger that yourself , and that is an important lesson to learn in school . In addition , volunteering gives you a sense of community , helps you feel connected to the place where you live , and also makes you see that similar and different people can be friends and connect in the same community . In short , doing volunteer work will only bring benefits to the students and having all those benefits at such a young age is great . 
A few days ago , I heard that the town council is thinking of banning the use of mobile phones in public transport , stores and restaurants , and I believe this ban could be a big mistake . Cell phones are part of our lives . Many use them to chat with friends , relatives , or even a co -workers on their way to work . You can also use your phone to , for example , read the news , just as many phones have apps to read books on them . Banning phones on public transport just makes no sense . In addition , you can also pay with your phones nowadays for whatever you want to buy , experts say it is safer to pay with your phone than with your card or cash , so why ban phones in stores if they are necessary ? Also , in restaurants , you can pay with your phone , but also you can view a restaurant menu using a QR code , which is safer because of the pandemic and possible infections . We cannot go back in time where people communicated differently , those times are long gone . We live in this age where mobile phones are not just for making a call , we have so many things on them , we can do so many things with them that a ban will only cause great dissatisfaction in people . I encourage the town council to focus on the real issues that affect the citizens and discard any ban on mobile phones . 
