Dear legislators , Recently , I have heard some news that you are going to pass a law for which people ca not use phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants for safety reasons because the government hopes people can care more about their environment they stay . Besides , the government also wants to enhance the interaction with others among civilians so that it can make the town become a more harmonious and warm town . Well , as long as I know the detail of this act , I have some suggestions for you , which are on behalf of us , to make an appropriate balance point between safety and the practical side in the future . First , I agree with the purpose of banning people from using phones on public transport for safety reasons . While I 'm opposed to putting this act into practice in places such as restaurants or shops because the probability of security problems like killing , robbing , rowdiness are far less than that on public transport . For example , if someone got robbed or hurt on public transport because everyone was phubbing , no one noticed that someone got hurt , then it may cause more casualties in transportation . Contrarily , in the restaurants or shops , it 's obvious that anyone but robbers will try to help victims suppress the bad guy because barely each person will look around the environment such as stores and goods , even if some people are still looking at their phones . Thus , the security may be safer in a shop and restaurants than on public transport , which is not to the extent for the government to mandate not using phones . Second , I 'm averse to banning phones in restaurants and shops just merely because the government hopes that civilians can have more face -to -face interactions so that everyone will not be indifferent to each other , even strangers , so that the measures can increase the reputation of hospitality among states . Nowadays , phones have become a medium to communicate , show concerns and express opinions . People will be connected closely than ever , and still most people will have interactions if necessary . Therefore , the government is overthinking . 
