In my opinion , always telling the truth is not the proper way to get along with others on any occasion , as we are usually taught to be honest about everything when we were children . Sometimes , we need to tell some sweet lies to achieve a future positive result or harmonious atmosphere rather than become embarrassed and have tense ramifications . Firstly , sometimes if we are too honest , we may have some straight words for others , especially for some who are sensitive to others ' words or inclined to be negative , then we will have worse consequences in both our social and personal life . For example , if someone is a little obses than before when you met last time , we could not tell the truth to him / her , contrarily , we should decorate our words to be more euphemistic lest he / she feel that their esteem is being hurt . Second , to have a positive consequence , there are some situations in life which are not appropriate to tell more details to others in case they will lose hope or even be killed . For instance , if we were doctors and facing a patient who has got a worsening status and may pass away soon , we have to inform their parents that there still is hope to cure only if they can abide by the directions , the purpose is giving some hope to patients and their family so that they will not feel like falling into the abyss of disparity . In conclusion , although not telling a lie is a virtue , we need to learn when should we decorate and pack our words in a little polite way and that will not hurt someone 's heart stikingly . Therefore , telling a lie can be accepted in some situations . 
