I usually go to sleep early and I try to relax two hours before that . The first , and maybe most important thing , is to disconnect the electronic gadgets such as the phone or computer . I make an infusion whereas I read or write something . Also I like to plan my next day to be able to have peace of mind during the night . When the time to go to bed arrives , I turn off every light and sleep in total darkness . Also I am very sensitive to sounds , therefore I sleep with ear plugs . 
Many people consider telling the truth to be always beneficial instead of telling lies . However , telling a lie sometimes is acceptable if the lie is not harmful to anyone . For example , telling a kid that Santa Claus exists to let them improve their imagination or keep the spirit and innocence in them . The first thing to consider is that people always lie for different reasons . Some lies have sincere intentions of not harming anyone , and some others are the opposite of this . Nevertheless , white lies are unavoidable many times to maintain order . For instance , telling someone , you fell asleep , and that is the reason for arriving late to a meeting is a lie to avoid memos or penalties . Hence that is why the difference between white lies and harmful lies is the key when people say the truth or a lie . Along with telling a lie when is required , it is acceptable to tell a lie . It is my view , truth is always important on account of the fact that people need to know what is happening around them . Whereas , it is also acceptable to tell a lie when the situation requires . In conclusion , a lie is not an act of evil if the purpose of the lie is to avoid harm or damage . Therefore , a lie is fair if the purpose of the lie is to protect people from the truth . We cannot discredit the importance of people knowing and grasping important facts and situations in their lives through the truth . 
Dear Sam , Hope you are in radiant health . Let me tell you that I am glad to have you as a friend , because you can understand my feelings and emotions well . Today , I would like to share about my favourite Hollywood film , called ' Eat , Pray and Love ' starring Julia Roberts . I first saw this movie during my adolescence , and since then it has been one of my most -liked films . Firstly , it sends a very strong message , which is to love yourself . Since we all are struggling in our lives , it is imperative for us to love and nurture ourselves regularly . Secondly , the last part of the film was shot in Bali , which according to me , is one of the most beautiful places on this planet . In my view , you should also watch this film , as we both have similar preferences . Moreover , the film provides a better understanding of several countries , such as India , Bali and Italy , along with their cultures . Hope you will like the movie and please share your feedback after watching it . Hope to hear from you soon . Best regards , Peter 
Nowadays , adolescents and young people tend to be more sedentary than in the past . Health science has proved that an inactive lifestyle can have various bad effects on both mental and physical health . For this reason , many governments suggest families to let their children move as much as they can , for example , by introducing it to different kinds of sports . Sports projects are usually joined by schools and universities to introduce young people to new activities , hoping they 'll like them and maybe start doing them on a regular basis . Personally , I think these programs should be implemented in order to keep students moving . First of all , doing some exercise three times a week is the best way to move your body especially if your main everyday activity involves sitting for many hours over your books . As a matter of fact , students who do not do sports tend to get more distracted , develop bad postures and are usually more isolated than others . Second of all , forcing students to do sports could be helpful for those who struggle making friends . In fact , many lifelong friendships are usually born during adolescence or college years thanks to sports . Especially in team sports , people tend to create a bond with other players pretty easily . On the other hand , there are also students who struggle with the idea of moving their bodies . Sometimes , overweight people are ashamed of their bodies and their difficulties when it comes to move around . For this reason , I would recommend universities and schools to pay attention to the necessities of each student before forcing them to do sports . Perhaps they could include some psychological help for young people who feel this is a bad thing for them . All in all , I would say that these programs could be very useful and effective only if carefully applied considering all the factors and different aptitudes . 
Nowadays , we have so many opportunities to learn something new about jobs . There are different ways in which we could practice , the one I am talking about is the chance for students to be volunteers . I personally admire this method . There are many reasons behind the fact that this is a good move in teenagers ' lives . One of them is to be capable of earning money while you are studying . By doing this , you can decide to save your money to pay for your future studies in university or wherever you decide to go and do . In addition , it is useful because you learn something about a new job and acquire skills you would have never imagine having , but above all , you help society by doing little things . In my opinion , this type of volunteering in high school should be spread to other countries , because it can also help students with school difficulties to graduate by simply doing something different that can balance their school grades . I am speaking about this because I have seen a lot of movies in which this method is often used and I would have liked to try it when I was a schoolchild . In conclusion , this is a good move because with one job , the opportunity to graduate , help people and earn money are given to the students . 
