I live in Brazil and living with your family while you study is completely normal . Mainly if you do not have much money to live on your own . However , there are some outstanding points here . But I need you to remember that the best way is living according to your reality . The best or the worst way to love do not exist . When it comes to living on your own , we can point out some good points like building up your survival . I know it 's strange , but you learn how to choose according to your money , if you do not have a lot , you learn how to solve problems when there 's nobody close to you to help you to solve them . Unhappily , you 'll notice that you wo not have much time to spend with your friends because you 'll dedicate that time to other things like doing the shopping , cleaning up your house at the weekend , besides you 'll have to prepare your food . When you live with your family , you 'll realize that you 'll have more time to spend with your family because your parents will clean up your house and prepare your food . Another main strength is that you wo not have lots of expenses like bills . However , you wo not have lots of privacy as your family will need your help to fix something , do the dishes and other tasks home . 
I prefer sleeping in a dark and quiet room . This ambient is appropriate for deep sleep . When people sleep , there are hormones secreted from the body during sleep . If people have a good quality of sleep , the hormones are able to be more effective . When I feel tired , I like to sleep in a proper room . This will make me feel fresh in the morning . On the other hand , sleeping in a small , light and noisy room can cause adverse consequences , for example , stress , cardiovascular disease and anxiety . Although some think that they do not mind sleeping in this environment , in my opinion , they should change their sleeping habits . 
