In the contemporary era , pupils , particularly undergraduates , and students studying in schools are seen consuming fast food on a regular basis , and following an unenergetic style of living , which leads to several detrimental effects on their well -being and fitness levels . The essay intends to describe how health and wellness can be maintained by adopting a healthy and active routine . Moreover , it emphasizes the role of exercise and physical activities in improving the quality of life , hence , I concur with the idea that youngsters should be urged to perform physical exercise at least three times in a week . As students are the future of our country , therefore , not only should they look after their physical health , but they should also maintain their mental health . Furthermore , playing outdoor games , such as cricket , and tennis , or performing physical exercise namely yoga , aerobics , and running , can help the youth to overcome several health -related problems . To begin with , it helps children to be active and energetic throughout the day . As a result , they do not feel lethargic while studying and they perform their daily tasks with enthusiasm and energy . To illustrate , as I started to exercise in my childhood , it helped me to lose weight and to concentrate better on my studies . Secondly , a healthy physical routine assists youngsters to overcome health -related challenges , namely obesity , diabetes , and asthma . In comparison to medicine , exercising is a better way to build immunity and fight against diseases . To demonstrate , a recent study by Times has revealed that 70 % of people suffering from diabetes can be cured if they imbibe a nutritious diet and perform physical activities on an average of three times per week . To conclude , it is undeniably true that playing outdoor sports and performing physical exercises can support the youth to overcome their health problems as well as to focus on their academic career in a better way . In my opinion , exercising is a great way to boost immunity ; in fact , it is the best way to be physically and mentally fit . 
As life is important to everyone , there are some individuals who prefer life to be short and full of energy , as well as intensity , whereas , the other class of individuals believe in living a long , and a peaceful life . This essay intends to highlight the reasons why I think a serene and a calm approach is integral to living a healthy and a long -lasting life . In the contemporary era , people are not only seen running after money and wealth , but are also seen becoming competitive against each other , particularly , against their friends and family members . As a result , they also let go of their relationships and friendships with their near and dear ones as they give more priority to their economic status in society . Therefore , it is sensible to live in a serene environment such as in the countryside , where people show respect and gratitude towards each other . This , furthermore , helps them to develop strong bondings among themselves , and to help one another during emergencies . To illustrate , since my parents lived in a small town , they believed in the simplicity of life and valued their relationships with others . Moreover , they learnt to be contented in their lives , and not to become money -minded . Secondly , adopting a calm and a peaceful lifestyle helps individuals and society to be healthy in terms of their physical and mental well -being , and to enjoy a long -lasting life . In my understanding , it is better to live a stress -free life because stress and anxiety are the two main factors for all types of health -related problems namely heart attacks , diabetes , and high cholesterol levels . For example , a recent study by Times has revealed that 70 % of youth living in the metropolitan areas are suffering from hypertension due to their intense and busy lifestyle . Thus , it is important for people to adopt a passive lifestyle , which is beneficial for their health and life . To conclude , as a complex and an intense lifestyle could lead to several detrimental effects , such as health and social problems in society , therefore , it is prudent to adopt a passive lifestyle to safeguard the interest of the human race . 
