A large number of studies indicate that obesity problems are rising nowadays . This is a big headache for public health and it is necessary to educate people about this matter . However , forcing people to do exercise could be counterproductive . On the one hand , we must stimulate a more active lifestyle and introducing a subject in schools and universities seem to be the right choice . Younger generations will be more educated about their health and , as a consequence , could raise awareness among their family members and everyone will benefit . But , on the other hand , forcing young people to do exercise when they do not want to , or feel embarrassed about it , could create the contrary effect : generate a distance from physical activity . Kids and young people are ruthless and not everyone is good at sports . We must be careful because bullying is also a big public issue in our schools . We do not want to create another issue in our schools . I agree on incentivising a healthier lifestyle for children and college students , nonetheless , this cannot be by forcing sports activities . We must find different ways to introduce a healthier lifestyle . For instance , we could educate and incentivise by rising college credit for those who do sports in schools . In other matters , changing the kind of food we give to children in school cafeterias to a healthier one could also be a good idea . As for university students , I think establishing more healthy cafeterias and restaurants on campus is the right way . Also , reducing college debt repayments for those who have taken some type of sport during their university time could motivate sports activities on campus . There are many ways to bring awareness to a healthier lifestyle for young people , forcing sports should not be one of them . 
