Should computers and tablets completely replace books in schools and universities ? I do not think so . Of course , tablets and computers are very useful . Think about it , all your notes and your information are in the cloud or on your computer . All our data , one way or another , is partly or completely in the computer ’s memory . But will they completely replace books made of paper ? I doubt it , because you can read books at any time , any place , including without electrical energy . You can make notes in your books . It 's so simple , just write . The advantage is that no one can see your notes and your notebook does not need to upgrade constantly . Anyway , in my opinion , the best about reading books is that you do not hurt your eyes . If you read on a screen , after a few hours , your eyes will hurt . My eyes never hurt when I read a book , obviously with adequate light . 
