There is no shortage of opinion on educational methods . Some people believe digital devices , such as computers or tablets , should be used instead of paper books in schools and universities . As far as my perspective is concerned , I agree with this statement . This is my firm belief based on two plausible reasons . In this regard , I will discuss how new educational instruments could contribute to a better educational understanding and also , how it would have significant impacts on the protection of the environment . The aforementioned justifications will be elaborated in the subsequent paragraphs . First and foremost , technology has constructive results on the quality of education . By using new devices , like tablets , students can have great access to various databases whilst they are attending a classroom . These databases can provide students with holistic information on every possible topic that could be presented by a lecturer in a classroom . If they did not have this possibility to use such useful appliances at a classroom , they would be deprived of an opportunity to gain a deep and asymmetric knowledge of issues . Besides , these instruments make the teaching process more accurate and understandable . In other words , learning through new tools presents better pedagogical outcomes . Secondly , a shift from using traditional books to taking advantage of new digital devices means that the number of trees that have to be cut every year to produce books will be lessen dramatically . In other words , if we increased the number of the electronic devices in schools or universities , it would result in the fact that we will consume less paper . This fact reveals that there is a negative correlation between these two things : more digital devices , less trees would be eradicated . Therefore , this policy have a positive environmental effect in itself . To put it in a nutshell , any replacement between paper books and digital devices should be considered as a fruitful decision . As I explained above , I fully support this idea . In this regard , I discussed how this measure would make teaching easier and learning more beneficial . Moreover , I stated that this policy would have environmental impacts , which is indispensable . Consequently , in my personal point of view , books should be replaced with new tablets and computers . 
