The aim of this writing is to analyse the impact video games have on children and how this topic can be dealt with by parents . When it comes to new technology , there is no doubt it has a great impact on our lifestyle nowadays . For better or worse , we all live in a technological world , where video games have an important role , especially among children . Surely , there must be some beneficial effects on children with the fact that they get to control such devices . However , the negative impact , from my point of view , should not be underestimated . On the one hand , video games provide children with technological and other different types of knowledge . For instance , historical video games can teach about different historical periods . However , children normally choose other less productive themes , such as war or racing . On the other hand , the overuse of video games and technological devices in general is making children lose their social skills and , what is more , it creates addiction . According to some studies , playing video games is progressively replacing face -to -face contact . Had it not been for that last point , it would not be wrong to think that video games can be beneficial for children . Nevertheless , the reality is very different . Children spend more time on their own and playing video games than they actually do with real people like their parents or friends . I would end by saying that , even though we cannot live refusing technology and how relevant it is in the current world , parents ought to control what their kids do and how much time they spend doing it . 
