There is no shortage of opinion on the negative or positive impacts of television . In this regard , many people are of the opinion that TV programs can be useful to learn new things , alongside the fact that it is mostly for entertainment . From my personal perspective , I agree with this statement . In this essay , I will discuss that TV programs can deliver shows in which pedagogical units of schools could be covered . Also , I will delineate that television has a great influence on children , who can learn many new things from its programs . These justifications will be elaborated in the subsequent paragraphs . First and foremost , the great majority of television 's audiences are youngsters who are students at schools . In addition , it has been reckoned that pupils spend three hours per day watching TV programs . Thus , there is a significant opportunity available to the authorities in order to take the most possible advantage of this situation . Should pedagogical complementary multimedia units be delivered through TV programs , students would be encouraged to spend their time more on fruitful programs . Therefore , television could be employed as a means to broadcast certain teaching courses in a more intricate and effective manner . Secondly , pupils are fascinated by TV . Scientists have been pondering the influence of TV broadcasting programs on youngsters , and the results reveal that material broadcast by television lingers for a period of time vis -a -vis those which were presented through traditional school classes . In this regard , if TV was used as a means to develop students ' knowledge on matters related to their course , they would face with a situation in which they could deepen their understanding about relevant issues that could not be developed at school . Hence , we can exploit kids ' keenness toward television , to provide them with comprehensive and conclusive information related to their courses . To put it in a nutshell , TV can provide amusement , as well as education . In this essay , I examined the possibility of using TV as an instrument to teach kids in an asymmetrical manner . Moreover , I articulated the fact that young people who are attending school can have a profound enthusiasm to follow certain teaching lessons through TV programs . Consequently , the utmost effectiveness of television should not be neglected . TV could crack open an opportunity to provide young people with essential pedagogical programs in a manner that appears to be more favorable to them . 
