There is no shortage of opinions on negative lifestyles . Many people believe that due to the harmful impacts of sedentariness on mankind 's well -being , all educational institutions , including universities and schools , must make physical exercise compulsory . The proponents of this idea recommend that these sports activities should be taken on every other day . From a personal point of view , I agree with the above -mentioned statements . In fact , this is my firm belief , for which I will provide two plausible reasons to prove my perspective . Firstly , I will address the negative ramifications of inactive lifestyles on health from a scientific context . Secondly , I will explore the benefits of an active lifestyle on mental robustness . All the aforementioned will be elaborated in the subsequent paragraphs . To begin with , undoubtedly , there are severe consequences on health which are driven from a sedentary lifestyle . In other words , our way of living will directly affect our medical conditions . It has been established through certain empirical research that people who are not active during the day are at stake of chronic physical conditions . For instance , if exercise has been eliminated from your daily schedule , you would be plagued with heart diseases . These medical disorders are in negative correlation with the extent of physical activities . Thus , if someone had been seated for a long time , in the long run , he would have gotten physical abnormalities . Therefore , doing sport and dedication to have an active lifestyle are associated with health strength . Secondly , on no account should we consider the impacts of sedentariness limited to medical health . Its effect and consequences are beyond . Apparently , a sedentary lifestyle has significant effects on mental health . The statistic findings delineate that those who benefit from vacancies in which they have to be active , for example , police officers or doctors who should invariably be rushed on their foot , feel happier than others with sitting jobs . In other words , you will feel more enthusiasm in your life if you allocate more time to physical activities , regardless of the purpose and nature of the activity . In this regard , one may accentuate the relation between physical and mental health and well -beings . It should be noted , however , we do not know a great deal about the exact interaction between body and mental health . Nevertheless , their importance and their mutual effects are undeniable . In conclusion , having a healthy life is rooted in our approach towards our life . One of the predominant examples is the effect of sport , physical activities and exercise on both mental robustness and medical conditions . According to this fact and based on the presented justifications , which have been explained in the paragraphs above , relevant authorities should take all the necessary measures in order to mitigate the severe outcomes of a hectic but inactive lifestyle . In this regard , educational complexes , such as universities , could provide certain measures to adequately address this problem . 
Hi Alex , How are things ? Sorry to be so slow getting back to you , but I 've been hitting the books . Moreover , I was afraid that you were mad with me . What great news ! I 'm so glad that you are great . In your letter , you mentioned that you really want to invite me to your party , but unfortunately I ca not attend , as I have to go to the doctor 's , as I have broken my leg in an awful way . My apologies to you Alex . Besides , why do not we meet up another day and line up another outstanding party ? Anyway , I will be delighted to get together another day , so let me know when you can hang out together . Well , that 's all for now . I hope that you can really forgive me for this sneak affair . I 'm looking forward to seeing you soon . Drop me a line soon . Best wishes H 
