The question of if computers and tablets should completely replace books in schools and universities has gained popularity , owing to the advancement of electronic books . Fortunately , renowned experts have a precise answer for this query . In order to learn what it is , please proceed to the next paragraph . In their view , this suggestion should not be put into action , due to the fact that e -books are quite vulnerable to power outages and corruption . To illustrate , all digital textbooks could be hacked in a matter of seconds , disabling education hazardously for a couple of weeks . Therefore , this kind of data always requires substitute resources such as books , no matter how bulky they are . However , it does not mean that we must discard e -books entirely . After all , they have numerous advantages . First and foremost , they do not use up much space . Furthermore , they greatly reduce deforestation levels . And last but not least , they are easier to carry around . In conclusion , I would argue that computers and tablets should be combined with traditional books instead of replacing them completely in schools and universities . 
The more the gap between the rich and the poor grows , the more alluring wealth becomes . This state of affairs reminds us of the old saying : It is more important to be healthy than to be rich . With the aim of solving this dilemma , the relationship between health and money will be covered in the essay . Obviously , money ca not cure all diseases . To illustrate , in spite of being heavily funded , oncologists have not found an effective treatment for cancer yet . Furthermore , there is a plethora of fatal rare diseases waiting for their cure . And as expected , they do not care about the one 's social status . On the other hand , it ca not be denied that money has a profound effect on our health . That is to say , maintaining health requires costly needs , such as a clean and secure shelter , hygiene and a healthcare infrastructure , a balanced diet , etc . Besides , some research suggests that wealthier patients usually receive more efficient treatments . In conclusion , I would argue that wealth is superior to health , due to the fact that it maintains health , though it is not always the case . 
Where I live , we have basically two seasons in the year . From September to March , we have a very hot , damp summer . The other months left , we have a relatively cold and dry winter . It is almost impossible to like this winter . So my favourite season is summer . Especially at the beginning , it is warm , but not too much . I like this part . During this part , it is perfect to go out any time of the day . You can really enjoy your life whatever the time . It is up to you . I also like the fact we can wear less clothes , our bodies are freer . We are a country of free bodies . Anything that stops that makes me sad . 
