Travelling is a curious topic , because I think that we as a society are getting stuck with it . In other topics , like the internet , computers , mobiles , vehicles , medicine and so on , humanity is developing new advances every day , but travelling remains with the same fastest way to travel , that is the airplane . What I am trying to say is that we ca not improve the speed that we can travel to another part of the world . For the last 3 decades , we have not been able to go faster and we spend the same time going between America and Europe for example . All advances are with short distances . Land vehicles are advancing every day . They are changing and maybe in the future all of that will have an electricity supply . To sum up , I think that in the future , to travel long distances , we will have the same periods of time , but to travel short distances , we will improve that more and more each day . 
