Dear Sir/Madam , I read your announcement about banning the use of mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants on the government website yesterday . I have some opinions I want to share to you . First , the mobile phone is a great invention of mankind , we use it to contact with other people around the world , search for information on the internet , play games , have a character like a camera which helps taking and storing nice memories in pictures . The mobile phone is very popular , most people around the world have one of them at present . You want to ban it , that means you refuse the development of mankind from the past to the present . Second , mobile phones have become a part of people 's lives now , people use them to read the newspaper online when they come back home by public transport , they use them to take some photos with a friend or just themselves when they go to a new store or new restaurant . People cannot use mobile phones on public transport and in shops and restaurants meaning that they leave a part of their life at home when they come here . I think they can do that instead they will leave them there . It will cause big damage to the economy of our city . Thirdly , people use mobile phones to contact each other like friends , members of their family , company staff . If they cannot use it , it will become a big problem for their daily life . For example , when you are coming back home , your wife wants you to buy meat and vegetables in a convenience store , then she will call you by mobile phone . However , the government promulgate a law about banning use mobile phone in public , she just talk to you when you stay at home . So you waste a lot of time for buying food . I think banning mobile phones are impossible in the present . 
