Everybody lies and that 's okay When we are children , our parents always say that lying is wrong , however , one common strategy to convince kids not to lie is saying phrases like : " if you lie , your nose will grow " and show the cartoon of Pinochio , a story about a doll made of wood by a carpenter . This doll has life and he likes to lie a lot , and always when he does that , his nose grows more and more . Adults always tell lies , for example , Santa exists and , in the reality , it is the father in a costume of Santa giving gifts at Christmas . One other problem is adults teaching children not to lie , but lying to them and even worse , asking kids to lie . As an example : say to answer on the telephone that they are not at home . The reality is everybody lies , and giving bad examples of it to the kids , does not help at all . There are white lies that sometimes are necessary to not hurt the people that we like . Or just not to be a bad mood person , like it 's not okay if someone asks " Are you fine ? . " and the other replies with every problem that they have in life . Sometimes , you need to lie so thieves do not steal from you , just give them the things that they could find . If you have a secret safe , you do not need to tell the truth to them . 
I had a discussion with my parents about people having to always tell the truth or if for people it is sometimes acceptable to tell a lie . In my opinion , I think for people it is sometimes acceptable to tell a lie . When you tell the truth to someone , it makes them hurt or feel shame , so we use a white lie in these situations . White lie is a term which is used to tell you something not true but useless and harmless to anyone . In the medical area , when patients have an incurable disease , doctors , who take care of patients , often do not tell the truth about the medical condition to them . In contrast , doctors will say their medical condition is very good and they are recovering to normal , they just say the truth for patients ' family . If doctors tell the truth about medical condition to patients , they could feel nervous and anxiety about it . It has a bad effect on treatment or makes the sickness worse . In addition , the truth is sometimes unacceptable for someone , people usually want to hear something good about themselves instead of bad . For example , when your staff , who work together with you in a company , ask you about how you feel about her new dress , which is wore on her body today . In your mind , you find it so ugly , terrible and unsuitable for her . However , if you tell the truth about your emotion towards her dress to her , she could feel uncomfortable , shameful , or angry . It can make a broken in bond between you and her in working and communication . Instead , you will say it is so beautiful and suitable for her . In the present , if you tell the truth , you will have enemies . If you tell a lie , you have friends . 
In my opinion , replacing paper books with tablets and computers in schools and universities has its pros and cons . One of the pros is certainly that there would be no risk of deforestation and therefore the non -cutting down of trees . Another pro is that it would greatly reduce the weight of the backpack , which is a problem for students who are far from school . One of the cons , however , is that , in my opinion , those who cannot afford a tablet or computer will not be able to attend school lessons . Another con is that , in my opinion , electronic devices will never be able to replace paper books , because even from the point of view of touch , it would change badly . In the end , if books are really replaced by tablets and computers , we will make a decision . 
