To begin with , travelling is one of my favourite hobbies , if not the most important one . A great part of my personality was built because of my travels . Everything started when I moved to Australia for an exchange semester abroad . There , I was able to learn a new language and explore a totally different world and culture . Furthermore , Australia specifically is a multicultural place , where you can learn a lot about many other cultures . Also , with the advance of technology , travel is getting more accurate , and accessible to more people , since the means of transport are getting more efficient , and travelling is becoming cheaper and quicker at the same time . At the same time , people working from home , or remotely , create a whole new category of travellers , where countries who want to get the benefits of these long -term tourists will have to create new places and entertainment for those called digital nomads . And not only for those , researchers are showing that in the future , people will work less hours , due to automation , and new tools will be created . Consequently , they will have more time to consume goods , services and of course , do tourism . To me , this will be the most significant change . 
People sleep on a daily basis , but everyone has their own sleeping preferences regarding things like the amount of light and noise . Although some people do not mind light and noise while they sleep , I personally need a quiet and dark place to sleep . Otherwise , not only do I find it difficult to fall asleep , but I am most likely to wake up frequently during the night . Indeed , I 'd like to go to bed early and fall asleep immediately . I prefer to sleep with a little bit of light and in a quiet place . That said , I have no problem with the sounds of nature like bird songs . Also , it would be great for me to have enough room to roll over while I 'm sleeping . 
