On the one hand , zapping books at schools and colleges is an impossible task . It is a matter of fact that we are now in the heyday of the information highway , but this does not mean the physical books ' demise . It is necessary to remember that not every school all over the country is in the high echelons of wealth . There are thousands and thousands of students unable to have proper facilities conducive to learning . The underdog lives on the edge of society . There are people unable to buy either top -notch tablets , cutting -edge computers , or sumptuous technologies . What is more , many are not even able to afford proper food or necessities . On the other hand , if society is someday able to provide the proper living conditions to all people , it would be a conducive sensation to change physical books to digital . Nevertheless , it does not mean that all physical books would disappear , only text books . There are a lot of individuals attached to having the real thing and who enjoy deluxe and hardcover editions . Colleges would benefit from format changes , because they would have access to up -to -date information always . 
Telling the truth is obviously essential . When we were children , we were taught not to tell lies , because it is wrong . Besides , a person caught while telling a lie will never be trusted again . Therefore , it seems that always telling the truth is important . But I do not quite agree with this idea . In my opinion , telling the truth should always be preferred to telling a lie . However , there are a few situations where telling a lie enables us to preserve a good relationship , or the sensibility of a person . For instance , telling someone who 's asking you whether his son died in an accident or not that , indeed , the son is dead is maybe not the best way to proceed . Rather than saying a brutal , violent truth , which may shock or despair someone , a soft lie which leads to the truth could help this person to cope with this event when she learns about it . Lying should never be accepted , except on the occasions where it 's in a view to conceal a hard , desperate truth , or when it leads to a softer way to the truth . Moreover , some lines of business require if not lies , a certain concealment of the truth . In politics , for instance , telling all the truth can be devastating for a faction which used back doors to have their candidate elected . To conclude , it is essential to always tell the truth , except in the few situations where it is better to make a small concealment of a shocking truth . 
That 's a fact , the school that we know today is about to disappear . A lot of research concludes that our current way of schooling was created in the industrial era , when people need to be guided in all the steps , with a passive way of learning , which is basically absorbing source content . The content , in this case , is defined by an educational curriculum and is passed by the figure of a teacher or professor , depending on what environment you are in . With the advance of technology , other skills and abilities are demanded from people to be able to perform and pursue a working career . But how do we prepare people for this new world ? In my opinion , the school of the future needs to focus on teaching people to learn how to learn . Today , with the internet , we do not need the figure of a teacher as we know it anymore , but instead a mentor , who will guide a student in what to learn and how to learn . We need to teach our kids to be self -learners , who will independently search for knowledge , adapting to their own needs . 
