Firstly , education is very significant for people because people want to set up great lives in the future . Therefore , the first step is education . Education has a lot of methods . For example , students use books or technological equipment . In my opinion , students would prefer to use computers and tablets , but these should not completely replace books in school and universities , because books are necessary for education . There are several students who prefer to use technological equipment , such as faster , It includes a lot of information and is very useful . The first reason , students want to have information quickly . Also , they want to have an easy educational life , so they prefer to use computers and tablets , because they have information , which is very important for students . In addition , according to them , it is more important that technological devices are faster than books . The second reason , books include a lot of information , but it is not possible to include many topics in a book . Therefore , students can have a computer or tablet , because these provide convenience for students . The other reason , libraries are absolutely very necessary places for studying or researching , but they have a lot of options for books , so they are not useful , but technological devices are better , because they can reach the information more easily . Finally , absolutely , computers and tablets should not completely replace books . Students need books and libraries all the time . Therefore I think they usually prefer computers and tablets in school and university . 
The straightforward answer to your question is yes , television can also educate people , especially if we 're talking about children . Furthermore , television is not the best way to educate , because it compromises your concentration capabilities . Also , it is very limited . It could be used as one resource to search for and absorb content , but you ca not do much more than that . In my opinion , television could be a smart way to educate your children , as it can be funny and could focus the kids ' attention on the television programs . Today , there 're many educational channels for children , and if they 're not used in an exaggerated way , I guess it can help in education . For adults on the other hand , I ca not find it very useful for educational purposes . Maybe when you are studying languages , it 's nice to get used to the accent and some more real -world vocabulary . To sum up , television is just a tool , like the internet , books , etc . The secret for a good education is a dedicated mentor , who analyses and reflects on what kind of information is being consumed . The mentor , in the case of adults , can be yourself . 
